onsulting your doctor, you should not discontinue taking this medicine abruptly.</p>\n\n<p>Abdominal pain, nausea, vomiting, a drop in libido, and itching are a few typical side effects of this drug. While using this medication, make sure to drink lots of fluids to stay hydrated as it may cause diarrhea. You should let your doctor know if you have any strange changes in mood or behavior, new or worsening depression, or suicidal thoughts or actions.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>The majority of adverse effects are temporary and go away as your body becomes used to the medication. If they persist or you&#39;re concerned about them, speak with your doctor.</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Diarrhea</li>\n	<li>Abdominal pain</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Decreased libido</li>\n</ul>','[\"acamprol-333mg-11-171404166182.webp\"]','ACA0333',1,'0','2023-12-05 06:26:43','2025-07-21 05:12:36'),(115,0,'Aciloc 150mg','aciloc-150mg','Tablet','aciloc-150mg-1-171532831977.webp','ACI0150','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>Take this medication precisely as your doctor has advised. If you continued taking your medication for as long as your doctor advised, it would help. If you quit too soon, your health can get worse and your symptoms might return. Common adverse effects of Aciloc 150 Tablet 30s include headache, diarrhea, constipation, and shortness of breath. These adverse effects are transient and may disappear with time. However, speak with your doctor if these adverse effects continue.</p>\n\n<p>Tablet/Capsule: It should be completely swallowed with water; do not break, crush, or chew it.Shake the bottle of the oral solution/syrup thoroughly before each use. Use the measuring cup, dosing syringe, or dropper to administer the recommended dose orally.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Relief from heartburn and acid reflux: Aciloc 150mg can provide relief from the symptoms of heartburn, including a burning sensation in the chest and acid regurgitation. It works by reducing the production of stomach acid, helping to alleviate discomfort and improve digestion.</p>\n\n<p>Healing of stomach ulcers: Aciloc 150mg is effective in treating and healing stomach ulcers caused by excess stomach acid. By reducing acid production, it allows the stomach lining to heal and prevents further damage.</p>\n\n<p>Prevention of acid-related damage: By decreasing stomach acid levels, Aciloc 150mg can help prevent acid-related damage to the esophagus, stomach, and other parts of the gastrointestinal tract. This is especially beneficial for individuals with conditions such as gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD).</p>\n\n<p>Improved digestion: Excess stomach acid can disrupt the normal digestive process, leading to discomfort and indigestion. Aciloc 150mg helps restore a more balanced acid environment in the stomach, promoting better digestion and reducing digestive symptoms.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>If you are allergic to any of the ingredients in Aciloc 150 Tablet 30s, it is advised that you avoid taking them. You shouldn&#39;t use this drug if you are pregnant, trying to get pregnant, or nursing unless your doctor deems it necessary. If you have liver disease, stomach or intestine cancer, or will soon undergo an endoscopy, let your doctor know. In order to rule out potential adverse effects, you should also inform your doctor about your medical history and any of the medications you are currently taking before taking Aciloc 150 Tablet 30.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>The category of gastrointestinal agents includes Aciloc 150 Tablet 30s. It is used to treat acid reflux, heartburn, and indigestion. When you have acid reflux, you can also use Aciloc 150 Tablet 30&#39;s to treat gastro-oesophageal reflux disease (GORD). Additionally used to treat and prevent stomach ulcers is Aciloc 150 Tablet 30. Zollinger-Ellison Syndrome, a rare disorder brought on by a pancreatic or intestinal tumor, is frequently treated with Aciloc 150 Tablet 30&#39;s.</p>\n\n<p>Ranitidine, a histamine-2 (H2) receptor blocker, is an ingredient in Aciloc 150 Tablet 30&#39;s that helps lower stomach acid by inhibiting the H2 receptor&#39;s functions. The stomach wall&#39;s parietal cells have the H2 receptor, which triggers the release of gastric acid secretion. Excess gastric acid secretion harms the tissues in the food pipe, stomach, and duodenum.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Constipation</li>\n	<li>Diarrhoea</li>\n	<li>Stomach pain</li>\n</ul>','[\"aciloc-150mg-1-171532831977.webp\"]','ACI0150',1,'0','2023-12-05 06:32:01','2025-07-21 05:09:42'),(116,0,'Aciloc 300mg','aciloc-300mg','Tablet','aciloc-300mg-1-171532917079.webp','ACI0300','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>Aciloc 300 Tablet is frequently used to alleviate heartburn and stomach ulcers that might occur when taking medications. The dosage and duration of the medication must be followed exactly as directed by the doctor. What you are being treated for will determine how much and how frequently you need to take it. Pay attention to your doctor&#39;s instructions. You may only need to take this medication for a brief period of time when you experience symptoms of indigestion and heartburn, which should subside within a few hours of taking it. You might need to take it for a longer period of time if you&#39;re taking it to avoid ulcers and other disorders. To keep issues from arising in the future, you should continue taking it consistently. By eating smaller meals more frequently and staying away from fatty or spicy foods, you might be able to reduce the severity of your symptoms.</p>\n\n<p>Follow your doctor&#39;s instructions for this medication&#39;s dosage and duration. Take it all in at once. Don&#39;t eat it, break it, or crush it. Although the Aciloc 300 Tablet can be taken any way, it is preferable to take it at a set time.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>GERD, also known as gastroesophageal reflux disease, is a chronic illness. It occurs when a muscle above your stomach relaxes excessively, allowing stomach contents to reflux into your mouth and esophagus. H2-receptor antagonists are a class of medications that includes Aciloc 300 Tablet. It lessens the amount of acid your stomach produces and lessens the discomfort brought on by acid reflux and heartburn. For it to work, you must take it exactly how it is intended.</p>\n\n<p>Simple lifestyle adjustments can halt or lessen heartburn. Eat smaller, more frequent meals; consider what foods make you feel heartburny and try to avoid them; if you are overweight, attempt to lose weight; and look for ways to relax. Eat nothing three to four hours before bedtime.</p>\n\n<p>Peptic ulcer disease treatment</p>\n\n<p>Non-steroidal anti-inflammatory medicines (NSAIDs) or the bug Helicobacter pylori are typically to blame for stomach ulcers. Both of these weaken the stomach&#39;s defenses against the acid that it secretes to break down food. Due to the injury to the stomach, an ulcer could develop. It&#39;s possible to treat these ulcers using Aciloc 300 Tablet. It lessens the amount of acid your stomach produces, protecting the ulcer as it naturally heals from additional harm. Depending on what caused the ulcer, various medications might be prescribed to you. Even if the symptoms appear to go away, you must continue taking the medication as directed for it to be successful. By lowering the acidity, it may also be given to stop stomach ulcers from developing.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>If you have any kidney or liver issues before taking it, let your doctor know. This could impact the dosage or appropriateness of this medication. Additionally, let your doctor know if you are taking any other medications, as some may interact with this medication. If it has been recommended by a doctor, this medication is often regarded as safe to take while expecting or nursing. Avoid drinking alcohol as it can worsen your symptoms by causing your stomach&#39;s acid production to increase.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>Aciloc 300 Tablet is under the category of gastrointestinal medications. It is employed to treat indigestion, heartburn, and acid reflux. You can also use Aciloc 300 Tablet to treat gastro-oesophageal reflux disease (GORD) when you have acid reflux. Aciloc 300 Tablet is also used to treat and prevent stomach ulcers. Aciloc 300 Tablet is widely used to treat Zollinger-Ellison Syndrome, a rare disorder brought on by an intestine or pancreatic tumor.</p>\n\n<p>Aciloc 300 Tablet contains ranitidine, a histamine-2 (H2) receptor blocker, which works by preventing the H2 receptor from doing its job. The H2 receptor is found on the parietal cells of the stomach wall, which is what causes the gastric acid to secrete. The tissues in the food pipe, stomach, and duodenum are harmed by excessive gastric acid output.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Diarrhea</li>\n	<li>Gastrointestinal disturbance</li>\n</ul>','[\"aciloc-300mg-1-171532917079.webp\"]','ACI0300',1,'0','2023-12-05 06:35:58','2025-07-21 05:12:40'),(117,0,'Acivir Cream 10gm','acivir-cream-10gm','Cream','acivir-cream-10gm-1-171532927638.webp','ACIV010','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>Only external usage is permitted for Acivir Cream 10 gm. Common Acivir Cream 10 gm side effects include flaky skin, dry/cracked lips, and a brief burning or stinging sensation. Not every patient taking this drug may experience these adverse effects, which gradually go away with time. Please visit a doctor if the adverse effects last longer or get worse.</p>\n\n<p>Only external usage is permitted for Acivir Cream 10 gm. As directed by your doctor, place a tiny amount on the tip of your finger and apply a thin coating to the clean, dry affected region. Avoid making contact with the mouth, eyes, or nose. Rinse with water liberally if you come into contact with these areas by accident. In order to stop the transmission of infection, wash your hands both before and after applying.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>