h, itching, swelling, or difficulty breathing. Discontinue use and seek medical assistance if any allergic symptoms occur.</li>\n	<li>Avoid sun exposure. Acnelak CLZ Cream may increase skin sensitivity to sunlight. Limit your exposure to the sun and protect your skin by using sunscreen, wearing protective clothing, and seeking shade.</li>\n	<li>Avoid Contact with Eyes and Mucous Membranes: Take care to prevent the cream from coming into contact with your eyes, mouth, nose, or any other mucous membranes. If accidental contact occurs, rinse thoroughly with water.</li>\n	<li>Wash Hands: Before and after applying Acnelak CLZ Cream, ensure that your hands are clean. This helps prevent the spread of bacteria and contamination.</li>\n	<li>Avoid Sharing: Do not share Acnelak CLZ Cream with others, even if they have similar skin conditions. This is to prevent cross-contamination and potential adverse reactions.</li>\n	<li>Keep out of reach of children. Store Acnelak CLZ Cream in a safe place, away from children and pets.</li>\n</ul>','<p>Acnelak-CLZ Cream is a combined medication prescribed for the treatment of acne. Its primary function is to reduce excessive oil production, thereby alleviating inflammation and inhibiting the growth of acne-causing microorganisms. Furthermore, it aids in minimizing the appearance of acne-related scars.</p>\n\n<p>For optimal results, Acnelak-CLZ Cream is designed exclusively for external use and should be administered in accordance with your doctor&#39;s instructions. Using clean and dry hands, apply a thin layer of the cream solely to the affected areas of your skin. Prior to and following application, ensure that you wash your hands. In the event of accidental contact with your eyes, nose, mouth, or vagina, rinse thoroughly with water. It may take several days to several weeks for a noticeable improvement in your symptoms, so it is important to use the cream regularly. To ensure the medicine&#39;s maximum effectiveness, complete the entire