rong>Precautions:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>External use only: Adaferin Gel 15 gm is intended for external use on the skin. Avoid ingestion or contact with the eyes, mouth, nostrils, or other sensitive areas. If accidental contact occurs, rinse thoroughly with water.</li>\n	<li>Allergic reactions: If you have a known allergy or hypersensitivity to Adapalene or any other ingredients present in Adaferin Gel 15 gm, avoid using it. If you experience any signs of an allergic reaction, such as a rash, itching, swelling, or difficulty breathing, seek medical attention immediately.</li>\n	<li>Avoid excessive sun exposure: Adapalene can increase sensitivity to sunlight, making your skin more prone to sunburn. Limit your time in direct sunlight, wear protective clothing, and use sunscreen with a high SPF when outdoors.</li>\n	<li>Skin irritation: Some individuals may experience mild skin irritation, redness, dryness, or peeling when using Adaferin Gel 15 gm. If these symptoms persist or become severe, consult your doctor for further guidance.</li>\n	<li>Age considerations: Adaferin Gel 15 gm is generally recommended for individuals aged 12 years and older. It may not be suitable for younger children, so consult a healthcare professional for appropriate acne treatment options for younger age groups.</li>\n</ul>','<p>Adaferin Gel 15 gm is classified as an &quot;antiacne&quot; dermatological preparation used for treating acne (pimples) in individuals aged 12 years or older. Acne, a common skin condition, occurs when dead skin cells and oil clog the hair follicles. The bacteria responsible for acne thrive on the skin&#39;s natural oil, known as sebum, leading to inflammation and swelling.</p>\n\n<p>The main ingredient in Adaferin Gel 15 gm is Adapalene, which falls under the category of retinoids (synthetic derivatives of vitamin A). It functions by loosening the surface cells of the skin and unclogging pores by reducing oil production. Consequently, it diminishes the occurrence of pimples, whiteheads, and blackheads.</p>','<p><strong>Side Effects:</strong></p>\n\n<p>The majority of side effects do not necessitate medical attention and typically subside as your body adapts to the medication. However, if they persist or if you have concerns about them, it is advisable to consult your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>The common side effects are listed below:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Dry skin</li>\n	<li>Skin irritation</li>\n	<li>Skin redness</li>\n	<li>Burning sensation of the skin</li>\n</ul>','[\"adaferin-gel-0-171567025627.jpg\"]','ADA015',1,'0','2023-12-13 06:51:37','2025-07-25 11:06:14'),(124,0,'Adalat Chrono 30 mg:','adalat-chrono-30-mg','Tablets','adalat-chrono-30-mg-170245055649.webp','ADA030','<p><strong>Usage:</strong></p>\n\n<p>It is important to follow your doctor&rsquo;s instructions and adhere to the prescribed dosage and schedule for Adalat Chrono 30 mg. The medication is usually taken orally with a glass of water, and it can be taken with or without food. It is important to swallow the tablet whole and not to crush or chew it. Adalat Chrono 30 mg is designed to provide sustained release of the medication over a 24-hour period, allowing for convenient once-daily dosing.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Benefits:</strong></p>\n\n<p>Adalat Chrono 30 mg offers several benefits in the treatment of cardiovascular conditions. Some of the positive aspects include:</p>\n\n<p>Managing high blood pressure: Adalat Chrono 30 mg helps lower blood pressure by relaxing and widening the blood vessels, which reduces the resistance to blood flow and helps maintain healthy blood pressure levels.</p>\n\n<p>Treating angina: This medication is effective in relieving and preventing angina symptoms, such as chest pain or discomfort, by improving blood flow to the heart muscle</p>\n\n<p>Raynaud&rsquo;s phenomenon: Adalat Chrono 30 mg is also used to manage the symptoms of Raynaud&rsquo;s phenomenon, a condition characterized by the narrowing of blood vessels in the extremities, typically