 about potential side effects.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','[\"adalat-chrono-30-mg-170245055649.webp\"]','ADA030',1,'0','2023-12-13 06:56:11','2025-07-25 11:06:17'),(125,0,'Adalat Chrono 60mg','adalat-chrono-60mg','Tablets','adalat-chrono-60mg-171567053282.jpg','ADA060','<p><strong>Usage:</strong></p>\n\n<p>It is important to follow your doctor&rsquo;s instructions and take Adalat Chrono 60mg exactly as prescribed. The medication comes in the form of extended-release tablets that should be swallowed whole and not crushed or chewed. It is usually taken once daily, preferably at the same time each day, with or without food. It is important to continue taking the medication regularly for it to be effective.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Benefits:</strong></p>\n\n<p>Adalat Chrono 60mg offers several benefits for individuals with hypertension or angina:</p>\n\n<p>Effective blood pressure control: Adalat Chrono 60mg helps lower high blood pressure, reducing the risk of complications such as heart attacks, strokes, and kidney problems.</p>\n\n<p>Chest pain relief: For individuals with angina, Adalat Chrono 60mg can help alleviate chest pain or discomfort by improving blood flow to the heart muscle.</p>\n\n<p>Improved exercise tolerance: By reducing the workload on the heart and improving blood flow, Adalat Chrono 60mg may enhance exercise capacity and enable individuals to engage in physical activities more comfortably.</p>\n\n<p>Long-lasting effect: Adalat Chrono 60mg is an extended-release formulation, providing sustained blood pressure control and symptom relief throughout the day.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Precautions:</strong></p>\n\n<p>Before starting Adalat Chrono 60mg, it is important to inform your healthcare provider about any pre-existing medical conditions, allergies, or medications you are taking. Some precautions to consider include:</p>\n\n<p>Grapefruit juice interaction: Avoid consuming grapefruit or grapefruit juice while taking Adalat Chrono 60mg, as it can interfere with the medication&rsquo;s effectiveness.</p>\n\n<p>Pregnancy and breastfeeding: If you are pregnant, planning to become pregnant, or breastfeeding, consult your doctor before using Adalat Chrono 60mg to determine if it is safe for you and your baby.</p>\n\n<p>Liver or kidney problems: Inform your doctor if you have any liver or kidney conditions, as the dosage of Adalat Chrono 60mg may need to be adjusted accordingly.</p>\n\n<p>Avoid sudden discontinuation: Adalat Chrono 60mg should not be stopped abruptly without consulting your doctor, as it may lead to an increase in blood pressure or chest pain.</p>','<p>Adalat Chrono 60mg is a medication that is primarily used to treat high blood pressure (hypertension) and certain types of chest pain (angina). It contains the active ingredient nifedipine, which belongs to a class of drugs called calcium channel blockers. Adalat Chrono 60mg helps relax and widen the blood vessels, allowing blood to flow more easily and reducing the workload on the heart.</p>','<p><strong>Side Effects:</strong></p>\n\n<p>While most people tolerate Adalat Chrono 60mg well, some individuals may experience mild side effects. It&rsquo;s important to note that not everyone will experience these side effects, and they are usually temporary. Common side effects may include:</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Flushing or warmth in the face</p>\n\n<p>Headache</p>\n\n<p>Dizziness or lightheadedness</p>\n\n<p>Swelling in the ankles or feet</p>\n\n<p>Nausea or upset stomach</p>\n\n<p>Remember to consult your doctor if you have any concerns about these side effects or if they persist or worsen over time.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Overall, Adalat Chrono 60mg is a valuable medication for the management of hypertension and angina, providing effective blood pressure control and chest pain relief. With proper usage and under medical supervision, it can contribute to a healthier cardiovascular system and improved quality of life.</p>','[\"adalat-chrono-60mg-170245647835.jpg\"]','AD