rbance), porphyria (rare genetic blood disorder), or electrolyte imbalance (low potassium or magnesium levels). If you get watery or bloody diarrhoea, stop taking Althrocin-500 Tablet 10&#39;s and consult your doctor. The usage of Althrocin-500 Tablet 10&#39;s may, in rare circumstances, induce diarrhoea. However, wait until your doctor instructs you before taking any anti-diarrhea medication. Before using this medication, talk to your doctor if you are pregnant, nursing, think you might be, or want to become pregnant. If absolutely essential, women should only take Erythromycin throughout pregnancy and nursing.</p>','<p>Althrocin 500 Tablet belongs to the macrolide antibiotic subclass. It is widely used to treat conditions like STDs, bronchitis, pneumonia, rosacea, acne, and dental abscesses (infected pockets of pus in the teeth). On the other hand, Althrocin 500 Tablet are commonly used to treat chest or ear infections in children. Bacterial infection is an infection caused by bacteria that have taken up residence inside the body. Any part of the body could be the target, and it spreads swiftly.</p>\n\n<p>The active ingredient in Althrocin 500 Tablets, erythromycin, works by preventing the production of proteins required for the life of bacteria, so slowing or stopping the spread of dangerous microorganisms. As a result, it effectively manages a range of bacterial diseases.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Diarrhoea</li>\n	<li>Feeling sick or nausea</li>\n	<li>Being sick or vomiting</li>\n	<li>Stomach cramps</li>\n	<li>Loss of appetite</li>\n	<li>Bloating</li>\n	<li>Indigestion</li>\n</ul>','[\"althrocin-500mg-17028724654.webp\"]','ALT0500',1,'0','2023-12-18 04:07:56','2025-07-25 11:06:43'),(131,0,'Altraz 1 mg','altraz-1-mg','Tablet','altraz-1-mg-170287275818.webp','ALT001','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>It is important to follow your doctor&rsquo;s instructions and the information provided on the medication label when taking Altraz 1 mg. Take the prescribed dose exactly as directed and at the same time each day for the best results. It is usually taken orally, with or without food.</p>\n\n<p>Beneits:</p>\n\n<p>Altraz 1 mg offers several benefits in the treatment of breast cancer:</p>\n\n<p>Effective treatment: Altraz has proven to be highly effective in the management of hormone receptor-positive breast cancer, which accounts for the majority of breast cancer cases. By inhibiting the production of estrogen, Altraz helps to slow down or stop the growth of cancer cells.</p>\n\n<p>Reduced risk of cancer recurrence: Altraz is often prescribed as an adjuvant therapy after surgery or other treatments to reduce the risk of cancer recurrence. It has been shown to significantly lower the chances of breast cancer returning, improving long-term outcomes for patients.</p>\n\n<p>Well-tolerated: Compared to other hormonal therapies, Altraz is generally well-tolerated with fewer side effects. This makes it a favorable option for many postmenopausal women undergoing breast cancer treatment.</p>\n\n<p>Non-invasive treatment: Altraz is taken orally in the form of a pill, making it a convenient and non-invasive treatment option. It allows patients to continue with their daily activities without interruption.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before starting Altraz 1 mg, it is important to inform your healthcare provider about any allergies or medical conditions you may have. Additionally, disclose all other medications you are taking, including over-the-counter drugs and herbal supplements, as they may interact with Altraz.</p>\n\n<p>It Is also crucial to let your doctor know if you have a history of osteoporosis or bone fractures, as Altraz may increase the risk of bone-related complications. Regular bone density monitoring and appropriate supplementation can help manage this risk.</p>','<p>Altraz 1 mg is a medication that is commonly prescribed for the treatment of breast cancer in postmenopausal women. The active ingredient in Altraz is anastrozole, which belongs to a class of drugs called aromatase inhibitors. It is specifically designed to target and block the enzyme aromatase, which is responsible for the production of estrogen in postmenopausal women.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>While Altraz 1 mg is generally well-tolerated, it may cause some side effects. It is important to remember that not all individuals will experience these side effects, and they may vary in severity. Common side effects include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Hot flashes</li>\n	<li>Joint pain or stiffness</li>\n	<li>Fatigue</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n</ul>','[\"altraz-1-mg-170287275818.webp\"]','ALT001',1,'0','2023-12-18 04:12:49','2025-07-25 11:06:46'),(132,0,'Amantrel 100mg','amantrel-100mg','Tablets','amantrel-100mg-170287303641.webp','AM0100','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>Follow the prescribed dosage as instructed by your healthcare professional.</p>\n\n<p>Take Amantrel 100mg orally with or without food.</p>\n\n<p>Swallow the tablet whole with a glass of water, without crushing or chewing it.</p>\n\n<p>It is recommended to take the medication at the same time each day to maintain a consistent level in the body.</p>\n\n<p>Do not stop taking Amantrel 100mg abruptly without consulting your healthcare professional.</p>\n\n<p>If you miss a dose, take it as soon as you remember. However, if it is close to the next scheduled dose, skip the missed dose and continue with the regular dosing schedule.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Parkinson&#39;s disease: Amantrel 100mg is commonly used in the management of Parkinson&#39;s disease. It can help alleviate symptoms such as tremors, stiffness, and difficulty with movement. It works by increasing the levels of dopamine, a neurotransmitter involved in movement control.</p>\n\n<p>Influenza A treatment and prevention: Amantrel 100mg can be effective in the treatment and prevention of influenza A virus infections. It can help reduce the severity and duration of flu symptoms when taken within 48 hours of onset. It may also be used as a preventive measure during flu outbreaks.</p>\n\n<p>Fatigue in multiple sclerosis: Amantrel 100mg may be prescribed to manage fatigue in individuals with multiple sclerosis (MS). It can help improve energy levels and reduce the impact of fatigue on daily activities.</p>\n\n<p>Off-label uses: Amantrel 100mg is sometimes used off-label for conditions such as chronic fatigue syndrome, fibromyalgia, and certain psychiatric disorders. However, the evidence for its effectiveness in these conditions is limited, and its use should be discussed with a healthcare professional.</p>\n\n<p>Well-tolerated: Amantrel 100mg is generally well-tolerated, and the incidence of serious side effects is relatively low. Common side effects may include nausea, dizziness, insomnia, and dry mouth.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Inform your healthcare professional about allergies to amantadine or other medications.</p>\n\n<p>Discuss medical history, especially kidney disease, heart disease, seizures, or psychiatric disorders.</p>\n\n<p>Inform about all current medications to check for interactions.</p>\n\n<p>Be cautious of dizziness and blurred vision.</p>\n\n<p>Use caution in elderly patients.</p>\n\n<p>Adjust dosage in case of impaired kidney function.</p>\n\n<p>Do not abruptly stop taking the medication.</p>\n\n<p>Consult a healthcare professional if pregnant, planning to become pregnant, or breastfeeding.</p>','<p>Parkinson&#39;s disease is treated with amantrel tablets alone or in combination with other medications. Additionally, it can be used to treat a problem known as drug-induced movement that is brought on by certain medicines.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Dryness in mouth</li>\n	<li>Constipation</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n	<li>Blurred vision</li>\n	<li>Insomnia</li>\n</ul>','[\"amantrel-100mg-170287303641.webp\"]','AM0100',1,'0','2023-12-18 04:17:37','2025-07-25 11:06:50'),(