p','ATO080','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>It is important to follow your doctor&rsquo;s instructions and take Atorvastatin 80mg Tablets exactly as prescribed. Read and adhere to all the directions on the medication label. Do not exceed the recommended dosage or take it for longer than advised.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Taking Atorvastatin 80mg Tablets can provide several benefits for your health:</p>\n\n<p>Lowering cholesterol levels: Atorvastatin effectively reduces LDL cholesterol, commonly known as &ldquo;bad&rdquo; cholesterol, as well as triglycerides, while increasing HDL cholesterol, often referred to as &ldquo;good&rdquo; cholesterol. This can help improve overall cardiovascular health and reduce the risk of heart-related complications.</p>\n\n<p>Cardiovascular protection: By reducing cholesterol levels, Atorvastatin helps prevent the buildup of plaque in the arteries, known as atherosclerosis. This can help maintain clear and healthy blood vessels, reducing the risk of heart attacks, strokes, and other cardiovascular diseases.</p>\n\n<p>Prevention of heart disease: Atorvastatin is particularly beneficial for individuals with existing heart disease or those at high risk of developing it. It can help manage and stabilize existing conditions, prevent the progression of heart disease, and potentially improve overall heart function.</p>\n\n<p>Diabetes management: Atorvastatin has shown potential in improving insulin sensitivity and reducing the risk of cardiovascular complications in individuals with diabetes.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before starting Atorvastatin 80mg Tablets, it is important to consider the following precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Allergies and interactions: Inform your healthcare provider about any known allergies, including allergies to Atorvastatin or any other statins. Additionally, disclose all other medications, supplements, or herbal products you are taking to avoid potential drug interactions.</p>\n\n<p>Liver function: Regular monitoring of liver function is typically recommended when taking Atorvastatin, as rare cases of liver damage have been reported. Inform your doctor of any pre-existing liver conditions or abnormal liver function tests.</p>\n\n<p>Pregnancy and breastfeeding: Atorvastatin is generally not recommended during pregnancy or while breastfeeding. If you are pregnant, planning to become pregnant, or breastfeeding, consult your doctor for alternative treatment options.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>Atorvastatin 80mg is a medication commonly prescribed to manage and control high cholesterol levels. It belongs to a class of drugs called statins, which work by inhibiting the enzyme responsible for cholesterol production in the liver. By lowering cholesterol levels, Atorvastatin can help reduce the risk of heart disease, heart attacks, and strokes.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>Most individuals tolerate Atorvastatin 80mg Tablets well, and side effects are usually mild and temporary. However, it&rsquo;s important to be aware of possible side effects and consult your doctor if any concerns arise. Common side effects may include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Muscle aches or weakness (myalgia)</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Nausea or vomiting</li>\n	<li>Abdominal pain or discomfort</li>\n	<li>Constipation or diarrhea</li>\n	<li>Mild memory problems</li>\n</ul>','[\"atorvastatin-80mg-1702882790100.webp\"]','ATO080',1,'0','2023-12-18 07:00:01','2025-07-25 11:08:27'),(146,0,'Augmentin 375','augmentin-375','Tablets','screenshot-2025-07-19-133538-175291235441.png','AUG0375','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>As directed, consume 10 of the Augmentin 375 Tablets. Depending on your health and how serious your infection is, Augmentin 375 Tablet 10&#39;s dosage and duration may change. Certain typical adverse effects, like skin rashes, nausea, vomiting, bloating, and gas, may occasionally occur. The majority of these adverse effects subside gradually and do not need medical intervention. If you have these side effects frequently, you are urged to speak with your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>Don&#39;t crush, break, or chew the tablet or capsule; instead, swallow it whole.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Broad-spectrum antibiotic: Augmentin 375 Tablet is effective against a wide range of bacterial infections. It can be used to treat various respiratory tract infections, urinary tract infections, skin and soft tissue infections, and other types of bacterial infections.</p>\n\n<p>Enhanced efficacy: The combination of amoxicillin and clavulanic acid in Augmentin 375 Tablet provides enhanced efficacy compared to using amoxicillin alone. Clavulanic acid helps to inhibit bacterial enzymes that can inactivate amoxicillin, allowing it to be more effective in treating infections.</p>\n\n<p>Treatment of resistant bacteria: Augmentin 375 Tablet is particularly useful in treating infections caused by bacteria that are resistant to amoxicillin alone. The addition of clavulanic acid helps overcome resistance and improves the chances of successfully treating the infection.</p>\n\n<p>Convenient dosing: Augmentin 375 Tablet is available in a higher strength, allowing for fewer tablets to be taken per day compared to lower-strength formulations. This can make dosing more convenient and improve adherence to the prescribed treatment.</p>\n\n<p>Rapid onset of action: Augmentin 375 Tablet is quickly absorbed by the body, leading to a rapid onset of action. This means that the medication starts working relatively quickly to combat the bacterial infection.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Allergies: Inform your healthcare professional if you have any known allergies to amoxicillin, clavulanic acid, or any other medications. Allergic reactions may include rash, itching, swelling, or difficulty breathing.</p>\n\n<p>Medical conditions: Discuss your medical history with your healthcare professional, especially if you have a history of liver disease, kidney disease, or gastrointestinal problems. These conditions may require special monitoring or dosage adjustments when taking Augmentin 375 Tablet.</p>\n\n<p>Antibiotic resistance: Misuse or overuse of antibiotics can lead to the development of antibiotic-resistant bacteria. Follow the prescribed dosage and duration of treatment to minimize the risk of antibiotic resistance.</p>\n\n<p>Drug interactions: Inform your healthcare professional about all the medications you are currently taking, including prescription drugs, over-the-counter medications, and herbal supplements. Certain medications may interact with Augmentin 375 Tablet, so it&#39;s important to check for potential drug interactions.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>To treat bacterial infections of the ear, nose, throat, skin, bone, soft tissue, joints, urinary system, and respiratory tract, Augmentin 375 Tablet 10s is a member of the class of drugs known as antibiotics. When harmful bacteria infiltrate our bodies, it is known as a bacterial infection. You can get sick from harmful or contagious bacteria, and they can proliferate swiftly in your body.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;The medication Augmentin 375 Tablet 10s contains both amoxicillin and clavulanic acid. Amoxicillin prevents the bacterial cell covering from forming, which is essential for the bacteria&#39;s survival. It therefore eliminates the microorganisms. By reducing bacterial resistance and boosting the effectiveness of amoxicillin against the bacterium, clavulanic acid works. Augmentin 375 Tablet 10s work together to treat bacterial infections.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Skin rashes</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Bloating</li>\n	<li>Gas</li>\n</ul>','[\"screenshot-2025-07-19-133538-175291235441.png\"]','AUG0375',1,'1','2023-12-18 07:02:26','2025-07-19 08:06:07'),(147,0,'Augmentin 625mg','augmentin-625mg','Tablets','screenshot-2025-07-23-220309-175328841354.png','AUG0625','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>It is important to follow your doctor&rsquo;s instructions and read the medication label carefully when taking Augmenti