e based on your specific circumstances and ensure the safe and effective use of the medication.</p>','<p>Antibiotic medicine Azee 100mg Tablet DT is available. It is frequently administered to kids to treat a variety of bacterial infections that affect the ear, eyes, nose, throat, lungs, skin, and digestive system.</p>\n\n<p>Azee 100mg Tablet DT functions by preventing the infection-causing germs from growing and replicating. This prevents the virus from spreading further. Typically, one Azee 100mg Tablet DT is administered each day, ideally in the morning. Typhoid, on the other hand, requires that it be administered twice. Give it at roughly the same time every day, with or without food. Given that youngsters frequently have sensitive stomachs and are susceptible to stomach discomfort, it is recommended to administer it with food.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<p>Children handle Azee 100mg Tablet DT well and there are no significant negative effects to report. If adverse effects do develop, they will probably go away once the body becomes used to the medication. If these side effects linger or irritate your kid, talk to their doctor. The most frequent side effects are:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Abdominal pain</li>\n	<li>Diarrhea</li>\n</ul>','[\"azee-dt-100mg-170288630395.webp\"]','AZDT0100',1,'0','2023-12-18 07:58:35','2025-07-25 11:08:53'),(155,0,'Aziderm Cream 10 % (15gm):','aziderm-cream-10--(15gm):','Cream','aziderm-cream-10-15gm-170290073550.webp','AZ010','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>Apply AZIDERM 10% cream as your doctor instructs. Only outside parties may utilize it. Both before and after using Aziderm 10% Cream, wash your hands with soap and water. This medication should be applied to the affected area in a thin layer and carefully massaged into the skin.</p>\n\n<p>Applying this medication near your mouth, eyes, or other mucous membranes or open wounds is not advised. If it does, quickly rinse the eyes, mouth, and other mucous membranes with lots of cool water.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Acne treatment: Aziderm 10% Cream effectively treats acne by targeting the underlying causes. It helps to unclog pores, reduce the formation of whiteheads, blackheads, and pimples, and clear existing acne lesions. The cream&#39;s antibacterial properties help eliminate acne-causing bacteria, leading to a reduction in inflammation and visible acne.</li>\n	<li>Rosacea management: Aziderm 10% Cream is also beneficial for managing rosacea. It helps reduce redness, visible blood vessels, and the presence of pimples associated with rosacea. The cream&#39;s anti-inflammatory properties help alleviate swelling and calm the skin, improving the overall appearance of rosacea-affected skin.</li>\n	<li>Keratolytic action: The keratolytic activity of Aziderm 10% Cream helps remove warts, calluses, and other skin lesions. It promotes exfoliation and the sloughing off of dead skin cells, leading to smoother and healthier skin.</li>\n	<li>Comedolytic effect: Aziderm 10% Cream inhibits the formation of blemishes by preventing the clogging of pores. It reduces the production of excess oil and helps keep the pores clear, reducing the occurrence of acne breakouts.</li>\n	<li>Antioxidant properties: The antioxidant activity of Aziderm 10% Cream helps protect the skin from oxidative damage caused by free radicals. This can contribute to the overall health and vitality of the skin.</li>\n	<li>Skin renewal: Aziderm 10% cream promotes skin renewal and regeneration. It helps the skin shed dead cells and stimulates the growth of new, healthy skin cells, resulting in a more rejuvenated and radiant complexion.</li>\n	<li>Targeted treatment: Aziderm 10% Cream is designed for topical application, allowing for targeted treatment of affected areas. This enables precise application on acne lesions or areas affected by rosacea, ensuring maximum effectiveness.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Some precautions to consider when using Aziderm 10% Cream 15 g include avoiding contact with the eyes, mouth, and other sensitive areas; conducting a patch test prior to use; informing your doctor about any allergies or skin conditions; and consulting a healthcare professional before use during pregnancy or breastfeeding.</p>\n\n<p>Avoid contact with sensitive areas: Take care to avoid contact with the eyes, mouth, nostrils, and other sensitive areas of the body. If accidental contact occurs, rinse thoroughly with water.</p>\n\n<p>Patch test: Before using Aziderm 10% Cream for the first time, perform a patch test on a small area of skin to check for any adverse reactions or allergies. Discontinue use if irritation or allergic reactions occur.</p>\n\n<p>Inform your doctor: Inform your doctor or healthcare professional about any allergies or skin conditions you may have before using Aziderm 10% Cream.</p>\n\n<p>Sun protection: Aziderm 10% Cream may increase the skin&#39;s sensitivity to sunlight. It is important to protect your skin from sun exposure by using sunscreen, wearing protective clothing, and avoiding prolonged sun exposure.</p>\n\n<p>Follow instructions: Follow the instructions provided by your doctor or healthcare professional regarding the frequency and duration of application. Do not exceed the recommended dosage or use the cream for a longer period of time without medical supervision.</p>','<p>Aziderm 10% Cream 15 gm is classified as an &quot;anti-acne medication&quot; and is primarily utilized for the treatment of acne (pimples) and rosacea (redness and visible blood vessels on the face). This cream possesses various properties, including antibacterial, keratolytic (removing warts, calluses, and other lesions), comedolytic (inhibiting blemish formation), and antioxidant activities. It effectively targets and clears bumps, lesions, and swelling associated with rosacea. Acne, which occurs when hair follicles become clogged with oil and dead skin cells, can result in the formation of whiteheads, blackheads, and pimples. Rosacea, on the other hand, is a skin condition characterized by facial redness, flushing, and the presence of pimples.</p>\n\n<p>Aziderm 10% Cream 15 gm contains &quot;azelaic acid,&#39; which acts as a bactericidal agent, killing bacteria. It functions by inhibiting the synthesis of microbial cellular proteins. By clearing the pores of bacteria that cause irritation and breakouts, Aziderm 10% Cream 15 gm reduces inflammation, resulting in less visible, less red, and less irritated acne. Moreover, it aids in the renewal of the skin and minimizes the formation of pimples and blackheads.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>The most common side effects are listed below:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Dryness</li>\n	<li>Peeling</li>\n	<li>Burning</li>\n	<li>Irritation</li>\n	<li>Itching</li>\n	<li>Redness at the application site</li>\n</ul>','[\"aziderm-cream-10-15gm-170290073550.webp\"]','AZ010',1,'0','2023-12-18 11:59:06','2025-07-25 11:08:56'),(156,0,'Endace 40mg','endace-40mg','Tablet','endace-40mg-170315634243.webp','EN040','<p><strong>Usage:</strong></p>\n\n<p>Both a tablet and an oral suspension of Endace 40 Tablet 10&#39;s are available. You must take this medication exactly as your doctor has instructed. elevated hunger, weight gain, shortness of breath, hot flushes (reddening of the face and neck), high blood pressure, elevated blood sugar levels, rounder face, constipation, and ballooning of a vein as a result of a blood clot are common adverse effects of Endace 40 Tablet 10. Inform your doctor right away if any of these adverse effects last longer than expected or develop worse.</p>\n\n<p>Take the entire pill with a glass of water. Do not chew, break, or chew it. Taking it with or without food is acceptable.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Benefits:</strong></p>\n\n<p>Megestrol, a substance used to treat breast and endometrial cancer, is a component of Endace 40 Tablet 10s. It works by hindering the hormones&#39; ability to produce the cancer-causing chemicals. Effective relief from cancer symptoms is provided by it. Patients with HIV/AIDS can also use it to alleviate their loss of appetite.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Precautions:</strong></p>\n\n<p>Endace 40 Tablet 10&#39;s should not be administered to patients with a history of thrombophlebitis since it raises the risk of blood clots. Additionally, you should let your doctor know right away if you experience any of the following symptoms: poor coordination, difficulty speaking, discomfort in the groin, pain in the arm or leg (particularly in the calf), shortness of breath, generalized weakness, headache, and dizziness. These symptoms could be indicators of blood clots. Pregnancy is not advised when using Endace 40 Tablet 10&#39;s. Use a trustworthy method of contraception while taking this medication to avoid getting pregnant. Before using this medication, you might also need to get tested for pregnancy. If you have a sugar intolerance, let your doctor know since Endace 40 Tablet 10s contain lactose.</p>','<p>As a symptomatic treatment for patients with endometrial and breast cancer, Endace 40 Tablet 10s is a member of the progestogen class of drugs. A lump in the breast, a change in the contour of the nipple or breast, and bloody flow from the nipples are all signs that breast cancer is developing in the breast cells. Endometrial cancer, which affects the lining of the uterus, is characterized by pelvic pain, bleeding between periods, and discomfort during sensual activity.</p>\n\n<p>Megestrol, a substance classified as a progestogen, is present in Endace 40 Tablet 10s. Similar to the feminine hormone &quot;progesterone,&quot; it functions. It obstructs hormones involved in the development of cancer from being produced or acting. This impact lessens the symptoms brought on by cancer and slows down its development.</p>','<p><strong>Side Effects:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Increase in appetite</li>\n	<li>Weight gain</li>\n	<li>Shortness of breath</li>\n	<li>Hot flushes (reddening of the face and neck)</li>\n	<li>High blood pressure</li>\n	<li>Increased blood sugar levels</li>\n	<li>Rounded face</li>\n	<li>Constipation</li>\n</ul>','[\"endace-40mg-170315634243.webp\"]','EN040',1,'0','2023-12-21 10:59:12','2025-07-25 11:08:58'),(157,0,'Azithral Eye Drops0.1% (3ml)','azithral-eye-drops0.1-(3ml)','Drops','azithral-eye-drops-0-170325015513.webp','AZI001','<p><strong>Usage:</strong></p>\n\n<p>To ensure safe and effective use of AZITHRAL EYE DROPS, it&#39;s important to follow your doctor&#39;s instructions exactly as prescribed. This medication is intended for use in the eyes only and should not be applied to any other part of the body. To reduce the risk of infection, always wash your hands thoroughly before handling the dropper.</p>\n\n<p>To apply the drops, gently tilt your head backward and use your fingers to create a small pocket by pulling down your lower eyelid. Take care not to touch the tip of the dropper to your eye or any other surface to prevent contamination. Instill the recommended number of drops into the pocket, and then close your eye gently. Applying gentle pressure to the inside corner of your eye with your finger can help improve the medication&#39;s effectiveness.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Benefits:</strong></p>\n\n<p>Azithral Eye Drops 3 ml contains azithromycin, an antibiotic medication that works by killing bacteria that cause infections. It is primarily used to treat bacterial infections of the eye, including bacterial conjunctivitis and trachoma conjunctivitis.</p>\n\n<p>In addition to treating eye infections, Azithral Eye Drops 3 ml can also be used to treat a variety of other bacterial infections throughout the body, such as those affecting the blood, brain, lungs, bones, joints, urinary tract, stomach, and intestines. It is even effective in treating sexually transmitted diseases.</p>\n\n<p>To ensure the medication is effective, it&#39;s important to take it for the full duration of treatment as prescribed by your doctor and to avoid skipping any doses. Doing so will ensure that all bacteria are eliminated and will help prevent the development of antibiotic resistance.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Precautions:</strong></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Use the medication only as directed by your doctor.</li>\n	<li>Do not share the medication with others.</li>\n	<li>Wash your hands before and after use to prevent the spread of infection.</li>\n	<li>Do not touch the tip of the dropper to your eye or any other surface to prevent contamination.</li>\n	<li>Discard any remaining medication after the prescribed course of treatment is complete.</li>\n	<li>Inform your doctor if you are pregnant, breastfeeding, or have any underlying medical conditions before using this medication.</li>\n	<li>If you experience any adverse reactions or allergy symptoms, stop using the medication immediately and seek medical attention.</li>\n</ul>','<p>Azithral Eye Drops 3 ml is a type of macrolide antibiotic that is used for treating bacterial infections of the eye. The medication is effective against bacterial conjunctivitis and trachoma conjunctivitis, which are both conditions that cause inflammation or infection of the transparent membrane that lines the eyelids and eyes. Bacterial conjunctivitis is a common type of eye infection that can cause discomfort and irritation, while trachoma conjunctivitis is caused by a specific bacteria known as Chlamydia trachomatis.</p>\n\n<p>Azithral Eye Drops 3 ml contains azithromycin, which is the active ingredient responsible for killing the bacteria that cause these eye infections. By eliminating the bacteria, Azithral Eye Drops 3 ml helps to relieve symptoms and treat the underlying infection. To get the best results from this medication, it is important to use it at the dose and duration recommended by your doctor. You should use the drops regularly, at the intervals prescribed by your doctor, and should not skip any doses. Even if you start feeling better, it is important to complete the full course of treatment to prevent the infection from coming back or getting worse. Stopping the medication too early can lead to the infection returning or becoming more severe.</p>','<p><strong>Side Effects:</strong></p>\n\n<p>The majority of side effects caused by the medication typically resolve on their own as your body adapts to the treatment and do not require medical intervention. However, if any side effects persist or cause you concern, it is recommended that you consult your doctor for further advice and guidance.</p>\n\n<p>The most common side Effects are listed below:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Burning eyes</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Abdominal pain</li>\n</ul>','[\"azithral-eye-drops-0-170325015513.webp\"]','AZI001',1,'0','2023-12-28 04:30:16','2025-07-22 04:59:02'),(158,0,'Melalite Forte 4% 30 gm','melalite-forte-4-30-gm-','Cream','melalite-forte-4-30-gm-170373829239.webp','MEL004','<p><strong>Usage:</strong></p>\n\n<p>It is important to follow your doctor&rsquo;s or dermatologist&rsquo;s instructions when using Melalite Forte Cream. Read the label carefully and follow the prescribed dosage and application guidelines. Apply a thin layer of the cream to the affected areas of the skin, gently massaging it until fully absorbed. It is usually recommended to apply the cream once or twice daily, depending on your doctor&rsquo;s recommendation.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Benefits:</strong></p>\n\n<p>Melalite Forte Cream 4% 30gm offers several benefits for those dealing with skin discoloration issues:</p>\n\n<p>Hyperpigmentation treatment: The cream&rsquo;s active ingredient, hydroquinone, works by reducing the production of melanin in the skin, thereby lightening dark spots and patches caused by conditions like melasma, sun damage, or hormonal changes.</p>\n\n<p>Even skin tone: Melalite Forte Cream helps to promote an even skin tone by reducing the appearance of uneven pigmentation, giving the skin a more radiant and youthful look.</p>\n\n<p>Boosts self-confidence: Skin discoloration can often affect a person&rsquo;s self-esteem. By effectively lightening dark spots and pigmentation, Melalite Forte Cream can help improve the appearance of the skin, leading to increased self-confidence.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Precautions:</strong></p>\n\n<p>While Melalite Forte Cream can be highly beneficial, it is essential to take certain precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Patch test: Before applying the cream to larger areas of the skin, it is recommended to perform a patch test on a small area to check for any allergic reactions or sensitivity.</p>\n\n<p>Sun protection: During the use of Melalite Forte Cream, it is crucial to protect your skin from the sun&rsquo;s harmful rays. Apply a broad-spectrum sunscreen with a high SPF and limit sun exposure to prevent further skin damage.</p>\n\n<p>Consultation with a healthcare professional: It is advisable to consult a dermatologist or healthcare professional before starting Melalite Forte Cream, especially if you have any underlying skin conditions or are using other medications or treatments.</p>','<p>Melalite Forte Cream 4% 30gm is a topical medication that is widely used for various skin conditions. It contains the active ingredient hydroquinone, which is known for its skin-lightening properties. This cream is primarily used to treat hyperpigmentation, dark spots, melasma, and other skin discoloration issues.</p>','<p><strong>Side Effects:</strong></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>While side effects from Melalite Forte Cream are rare, it is important to be aware of potential reactions. These side effects are usually mild and temporary, and they may include:</p>\n\n<p>Temporary skin irritation: Some individuals may experience mild redness, itching, or stinging at the site of application. These effects typically subside as your skin adjusts to the cream.</p>\n\n<p>Skin sensitivity: Prolonged or excessive use of hydroquinone-based creams can sometimes lead to increased skin sensitivity. If you experience severe or persistent irritation, discontinue use and consult your healthcare professional.</p>\n\n<p>Remember, it is essential to consult a dermatologist or healthcare professional before starting any new skincare regimen or using Melalite Forte Cream, as they can provide personalized advice based on your specific skin needs and concerns.</p>','[\"melalite-forte-4-30-gm-170373829239.webp\"]','MEL004',1,'0','2023-12-28 04:38:24','2025-07-22 04:59:07'),(159,0,'9 PM Eye Drop 2.5ml (0.005%)','9-pm-eye-drop-2.5ml-(0.005-)','Drops','9-pm-eye-drop-2-171404133425.jpg','PM009','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>This medication is intended for external use only. Use it according to the dosage and duration prescribed by your doctor. Prior to use, refer to the label for instructions. When administering, hold the dropper near the eye without making contact. Gently squeeze the dropper to place the medication inside the lower eyelid. Remove any excess liquid.</p>\n\n<p>9 PM Eye drops are appropriate for both adults and children. It can be used alone or in combination with other eye medications to reduce eye pressure. Adhere to your doctor&#39;s instructions and use this medication regularly to achieve optimal benefits. Ceasing its usage may lead to an increase in eye pressure, potentially causing vision damage. Never use a bottle if the seal is broken before initial use. If you wear contact lenses, remove them before instilling the medication and wait for at least 15 minutes before reinserting them.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>For Glaucoma: 9 PM Eye drops are medications utilized to decrease the pressure in the eyes caused by ocular hypertension. Elevated eye pressure can lead to a condition known as glaucoma, which can result in vision impairment. This medication functions by facilitating the drainage of fluid from the interior of the eye into the bloodstream. It can be used alone or in combination with other eye drops. Avoid excessive use, as it may reduce the effectiveness of the medication. It should only be applied to the affected eye and taken regularly as directed by your doctor. Discontinuing its use may lead to uncontrolled eye pressure and potential vision loss.</p>\n\n<p>For Ocular Hypertension: 9 PM Eye drops belong to a group of medications called prostaglandin analogues. It is employed to reduce elevated eye pressure in cases of ocular hypertension. By enhancing the flow of fluid from the interior of the eye into the bloodstream, it effectively lowers the heightened pressure. Excessive eye pressure can have detrimental effects on vision. Apply the eye drop only to the affected eye and take it regularly as prescribed by your doctor. Ceasing its usage may result in uncontrolled eye pressure and its associated risks.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Use 9 PM Eye Drop only for external application as directed.</li>\n	<li>Follow the prescribed dosage and duration recommended by your doctor.</li>\n	<li>Check the label instructions before use.</li>\n	<li>Administer the drops without touching the eye.</li>\n	<li>Wipe off any excess liquid.</li>\n	<li>Avoid excessive use, as it may reduce effectiveness.</li>\n	<li>Use the medication only in the affected eye.</li>\n	<li>Take it regularly, as prescribed, to maintain controlled eye pressure.</li>\n	<li>Do not discontinue without consulting your doctor, as it may lead to uncontrolled eye pressure and potential vision loss.</li>\n	<li>Check for an unbroken seal before using the bottle for the first time.</li>\n	<li>If you wear contact lenses, remove them before instilling the eye drops and wait for at least 15 minutes before reinserting them.</li>\n</ul>','<p>9 PM Eye Drop is a medication prescribed for individuals with glaucoma and ocular hypertension (elevated eye pressure) to decrease the pressure within the eyes. High eye pressure can be detrimental to vision and may even result in blindness. This medication works by facilitating the drainage of fluid from the interior of the eye into the bloodstream.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>The majority of side effects do not need medical attention and typically subside as your body adapts to the medication. However, if you are concerned or if the side effects persist, it is recommended that you consult your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>The most common side effects are listed below:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Th Eyelash changes</li>\n	<li>Eye pain</li>\n	<li>Increased sensitivity to light</li>\n	<li>Burning sensation in eye</li>\n	<li>Eye itching</li>\n	<li>Foreign body sensation</li>\n	<li>Itching</li>\n</ul>','[\"9-pm-eye-drop-2-171404133425.jpg\"]','PM009',1,'0','2024-01-05 06:43:03','2025-07-22 04:59:10'),(160,0,'Accuzide Forte 20/25 mg','accuzide-forte-20/25-mg','Tablet','accuzide-forte-20-25-mg-17044376354.jpg','ACU0225','<p>How to Use:</p>\n\n<p>To benefit from Accuzide Forte 20/25 mg, it is important to follow your doctor&rsquo;s instructions carefully. Read and adhere to all the guidelines provided on the medication label. Take the prescribed dosage as directed by your healthcare professional, usually once a day. It can be taken with or without food, but consistency in timing is recommended for best results.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Blood pressure management: Accuzide Forte 20/25 mg combines hydrochlorothiazide and quinapril to effectively control high blood pressure. Hydrochlorothiazide is a diuretic that helps remove excess fluid from the body, while quinapril is an ACE inhibitor that relaxes blood vessels, reducing resistance and improving blood flow. Together, they help lower blood pressure, reducing the risk of cardiovascular problems.</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Cardiovascular protection: By effectively managing blood pressure, Accuzide Forte 20/25 mg helps reduce the risk of heart attack, stroke, and other cardiovascular complications. It improves overall heart health and promotes healthy blood circulation.</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Kidney protection: Accuzide Forte 20/25 mg has been shown to have protective effects on the kidneys, particularly in individuals with diabetes and high blood pressure. By controlling blood pressure, it helps prevent damage to the kidneys and reduces the risk of kidney-related complications.</p>\n\n<p>Precuations:</p>\n\n<p>Before starting Accuzide Forte 20/25 mg, it is important to inform your healthcare provider about any allergies you have, including to this medication, other ACE inhibitors, diuretics, or any other substances. Discuss your complete medical history, including any kidney or liver problems, diabetes, or a history of angioedema.</p>\n\n<p>It Is advisable to avoid alcohol consumption while taking Accuzide Forte 20/25 mg, as it can potentiate the blood pressure-lowering effects and increase the likelihood of side effects.</p>\n\n<p>If you are pregnant, planning to become pregnant, or breastfeeding, consult your healthcare professional before using Accuzide Forte 20/25 mg, as it may not be suitable during these times.</p>','<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Accuzide Forte 20/25 mg is a medication that combines two active ingredients, hydrochlorothiazide and quinapril, to effectively manage high blood pressure (hypertension). It belongs to a class of medications known as ACE inhibitors and diuretics.</p>','<p>Side Efects:</p>\n\n<p>Most side effects associated with Accuzide Forte 20/25 mg are mild and temporary. If you experience any concerns or persistent side effects, consult your doctor. Common side effects may include:</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Dizziness or lightheadedness: Some individuals may experience mild dizziness or lightheadedness, particularly when standing up quickly. It is advisable to rise slowly from a sitting or lying position to minimize these effects.</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Increased urination: Due to the diuretic effect of hydrochlorothiazide, you may notice an increase in urination frequency. This is a normal response and helps remove excess fluid from the body.</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Dry cough: ACE inhibitors like quinapril can sometimes cause a dry, persistent cough. If the cough becomes bothersome, inform your doctor for further evaluation.</p>','[\"accuzide-forte-20-25-mg-17044376354.jpg\"]','ACU0225',1,'0','2024-01-05 06:54:05','2025-07-25 11:09:02'),(161,0,'Acnesol Gel 1% (20gm)','acnesol-gel-1-(20gm)','Cream','acnesol-gel-1-20gm-22-171562244882.jpg','ACN0120','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>Follow the instructions provided by your doctor when applying ACNESOL GEL. Remember that it is meant for external use only. Prior to application, ensure that you wash your hands. Clean and dry the entire affected area, then apply a thin layer of the gel once daily to the skin where acne lesions are present, using enough to cover the entire affected area. If the gel comes into contact with your eyes, mouth, or nostrils, promptly and thoroughly rinse it off with water. Your doctor will determine the appropriate dosage and duration of treatment based on factors such as your age, body weight, and the severity of your condition.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Acne treatment: Acnesol Gel is primarily used for the treatment of acne. It helps to reduce the symptoms associated with acne, such as blackheads, pimples, and red bumps. The gel works by inhibiting bacterial growth, which is a common cause of acne.</li>\n	<li>Antibacterial action: Acnesol Gel contains the active ingredient clindamycin, which has potent antibacterial properties. It works by inhibiting the synthesis of bacterial proteins, thereby preventing the growth and multiplication of acne-causing bacteria.</li>\n	<li>Reduction of inflammation: Acnesol Gel possesses anti-inflammatory properties, which help to decrease inflammation associated with acne lesions. This can lead to a reduction in the redness, swelling, and discomfort caused by acne breakouts.</li>\n	<li>Improved skin appearance: Regular use of Acnesol Gel can lead to an improvement in the overall appearance of the skin. It helps to clear up existing acne lesions and prevent the formation of new ones, resulting in smoother, clearer skin.</li>\n	<li>Convenient and easy to use: Acnesol Gel is formulated for topical application, making it convenient and easy to use. It can be applied directly to the affected areas of the skin, allowing for targeted treatment of acne lesions.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>For external use only: Acnesol Gel is meant for external use on the skin and should not be ingested. Avoid contact with the eyes, mouth, nostrils, and other sensitive areas. In the event of accidental contact, rinse thoroughly with water.</li>\n	<li>Allergic reactions: Before using Acnesol Gel, inform your doctor if you have a history of allergies or hypersensitivity to clindamycin or any other ingredients present in the gel. If you experience any signs of an allergic reaction, such as a rash, itching, swelling, or difficulty breathing, discontinue use and seek medical attention.</li>\n	<li>Avoid excessive sun exposure: Acnesol Gel may increase the skin&#39;s sensitivity to sunlight. It is recommended to limit your exposure to the sun and to use protective measures, such as wearing sunscreen and protective clothing and avoiding tanning beds or sunlamps.</li>\n	<li>Pregnancy and breastfeeding: If you are pregnant, planning to become pregnant, or breastfeeding, consult your doctor before using Acnesol Gel. They will assess the potential risks and benefits and guide you accordingly.</li>\n	<li>Skin irritation: In some cases, Acnesol Gel may cause skin dryness, redness, itching, or irritation. If you experience any persistent or severe skin reactions, discontinue use and consult your doctor.</li>\n</ul>','<p>Acnesol Gel 20 gm is categorized as an antibiotic medication utilized primarily for the treatment of acne, a skin condition resulting from the clogging of hair follicles with oil and dead skin cells. Common symptoms include blackheads, pus-filled pimples, and swollen or red bumps. The active ingredient in Acnesol Gel 20 gm is &#39;Clindamycin&#39;, which acts by hindering bacterial protein synthesis and effectively halting bacterial growth. It demonstrates a bacteriostatic effect, impeding the multiplication of bacteria.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>The most common side effects are listed below:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Burning sensation</li>\n	<li>Itching</li>\n	<li>Dryness</li>\n	<li>Redness</li>\n	<li>Oily skin</li>\n</ul>','[\"acnesol-gel-1-20gm-22-171562244882.jpg\"]','ACN0120',1,'0','2024-01-05 07:17:40','2025-07-25 11:09:07'),(162,0,'Activelle (1+0.5)mg','activelle-(1+0.5)mg','Tablet','activelle-1-0-170490053384.jpg','ACT0105','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>It is crucial to follow your doctor&rsquo;s instructions and carefully read the medication label before using Activelle. The typical recommended dosage is one tablet per day, preferably taken at the same time each day. It is advised to swallow the tablet whole with water, without crushing or chewing it. Consistency in taking the medication will help ensure its effectiveness.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Activelle offers several benefits to women experiencing menopausal symptoms, enhancing their overall well-being and quality of life. Some of the positive effects of Activelle include:</p>\n\n<p>Alleviating menopausal symptoms: Activelle helps reduce or eliminate the various symptoms associated with menopause, such as hot flashes, night sweats, mood swings, vaginal dryness, and sleep disturbances. By providing a balance of hormones, it can significantly improve the comfort and daily lives of women going through this transitional phase.</p>\n\n<p>Preventing osteoporosis: Menopause is often accompanied by a decrease in bone density, making women more susceptible to osteoporosis. Activelle contains estradiol, which helps to prevent bone loss and maintain bone strength, reducing the risk of fractures and osteoporotic complications.</p>\n\n<p>Improving vaginal health: During menopause, declining estrogen levels can lead to vaginal dryness and discomfort. Activelle, with its estrogen component, helps restore vaginal health by replenishing moisture and reducing irritation, itching, and painful intercourse.</p>\n\n<p>Supporting cardiovascular health: Hormone fluctuations during menopause can have an impact on cardiovascular health. Activelle contains estradiol, which may contribute to maintaining healthy cholesterol levels, reducing the risk of heart disease and maintaining overall cardiovascular well-being.</p>\n\n<p>Promoting emotional balance: Menopausal symptoms can often lead to emotional changes and mood swings. Activelle can help stabilize hormonal levels, promoting emotional balance and overall mental well-being.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before starting Activelle, it is important to consult with your healthcare provider and disclose your complete medical history, including any existing conditions or allergies. Your doctor will consider individual factors and assess if Activelle is suitable for you.</p>','<p>Activelle (1+0.5)mg is a medication that combines two active ingredients, estradiol and norethisterone acetate, to provide relief and support for women experiencing menopausal symptoms. It is a hormone replacement therapy (HRT) that aims to alleviate the discomfort and challenges associated with hormonal changes during menopause. Here are some Important points about Activelle:</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>While most women tolerate Activelle well, it is essential to be aware of potential side effects, even though they are generally mild and temporary. Some reported side effects may include:</p>\n\n<p>Nausea or gastrointestinal discomfort: Some women may experience mild gastrointestinal symptoms such as nausea or bloating initially. These symptoms often improve over time as the body adjusts to the medication.</p>\n\n<p>Breast tenderness: In some cases, breast tenderness or mild breast enlargement may occur. These effects usually subside on their own, but if they persist or become bothersome, consulting with your doctor is recommended.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','[\"activelle-1-0-170490053384.jpg\"]','ACT0105',1,'0','2024-01-10 15:29:26','2025-07-25 10:48:09'),(163,0,'Aldactone 100 mg','aldactone-100-mg','Tablet','aldactone-100-mg-170490129934.webp','ALD0100','<p>How to Use a Tablet of Aldactone:</p>\n\n<p>Follow your doctor&#39;s instructions for this medication&#39;s dosage and duration. Take it all in at once. Don&#39;t eat it, break it, or crush it. Aldactone 100 Tablet should be consumed alongside food.</p>\n\n<p>Functions of Aldactone Tablet:</p>\n\n<p>A diuretic that conserves potassium is Aldactone 100 Tablet. By eliminating the surplus water and electrolytes from the body without losing potassium, it reduces blood pressure and swelling.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>High blood pressure, or hypertension</p>\n\n<p>By eliminating extra salt and water from your body, Aldactone 100 Tablet reduces blood pressure. Lowering your blood pressure reduces your risk of suffering a heart attack or stroke and makes it easier for your heart to pump blood throughout your body.</p>\n\n<p>Typically, this medication is taken in addition to other blood pressure-lowering drugs. Usually, taking this medication does not result in any immediate benefits for you, but over time, it keeps you healthy. Even if you feel better, you should still take the medication as directed to get the most benefit.</p>\n\n<p>The Edoema</p>\n\n<p>Your body retaining too much water results in edoema. Aldactone 100 Tablet increases the amount of urine generated, which aids in eliminating surplus water and electrolytes from your body. By allowing your body to expel surplus water, symptoms like shortness of breath and edoema in your arms, legs, or abdomen are lessened. As a result, you can go about your everyday activities in more comfort. For best results, take it consistently and adjust your lifestyle appropriately.</p>\n\n<p>Low potassium levels</p>\n\n<p>Aldactone 100 Tablet maintains your potassium levels from dropping too low, stops your body from absorbing too much salt, and removes extra water.</p>\n\n<p>A heart attack</p>\n\n<p>Heart failure is a condition in which your heart is unable to adequately pump blood to your lungs and the rest of your body. Breathlessness, exhaustion, and swelling in your legs, ankles, abdomen, and other body parts are the most typical symptoms.</p>\n\n<p>With the help of this medication, you will feel better and have more energy. To ensure that this medication is as successful as possible, you should make the necessary lifestyle adjustments (such eating well and exercising often). Even if you start to feel better, continue taking it on a daily basis.</p>','<p>A diuretic (water pill) is a medication by the name of Aldactone 100 Tablet. It is primarily used to treat excessive blood pressure and heart failure. It lessens the edoema (swelling) brought on by a few other conditions. The condition known as hypokalemia is also treated with this medication.</p>\n\n<p>To receive the best benefit, Aldactone 100 Tablet should be taken with food at the same time every day. You should continue using this medication as prescribed, even if you feel better. Taking it early in the day can help prevent you from needing to get up repeatedly during the night to use the restroom. Your condition could worsen if you stop taking it. Follow your doctor&#39;s recommendations regarding the kinds and quantities of liquids you should consume. A low-salt diet and other lifestyle modifications, such as frequent exercise, may help this medication work better if you are being treated for high blood pressure.</p>\n\n<p>Nausea, vomiting, dizziness, and swelling as well as breast tenderness in both men and women are typical adverse effects. Inform your doctor if these disturb you or seem serious. There might be techniques to lessen or stop them. Avoid drinking alcohol since it can make some adverse effects worse.</p>\n\n<p>If you have kidney issues or are unable to pee, you 