ortant to take certain precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Use sunscreen: Tretinoin can increase the skin&rsquo;s sensitivity to sunlight. It is crucial to use sunscreen with a high SPF to protect your skin from harmful UV rays and prevent further skin damage.</p>\n\n<p>Start with a low concentration: A-Ret Gel 0.1% is a relatively strong formulation. If you are new to using tretinoin, it is recommended to start with a lower concentration and gradually increase it to allow your skin to adjust and minimize potential irritation.</p>\n\n<p>Avoid during pregnancy: Tretinoin has been associated with potential risks to developing fetuses. It is advisable to avoid using A-Ret Gel 0.1% if you are pregnant or planning to become pregnant. Consult with your healthcare provider for alternative options.</p>','<p>A-Ret Gel 0.1% is a topical medication that is primarily used for the treatment of acne and other skin conditions. It contains tretinoin, a derivative of vitamin A, which helps to unclog pores, reduce inflammation, and promote skin cell turnover. This gel formulation is beneficial for various reasons, and its positive effects on the skin make it a popular choice among individuals seeking acne treatment.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>Some individuals may experience mild side effects when using A-Ret Gel 0.1%. These side effects are usually temporary and tend to diminish as the skin adjusts to the medication. They may include:</p>\n\n<p>Dryness and peeling: Tretinoin can cause initial dryness and peeling of the skin. This is a normal part of the treatment process as the medication works to renew the skin.</p>\n\n<p>Mild redness and irritation: Some individuals may experience mild redness and irritation, especially during the early stages of treatment. This typically subsides as the skin adapts to the medication.</p>\n\n<p>Sensitivity to sunlight: Tretinoin can increase sun sensitivity, making the skin more prone to sunburn. It is essential to use sunscreen and protective measures when</p>','[\"a-ret-gel-0-171404145199.jpg\"]','ARE001',1,'0','2024-01-28 13:25:08','2025-07-25 11:09:18'),(167,0,'Accuzide Forte 20/12.5 mg','accuzide-forte-20/12.5-mg','Tablet','accuzide-forte-20-12-170646129027.webp','ACC20125','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>It is crucial to follow your doctor&rsquo;s instructions and read the medication label carefully before taking Accuzide Forte 20/12.5 mg. Take the prescribed dose exactly as directed and avoid taking more or less than recommended or for a longer duration than advised.</p>\n\n<p>Accuzide Forte 20/12.5 mg is available in tablet form. The recommended dosage is one tablet per day. It is typically taken orally with or without food. Swallow the tablet whole, without crushing or chewing it.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Accuzide Forte 20/12.5 mg offers several benefits in managing high blood pressure:</p>\n\n<p>Effective blood pressure control: Accuzide Forte combines the benefits of both hydrochlorothiazide and quinapril to effectively lower high blood pressure. Hydrochlorothiazide is a diuretic that helps remove excess fluid from the body, while quinapril is an ACE inhibitor that relaxes and widens blood vessels.</p>\n\n<p>Reduced risk of cardiovascular complications: By controlling high blood pressure, Accuzide Forte can help reduce the risk of serious cardiovascular conditions such as heart attack, stroke, and kidney problems.</p>\n\n<p>Combination therapy convenience: Accuzide Forte 20/12.5 mg offers the convenience of combining two medications in a single tablet, making it easier to manage high blood pressure by reducing the number of pills to take.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before starting Accuzide Forte 20/12.5 mg, it is important to inform your healthcare provider about any allergies you may have, especially to ACE inhibitors or thiazide diuretics. Discuss your medical history, including any kidney or liver problems, diabetes, or history of angioedema.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>Accuzide Forte 20/12.5 mg is a med