s:</p>\n\n<p>The majority of side effects do not need medical attention and typically subside as your body adapts to the medication. However, if you are concerned or if the side effects persist, it is recommended that you consult your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>The most common side effects are listed below:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Hoarseness of voice</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n	<li>Pharyngitis</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n</ul>','[\"aerocort-forte-rotacaps-200-100-170646529733.webp\"]','AER020',1,'0','2024-01-28 18:08:26','2025-07-25 11:09:23'),(171,0,'Aerocort Inhaler 50mcg 50mcg (200 mdi)','aerocort-inhaler-50mcg-50mcg-(200-mdi)','Inhaler','aerocort-inhaler-50mcg-50mcg-200-mdi-22-171567184919.webp','AER050','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>Shake the inhaler well before each use to ensure that the medication is properly mixed.</p>\n\n<p>Prepare the inhaler: Remove the cap from the mouthpiece of the inhaler. Check the inhaler to ensure that it is clean and free from any debris.</p>\n\n<p>Prime the inhaler (if required): If it is a new inhaler or has not been used for a certain period of time, it may require priming. This involves releasing a few sprays into the air to ensure proper functioning. Refer to the specific instructions provided with the inhaler for priming details.</p>\n\n<p>Breathe out. Exhale fully to empty your lungs.</p>\n\n<p>Place the mouthpiece in your mouth: Hold the inhaler with the mouthpiece toward you and place it in your mouth, ensuring a tight seal with your lips.</p>\n\n<p>Start inhaling: Begin inhaling slowly and deeply through your mouth. Press down on the inhaler to release one puff of medication into your mouth while continuing to breathe steadily.</p>\n\n<p>Hold your breath: After inhaling, remove the inhaler from your mouth and hold your breath for about 10 seconds, or for as long as is comfortable.</p>\n\n<p>Breathe out slowly. Exhale slowly through your nose or mouth.</p>\n\n<p>Repeat (if necessary): If your healthcare professional has prescri