y of liver disease, kidney disease, or gastrointestinal problems. These conditions may require special monitoring or dosage adjustments when taking Augmentin DUO 1000 Tablet.</p>\n\n<p>Antibiotic resistance: Misuse or overuse of antibiotics can lead to the development of antibiotic-resistant bacteria. Follow the prescribed dosage and duration of treatment to minimize the risk of antibiotic resistance.</p>\n\n<p>Drug interactions: Inform your healthcare professional about all the medications you are currently taking, including prescription drugs, over-the-counter medications, and herbal supplements. Certain medications may interact with Augmentin DUO 1000 Tablet, so it&#39;s important to check for potential drug interactions.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','[\"screenshot-2025-07-16-152153-175265956098.png\"]','AU001',1,'1','2024-01-30 08:52:05','2025-07-16 09:53:55'),(189,0,'Augmentin 500/125mg','augmentin-500/125mg','Tablet','augmentin-500-125mg-170660759327.jpg','AU005','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>It is important to follow your doctor&rsquo;s instructions and read the medication label carefully when taking Augmentin. Take the prescribed dose as directed and complete the full course of treatment, even if you start feeling better before finishing the medication.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Broad-spectrum antibiotic: Augmentin is highly effective against a wide range of bacterial infections, including respiratory tract infections (such as bronchitis and pneumonia), urinary tract infections, skin and soft tissue infections, ear infections, and sinus infections. It targets and eliminates bacteria responsible for these infections, helping to alleviate symptoms and promote recovery.</p>\n\n<p>Enhanced effectiveness: The addition of clavulanic acid to amoxicillin helps to prevent the breakdown of amoxicillin by certain bacteria that produce an enzyme called beta-lactamase. This enzyme can render amoxicillin ineffective against some bacteria. By inhibiting beta-lactamase, Augmentin ensures a more potent and reliable treatment against bacterial infections.</p>\n\n<p>Combination therapy: The combination of amoxicillin and clavulanic acid allows for a synergistic effect, meaning the two drugs work together to provide better outcomes than when used individually. This makes Augmentin a valuable choice for infections caused by bacteria that may be resistant to other antibiotics.</p>\n\n<p>Versatile usage: Augmentin is prescribed for both adults and children, making it suitable for a wide range of patients. It is available in different formulations, including tablets, chewable tablets, and oral suspensions, allowing for flexibility in dosing and administration.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before taking Augmentin, it is important to inform your healthcare provider about any allergies you have, including to penicillin or cephalosporin antibiotics. This will help ensure your safety and prevent potential allergic reactions.</p>\n\n<p>It is also crucial to disclose your medical history, especially if you have a history of liver disease, kidney disease, or gastrointestinal disorders. Your doctor will consider these factors to determine the appropriate dosage and monitor your response to the medication.</p>','<p>Augmentin is a combination medication that combines the antibiotic amoxicillin with clavulanic acid. This combination provides a broader spectrum of activity against bacteria and enhances the effectiveness of amoxicillin. It is commonly prescribed by healthcare professionals to treat a variety of bacterial infections. Here is some important information about Augmentin:</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>Most people tolerate Augmentin well, but like any medication, it can cause side effects. These side effects are usually mild and temporary. Common side effects may include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Diarrhea</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Rash or skin itching</li>\n</ul>','[\"augmentin-500-125mg-170660759327.jpg\"]','AU005