 conditions may require special monitoring or dosage adjustments when taking Augmentin DDS Syrup.</p>\n\n<p>Antibiotic resistance: Misuse or overuse of antibiotics can lead to the development of antibiotic-resistant bacteria. Follow the prescribed dosage and duration of treatment to minimize the risk of antibiotic resistance.</p>\n\n<p>Drug interactions: Inform your healthcare professional about all the medications you are currently taking, including prescription drugs, over-the-counter medications, and herbal supplements. Certain medications may interact with Augmentin DDS Syrup, so it&#39;s important to check for potential drug interactions.</p>','<p>The antibiotic class known as penicillin antibiotics includes Augmentin DDS Syrup 30 ml. It is typically used to prevent joint and bone infections, middle ear and sinus infections, respiratory tract infections of the throat or lungs, urinary tract infections, skin infections, soft tissue infections, and dental infections.</p>\n\n<p>Amoxycillin and clavulanic acid are the two medications found in 30 ml of Augmentin DDS Syrup. Amoxycillin has a bactericidal activity because it kills bacteria by damaging their outer protein covering. Beta-lactamase is a bacterial enzyme that is inhibited by clavulanic acid, which keeps amoxycillin from losing its effectiveness. As a result, Amoxycillin can work more effectively and eliminate the germs thanks to Clavulanic acid&#39;s action. Viral infections, such as colds and the flu, are not treated by Augmentin DDS Syrup 30 ml.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Diarrhea</li>\n	<li>Indigestion</li>\n</ul>','[\"augmentin-dry-syrup-30-ml-170668274364.webp\"]','Au030',0,'1','2024-01-31 06:33:59','2024-01-31 06:33:59'),(191,0,'Aurogra 100','aurogra-100','Tablet','aurogra-100-170668608526.png','AU001','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>It is important to follow the instructions provided by your healthcare professional when taking Aurogra 100. Typically, it is recommended to take