 professional about any known allergies, medical history, and medications you are taking. Follow the prescribed dosage and complete the full course of treatment to ensure effectiveness and minimize the risk of developing antibiotic resistance. Be aware of the possibility of severe diarrhea, including Clostridium difficile-associated diarrhea, and seek medical advice if it occurs. By providing this information and adhering to the recommended precautions, you can help ensure the safe and effective use of Azithral 500mg.</p>','<p>The macrolide antibiotic class of drugs includes Azithral-500 Tablet 5&#39;s. It is used to treat a variety of bacterial illnesses of the respiratory system, including bronchitis, tonsillitis, pharyngitis, sinusitis, acne, rosacea, ear infections, and sexually transmitted diseases. Infection brought on by bacteria growing inside the body is known as a bacterial infection. Any bodily component can be the target, and it multiplies very quickly.</p>\n\n<p>By blocking the development of the proteins necessary for the bacterium&#39;s life, Azithral-500 Tablet 5&#39;s inhibit the growth of hazardous germs and, in certain cases, cause their death. Viral infections like the flu or a common cold are not treated by Azithral-500 Tablet 5.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Diarrhoea</li>\n	<li>Feeling or being sick (nausea or vomiting)</li>\n	<li>Stomach cramps</li>\n	<li>Loss of appetite</li>\n	<li>Bloating</li>\n	<li>Indigestion</li>\n</ul>','[\"azithral-500mg-1707115271100.webp\"]','AZ0500',1,'0','2024-02-05 06:41:19','2025-09-17 09:22:33'),(196,0,'Azopt Eye Drop 1% (5 ml) Eye Drop','azopt-eye-drop-1-(5-ml)-eye-drop','Drops','azopt-eye-drop-1-5-ml-eye-drop-170711558268.webp','AZ001','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>Follow your physician&#39;s instructions when using AZOPT eye drops. They are intended for ophthalmic use only, so do not ingest them. Before and after administration, wash your hands. Tilt your head slightly and gently pull down your lower eyelid. Apply a few drops of the medication to the affected eye(s). Shut your eyes and press the corner of your eye with your finger for about a minute. To avoid contamination, avoid touching the dropper&#39;s tip to your eye or any other surface.</p>\n\n<p>Wait at least 5 minutes between using other eye drops or ointments after applying AZOPT EYE DROPS. If you wear soft contact lenses, remove them before using AZOPT Eye Drops and wait at least 15 minutes before reinserting them.</p>\n\n<p>The appropriate dosage and duration of treatment will be determined by your doctor based on the severity of your condition. Do not discontinue using AZOPT EYE DROPS without first consulting your doctor, as intraocular pressure may rise again and become unmanageable.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Azopt Opthalmic Suspension 5 ml is prescribed to treat high pressure in the eye caused by conditions like glaucoma (a condition that damages the optic nerve) and ocular hypertension (high pressure of the fluid inside the eye). The active ingredient in Azopt Opthalmic Suspension 5 ml is brinzolamide, which inhibits the action of the carbonic anhydrase enzyme, reducing bicarbonate production necessary for the production of aqueous humor. As a result, the secretion of aqueous humor is decreased, which helps lower the pressure in the eye by reducing the entry of aqueous humor into the eyeball.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Use the eye drops as directed by your doctor. Do not use more or less than the recommended dose.</li>\n	<li>Wash your hands thoroughly before and after using the eye drops.</li>\n	<li>Do not touch the tip of the dropper to your eye or any other surface to avoid contamination.</li>\n	<li>If you wear contact lenses, remove them before using the eye drops. Wait at least 15 minutes before reinserting them.</li>\n	<li>Inform your doctor if you have any allergies or medical conditions before using the eye drops.</li>\n	<li>If you experience any eye irritation or discomfort, stop using the eye drops and consult your doctor.</li>\n	<li>Azopt Eye Drops may cause temporary blurred vision, so avoid activities that require clear vision, such as driving or operating machinery, until your vision clears.</li>\n	<li>Do not use the eye drops if the solution has changed color or become cloudy.</li>\n	<li>Store the eye drops in a cool, dry place and keep them out of the reach of children.</li>\n</ul>','<p>Azopt Opthalmic Suspension 5 ml is a carbonic anhydrase inhibitor used primarily to treat conditions associated with increased pressure in the eyes, such as glaucoma and ocular hypertension. Glaucoma is an eye disease that can damage the optic nerve and cause vision loss due to increased pressure in the eye. Ocular hypertension is a condition in which there is increased pressure in the eye due to poor drainage of fluid.</p>\n\n<p>The active ingredient in Azopt Opthalmic Suspension 5 ml is brinzolamide, which works by inhibiting the carbonic anhydrase enzyme. This decreases the production of bicarbonate, which is essential for the production of aqueous humor, the fluid that maintains normal pressure in the eye by continuously flowing through it. By reducing the secretion of aqueous humor, Azopt Opthalmic Suspension 5 ml lowers the raised pressure in the eye and prevents vision loss associated with open-angle type glaucoma and ocular hypertension.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Eye discharge</li>\n	<li>Redness, itching, irritation or pain in the eyes</li>\n	<li>Blurred vision</li>\n	<li>Abnormal eye sensation</li>\n	<li>Dry eyes</li>\n</ul>','[\"azopt-eye-drop-1-5-ml-eye-drop-170711558268.webp\"]','AZ001',1,'0','2024-02-05 06:46:30','2025-08-06 05:22:58'),(197,0,'Bactrim DS (800 160)mg','bactrim-ds-(800-160)mg','Tablet','bactrim-ds-800-160-mg-170711604464.jpg','BA0816','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>Your condition and the severity of the infection will be taken into account by your doctor when determining the dosage and length of Bactrim DS Tablet 1