g airway inflammation, it helps prevent bronchospasm triggered by exercise.</li>\n	<li>Individualized dosage: Budecort Rotacaps are available in various strengths, allowing healthcare professionals to prescribe the appropriate dosage based on the severity of the respiratory condition. This individualized dosing ensures optimal efficacy and safety for each patient.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Follow instructions: Read and follow the instructions provided with the medication carefully. Ensure that you understand the correct way to use the Rotacaps and the inhalation device (rotahaler) associated with them.</p>\n\n<p>Allergic reactions: If you have known allergies to budesonide or any other corticosteroids, inform your doctor before using Budecort Rotacaps. Allergic reactions may include a rash, itching, swelling, or difficulty breathing.</p>\n\n<p>Medical conditions: Inform your doctor about any pre-existing medical conditions, especially if you have liver disease, tuberculosis, herpes simplex infection in the eye, or any other infections. These conditions may require special monitoring or adjustments in the treatment plan.</p>\n\n<p>Other medications: It is important to inform your doctor about all the medications you are currently taking, including prescription drugs, over-the-counter medications, and herbal supplements. Some medications may interact with budesonide and affect its effectiveness or increase the risk of side effects.</p>','<p>Budesonide 200 contains the active ingredient budesonide, classified as a corticosteroid medication. It is prescribed for the prevention of asthma symptoms. Asthma is a respiratory condition characterized by airway inflammation, swelling, and narrowing. It leads to increased mucus production, causing symptoms like wheezing, difficulty breathing, chest pain, and coughing.</p>\n\n<p>Budesonide acts directly on the airways, preventing the release of certain chemicals that trigger inflammation and swelling. However, it is important to note that Budecort 200 is not intended to treat an ongoing asthma attack. For immediate relief during an attack, it is recommended to carry a fast-acting &quot;rescue&quot; inhaler containing a beta-2 agonist like salbutamol.</p>\n\n<p>Your doctor will regularly monitor your condition and adjust the dosage of Budecort 200 as needed. If you are already taking oral corticosteroids for asthma, your doctor may gradually decrease the dosage of the oral medication before transitioning to Budecort 200.</p>\n\n<p>It is crucial to inform your doctor about any other medications you are taking, especially oral corticosteroids, to ensure proper management of your asthma symptoms.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>The majority of side effects do not need medical attention and typically subside as your body adapts to the medication. However, if you are concerned or if the side effects persist, it is recommended that you consult your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>The most common side effects are listed below:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Indigestion</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Abdominal pain</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Bloating</li>\n</ul>','[\"budecort-rotacaps-200mcg-170714084320.jpg\"]','BU200',1,'0','2024-02-05 13:47:32','2025-07-25 11:10:56'),(211,0,'Budecort Rotacaps 400 mcg','budecort-rotacaps-400-mcg','Rotacaps','budecort-rotacaps-400-mcg-170714096225.jpg','BU400','<p>How to Use:</p>\n\n<p>Do not ingest Rotacaps. Prior to usage, refer to the instructions on the label. Position the capsule at the bottom of the rotahaler, not in the mouthpiece. Rotate the mouthpiece fully until you hear a clicking sound, then inhale deeply through the mouthpiece. Retain your breath for around 10 seconds. If there is any remaining powder in the rotahaler, repeat the procedure.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Budecort 400 Rotacap 30&#39;s is a medication that effectively relieves respiratory conditions by reducing airway swelling and irritation. It is commonly used to address various respiratory diseases, including allergic rhinitis (an allergy causing itchy, watery eyes and sneezing), COPD (chronic obstructive pulmonary disease, which obstructs airflow and leads to breathing difficulties), as well as chest tightness, wheezing, and coughing associated with asthma.</p>\n\n<p>This combination medicine, Budecort 400 Rotacap, functions by minimizing and preventing inflammation and swelling in the lungs. While it doesn&#39;t immediately halt an ongoing asthma attack, it effectively prevents and alleviates its symptoms, such as chest tightness, wheezing, breathlessness, and coughing. By doing so, it enables you to engage in your daily activities more comfortably and confidently. It is important to continue taking this medication as prescribed, even if you are not experiencing any symptoms, as it may take several weeks for the full effects to become evident. Abruptly stopping the medication may result in a return of symptoms.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>When using Budecort Rotacaps 400 mcg, it is important to take certain precautions. Firstly, follow the instructions provided by your healthcare professional or the product label. Avoid swallowing the Rotacaps, as they are meant to be used with a suitable inhaler device. Be cautious of potential side effects, such as fungal infections in the mouth or throat, and seek medical advice if any symptoms occur. Monitor for headaches, abdominal pain, and signs of depression, and consult a healthcare provider if these symptoms become severe or persistent. Regularly review your treatment with your doctor to ensure its effectiveness and adjust the dosage if necessary.</p>','<p>Budecort 400 Rotacap 30&#39;s is classified as a type of medication known as &quot;glucocorticosteroids,&quot; which are used to alleviate symptoms associated with asthma and COPD (chronic obstructive pulmonary disease). Asthma is a chronic respiratory condition characterized by narrowing, swelling, and excess mucus production in the airways, resulting in breathing difficulties. COPD refers to a group of lung diseases that cause obstructions in the airflow from the lungs.</p>\n\n<p>Containing the active ingredient &quot;Budesonide,&quot; Budecort 400 Rotacap 30 functions by inhibiting the production of specific chemical messengers involved in both allergic and non-allergic-induced inflammation. As a result, Budecort 400 Rotacap 30 effectively treats inflammatory conditions. It reduces inflammation and irritation in the airways, making breathing easier and providing relief from the symptoms associated with asthma and COPD.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<p>The majority of side effects do not need medical attention and typically subside as your body adapts to the medication. However, if you are concerned or if the side effects persist, it is recommended that you consult your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>The most common side effects are listed below:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Difficulty in swallowing</li>\n	<li>Fungal infection of mouth</li>\n	<li>Fungal infection of oropharynx</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Abdominal pain</li>\n	<li>Depression</li>\n</ul>','[\"budecort-rotacaps-400-mcg-170714096225.jpg\"]','BU400',1,'0','2024-02-05 13:49:29','2025-08-06 05:23:57'),(212,0,'Budesal Respules 0.5mg-2.5 ml','budesal-respules-0.5mg-2.5-ml','Respules','budesal-respules-0-170714107539.jpg','BU005','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Before taking Budesal 0.5 mg Respules 5 x 2 ml, make sure you read the guidelines on the label. Squeeze the solution into the nebulizer after twisting off the respule top. To breathe in, this solution is turned into a thin mist. Utilize the nebulizer&#39;s mouthpiece to inhale the medication. Use as soon as it&#39;s opened.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Levosalbutamol and Budesonide, which are used to prevent or treat the symptoms of asthma and chronic obstructive pulmonary disorders (COPD), such as shortness of breath, coughing, or wheezing (making a whistling sound when breathing), are both present in Budesal 0.5 mg Respules 5 x 2 ml. Levosalbutamol is a bronchodilator, which means it relaxes muscles and opens up the lungs&#39; airways. It thereby facilitates simpler breathing. A corticosteroid called budesonide works inside the cells of the nasal lining and prevents the body from releasing specific chemicals that lead to inflammatory reactions. Sneezing, a runny or plugged nose, and sinus discomfort are thus relieved.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Allergies: Check for allergies to budesonide or other similar medications.</p>\n\n<p>Respiratory infections: Use caution if you have an active or recent respiratory infection, as budesonide may mask or worsen the symptoms.</p>\n\n<p>Systemic effects: Long-term use of high doses of budesonide may lead to systemic effects such as adrenal suppression, growth retardation in children, and increased susceptibility to infections. Regular monitoring is advised.</p>\n\n<p>Glaucoma and cataracts: Budesonide may increase the risk of glaucoma and cataracts. Regular eye examinations are recommended.</p>\n\n<p>Immunosuppression: Budesonide can suppress the immune system, increasing the risk of infections. Avoid contact with individuals who have contagious diseases, such as chickenpox or measles.</p>\n\n<p>Diabetes: Budesonide may affect blood glucose levels. Monitor blood sugar regularly if you have diabetes.</p>','<p>A combination drug called budesal 0.5 mg Respules 5 x 2 ml is generally used to prevent or treat asthma and chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD) symptoms like shortness of breath, coughing, or wheezing (making a whistling sound while breathing). Airways in people with asthma narrow, swell, and generate excess mucus, making breathing difficult. Asthma is a chronic (long-term) respiratory disorder. Emphysema and chronic bronchitis, two lung conditions that cause shortness of breath, are included in the COPD group of diseases.</p>\n\n<p>Budesonide, a corticosteroid, and Levosalbutamol, a bronchodilator, are both present in Budesal 0.5 mg Respules 5 x 2 ml. Levosalbutamol is a bronchodilator, which means that it widens the lungs&#39; airways by relaxing muscles. As a result, breathing becomes simpler. Budesonide is a member of the group of corticosteroids that inhibits the production of specific substances in the body that lead to inflammatory reactions by working inside the cells of the nasal lining. As a result, it relieves the symptoms of sneezing, a runny or congested nose, and sinus discomfort.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Fungal infection in the mouth</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Sore throat</li>\n	<li>Hoarse voice</li>\n	<li>Back pain</li>\n	<li>Fast heartbeat</li>\n	<li>Muscle cramps</li>\n</ul>','[\"budesal-respules-0-170714107539.jpg\"]','BU005',1,'0','2024-02-05 13:51:23','2025-08-06 05:23:06'),(213,0,'Butop 15gm','butop-15gm','Cream','butop-15gm-170714120267.jpg','BU15','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Apply BUTOP as your doctor advises. Only outside parties may utilize it. Before and after using the medication, wash your hands. This medication should be applied in a thin layer over the afflicted area and its immediate surroundings. Avoid covering the treated region with an occlusive dressing, such as plastic wrap or a bandage. Depending on your age and medical state, your doctor will determine the appropriate dose and duration for you.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Only if it is deemed absolutely necessary should PREGNANCY BUTOP be used during pregnancy. Before using this medication, speak with your physician.</p>\n\n<p>Breastfeeding women should use BREASTFEEDING BUTOP with caution because it may contaminate the breast milk. Before using this medication, speak with your physician.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Your ability to operate a vehicle or operate machinery is unaffected or minimally impacted by DRIVING AND USING MACHINES BUTOP. Before using this medication, speak with your physician.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>KIDNEY BUTOP should be administered to patients with severe renal insufficiency with caution. Before using this medication, speak with your physician.</p>\n\n<p>When administering LIVER BUTOP to individuals who have severe liver failure, care should be taken. Before using this medication, speak with your physician.</p>','<p>BUTOP includes Butenafine, a medication from the class of drugs known as antifungals. It is applied topically to treat tinea versicolor (a skin infection caused by a fungus), tinea corporis (a body illness caused by a fungus), athlete&#39;s foot (a foot infection caused by a fungus), and crotch itch (a fungus that affects the groin and pubic region).</p>\n\n<p>In order to properly cure a fungal infection, BUTOP interferes with the creation of some crucial elements of the fungal cell membrane. This increased cellular permeability of the cell membrane causes leakage of cellular contents, which leads to the demise of the fungal cells.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<p>Reactions at the place of application (such as a burning, stinging, or itching feeling or contact dermatitis, which causes itchy rashes)</p>','[\"butop-15gm-170714120267.jpg\"]','BU15',1,'0','2024-02-05 13:54:15','2025-08-06 05:23:17'),(214,0,'Cabgolin 0.25 mg','cabgolin-0.25-mg','tablet','cabgolin-0-170714152911.jpg','CA025','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>It is crucial to follow the instructions provided by your doctor when taking Cabgolin 0.25mg. Read and adhere to the guidelines mentioned on the medication label. Take the prescribed dosage as directed by your healthcare professional and avoid taking more or less than recommended. It is typically taken orally, and the dosage may vary depending on the specific condition being treated.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Treatment of Hyperprolactinemia: Cabgolin 0.25mg is highly effective in treating hyperprolactinemia, a condition characterized by abnormally high levels of prolactin hormone in the blood. By reducing the elevated prolactin levels, Cabgolin helps restore normal hormone balance, alleviating associated symptoms.</p>\n\n<p>Management of Prolactinoma: Prolactinoma is a benign tumor of the pituitary gland that causes excessive prolactin production. Cabgolin 0.25mg is commonly prescribed to manage prolactinoma, helping to shrink the tumor and normalize prolactin levels. This treatment can reduce symptoms associated with the condition, such as irregular menstruation, infertility, and milk secretion from the breasts.</p>\n\n<p>Improved Fertility: Cabgolin 0.25mg can aid in restoring normal fertility for individuals experiencing infertility due to high prolactin levels. By regulating prolactin secretion, it helps improve menstrual cycles and enhances the chances of conception.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before starting a Cabgolin regimen, it is essential to inform your healthcare provider about any allergies you have, including to this medication or any other substances. Your doctor should also be aware of your complete medical history, especially if you have liver or kidney problems.</p>','<p>Cabgolin 0.25mg, also known as Cabergoline 0.25mg, is a medication that offers several positive benefits for individuals who require its use. It belongs to a class of medications called dopamine receptor agonists and is primarily prescribed for the treatment of conditions related to the hormone prolactin.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Here is some information about Cabgolin 0.25mg</p>','<p>Like any medication, Cabgolin 0.25mg may cause some side effects, although they are generally well-tolerated. It&rsquo;s important to remember that not everyone experiences these side effects, and they may vary in severity. Some commonly reported side effects include:</p>\n\n<p>Nausea and vomiting: These symptoms may occur initially but usually subside with ontinued use.</p>\n\n<p>Headache: Mild headaches are occasionally reported but tend to diminish over time.</p>\n\n<p>Dizziness or lightheadedness: Some individuals may experience these sensations, particularly when standing up quickly.</p>\n\n<p>It is essential to discuss any concerns or potential side effects with your doctor, as they can provide guidance and support throughout your treatment.</p>','[\"cabgolin-0-170714152911.jpg\"]','CA025',1,'0','2024-02-05 13:59:04','2025-08-06 05:23:27'),(215,0,'Cabgolin 0.5 mg','cabgolin-0.5-mg','tablet','cabgolin-0-170714176982.webp','CA50','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>To ensure optimal results, it is recommended to follow the instructions provided by your healthcare provider or pharmacist when taking this medication. It is important to read and adhere to all the instructions on the medication label. By using the medication as directed, you can maximize its effectiveness and safety.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Treatment of Hyperprolactinemia: Cabgolin 0.5 mg is highly effective in the treatment of hyperprolactinemia, a condition characterized by an excessive production of the hormone prolactin. By reducing the levels of prolactin in the body, Cabgolin helps restore hormonal balance, thereby alleviating associated symptoms.</p>\n\n<p>Management of Prolactin-Related Disorders: Cabgolin 0.5 mg is used to manage various disorders caused by elevated levels of prolactin, such as irregular menstrual periods, infertility, abnormal milk production, and breast engorgement. By regulating prolactin levels, Cabgolin helps normalize reproductive function and improve fertility outcomes.</p>\n\n<p>Treatment of Prolactinomas: Prolactinomas are benign tumors of the pituitary gland that secrete excess prolactin. Cabgolin 0.5 mg is an effective long-term treatment for prolactinomas, helping to shrink the tumors and reduce prolactin levels. This medication can significantly improve symptoms associated with these tumors, such as headaches and visual disturbances.</p>\n\n<p>Management of Parkinson&rsquo;s Disease: Cabgolin 0.5 mg is sometimes used as an adjunct therapy in the management of Parkinson&rsquo;s disease. It helps to control the symptoms of the condition by stimulating dopamine receptors in the brain. By increasing dopamine activity, Cabgolin can improve motor function and reduce tremors in Parkinson&rsquo;s patients.</p>\n\n<p>Improved Quality of Life: By effectively treating hyperprolactinemia and related conditions, Cabgolin 0.5 mg can greatly improve the quality of life for individuals affected by these disorders. It helps relieve symptoms such as irregular menstrual cycles, infertility, breast discomfort, and other prolactin-related issues, allowing patients to lead more fulfilling lives.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before taking Cabgolin 0.5 mg, it is important to inform your healthcare provider about any medical conditions you have and any medications you are currently taking, including over-the-counter drugs and herbal supplements. This helps ensure the safe and effective use of the medication.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>Cabgolin 0.5 mg, also known as Cabergoline 0.5 mg, is a medication that is commonly used to treat conditions related to the hormone prolactin. It belongs to a class of drugs called dopamine agonists.</p>','<p><strong><em>Side Effects:</em></strong></p>\n\n<p>While Cabgolin 0.5 mg is generally well-tolerated, it may cause some temporary side effects. These side effects are usually mild and may include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n	<li>Fatigue</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Stomach discomfort</li>\n</ul>','[\"cabgolin-0-170714176982.webp\"]','CA50',1,'0','2024-02-05 14:03:03','2025-08-06 05:23:33'),(216,0,'Calaptin 40mg','calaptin-40mg','tablet','calaptin-40mg-170714209734.webp','CA40','<p>How to take a tablet of Calaptin</p>\n\n<p>Follow your doctor&#39;s instructions for this medication&#39;s dosage and duration. Take it all in at once. Don&#39;t eat it, break it, or crush it. Calaptin 40 Tablet should be consumed alongside food.</p>\n\n<p>Calaptin Tablet Function</p>\n\n<p>A calcium channel blocker is called Calaptin 40 Tablet. It prevents calcium from acting on the heart and blood vessels, allowing more blood and oxygen to reach the heart and enlarging the blood arteries. As a result, there is a decreased risk of angina (chest pain) and blood pressure reduction.</p>\n\n<p>Calaptin Tablet Benefits</p>\n\n<p>Hypertension (high blood pressure) treatment</p>\n\n<p>Calaptin 40 Tablet eases the flow of blood throughout the body by relaxing blood vessels. This decreases blood pressure and lessens the possibility of future kidney issues, heart attacks, or stroke. To be effective, it must be taken as directed on a regular basis. Usually, taking this medication does not result in any immediate benefits for you, but over time, it keeps you healthy. Even if you feel OK, do not discontinue taking this medication without consulting your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>Treatment for Angina (chest pain associated with the heart)</p>\n\n<p>The Calaptin 40 Tablet treats and prevents angina attacks, which are chest pains caused by the heart. It should not be used, though, for severe angina attacks. It causes the blood arteries in the heart to relax and enlarge. The heart receives more oxygen as a result of the easier blood flow to it. As a result, using this medication makes it easier and more confident for you to exercise and carry out your everyday activities. For best results, take it frequently. Even if you feel fine, do not stop taking medication without first consulting your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>In Arrhythmia Treatment</p>\n\n<p>The Calaptin 40 Tablet can also be used to treat arrhythmias, which are irregular heartbeats. It might assist in halting an irregular rhythm in progress or averting one altogether.</p>','<p>The medication Calaptin 40 Tablet is used to treat arrhythmia, excessive blood pressure, and some types of angina (chest pain associated with the heart). In order to lower blood pressure, it works by relaxing blood vessels. The workload on the heart is lessened as a result.</p>\n\n<p>Calaptin 40 Tablet can be taken with or without meals, however your doctor may suggest you to take it regularly at a set time each day. Even if you feel OK, keep taking this medication. Your condition could get worse if you stop taking it abruptly. Only a small portion of a comprehensive treatment plan, which should also include weight loss as directed by your doctor, a nutritious diet, and regular exercise.</p>\n\n<p>Constipation, lightheadedness, nausea, hypotension, and headaches are among of this medication&#39;s most frequent side effects. These are typically minor and go away quickly. If they disturb you or do not go away, speak with your doctor. While taking this medication, drinking alcohol should be avoided as it may make the negative effects worse.</p>\n\n<p>Inform your doctor if you have any liver or kidney issues prior to using this medication. Also let your doctor know if you have heart failure, very low blood pressure (hypotension), a recent heart attack, or fluid in your lungs. While using it, your doctor might want to check your blood pressure, and you could require frequent blood tests. Before using it, pregnant or nursing women should talk to their doctor.</p>','<p>Common Calaptin side effects</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Constipation</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Dizziness</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Nausea</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Low blood pressure, or hypotension</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Headache</li>\n</ul>','[\"calaptin-40mg-170714209734.webp\"]','CA40',1,'0','2024-02-05 14:08:26','2025-08-06 05:23:41'),(217,0,'Calaptin 80mg','calaptin-80mg','tablet','calaptin-80mg-170714487453.webp','CA80','<p>How to take a tablet of Calaptin</p>\n\n<p>Follow your doctor&#39;s instructions for this medication&#39;s dosage and duration. Take it all in at once. Don&#39;t eat it, break it, or crush it. Calaptin 80 Tablet should be consumed alongside food.</p>\n\n<p>Calaptin Tablet Function</p>\n\n<p>A calcium channel blocker is called Calaptin 80 Tablet. It prevents calcium from acting on the heart and blood vessels, allowing more b