ess when starting Candesartan, but this side effect typically resolves quickly as the body adjusts to the medication.</p>\n\n<p>Fatigue: In rare cases, Candesartan may cause temporary fatigue. However, this side effect is usually mild and transient.</p>\n\n<p>Headache: Occasionally, individuals may experience mild headaches, which usually resolve on their own or can be managed with over-the-counter pain relievers.</p>','[\"candesartan-tab-32mg-170724025016.jpg\"]','CA32',1,'0','2024-02-06 17:24:26','2025-08-06 05:24:36'),(224,0,'Candid B Cream 20 gm','candid-b-cream-20-gm','Cream','screenshot-2025-10-08-175804-175992655223.png','CA20','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>The dosage that is best for your infection will be suggested by your doctor. The 20 gm Candid-B Cream can only be applied topically (to the skin). Rinse with cold water if the medication spills into your eyes, nose, mouth, or vagina. Every medicine, including Candid-B Cream 20 gm, has typical side effects. At the application site, these adverse effects include itching, dryness, redness, and a burning feeling.</p>\n\n<p>With clean, dry hands, apply a light layer of Candid-B Cream 20 gm to the skin&#39;s afflicted regions. You can also use a piece of fresh cotton wool or gauze to apply it. Gently massage the medication into the affected area until it disappears.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Cream Candid-B 20 gm is used to treat fungal infections such as ringworm of the foot, also known as tinea pedis or athlete&#39;s foot, tinea cruris or jock itch, and tinea corporis, which affects the entire body. It comprises of two drugs, mainly the antifungal Clotrimazole and the steroid Beclometasone. An antifungal drug called clotrimazole is used to treat ringworm, oral thrush, and vaginal yeast infections. By rupturing and allowing fluid to leak through the fungal cell membrane, clotrimazole prevents the growth of fungus. Beclometasone is a member of the corticosteroid family. Prostaglandins are chemical messengers that