&nbsp; Tiredness</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Weakness</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Raynaud&#39;s syndrome</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; heartbeat irregularity, or arrhythmia</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Nausea</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; nausea and diarrhoea</li>\n</ul>','[\"ciplar-la-40mg-170799720339.webp\"]','CI40',1,'0','2024-02-15 11:40:14','2025-09-17 04:30:19'),(251,0,'Ciplar LA 80mg','ciplar-la-80mg','tablet','cipla-la-80-mg-170799742670.jpg','CI80','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>It is important to follow your doctor&rsquo;s instructions and read the medication label carefully before taking Ciplar LA 80mg. It is typically taken orally with or without food, usually once daily or as directed by your healthcare provider. It is important to take the medication consistently at the same time each day to achieve the best results.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Blood pressure management: Ciplar LA 80mg is commonly used to treat high blood pressure (hypertension). It helps to relax the blood vessels, allowing blood to flow more easily and reducing the workload on the heart. By controlling blood pressure, it can help reduce the risk of heart attacks, strokes, and other cardiovascular complications.</p>\n\n<p>Angina prevention: Ciplar LA 80mg is effective in preventing angina, a condition characterized by chest pain or discomfort due to reduced blood flow to the heart. By blocking certain beta receptors, it helps to decrease the heart&#39;s workload and oxygen demand, thus alleviating angina symptoms and improving overall heart function.</p>\n\n<p>Heart rhythm disorders: This medication is also used to manage certain heart rhythm disorders such as atrial fibrillation and ventricular arrhythmias. By regulating the electrical activity of the heart, Ciplar LA 80mg can help stabilize the heart rhythm and reduce the occurrence of irregular heartbeats.</p>\n\n<p>Migraine prevention: Ciplar LA 80mg is sometimes prescribed for the prevention of migraines. It can help reduce the frequency and severity of migraine attacks by regulating blood vessel dilation and calming overactive nerves in the brain.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before starting Ciplar LA 80mg, it is important to inform your healthcare provider about any existing medical conditions, allergies, or medications you are currently taking. This will help ensure its safe and effective use. Your doctor should also be informed if you have a history of asthma or other respiratory conditions, diabetes, liver or kidney problems, or any circulation disorders.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>Ciplar LA 80mg is a medication that belongs to the class of drugs known as beta-blockers. It is primarily prescribed for the management of various cardiovascular conditions. Here is some information about Ciplar LA 80mg:</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>While most people tolerate Ciplar LA 80mg well, some individuals may experience mild and temporary side effects. It is important to note that not everyone will experience these side effects, and they may vary from person to person. Some of the commonly reported side effects include:</p>\n\n<p>Fatigue or drowsiness: Ciplar LA 80mg may cause mild fatigue or drowsiness, especially when starting the medication. These effects usually diminish as your body adjusts to the medication.</p>\n\n<p>Dizziness or lightheadedness: Some individuals may experience dizziness or lightheadedness, particularly when standing up quickly. Taking precautions such as getting up slowly from a seated or lying position can help minimize these effects.</p>\n\n<p>Gastrointestinal issues: Ciplar LA 80mg may occasionally cause gastrointestinal symptoms such as nausea, vomiting, or stomach discomfort. These side effects are usually mild and transient.</p>\n\n<p>It is important to remember that these side effects are typically temporary and should be reported to your doctor only if they persist or worsen. Your healthcare provider can provide further guidance on managing these side effects.</p>\n\n<p>Please note that this information is not exhaustive, and it is crucial to consult your doctor or healthcare professional for personalized advice and guidance regarding the use of Ciplar LA 80mg.</p>','[\"cipla-la-80-mg-170799742670.jpg\"]','CI80',1,'0','2024-02-15 11:43:57','2025-09-17 04:30:35'),(252,0,'Ciplox 0.3% 10 ml','ciplox-0.3-10-ml','Drops','ciplox-0-170799766560.bmp','CI10','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>As long as your doctor has recommended Ciplox Eye/Ear Drop 10 ml to you, you should continue using it. You might occasionally feel common side effects include soreness, irritability, and stinging. Most of these adverse effects go away gradually over time without the need for medical intervention. However, if you have these side effects frequently, you should consult your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>Both before and after using, wash your hands. To apply the drops to the eye or ear, use the dropper that came with the pack. Avoid touching the dropper&#39;s tip to your eyes, ears, or any nearby regions as this could contaminate the solution.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Bacterial Eye Infections: Ciplox 0.3% 10 ml is commonly prescribed for the treatment of bacterial eye infections, such as conjunctivitis (pink eye) and keratitis. Ciprofloxacin, the active ingredient, is a broad-spectrum antibiotic that helps eliminate the bacteria causing the infection.</p>\n\n<p>Fast Relief: Ciplox 0.3% 10 ml provides quick relief from symptoms associated with bacterial eye infections, including redness, itching, swelling, discharge, and discomfort. It targets the underlying cause of the infection, helping to alleviate these symptoms.</p>\n\n<p>Wide Spectrum of Activity: Ciprofloxacin in Ciplox 0.3% 10 ml has a broad spectrum of activity, meaning it is effective against a wide range of bacteria that can cause eye infections. This makes it a versatile option for treating various bacterial strains.</p>\n\n<p>Convenient and Easy to Use: Ciplox 0.3% 10 ml comes in the form of eye drops, making it easy to apply directly to the affected eye. The packaging ensures accurate dosing, and the solution is usually well-tolerated.</p>\n\n<p>Prevents Spread of Infection: By effectively eliminating bacteria causing the eye infection, Ciplox 0.3% 10 ml helps prevent the spread of the infection to other parts of the eye or to other individuals in close contact.</p>\n\n<p>Prescribed for Different Age Groups: Ciplox 0.3% 10 ml is prescribed for both adults and children, allowing for effective treatment of bacterial eye infections across different age groups.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>If any of the ingredients in Ciplox Eye/Ear Drop 10 ml causes your allergies, avoid using it. Inform your doctor if you have vision issues, excruciating eye discomfort, glaucoma (high blood pressure), eye damage, recent eye surgery, hearing issues (cytotoxicity), a perforated eardrum, or persistent otitis media before using Ciplox Eye/Ear Drop 10 ml. If you are breastfeeding, planning a pregnancy, or are already pregnant, let the doctor know. If the infection symptoms continue or get worse after two weeks of treatment, call your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>The antibiotic drug class includes products like Ciplox Eye/Ear Drop 10 ml, which are used to treat bacterial eye and ear infections. Bacteria that enter the middle or outer ear and cause discomfort and inflammation are the cause of an ear infection. When pathogenic bacteria infiltrate any part of the eye, including the cornea, conjunctiva, or eyeball, bacterial eye infection results.</p>\n\n<p>Ciprofloxacin, a drug with antibacterial activity, is present in Ciplox Eye/Ear Drop, 10 ml. It functions by inhibiting the DNA gyrase enzyme, which is necessary for the production of bacterial DNA. Ciplox Eye/Ear Drop 10 ml thereby prevents the growth of bacteria and treats bacterial eye/ear infections.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Discomfort</li>\n	<li>Irritation</li>\n	<li>Stinging sensation</li>\n</ul>','[\"ciplox-0-170799766560.bmp\"]','CI10',1,'1','2024-02-15 11:47:54','2024-02-15 11:47:54'),(253,0,'Ciplox 250mg','ciplox-250mg','tablet','screenshot-2025-07-20-212856-175302715048.png','CI250','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>It is best to take Ciplox-250 Tablet 10&#39;s for the recommended dosage and time frame. You could occasionally have a rash, diarrhoea, abnormal liver function tests, nausea, and vomiting. The majority of these Ciplox-250 Tablet 10 adverse effects go away gradually over time without the need for medical intervention. Consult your doctor, nevertheless, if the negative effects continue.</p>\n\n<p>Never break, crush, or chew it; instead, swallow it whole with water.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>The antibiotic Ciprofloxacin, which aids in treating and preventing a variety of bacterial illnesses, is present in Ciplox-250 Tablet 10&#39;s. Its bactericidal nature enables it to function by eradicating the germs that cause illnesses. Both bacterial cell division and bacterial cell repair are inhibited by it. The death of the bacterium results from both of these events.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>If you have ever experienced an adverse response to ciprofloxacin or any other quinolone or fluoroquinolone antibiotic, including delafloxacin, gemifloxacin, levofloxacin, moxifloxacin, or ofloxacin, you should not take Ciplox-250 Tablet 10&#39;s. Tendon rupture, which is the tearing of a tendon that connects a bone to a muscle, and tendinitis, which is the swelling of a tendon that connects a bone to a muscle, may occur as a result of taking Ciplox-250 Tablet 10&#39;s. A kidney, heart, or lung transplant, kidney disease, a joint or tendon disorder like rheumatoid arthritis (an autoimmune disorder of the joints that causes pain, swelling, and loss of function), fits, epilepsy, or regular physical activity should all be disclosed to your doctor. When myasthenia gravis, a nerve system ailment that causes muscle weakness, is present, taking Ciplox-250 Tablet 10s may make the condition worse and even result in death. The combination of dairy products with Ciplox-250 Tablet 10&#39;s should be avoided. Additionally, it&#39;s best to avoid being in the sun when taking Ciplox-250 Tablet 10s because it could increase phototoxicity or photosensitivity. Before taking Ciplox-250 Tablet 10&#39;s, patients with epilepsy and irregular heartbeat (particularly a condition known as QT prolongation) should inform their doctor.</p>','<p>The antibiotic fluoroquinolones, which are generally used to treat or prevent specific bacterial infections, are present in Ciplox-250 Tablet 10&#39;s. It is prescribed for the treatment of infections of the skin, bone, joint, abdomen (stomach area), prostate (male reproductive gland), and gonorrhoea, which is a sexually transmitted disease. It is also used to treat infectious diarrhoea, typhoid fever, a serious infection that is common in developing nations.</p>\n\n<p>The antibiotic &quot;Ciprofloxacin&quot; found in Ciplox-250 Tablet 10&#39;s is bactericidal in nature and works by eradicating germs that cause infections. It stops bacterial cells from dividing. Additionally, it prevents the healing of bacterial cells. The microorganisms are eradicated as a whole.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Diarrhoea</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Rash</li>\n	<li>Liver function tests abnormal</li>\n	<li>Change of the heart rhythm (ECG)</li>\n	<li>Low blood potassium level</li>\n</ul>','[\"screenshot-2025-07-20-212856-175302715048.png\"]','CI250',1,'1','2024-02-15 11:51:40','2025-07-20 15:59:21'),(254,0,'Ciplox 500mg','ciplox-500mg','tablet','screenshot-2025-07-20-213349-175302764654.png','CI500','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>The dosage and duration of Ciplox-500 Tablet 10&#39;s should be followed, as prescribed by your doctor. You might occasionally have nausea, diarrhea, abnormal liver function tests, vomiting, and rash. Most of these Ciplox-500 Tablet 10 adverse effects subside with time without the need for medical intervention. However, contact your doctor if the adverse effects continue to bother you.</p>\n\n<p>It should be completely swallowed with water; do not break, crush, or chew it.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>The antibiotic Ciprofloxacin, which aids in treating and preventing a variety of bacterial illnesses, is present in Ciplox-500 Tablet 10&#39;s. Its bactericidal nature enables it to function by eradicating the germs that cause illnesses. Both bacterial cell division and bacterial cell repair are inhibited by it. The death of the bacterium results from both of these events.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>If you have ever experienced an adverse response to ciprofloxacin or any other quinolone or fluoroquinolone antibiotic, including delafloxacin, gemifloxacin, levofloxacin, moxifloxacin, or ofloxacin, you should not take Ciplox-500 Tablet 10&#39;s. Tendon rupture (tearing of a tendon connecting a bone to a muscle) and tendinitis (inflammation of the fibrous tissue that connects a bone to a muscle) may occur as a result of taking Ciplox-500 Tablet 10&#39;s. A kidney, heart, or lung transplant, kidney disease, a joint or tendon disorder like rheumatoid arthritis (an autoimmune disorder of the joints that causes pain, swelling, and loss of function), fits, epilepsy, or regular physical activity should all be disclosed to your doctor. People who have myasthenia gravis, a nerve system illness that causes muscle weakness, may experience worsening muscle weakness after using Ciplox-500 Tablet 10&#39;s, which could result in serious breathing problems or even death. The combination of dairy products with Ciplox-500 Tablet 10&#39;s should be avoided. Additionally, it&#39;s best to avoid being in the sun when taking Ciplox-500 Tablet 10s because it could increase phototoxicity or photosensitivity. Before taking Ciplox-500 Tablet 10&#39;s, patients with epilepsy and irregular heartbeat (particularly a condition known as QT prolongation) should inform their doctor.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>Fluoroquinolones, a family of antibiotics found in Ciplox-500 Tablet 10, are typically used to treat or prevent specific bacterial illnesses. It is prescribed for the treatment of infections of the skin, bone, joint, abdomen (stomach area), prostate (male reproductive gland), and gonorrhoea, which is a sexually transmitted disease. It is also used to treat infectious diarrhoea, typhoid fever, a serious infection that is common in developing nations.</p>\n\n<p>The antibiotic &quot;Ciprofloxacin&quot; found in Ciplox-500 Tablet 10s is bactericidal in nature and works by eradicating germs that cause infections. It stops bacterial cells from dividing. Additionally, it prevents the healing of bacterial cells. The microorganisms are eradicated as a whole.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Diarrhoea</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Rash</li>\n	<li>Liver function tests abnormal</li>\n	<li>Change of the heart rhythm (ECG)</li>\n	<li>Low blood potassium level</li>\n</ul>','[\"screenshot-2025-07-20-213349-175302764654.png\"]','CI500',1,'1','2024-02-15 11:54:07','2025-07-20 16:07:37'),(255,0,'Ciplox 750mg','ciplox-750mg','tablet','ciplox-750mg-170801525720.jpg','CI750','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>The dosage and duration of Ciplox 750 Tablet should be taken as prescribed by your doctor. It can be consumed either with or without meals, ideally at a set time. Even if you feel better, avoid skipping any doses and complete the entire course of medication. To make up for a missing dose, do not take a second dose. Just take the subsequent dose as scheduled.</p>\n\n<p>Follow your doctor&#39;s instructions for this medication&#39;s dosage and duration. Take it all in at once. Don&#39;t eat it, break it, or crush it. It is preferable to take the Ciplox 750 Tablet at a set time rather than with or without food.</p>\n\n<p>Avoid foods, such as tea leaves and cocoa beans, that include chocolate and caffeine, such as Ciplox 750 Tablet.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Wide Spectrum of Activity: Ciplox 750 mg is a broad-spectrum antibiotic, meaning it is effective against a wide range of bacteria. It can target both Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria, making it useful for treating various types of infections.</p>\n\n<p>Bacterial Infection Treatment: Ciplox 750 mg is prescribed to treat bacterial infections in different parts of the body, such as respiratory tract infections, urinary tract infections, skin and soft tissue infections, bone and joint infections, and certain types of sexually transmitted infections.</p>\n\n<p>Rapid Symptom Relief: By eliminating the bacteria causing the infection, Ciplox 750 mg can help alleviate symptoms such as fever, pain, inflammation, and discomfort. It works by inhibiting bacterial growth and preventing the spread of the infection.</p>\n\n<p>Oral Administration: Ciplox 750 mg is available in tablet form for oral administration, which makes it convenient and easy to take. The tablets are usually swallowed whole with water, and the prescribed dosage and duration of treatment should be followed as directed by the healthcare provider.</p>\n\n<p>High Efficacy: Ciplox 750 mg contains a higher dosage of ciprofloxacin compared to lower-strength formulations. This higher dosage may be particularly beneficial in cases where the infection is severe or resistant to other antibiotics, as it provides a higher concentration of the active ingredient to combat the bacteria.</p>\n\n<p>Well-Tolerated: Ciplox 750 mg is generally well-tolerated by most individuals. However, as with any medication, there is a possibility of side effects. It is important to discuss any concerns or existing medical conditions with your healthcare provider before starting treatment.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Allergies: If you have a known allergy to ciprofloxacin or any other quinolone antibiotics, inform your doctor before taking Ciplox 750 mg. Allergic reactions can range from mild rashes to severe anaphylaxis, which is a life-threatening condition.</p>\n\n<p>Medical History: Share your complete medical history with your healthcare provider, especially if you have a history of tendon disorders, seizures, liver or kidney problems, myasthenia gravis, or any other underlying medical conditions. This information will help your doctor determine the appropriateness and dosage of Ciplox 750 mg for you.</p>\n\n<p>Drug Interactions: Notify your doctor about all the medications, herbal supplements, and over-the-counter drugs you are currently taking. Certain medications can interact with Ciplox 750 mg and affect its efficacy or increase the risk of side effects. It is particularly important to mention any medications that can cause QT prolongation (a heart rhythm disorder) or increase the risk of seizures.</p>\n\n<p>Pregnancy and Breastfeeding: If you are pregnant, planning to become pregnant, or breastfeeding, discuss the potential risks and benefits of taking Ciplox 750 mg with your doctor. Ciprofloxacin may have potential risks to the developing fetus or the nursing baby, and its use should be carefully evaluated in such cases.</p>\n\n<p>Tendonitis and Tendon Rupture: Ciplox 750 mg has been associated with an increased risk of tendonitis (inflammation of tendons) and tendon rupture, especially in older adults. If you experience any tendon pain, swelling, or inflammation while taking Ciplox 750 mg, contact your doctor immediately and avoid strenuous physical activity.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>An antibiotic called Ciplox 750 Tablet is used to treat bacterial infections. Additionally, it is used to treat infections of the lungs (pneumonia), nose, throat, skin, and soft tissues. By eradicating and halting the development of the infectious germs, it treats the infection.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<p>The majority of adverse effects are temporary and go away as your body becomes used to the medication. If they persist or you&#39;re concerned about them, speak with your doctor.</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n	<li>Gastrointestinal disorder</li>\n	<li>Joint pain</li>\n	<li>Urticaria</li>\n</ul>','[\"ciplox-750mg-170801525720.jpg\"]','CI750',1,'0','2024-02-15 16:41:06','2025-07-20 12:28:43'),(256,0,'Ciplox Ointment 5 gm','ciplox-ointment-5-gm','Cream & Ointment','ciplox-ointment-5-gm-170801537414.jpg','CI005','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>As directed by the physician, apply Ciplox-D Eye Ointment 5 gm. Ciplox-D Eye Ointment 5 gm frequently causes stinging or burning sensations, gritty feelings in the eyes, irritation, white deposits on the eye surface (cornea), and redness. Most of these side symptoms disappear over time without the need for treatment from a doctor. However, you should see your doctor if you frequently have these adverse effects.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;Tilt your head back when lying down. Create a pocket by gently pulling the lower eyelid with your index finger. Insert a small amount of the gel or ointment into the lower eyelid&#39;s pocket. For one to two minutes, close your eyes.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Bacterial Eye Infections: Ciplox-D Eye is primarily prescribed for the treatment of bacterial eye infections, such as conjunctivitis (pink eye) and corneal ulcers. Ciprofloxacin, one of the active ingredients, is a broad-spectrum antibiotic that helps eliminate the bacteria causing the infection.</p>\n\n<p>Anti-inflammatory Effects: Dexamethasone, the other active ingredient in Ciplox-D Eye, is a corticosteroid with potent anti-inflammatory properties. It helps reduce inflammation, redness, swelling, and itching associated with eye conditions.</p>\n\n<p>Rapid Symptom Relief: By targeting both the bacterial infection and the accompanying inflammation, Ciplox-D Eye can provide quick relief from symptoms such as redness, itching, discharge, pain, and discomfort.</p>\n\n<p>Dual Action: The combination of ciprofloxacin and dexamethasone in Ciplox-D Eye provides a dual action approach 