ng the amount of the brain chemical that causes Alzheimer&#39;s disease symptoms. Together, they maintain equilibrium in the brain&#39;s levels of chemical messengers and facilitate the transmission of nerve signals.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Loss of appetite</li>\n	<li>Dryness in the mouth</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n	<li>Weight loss</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Diarrhoea</li>\n</ul>','[\"donamem-5-10-mg-1708262812100.webp\"]','DO005',1,'0','2024-02-18 13:28:26','2025-09-17 11:55:07'),(296,0,'Donep 10 mg','donep-10-mg','tablet','donep-10-mg-17082629465.jpg','DO10','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Take 10 Donep-10 Tablets exactly as directed. In accordance with your medical condition, your doctor will advise you on how frequently to take Donep-10 Tablets. If you&#39;re using Donep-10 Tablets 10, you can have certain side effects like nausea, diarrhoea, cramping in your muscles, vomiting, lethargy, and insomnia. This occurs as the body adjusts to the new medication. A person should seek medical attention right away if they experience any serious adverse effects from a medication, such as dizziness, constipation, sleepiness, fainting, frequent urination, headache, joint pain, mental depression, or pain, or if these side effects do not go away in a few days.</p>\n\n<p>According to a doctor&#39;s advice, take 10 Donep-10 Tablets with or without food. With a glass of water, completely swallow it. Don&#39;t eat it, break it, or crush it.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Alzheimer&#39;s Disease Treatment: Donep-10 is primarily prescribed for the treatment of symptoms associated with Alzheimer&#39;s disease, a progressive brain disorder that affects memory, thinking, and behavior. It helps improve cognitive function, including memory, attention, and problem-solving abilities, in individuals with mild to moderate Alzheimer&#39;s disease.</p>\n\n<p>Cholinesterase Inhibitor: Donep-10 belongs to a class of medications known as cholinesterase inhibitors. It works by blocking the breakdown of acetylcholine, a chemical messenger involved in memory and cognitive processes. By increasing acetylcholine levels in the brain, Donep-10 helps enhance communication between nerve cells and improves cognitive function.</p>\n\n<p>Symptom Management: Donep-10 can help manage various symptoms associated with Alzheimer&#39;s disease, such as memory loss, confusion, disorientation, and difficulties with language and daily activities. It may also help slow down the progression of cognitive decline in some individuals.</p>\n\n<p>Improved Quality of Life: By improving cognitive function and helping to manage Alzheimer&#39;s disease symptoms, Donep-10 can enhance the overall quality of life for individuals with the condition. It may lead to better engagement in daily activities, improved social interactions, and a reduced burden on caregivers.</p>\n\n<p>Well-Tolerated: Donep-10 is generally well-tolerated, with most side effects being mild and transient. Common side effects may include nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, loss of appetite, and dizziness. These side effects can often be managed with dose adjustments or symptomatic treatment.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>The effects of Donep-10 Tablet 10s may be weakened or strengthened by other medications, therefore a person should inform their doctor if they are using any prescription or herbal medications. Since alcohol may lessen the effects of medication, a person should avoid drinking it.&nbsp; Before using this medication, a woman who is breastfeeding or pregnant should consult her doctor. Driving may be impacted by Alzheimer&#39;s disease; therefore, unless your doctor certifies that it is safe for you to do so, you should not engage in any activity that requires mental alertness.</p>','<p>Tablet Donep-10 The drug 10&#39;s is a member of the class of drugs known as &quot;anti-Alzheimer&#39;s drugs&quot; and is primarily used to treat Alzheimer&#39;s-related dementia. Alzheimer&#39;s disease is characterized by the degeneration and death of brain cells, which results in dementia, a progressive deterioration of thinking and behavioral abilities that impairs an individual&#39;s capacity for independent functioning. Confusion, worsening memory loss, and behavioral abnormalities are the symptoms.</p>\n\n<p>The substance Donepezil, which belongs to the class of medications known as acetylcholinesterase inhibitors, is found in Donep-10 Tablets 10s. This medication raises levels of acetylcholine in the brain, which helps with memory function by delaying the breakdown of acetylcholine, a chemical that facilitates neuron communication and is necessary for healthy brain function.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Diarrhoea</li>\n	<li>Loss of appetite</li>\n	<li>Muscle cramps</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Trouble in sleeping</li>\n	<li>Unusual tiredness</li>\n	<li>Weakness</li>\n</ul>','[\"donep-10-mg-17082629465.jpg\"]','DO10',1,'0','2024-02-18 13:30:19','2025-09-17 11:55:42'),(297,0,'Donep 5 mg','donep-5-mg','tablet','donep-5-mg-170826308083.jpg','DO005','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>As directed, take 15 Donep 5 Tablets. Based on your health, your doctor will advise you on how frequently to take Donep 5 Tablet 15&#39;s. When taking Donep 5 Tablet 15s, a patient may encounter certain side effects like nausea, diarrhoea, vomiting, lethargy, sleeplessness, and muscle cramps. The body is adjusting to the new medication, which is why this occurs. A person has to consult a doctor right away if they experience significant side effects from medication, such as dizziness, constipation, sleepiness, fainting, frequent urination, headache, joint pain, mental depression, and pain, or if the side effects do not go away in a few days.</p>\n\n<p>As directed by a doctor, take Donep 5 Tablet 15&#39;s with or without food. With a glass of water, swallow it whole. Do not chew, break, or chew it.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Alzheimer&#39;s Disease Treatment: Donep-5 is primarily prescribed for the treatment of symptoms associated with Alzheimer&#39;s disease, a progressive brain disorder that affects memory, thinking, and behavior. It helps improve cognitive function, including memory, attention, and problem-solving abilities, in individuals with mild to moderate Alzheimer&#39;s disease.</p>\n\n<p>Cholinesterase Inhibitor: Donep-5 belongs to a class of medications known as cholinesterase inhibitors. It works by blocking the breakdown of acetylcholine, a chemical messenger involved in memory and cognitive processes. By increasing acetylcholine levels in the brain, Donep-5 helps enhance communication between nerve cells and improves cognitive function.</p>\n\n<p>Symptom Management: Donep-5 can help manage various symptoms associated with Alzheimer&#39;s disease, such as memory loss, confusion, disorientation, and difficulties with language and daily activities. It may also help slow down the progression of cognitive decline in some individuals.</p>\n\n<p>Improved Quality of Life: By improving cognitive function and helping to manage Alzheimer&#39;s disease symptoms, Donep-5 can enhance the overall quality of life for individuals with the condition. It may lead to better engagement in daily activities, improved social interactions, and a reduced burden on caregivers.</p>\n\n<p>Well-Tolerated: Donep-5 is generally well-tolerated, with most side effects being mild and transient. Common side effects may include nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, loss of appetite, and dizziness. These side effects can often be managed with dose adjustments or symptomatic treatment.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>If a patient is taking any prescription or over-the-counter medication, they should let their doctor know because some drugs may amplify or reduce the effects of Donep 5 Tablet 15s. Since alcohol may lessen the effects of medication, a person should avoid drinking it.&nbsp; Before using this medication, a woman who is breastfeeding or pregnant should consult her doctor. Driving may be impacted by Alzheimer&#39;s disease; therefore, unless your doctor certifies that it is safe for you to do so, you should not engage in any activity that requires mental alertness.</p>','<p>Donep 5 Tablet 15s is a member of the class of drugs known as &quot;anti-Alzheimer&#39;s drugs,&quot; which are principally used to treat dementia caused by Alzheimer&#39;s disease. Alzheimer&#39;s disease is characterized by the degeneration and death of brain cells, which results in dementia, a progressive deterioration of thinking and behavioral abilities that impairs an individual&#39;s capacity for independent functioning. Confusion, worsening memory loss, and behavioral abnormalities are the symptoms.</p>\n\n<p>The substance Donepezil, which belongs to the class of medications known as acetylcholinesterase inhibitors, is found in Donep 5 Tablet 15&#39;s. This medication raises levels of acetylcholine in the brain, which helps with memory function by delaying the breakdown of acetylcholine, a chemical that facilitates neuron communication and is necessary for healthy brain function.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Diarrhoea</li>\n	<li>Loss of appetite</li>\n	<li>Muscle cramps</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Trouble in sleeping</li>\n	<li>Unusual tiredness</li>\n	<li>Weakness</li>\n</ul>','[\"donep-5-mg-170826308083.jpg\"]','DO005',1,'0','2024-02-18 13:32:33','2025-09-17 11:56:07'),(298,0,'Dorzox Eye Drop 2% (5 ml)','dorzox-eye-drop-2-(5-ml)-','Drops','dorzox-eye-drop-2-5-ml-170826338416.jpg','DO002','<p>How to Use:</p>\n\n<p>Dorzox Eye Drops (5 ml) should be used exclusively for ophthalmic (eye) purposes. Prior to and following administration, it is crucial to wash your hands thoroughly. To apply the drops, recline and tilt your head backward. Gently pull down your lower eyelid using your index finger to create a small pocket. Place the recommended number of drops into the pocket of the lower eyelid as advised by your doctor. Close your eyes and keep them shut for 1-2 minutes.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Reduction of eye pressure: Dorzox Eye Drops help to lower the elevated intraocular pressure (IOP) in the eyes. By inhibiting carbonic anhydrase, it reduces the production of aqueous humor, the fluid present in the eye, which results in a decrease in eye pressure.</p>\n\n<p>Prevention of vision loss: Elevated eye pressure is a major risk factor for glaucoma, a condition that can lead to optic nerve damage and permanent vision loss. By effectively reducing eye pressure, Dorzox Eye Drops help to prevent the gradual loss of vision and protect the optic nerve.</p>\n\n<p>Management of glaucoma: Dorzox eye drops are commonly prescribed as part of the treatment regimen for open-angle glaucoma and ocular hypertension. By controlling eye pressure, it aids in managing these conditions and preventing their progression.</p>\n\n<p>Convenient and targeted application: Dorzox Eye Drops provide a convenient and targeted way of delivering medication directly to the affected eye. The drops can be easily administered into the eye, allowing the active ingredient to work directly at the site of action.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Use Dorzox eye drops as prescribed by your doctor.</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Wash your hands before using the eye drops.</li>\n	<li>Avoid touching the tip of the bottle to prevent contamination.</li>\n	<li>Apply the drops only to the affected eye(s).</li>\n	<li>Remove contact lenses before using the eye drops.</li>\n	<li>Temporary blurred vision may occur, so avoid activities requiring clear vision.</li>\n	<li>Inform your doctor about any other medications you are taking.</li>\n	<li>Discontinue use and seek medical attention if you experience signs of an allergic reaction.</li>\n	<li>Attend regular follow-up appointments with your doctor.</li>\n</ul>','<p>Dorzox Eye Drops 5 ml is classified as an antiglaucoma medication, primarily prescribed to address elevated intraocular pressure. Its main objective is to prevent the gradual deterioration of vision by reducing the heightened pressure within the eyes. Glaucoma is an ocular condition characterized by optic nerve damage, resulting in increased intraocular pressure, which, if left untreated, can lead to irreversible blindness.</p>\n\n<p>The active ingredient in Dorzox Eye Drops (5 ml) is dorzolamide, a carbonic anhydrase inhibitor. It functions by decreasing intraocular pressure. It is essential to administer Dorzox Eye Drops (5 ml) solely to the affected eye, and contact with the unaffected eye should be avoided.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<p>The majority of side effects do not need medical attention and typically subside as your body adapts to the medication. However, if you are concerned or if the side effects persist, it is recommended that you consult your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>The most common side effects are listed below:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Bitter taste</li>\n	<li>Blurred vision</li>\n	<li>Stinging in the eyes</li>\n	<li>Burning eyes</li>\n</ul>','[\"dorzox-eye-drop-2-5-ml-170826338416.jpg\"]','DO002',1,'0','2024-02-18 13:37:31','2025-09-17 11:56:56'),(299,0,'Dorzox T 5 ml Eye Drop','dorzox-t-5-ml-eye-drop','Drops','dorzox-t-5-ml-eye-drop-170826349646.jpg','DO005','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Dorzox T Drops (5 ml) are intended for use in the eyes only. Prior to and following the application of Dorzox T Drops (5 ml), ensure that you thoroughly wash your hands. To administer the drops, lie down and tilt your head backward. Gently pull down your lower eyelid with your index finger to create a small pocket. As instructed by your doctor, place the recommended number of drops into the pocket formed by the lower eyelid. Close your eyes for approximately 1&ndash;2 minutes. After use, replace the outer cap of the container. Avoid touching the tip of the container to your eye, eyelids, or surrounding areas, as it may lead to contamination of Dorzox T Drops 5 ml.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Dorzox T Drops 5 ml is an ophthalmic medication specifically designed to effectively treat open-angle glaucoma and ocular hypertension, which refers to high eye pressure. It contains dorzolamide and timolol in the form of an ophthalmic solution, or eye drops. Dorzolamide functions as a topical carbonic anhydrase inhibitor, while timolol acts as a topical beta-blocker. Together, they work to reduce the secretion of aqueous humor, the natural fluid present in the eye, by the ciliary body. This action leads to a decrease in eye pressure.</p>\n\n<p>In the treatment of glaucoma, a condition that causes damage to the optic nerve and can result in vision impairment, Dorzox T Eye Drops effectively reduce swelling and pressure within the eye. This helps prevent complications associated with glaucoma, including vision loss and blindness, while improving overall vision. Dorzox T Eye Drops may be used alone or in conjunction with other eye drops. While glaucoma cannot be prevented, regular monitoring and checkups can aid in the early detection of the disease.</p>\n\n<p>For the treatment of ocular hypertension, where there is higher than normal eye pressure due to fluid buildup, Dorzox T Eye Drops enhance the flow of fluid from inside the eye into the bloodstream. By doing so, it reduces the increased eye pressure and prevents further damage or complications, such as changes in vision or vision loss. It is important to use Dorzox T Eye Drops only in the affected eye and to adhere to the prescribed dosage and frequency as directed by your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>When using Dorzox T 5 ml eye drops, it is important to take precautions to ensure safe and effective use. Use the drops under medical supervision and follow your doctor&#39;s instructions. Inform your doctor about any allergies and existing eye conditions. Be cautious of potential interactions with other medications. Remove contact lenses before using the drops, and wait 15 minutes before reinserting them. Avoid touching the eye or surfaces with the dropper to prevent contamination. Discontinue use and seek medical advice if you experience eye irritation or signs of infection. Consult your doctor if you are pregnant, planning to become pregnant, or breastfeeding. Regularly visit your eye doctor for checkups and monitoring. Follow your doctor&#39;s guidance for the proper use of Dorzox T 5 ml eye drops.</p>','<p>Dorzox T Drops 5 ml is a combination medication belonging to the category of antiglaucoma agents, specifically used to treat open-angle glaucoma and ocular hypertension (high eye pressure). It is typically prescribed when other medications have not effectively addressed these conditions. Glaucoma is an eye disorder that results in optic nerve damage due to abnormally increased eye pressure. Ocular hypertension refers to elevated eye pressure caused by inadequate drainage of a fluid called aqueous humor, which is responsible for maintaining normal eye pressure.</p>\n\n<p>Dorzox T Drops (5 ml) contain two active ingredients, dorzolamide and timolol. Dorzolamide is a topical carbonic anhydrase inhibitor, while timolol is a topical beta-blocker. Together, they work by reducing the production of aqueous humor in the eye&#39;s ciliary body, leading to a decrease in eye pressure. This mechanism helps in the management of open-angle glaucoma and ocular hypertension.</p>','<p>Side effects:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Burning sensation</li>\n	<li>Eye redness</li>\n	<li>Itching</li>\n	<li>Stinging sensation</li>\n	<li>Blurred vision</li>\n</ul>','[\"dorzox-t-5-ml-eye-drop-170826349646.jpg\"]','DO005',1,'0','2024-02-18 13:39:44','2025-09-17 11:58:38'),(300,0,'Double X Power','double-x-power','tablet','double-x-power-170826364039.jpg','DO160','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Regardless of the influence of a person&#39;s mental or physical health, Double X power is an excellent treatment for improving mild to severe sensual p