ake Doxt-SL Capsules 10 with food. Doxt-SL Capsule 10 should only be taken whole, with water; do not chew or crush it.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Doxycycline and Lactic acid bacillus are both found in Doxt-SL Capsule 10. Doxt-SL Capsule 10&#39;s are used to treat bacterial illnesses like gonorrhea and syphilis as well as respiratory, eye, mouth, and urinary tract infections, intestinal infections, respiratory infections, and sexually transmitted infections. The antibiotic doxycycline stops the manufacture of crucial proteins that the bacteria need to survive, killing the germs in the process. A microorganism called lactic acid bacteria aids in reestablishing the balance of beneficial bacteria in the gut, which may have become out of whack as a result of illnesses or antibiotic use. Doxt-SL Capsule 10&#39;s work together to treat bacterial infections.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>If any of the ingredients in Doxt-SL Capsule 10s cause your allergies, avoid taking them. Avoid taking Doxt-SL Capsules 10 on your own as this could result in antibiotic resistance, which is when some bacterial illnesses are resistant to the effects of antibiotics. You should let your doctor know if you suffer from myasthenia gravis (muscle wasting/fatigue), porphyria (a genetic disorder of the blood pigments), kidney, or liver issues. If you are expecting a child or nursing a baby, speak with your doctor. Avoid drinking alcohol since it may interfere with how Doxt-SL Capsule 10s work. Be careful while driving if taking Doxt-SL Capsule 10s since they may make you feel dizzy.</p>','<p>Doxt-SL Capsule 10s are an example of an antibiotic, which is a class of drugs used to treat bacterial illnesses such as gonorrhea, syphilis, and urinary tract infections as well as lung infections, eye infections, gum infections, and intestinal infections. The proliferation of dangerous bacteria inside or on the body results in bacterial illnesses. Doxt-SL Capsule 10&#39;s are ineffective against viral illnesses, such as the common cold and the flu.</p>\n\n<p>Doxycycline and Lactic acid bacillus are both found in Doxt-SL Capsule 10. The antibiotic doxycycline stops the manufacture of crucial proteins that the bacteria need to survive, killing the germs in the process. A microorganism called lactic acid bacteria aids in reestablishing the balance of beneficial bacteria in the gut, which may have become out of whack as a result of illnesses or antibiotic use. Doxt-SL Capsule 10&#39;s work together to treat bacterial infections.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Stomach upset</li>\n	<li>Loss of appetite</li>\n</ul>','[\"dox-t-sl-170826376266.jpg\"]','DO10',1,'1','2024-02-18 13:43:42','2025-07-20 16:15:39'),(302,0,'Doxacard 2mg','doxacard-2mg','tablet','doxacard-2mg-170826506012.jpg','DO002','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>It is important to follow your doctor&rsquo;s instructions and read the medication label carefully before taking Doxacard 2mg. Take the prescribed dosage as directed and do not exceed it. The medication is usually taken orally, with or without food, once a day or as recommended by your healthcare provider. It is important to take it consistently at the same time each day to maintain its effectiveness.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Effective blood pressure control: Doxacard 2mg is highly effective in managing high blood pressure. By relaxing the blood vessels, it helps to lower blood pressure and reduce the risk of cardiovascular complications associated with hypertension, such as heart attacks and strokes.</p>\n\n<p>Improved heart health: By reducing the workload on the heart, Doxacard 2mg can help improve overall heart function and decrease the strain on this vital organ.</p>\n\n<p>Symptom relief: In addition to its blood pressure-lowering effects, Doxacard 2mg may also help alleviate certain symptoms associated with high blood pressure, such as headaches, dizziness, and shortness of breath.</p>\n\n<p>Urinary symptoms improvement: Doxacard 2mg has been found to be beneficial in managing urinary symptoms related to an enlarged prostate gland (benign prostatic hyperplasia). It helps relax the smooth muscles in the prostate and bladder neck, leading to improved urine flow and reduced urinary frequency and urgency.</p>\n\n<p>Potential for combination therapy: Doxacard 2mg can be used in combination with other antihypertensive medications to achieve better blood pressure control, allowing for a more personalized and effective treatment approach.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before taking Doxacard 2mg, it is important to inform your doctor about any pre-existing medical conditions, allergies, or medications you are currently taking. This will help ensure the medication is safe for you to use and will not interact negatively with other substances.</p>','<p>Doxacard 2mg is a medication that is primarily used to treat high blood pressure (hypertension). It belongs to a class of drugs known as alpha blockers, which work by relaxing and widening the blood vessels, allowing for easier blood flow. This helps to lower blood pressure and reduce the workload on the heart.</p>\n\n<p>Here are some key points about Doxacard 2mg:</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>While side effects can occur with any medication, most individuals tolerate Doxacard 2mg well. Common side effects may include dizziness, lightheadedness, fatigue, nasal congestion, and fluid retention. These side effects are usually temporary and subside as your body adjusts to the medication. If you have any concerns about side effects, it is advisable to consult your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>Remember, it is crucial to consult with a healthcare professional for personalized advice and dosage instructions based on your specific medical condition.</p>','[\"doxacard-2mg-170826506012.jpg\"]','DO002',1,'0','2024-02-18 14:04:28','2025-09-18 08:00:05'),(303,0,'Doxazosin 1mg','doxazosin-1mg','tablet','doxazosin-1mg-170826515438.jpg','DO001','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>Follow your doctor&rsquo;s instructions on how to take Doxazosin 1mg. Read and follow all the directions on the medication label. It is important not to exceed or reduce the prescribed dosage without consulting your healthcare provider.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Doxazosin 1mg offers several benefits for individuals with high blood pressure or BPH:</p>\n\n<p>Management of high blood pressure: Doxazosin helps to lower blood pressure by relaxing and widening the blood vessels, allowing blood to flow more easily. By controlling blood pressure, it can reduce the risk of heart attacks, strokes, and other cardiovascular complications.</p>\n\n<p>Relief from urinary symptoms: For men with an enlarged prostate, Doxazosin can alleviate bothersome symptoms such as frequent urination, weak urine flow, difficulty starting and stopping urination, and the feeling of incomplete bladder emptying. By relaxing the muscles in the prostate gland and urinary tract, it helps to improve urinary flow and reduces the need for frequent nighttime urination.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before taking Doxazosin 1mg, it is important to inform your healthcare provider about any existing medical conditions, including allergies, liver or kidney problems, or a history of low blood pressure. Also, disclose all the medications, supplements, and herbal products you are currently taking, as they may interact with Doxazosin.</p>','<p>Doxazosin 1mg is a medication that is commonly prescribed to treat high blood pressure and symptoms associated with an enlarged prostate gland, a condition known as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH). It belongs to a class of drugs called alpha-blockers, which work by relaxing the muscles in the blood vessels and prostate, thereby improving blood flow and relieving urinary symptoms.</p>\n\n<p>Here is some important information about Doxazosin 1mg:</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>Like any medication, Doxazosin 1mg may cause some side effects, but they are usually mild and temporary. Common side effects may include:</p>\n\n<p>Dizziness: Some individuals may experience mild dizziness when starting Doxazosin. It is advisable to avoid sudden movements or activities that require mental alertness until you know how the medication affects you.</p>\n\n<p>Fatigue: Feeling tired or drowsy is another possible side effect. If you experience excessive fatigue, it is recommended to speak with your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>It Is important to note that not everyone will experience these side effects, and many individuals tolerate Doxazosin well without any significant issues.</p>\n\n<p>Remember to consult your healthcare provider or pharmacist if you have any concerns or questions about Doxazosin 1mg. They can provide you with personalized advice and guidance based on your specific medical situation.</p>','[\"doxazosin-1mg-170826515438.jpg\"]','DO001',1,'0','2024-02-18 14:07:07','2025-09-18 08:01:51'),(304,0,'Doxazosin 4mg','doxazosin-4mg','tablet','doxazosin-4mg-170826531937.jpg','DO004','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>It is important to follow your doctor&rsquo;s instructions carefully when taking Doxazosin 4mg. Read and follow all the directions on the medication label. Take the medication exactly as prescribed, and do not exceed the recommended dose.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Doxazosin 4mg offers several benefits for individuals with hypertension or BPH:</p>\n\n<p>Blood pressure management: Doxazosin helps lower high blood pressure by relaxing and widening blood vessels, allowing blood to flow more easily. This can help reduce the risk of heart attacks, strokes, and other cardiovascular complications.</p>\n\n<p>Urinary symptom relief: For individuals with an enlarged prostate gland, Doxazosin can effectively alleviate urinary symptoms such as frequent urination, weak urine flow, and difficulty starting or stopping urination. By relaxing the smooth muscles in the prostate and bladder neck, Doxazosin improves urinary flow and reduces the urgency to urinate.</p>\n\n<p>Non-invasive treatment option: Doxazosin provides a non-invasive alternative for managing hypertension and BPH. It can be taken orally and does not require surgical procedures or invasive interventions.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before taking Doxazosin 4mg, it is important to inform your healthcare provider or pharmacist about any medical conditions you have, including allergies, liver or kidney problems, and any medications or supplements you are currently taking. This information will help ensure the safe and effective use of the medication.</p>','<p>Doxazosin 4mg is a medication commonly prescribed for the treatment of high blood pressure and urinary symptoms associated with an enlarged prostate gland, also known as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH). This medication belongs to a class of drugs called alpha-blockers, which work by relaxing the muscles in the prostate and blood vessels, thereby improving urine flow and reducing blood pressure.</p>\n\n<p>Here Is some important information about Doxazosin 4mg</p>','<p>Side Effects:<br />\nWhile most people tolerate Doxazosin well, it is important to be aware of potential side effects. Common side effects of Doxazosin 4mg may include:</p>\n\n<p>Dizziness or lightheadedness: Doxazosin may cause temporary dizziness or a feeling of faintness, especially when standing up from a sitting or lying position. It is recommended to get up slowly to minimize this effect.</p>\n\n<p>Fatigue or drowsiness: Some individuals may experience mild fatigue or drowsiness while taking Doxazosin. If these symptoms occur, it is advisable to avoid activities that require alertness until you know how the medication affects you.</p>\n\n<p>Headache: Headaches are a potential side effect of Doxazosin, although they are generally mild and transient. Drinking plenty of fluids and taking over-the-counter pain relievers as directed by your healthcare provider can help alleviate this symptom.</p>\n\n<p>Remember, these side effects are usually temporary and tend to improve as your body adjusts to the medication. If you have any concerns or experience severe or persistent side effects, it is important to consult your doctor for further guidance.</p>\n\n<p>Overall, Doxazosin 4mg can be an effective and well-tolerated medication for managing high blood pressure and urinary symptoms associated with an enlarged prostate gland. By following your doctor&rsquo;s instructions and maintaining regular check-ups, you can benefit from its positive effects on your health and well-being.</p>','[\"doxazosin-4mg-170826531937.jpg\"]','DO004',1,'0','2024-02-18 14:10:42','2025-09-18 08:02:17'),(305,0,'Doxycyline 100mg','doxycyline-100mg','Capsule','doxycyline-100mg-170826553925.jpg','DO100','<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Treating bacterial infections: Doxycycline 100mg is renowned for its efficacy in treating a diverse range of bacterial infections. It can effectively address respiratory infections, urinary tract infections, skin infections, and sensually transmitted infections (STIs) such as chlamydia, gonorrhea, and syphilis. Its broad-spectrum nature ensures it can target and eliminate a wide array of bacterial strains.</p>\n\n<p>Malaria prevention: Doxycycline 100mg is also used as a preventive measure for malaria in individuals traveling to regions where the disease is prevalent. Its effectiveness in preventing the transmission of malaria-causing parasites makes it a valuable tool in safeguarding travelers&rsquo; health.</p>\n\n<p>Acne treatment: For individuals dealing with acne, Doxycycline 100mg offers significant benefits. It can effectively reduce inflammation and redness associated with acne, leading to clearer and healthier skin. Its ability to regulate sebum production also contributes to its positive impact on acne management.</p>\n\n<p>Lyme disease treatment: Doxycycline 100mg is commonly utilized in the treatment of Lyme disease, a bacterial infection transmitted by ticks. Its effectiveness in combating the bacteria responsible for Lyme disease makes it an essential tool in managing this condition and preventing its long-term complications.</p>\n\n<p>Anti-inflammatory properties: Beyond its antibiotic properties, Doxycycline 100mg possesses anti-inflammatory properties that prove beneficial in treating various conditions. It can help manage inflammatory conditions like rosacea and periodontitis, providing relief to individuals experiencing discomfort and promoting overall oral and skin health.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>While Doxycycline 100mg offers numerous benefits, it&rsquo;s essential to take certain precautions before starting this medication:</p>\n\n<p>Allergies: Inform your healthcare provider or pharmacist about any known allergies, including allergies to doxycycline or other tetracycline antibiotics. This helps ensure your safety and prevents adverse reactions.</p>\n\n<p>Medical history: Disclose your complete medical history to your healthcare provider, particularly if you have experienced difficulty swallowing or have esophagus-related issues. This information allows them to make informed decisions regarding your treatment plan.</p>\n\n<p>Immunizations: Doxycycline may interfere with the effectiveness of live bacterial vaccines, such as the typhoid vaccine. Prioritize open communication with your healthcare professional to ensure appropriate timing and efficacy of immunizations.</p>','<p>Doxycycline 100mg is a trusted and widely prescribed antibiotic medication belonging to the tetracycline family. It is known for its ability to effectively combat bacterial infections and provide relief to individuals suffering from such conditions.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>While Doxycycline 100mg is generally well-tolerated, some individuals may experience temporary side effects that diminish as their body adjusts to the medication. Common side effects include loss of appetite, nasal congestion, drowsiness, and dizziness. It&rsquo;s important to consult your doctor if you have any concerns about these side effects.</p>\n\n<p>Remember, Doxycycline 100mg is a trusted medication that offers significant benefits in the treatment of bacterial infections. Always follow your doctor&rsquo;s instructions and seek their guidance if you have any questions or concerns.</p>','[\"doxycyline-100mg-170826553925.jpg\"]','DO100',1,'1','2024-02-18 14:14:19','2024-02-18 14:14:19'),(306,0,'Dronis  3 mg .02 mg','dronis-3-mg-.02-mg','tablet','dronis-3-mg-170826579135.jpg','DR003','<p>WORKINGS OF DRONIS 30MCG</p>\n\n<p>DRONIS 30MCG works by preventing the production of the gonadotrophic hormones necessary to initiate ovulation (the release of a mature egg from the ovaries) and ensure that the fertilised egg is successfully implanted. They also lessen the thickness of the uterus&#39; inner lining, which renders it unsuitable for the embryo to develop and implant. They can also change the cervical mucus&#39; thickness, which makes it more challenging for the sperm to reach the uterus and fertilise the egg. They consequently make it difficult for a woman to become pregnant.</p>\n\n<p>INFORMATION FOR USE</p>\n\n<p>Only use DRONIS 30MCG as prescribed by your doctor. DRONIS 30MCG should be taken with a glass of water. Don&#39;t chew or crush the medication. You can take DRONIS 30MCG with or without food. Try to take DRONIS 30MCG every day at roughly the same time.</p>\n\n<p>Do not skip any DRONIS 30MCG doses during the course of the therapy since doing so could decrease its efficacy. Take DRONIS 30MCG as soon as you recall if you have missed a dose. To make up for a missing dose, do not take a second dose of DRONIS 30MCG since this may cause bleeding or spotting. Depending on your age, body weight, and health state, your doctor will choose the proper therapy dose and length for you.</p>','<p>Drospirenone and ethinyl estradiol are combined in the drug DRONIS 30MCG, which is a member of the class of drugs known as combined oral contraceptives. It is employed as contraception to avoid becoming pregnant.</p>\n\n<p>Female sex hormones (oestrogen and progesterone) made synthetically include drospirenone and ethinyl estradiol. By inhibiting the release of gonadotrophic hormones, which cause ovulation (the release of a mature egg from the ovaries), they lower the likelihood of becoming pregnant. They also modify the thickness of cervical mucus (a type of fluid generated by the cervix), which makes it challenging for the sperm to go inside the uterus, and lower the thickness of the uterus&#39; inner lining, which makes it unsuitable for the foetus to implant and grow.</p>\n\n<p>Use rhythm or temperature measures to track ovulation instead because DRONIS 30MCG may affect your typical monthly menstrual cycle and cause inaccurate findings.</p>\n\n<p>If you have depression or a family history of breast cancer, let your doctor know before taking DRONIS 30MCG. Additionally, you need to let your doctor know if you suffer from migraines, high blood cholesterol, or diabetes.</p>\n\n<p>Before taking DRONIS 30MCG, talk to your doctor if you have any liver, kidney, heart, or blood clot issues. It is categorically not advised for usage by women who are expecting, nursing, or who are older than 35 and who smoke.</p>\n\n<p>To reduce the possibility of unfavourable side effects, your doctor may advise routinely monitoring your health while you take DRONIS 30MCG. The most frequent adverse effects of DRONIS 30MCG include headache, nausea, sensitive breasts, irregular spotting or bleeding, and nausea. If any of these adverse effects worsen, speak with your doctor. Additionally, let your doctor know if you experience severe depression or have suicidal or self-harming ideas.</p>','<p>SIDE EFFECTS OF 30MCG DRONIS</p>\n\n<p>COMMON&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>unusual bleeding or spotting</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Breast sensitivity</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>White vaginal discharge that is thick, vaginal yeast infection</li>\n	<li>Depression</li>\n	<li>UNCOMMON</li>\n	<li>alterations in weight</li>\n	<li>A larger breast</li>\n	<li>alterations in libido</li>\n	<li>modifications in blood pressure</li>\n	<li>nausea and diarrhoea</li>\n	<li>skin rash, intense itching, and acne</li>\n	<li>Loss of hair (alopecia)</li>\n	<li>Retention of fluid</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>RARE</p>\n\n<p>Asthma</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>disruptions in hearing</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>MANAGING SIDE EFFECTS</p>\n\n<p>Headache:&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Rest and unwind. Drink plenty of liquids, such as water or electrolytes, to keep oneself hydrated. It may be helpful to apply a pain-relieving balm to your forehead. Avoid drinking too much alcohol because it could make your headache worse. In case your headache gets worse, go to your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>Vomiting and nauseous:</p>\n\n<p>DRONIS 30MCG should be taken with or right after meals. Keep your meals basic. Eat less spicy and oil-rich cuisine. If your nausea gets worse, see a doctor.</p>\n\n<p>Advisory and precautions</p>\n\n<p>PREGNANCY</p>\n\n<p>Women who are pregnant or who suspect they may be pregnant should not use DRONIS 30MCG. Additionally, it is not advised to be used by pregnant women who currently have or have previously had jaundice. It should be taken with caution in women who experienced unexpected body movements (Sydenham&#39;s chorea) or pregnancy patches (golden brown patches in the face), hearing loss, porphyria, skin itching with rash and blisters, during their pregnancy, or after using specific sex hormones. Therefore, before using it, talk to your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>BREASTFEEDING</p>\n\n<p>It is not advised for breastfeeding women to use DRONIS 30MCG. Therefore, before using it, talk to your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>AUTOMOBILITY AND MACHINERY USE</p>\n\n<p>If you suffer lightheadedness, drowsiness, fatigue, or blurred vision after taking DRONIS 30MCG, do not operate heavy machinery or drive.</p>\n\n<p>ALCOHOL</p>\n\n<p>Alcohol shouldn&#39;t be consumed while taking DRONIS 30MCG.</p>\n\n<p>KIDNEY</p>\n\n<p>Patients with kidney disorders (such as kidney failure) should not use DRONIS 30MCG. Therefore, before using it, talk to your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>LIVER</p>\n\n<p>Patients who currently have, or have ever had, liver disorders (such as liver tumours), should not use DRONIS 30MCG. In people with gall bladder issues, it should be used cautiously. Therefore, before using it, talk to your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>ALLERGY</p>\n\n<p>If you are allergic to drospirenone or ethinyl estradiol, avoid taking DRONIS 30MCG.</p>\n\n<p>LUNGS</p>\n\n<p>Patients suffering pulmonary embolisms (blood clots in the lungs) should not use DRONIS 30MCG. Therefore, before using it, talk to your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>HEART ILLNESS</p>\n\n<p>Patients who have or have ever had cardiac disorders (such as heart attack, stroke, angina, mini stroke, or uncontrolled high blood pressure) should not take DRONIS 30MCG. Therefore, before using it, talk to your doctor.</p>','[\"dronis-3-mg-170826579135.jpg\"]','DR003',1,'0','2024-02-18 14:19:42','2025-07-20 16:22:04'),(307,0,'Drotin 40 mg','drotin-40-mg','tablet','drotin-40-mg-170826613479.jpg','DR40','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>It is important to follow your doctor&rsquo;s instructions when taking Drotin 40mg. Read and adhere to all the guidelines provided on the medication label. Avoid self-medication and always consult with a healthcare professional before starting or adjusting the dosage.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Relieving smooth muscle spasms: Drotin 40mg is primarily used to relieve spasms in the smooth muscles of the gastrointestinal tract, uterus, and other organs. It helps to relax these muscles, reducing pain and discomfort associated with conditions like irritable bowel syndrome (IBS), menstrual cramps, and urinary tract spasms.</p>\n\n<p>Improved gastrointestinal function: Drotin 40mg can help regulate bowel movements and alleviate symptoms such as abdominal pain, bloating, and cramping associated with gastrointestinal disorders.</p>\n\n<p>Enhanced quality of life: By effectively relieving muscle spasms and associated pain, Drotin 40mg can improve your overall well-being and daily functioning. It allows you to carry out your daily activities without significant discomfort or interruptions.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before taking Drotin 40mg, it is important to inform your healthcare provider or pharmacist about any allergies you may have, including allergies to Drotaverine or any other medications. They can provide you with proper guidance and alternatives if needed.</p>','<p>Drotin 40mg, also known as Drotaverine 40mg, is a medication that offers several beneficial effects in managing certain conditions. It belongs to a class of drugs called antispasmodics, which work by relaxing smooth muscles in the body. Here&rsquo;s some information about Drotin 40mg:</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>While Drotin 40mg is generally well-tolerated, like any medication, it may cause some side effects. It is important to note that these side effects are usually temporary and not experienced by everyone. If you have any concerns, it is recommended to consult with your doctor. Some potential side effects include:</p>\n\n<p>Mild drowsiness: Some individuals may experience mild drowsiness while taking Drotin 40mg. If this occurs, it is advisable to avoid activities that require alertness until you know how your body responds to the medication.</p>\n\n<p>Gastrointestinal disturbances: In rare cases, Drotin 40mg may cause mild gastrointestinal side effects such as nausea, diarrhea, or constipation. These symptoms are usually temporary and subside on their own.</p>','[\"drotin-40-mg-170826613479.jpg\"]','DR40',1,'0','2024-02-18 14:23:23','2025-09-18 08:03:01'),(308,0,'Duolin Inhaler 50 mcg 20 mcg','duolin-inhaler-50-mcg-20-mcg','Inhaler','duolin-inhaler-50-mcg-20-mcg-170826633489.jpg','DU0520','<p>How to Use:</p>\n\n<p>Follow your physician&#39;s instructions when using Duolin inhaler. It is designed for inhalation only. Remove the cap and shake the inhaler. Insert the inhaler into a spacer and exhale. Depress the inhaler while inhaling slowly through it. Hold your breath for about 10 seconds and exhale slowly. After use, close the inhaler. The appropriate dosage and duration of use will be determined by your doctor, taking into consideration factors such as your age, body weight, and the specific condition being treated.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Duolin Inhaler is a combination medication consisting of levosalbutamol and ipratropium bromide. Together, these bronchodilators effectively relax the muscles in your lung airways, helping them to stay open. This allows for easier airflow, relieving symptoms like chest tightness, shortness of breath, wheezing, and coughing. By using the Duolin Inhaler correctly, you can experience the benefits of improved breathing and carry out your daily activities more comfortably.</p>\n\n<p>When used as directed, Duolin inhaler is both safe and effective. Its action begins within a few minutes of inhalation, and the effects can last for several hours. It is important to follow your doctor&#39;s advice and not discontinue use without their guidance. Proper inhaler technique is essential for optimal results, so if you have any doubts, consult your doctor or nurse for guidance.</p>\n\n<p>Duolin inhaler belongs to the class of bronchodilators and works by relaxing the muscles and widening the airways in the lungs. This mechanism of action allows for easier breathing, providing relief from symptoms such as shortness of breath, coughing, and wheezing (a whistling sound during breathing). With the Duolin Inhaler, you can experience improved respiratory comfort and manage your symptoms effectively.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>When using Duolin Inhaler 50 mcg/20 mcg, it is important to take precautions for safe and effective use. Use the inhaler under medical supervision, following your doctor&#39;s instructions. Inform your doctor about any allergies and existing medical conditions. Be cautious of potential interactions with other medications. Ensure proper inhaler technique for optimal results. Watch out for possible side effects and seek medical attention if needed. Consult your doctor if you are pregnant, planning to become pregnant, or breastfeeding. Regular check-ups with your doctor are essential to monitor your progress and adjust the treatment plan if necessary.</p>','<p>Duolin Inhaler is primarily prescribed as a combination medication for the treatment and prevention of symptoms associated with chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD), including shortness of breath, coughing, and wheezing (an audible whistling sound during breathing). COPD encompasses lung conditions such as emphysema (difficulty breathing due to damaged air sacs) and chronic bronchitis (inflammation and narrowing of the bronchial tubes).</p>\n\n<p>The composition of Duolin Inhaler includes two bronchodilators: levosalbutamol and ipratropium bromide. These medications belong to the class of bronchodilators, which function by relaxing the muscles and expanding the airways in the lungs. This action facilitates easier breathing and provides relief from COPD symptoms.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<p>The majority of side effects do not need medical attention and typically subside as your body adapts to the medication. However, if you are concerned or if the side effects persist, it is recommended that you consult your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>The most common side effects are listed below:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Sore throat</li>\n	<li>Dry mouth</li>\n	<li>Runny or stuffy nose</li>\n	<li>Chest tightness</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n	<li>Nervousness</li>\n</ul>','[\"duolin-inhaler-50-mcg-20-mcg-170826633489.jpg\"]','DU0520',1,'0','2024-02-18 14:26:23','2025-09-18 08:03:29'),(309,0,'Duolin Respules 1.25 mg 500 mcg','duolin-respules-1.25-mg-500-mcg','tablet','duolin-respules-1-17082676671.jpg','DU500','<p>How to Use:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>DUOLIN 500MCG/1.25MG RESPULE is intended for inhalation use only and should be administered by a nebulizer under the supervision of a physician.</li>\n	<li>To use DUOLIN 500MCG/1.25MG RESPULE, tear open one respule and squeeze the contents into the reservoir of a nebulizing chamber connected to an air compressor.</li>\n	<li>After using DUOLIN 500MCG/1.25MG RESPULE, discard the empty respule and any leftover solution in the nebulizer.</li>\n	<li>Do not dilute or inhale the contents of DUOLIN 500MCG/1.25MG RESPULE directly.</li>\n	<li>Follow your doctor&#39;s instructions regarding the dose and duration of treatment for DUOLIN 500MCG/1.25MG RESPULE.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Duolin 3 Respules 3ml is a medication that contains a combination of drugs that help keep the airways in the lungs open. By relaxing the muscles of the airways, it eases breathing, relieves tightness in the chest, shortness of breath, wheezing, and coughing, and improves your ability to perform daily activities with ease.</p>\n\n<p>This medication is generally considered safe and effective, and its effects typically begin within a few minutes and can last for several hours. It is important to follow your doctor&#39;s instructions and not stop using the medication unless advised to do so. Proper use of the inhaler is essential for optimal results, so if you are uncertain, seek advice from your doctor or nurse.</p>\n\n<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>Minor side effects of this medication usually go away on their own as your body adjusts to the treatment. However, if you experience persistent or concerning symptoms, it is important to consult your doctor for medical advice.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Allergy: The use of DUOLIN 500MCG/1.25MG RESPULE is not recommended in patients who are allergic to ipratropium, levosalbutamol, or atropine.</li>\n	<li>Medical conditions: Inform your doctor before using DUOLIN 500MCG/1.25MG RESPULE if you have high blood pressure, seizures, diabetes, narrow-angle glaucoma, lung problems like asthma, heart problems like coronary insufficiency and cardiac arrhythmias, kidney problems like renal impairment, and liver problems like hepatic impairment.</li>\n	<li>Pregnancy and breastfeeding: DUOLIN 500MCG/1.25MG RESPULE should be used with caution during pregnancy and in women planning for pregnancy. It should also be used with caution by breastfeeding women only if necessary.</li>\n	<li>Children: DUOLIN 500MCG/1.25MG RESPULE is not recommended for use in children under 6 years of age. It should be used with caution by children and adolescents between 6 to 18 years of age.</li>\n	<li>Inhalation use only: DUOLIN 500MCG/1.25MG RESPULE should be administered only by a nebulizer (with a face mask connected to an air compressor) under the direction of a physician. It is for inhalation use only.</li>\n	<li>Correct inhalation technique: Use your inhaler correctly for it to work properly. If you are not sure, ask your doctor or nurse.</li>\n	<li>Storage: DUOLIN 500MCG/1.25MG RESPULE should be stored at room temperature, away from direct sunlight and heat. Keep it out of the reach of children.</li>\n</ul>','<p>Duolin respules are prescribed for the treatment of symptoms associated with chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD), including breathing difficulty, coughing, and wheezing. This condition causes damage to the lungs, making it difficult for air to pass through. The medication contains ipratropium and levosalbutamol.</p>\n\n<p>The combination of ipratropium and levosalbutamol in Duolin respules works by inhibiting the substances that cause the air tubes in the lungs to constrict, thereby relaxing them and easing the symptoms of COPD. Individuals with certain health conditions, such as diabetes, glaucoma, prostate problems, or heart problems, should exercise caution while using Duolin respules.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>Minor side effects of this medication usually go away on their own as your body adjusts to the treatment. However, if you experience persistent or concerning symptoms, it is important to consult your doctor for medical advice.</p>\n\n<p>The most common side effects are listed below:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Dryness in mouth</li>\n	<li>Breathlessness</li>\n	<li>Cough</li>\n	<li>Tremors</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n</ul>','[\"duolin-respules-1-17082676671.jpg\"]','DU500',1,'0','2024-02-18 14:48:33','2025-09-18 08:03:57'),(310,0,'Duolin Rotacaps 100 mg 40 mg','duolin-rotacaps-100-mg-40-mg','Rotacaps','duolin-rotacaps-100-mg-40-mg-170826779331.jpg','DU100','<p>How to Use:</p>\n\n<p>To ensure proper usage of Rotacaps, please follow the instructions provided on the label. Avoid swallowing the rotacaps. Instead, place the capsule at the base of the rotahaler, not in the mouthpiece. Twist the mouthpiece until you hear a click, then breathe deeply through the mouthpiece. Hold your breath for up to 10 seconds. If there is any remaining powder in the rotahaler, repeat the process.</p>\n\n<p>When using Duolin ROTACAP, it is important to follow your physician&#39;s instructions. Remember, it is for inhalation use only. Hold the revolizer at the base and pull back the mouthpiece. Take the rotacap, or inhalation capsule, from its bottle and insert it into the rotacap chamber. Close the mouthpiece firmly and exhale completely through your mouth. Position the mouthpiece between your teeth and close your lips tightly around it. Sit or stand upright, keeping your head straight, and inhale rapidly and deeply through your mouth. Remove the revolizer from your mouth and hold your breath for 10 seconds, or as long as is comfortable. After use, open the mouthpiece and dispose of the empty rotacap. Repeat this process after each use.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Duolin Rotacap is a combination medication that effectively helps keep your lung airways open by relaxing the muscles within them. This action facilitates easier airflow in and out of the lungs, providing relief from symptoms such as chest tightness, shortness of breath, wheezing, and coughing. By using Duolin Rotacap, you can carry out your daily activities with greater ease.</p>\n\n<p>It is important to note that Duolin Rotacap is a safe and reliable medicine. Its effects typically begin within a few minutes of use and can last for several hours. It is crucial not to discontinue usage unless specifically advised to do so by your doctor. To ensure optimal effectiveness, it is essential to use your inhaler correctly. If you have any doubts, do not hesitate to consult your doctor or nurse for guidance.</p>\n\n<p>Duolin Rotacaps is specifically composed of two bronchodilators: levosalbutamol and ipratropium bromide. As a member of the bronchodilator class, Duolin Rotacaps works by relaxing the muscles and widening the airways in the lungs. This mechanism allows for easier breathing, providing relief from symptoms such as shortness of breath, coughing, and wheezing (characterized by a whistling sound during breathing).</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>When using Duolin Rotacap, it&#39;s important to take certain precautions. First and foremost, use the medication under the guidance of your healthcare provider. They will determine the appropriate dosage and duration of treatment based on your specific condition. Make sure to inform your doctor about any allergies you have and any pre-existing medical conditions, such as heart problems, high blood pressure, glaucoma, or diabetes. If you are pregnant, planning to become pregnant, or breastfeeding, discuss the risks and benefits with your doctor. It&#39;s also important to disclose all medications you are currently taking, as some may interact with Duolin Rotacap. Be aware of possible side effects and contact your doctor if you experience any unusual or severe reactions. Learn and follow the proper inhalation technique for using Duolin Rotacap, and store it in a cool, dry place as directed. Remember to consult your healthcare provider for personalized advice based on your specific situation.</p>','<p>Duolin Rotacaps is a medication that contains a combination of two bronchodilators, levosalbutamol and ipratropium bromide. It is primarily prescribed to treat or prevent symptoms associated with chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD), such as shortness of breath, coughing, and wheezing (a whistling sound while breathing). COPD refers to a group of lung diseases characterized by emphysema (difficulty breathing due to damaged air sacs) and chronic bronchitis (inflammation and narrowing of the airways or bronchial tubes).</p>\n\n<p>By acting as bronchodilators, Duolin Rotacaps relaxthe muscles and wwidenthe airways in the lungs, allowing for easier breathing.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>The majority of side effects do not need medical attention and typically subside as your body adapts to the medication. However, if you are concerned or if the side effects persist, it is recommended that you consult your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>The most common side effects are listed below:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Tremor, pain, nervousness</li>\n	<li>Dry mouth, sore throat, stuffy nose, throat irritation</li>\n	<li>Fast heartrate, irregular heartbeat, high blood pressure</li>\n	<li>Dizziness, headache, sweating, weakness</li>\n	<li>Signs of hypokalaemia (low potassium level in blood) such as muscle twitches, muscle cramps, light-headedness</li>\n	<li>Nausea, vomiting, constipation</li>\n</ul>','[\"duolin-rotacaps-100-mg-40-mg-170826779331.jpg\"]','DU100',1,'0','2024-02-18 14:50:34','2025-09-18 08:04:28'),(311,0,'Duonase Nasal Spray  140 mcg 50 mcg (70 Doses)','duonase-nasal-spray-140-mcg-50-mcg-(70-doses)','Nasal Spray','duonase-nasal-spray-140-mcg-50-mcg-70-doses-170827183491.jpg','DU140','<p>How to Use:</p>\n\n<p>To ensure proper usage of Duonase Nasal Spray, follow your doctor&#39;s prescription. Before using the spray, carefully read and follow the instructions provided on the label. Insert the tip of the bottle into one nostril while closing the other nostril, then spray the medication toward the sides of the nostril. Keep your head in a straight position and breathe gently. Repeat the process for the other nostril.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Duonase Nasal Spray is an effective solution for relieving symptoms associated with allergies, such as a blocked or runny nose, sneezing, and itchy or watery eyes. By alleviating these symptoms, it enables you to carry out your daily activities more comfortably. One of the advantages of Duonase Nasal Spray is its minimal risk of serious side effects, and you may only need to use it on days when you experience symptoms. Additionally, compared to other antihistamine medications, Duonase nasal spray is less likely to cause drowsiness. If you are using it for preventive purposes, it is recommended to use it regularly for maximum benefit.</p>\n\n<p>Duonase Nasal Spray is a combination medication comprising fluticasone propionate and azelastine hydrochloride. Fluticasone propionate, a corticosteroid, acts by targeting the cells within the nasal lining to inhibit the release of specific chemicals responsible for inflammatory reactions. This action provides relief from symptoms such as sneezing, a runny or blocked nose, and sinus discomfort. Azelastine hydrochloride, an antihistamine belonging to the class of anti-allergic drugs, functions by blocking the activity of histamine, a substance responsible for allergic reactions. Together, Duonase Nasal Spray (7 g) effectively alleviates symptoms of allergies, including seasonal allergies, and reduces inflammation in the nasal passages.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>When using Duonase nasal spray, it is crucial to take certain precautions to ensure safe and effective use. First and foremost, follow the instructions provided by your doctor and carefully read the label before using the spray. Use the medication exactly as prescribed, taking note of the recommended dosage and frequency. Be cautious to avoid getting the spray into your eyes, as it is intended for nasal use only. If you have any known allergies or medical conditions, inform your doctor to ensure the suitability of Duonase nasal spray for you. It&#39;s important to monitor your symptoms while using the spray and consult your doctor if they worsen or if you experience any severe side effects. In the event of an allergic reaction or any other serious concern, seek immediate medical attention.</p>','<p>Duonase Nasal Spray is classified as an &quot;anti-allergic&quot; medication primarily used to treat allergic symptoms, including sneezing, runny nose, congestion, stuffy nose, and watery eyes. Allergies occur when the immune system reacts to foreign substances known as allergens, which are typically harmless to the body. Specific allergic conditions can vary among individuals, such as food allergies or seasonal allergies like hay fever, pollen, or pet dander. Coughing is a common symptom of allergies, serving as a reflex action in the throat when there is an entry of mucus or foreign irritants into the respiratory system.</p>\n\n<p>Duonase Nasal Spray combines two drugs: fluticasone propionate (a corticosteroid) and azelastine hydrochloride (an antihistamine/antiallergic). Fluticasone propionate, a corticosteroid, works by acting within the cells of the nasal lining to inhibit the release of certain chemicals in the body that cause inflammatory reactions. This action helps relieve symptoms such as sneezing, a runny or blocked nose, and sinus discomfort. Azelastine hydrochloride, an antihistamine, belongs to the class of anti-allergic drugs and functions by blocking the action of histamine, a substance responsible for triggering allergic reactions. It provides relief from various allergy symptoms, including sneezing, runny nose, watery eyes, itching, swelling, congestion, and stiffness.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<p>The majority of side effects do not need medical attention and typically subside as your body adapts to the medication. However, if you are concerned or if the side effects persist, it is recommended that you consult your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>The most common side effects are listed below:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Taste change</li>\n	<li>Nosebleeds</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Cough</li>\n	<li>Upper respiratory tract infection</li>\n	<li>Dryness in mouth</li>\n</ul>','[\"duonase-nasal-spray-140-mcg-50-mcg-70-doses-170827183491.jpg\"]','DU140',1,'0','2024-02-18 15:57:51','2025-09-17 11:59:11'),(312,0,'Duova Inhaler 9mcg 6mcg (200 mdi)','duova-inhaler-9mcg-6mcg-(200-mdi)','Inhaler','duova-inhaler-9mcg-6mcg-200-mdi-170827211188.jpg','Du009','<p>How to Use:</p>\n\n<p>It may take a few days for the effects of this medication to become noticeable, but its maximum benefits may take a few weeks to fully manifest. Prior to using the inhaler, carefully review the instructions provided on the label. Ensure that you shake the inhaler properly. While inhaling through your mouth, press the inhaler down once to release the medication, and hold your breath for 10 seconds. Repeat this process until you have taken the recommended number of puffs, as advised by your doctor. Following inhalation, it is important to rinse your mouth thoroughly with water and then spit it out.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Duova Inhaler 200 mdi is a medication specifically designed for the treatment and prevention of respiratory disorders, including asthma and chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD). By improving pulmonary function, it effectively addresses conditions like emphysema (characterized by shortness of breath) and chronic bronchitis (inflammation of the bronchial tubes). The inhaler combines two active ingredients: formoterol (a bronchodilator) and tiotropium (an anticholinergic). Formoterol, a long-acting 2-agonist, acts as a bronchodilator, relaxing the muscles in the airways and promoting increased airflow to the lungs. This widening of the airways facilitates easier breathing. Tiotropium, on the other hand, blocks the receptors for acetylcholine that are released in the cholinergic nerve endings within the airways.</p>\n\n<p>COPD refers to a group of lung diseases that can cause significant breathing difficulties. These conditions are characterized by the swelling of the airways responsible for the passage of air in and out of the lungs. Duova 6mcg/9mcg Inhalers effectively address these symptoms by relaxing the muscles within the airways and widening them. This mechanism promotes easier breathing and provides relief from associated symptoms such as chest tightness, shortness of breath, wheezing, and coughing. To manage COPD effectively, it is crucial to avoid smoking and minimize exposure to environmental pollutants such as pollution, dust, and fumes. Additionally, incorporating regular exercise into your routine can help maintain strength and overall well-being. It is recommended to consult with your doctor regarding the appropriate amount of exercise for your individual condition.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Follow the doctor&#39;s instructions regarding dosage and usage.</li>\n	<li>Inform your doctor about any allergies to the medication.</li>\n	<li>Discuss any pre-existing medical conditions with your doctor.</li>\n	<li>Consult your doctor if you are pregnant or breastfeeding.</li>\n	<li>Inform your doctor about all other medications you are taking.</li>\n	<li>Be aware of potential side effects and seek medical attention if needed.</li>\n	<li>Ensure the correct inhaler technique for maximum effectiveness.</li>\n	<li>Avoid smoking and exposure to secondhand smoke.</li>\n	<li>Attend regular checkups to monitor your condition.</li>\n</ul>','<p>Duova Inhaler 200 mdi is a respiratory medication used primarily for the treatment and prevention of asthma and chronic obstructive pulmonary diseases (COPD), including bronchitis and emphysema. Asthma is a chronic respiratory condition characterized by narrowed airways, inflammation, and excess mucus production, leading to breathing difficulties. COPD refers to a group of lung diseases that result in obstructed airflow from the lungs.</p>\n\n<p>Combining formoterol, a bronchodilator, and tiotropium, an anticholinergic, Duova Inhaler 200 mDi provides its therapeutic effects. Formoterol works by relaxing the muscles in the airways, allowing for increased airflow to the lungs. By widening the airways, it facilitates easier breathing. Tiotropium, on the other hand, acts by blocking the receptors for acetylcholine released in the cholinergic nerve endings within the airways. The combination of these two medications in Duova Inhaler 200 mDi helps relax and widen the openings of the airways, making it easier for air to enter and exit the lungs. This mechanism aids in the prevention of asthma attacks and provides relief to individuals with respiratory conditions.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<p>The majority of side effects do not need medical attention and typically subside as your body adapts to the medication. However, if you are concerned or if the side effects persist, it is recommended that you consult your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>The most common side effects are listed below:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Respiratory tract infection</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Sore throat</li>\n	<li>Cough</li>\n</ul>','[\"duova-inhaler-9mcg-6mcg-200-mdi-170827211188.jpg\"]','Du009',1,'0','2024-02-18 16:02:00','2025-09-17 11:59:40'),(313,0,'Duovir 150 300 mg','duovir-150-300-mg','tablet','duovir-150-300-mg-170827396298.webp','DU1530','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>The 150 mg/300 mg Duovir EP Tablet prolongs life by limiting the spread of HIV within the body and lowering the chance of contracting problems linked to the virus. It&#39;s possible to take the medication with or without food. The effectiveness of these drugs is increased by taking them consistently and at the same time. The recovery process may be hampered if a dose of this medication is missed. Until your doctor tells you to discontinue the therapy, it&#39;s crucial to finish the entire course.</p>\n\n<p>As directed by your doctor, take this medication for the prescribed amount of time. Completely inhale it. Never eat, shatter, or crush it. You can take a Duovir EP 150 mg/300 mg Tablet with or without food, however it&#39;s best to take it at a set time.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Antiretroviral therapy: Duovir is classified as an antiretroviral medication and is used as part of a combination therapy regimen for HIV. It helps to suppress the replication of the virus, reduce the viral load in the body, and slow down the progression of the disease.</p>\n\n<p>Effective against HIV: Duovir is effective against HIV-1, the most common strain of the virus. By inhibiting the reverse transcriptase enzyme, lamivudine and zidovudine work together to disrupt the viral replication process, thereby reducing the amount of virus in the body.</p>\n\n<p>Delayed disease progression: With regular and appropriate use, Duovir can help delay the progression of HIV infection to acquired immunodeficiency syndrome (AIDS) and related complications. It plays a crucial role in managing the disease and improving the quality of life for individuals living with HIV.</p>\n\n<p>Increased CD4 cell count: CD4 cells are a type of white blood cells that are specifically targeted and destroyed by HIV. Duovir helps to increase the CD4 cell count, which is important for maintaining a healthy immune system. This helps the body fight off infections and reduces the risk of opportunistic infections associated with HIV.</p>\n\n<p>Convenience: Duovir combines two active ingredients in a single tablet, which simplifies the treatment regimen for patients. This can make it easier to adhere to the prescribed medication schedule and ensure consistent and effective treatment.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Medical supervision: Duovir should be taken under the supervision of a healthcare professional experienced in the treatment of HIV infection. They can provide appropriate dosing instructions, monitor your progress, and address any concerns or side effects that may arise.</p>\n\n<p>Allergies: Inform your healthcare provider if you have any known allergies to lamivudine, zidovudine, or any other components of Duovir. Allergic reactions can range from mild to severe, and it&#39;s essential to avoid medications that may trigger an allergic response.</p>\n\n<p>HIV resistance: Duovir may not be effective against strains of HIV that have developed resistance to lamivudine or zidovudine. It&#39;s crucial to undergo regular monitoring of viral load and CD4 cell count to ensure the medication remains effective. If resistance is detected, alternative treatment options may be necessary.</p>\n\n<p>Kidney and liver function: Duovir is primarily eliminated from the body through the kidneys. Individuals with impaired kidney function may require dose adjustments or close monitoring to prevent the accumulation of the medication. Similarly, individuals with liver disease should exercise caution when taking Duovir, as it can affect liver function.</p>\n\n<p>Other medications and interactions: Inform your healthcare provider about all the medications you are currently taking, including prescription drugs, over-the-counter medications, and herbal supplements. Some medications may interact with Duovir, potentially reducing its effectiveness or increasing the risk of side effects.</p>','<p>A tablet called Duovir EP 150 mg/300 mg contains two antiretrovirals. HIV (human immunodeficiency virus) infection is treated with it. In order to manage or treat AIDS (acquired immunodeficiency syndrome), it increases immunity to combat HIV.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<p>The majority of adverse effects are temporary and go away as your body becomes used to the medication. If they persist or you&#39;re concerned about them, speak with your doctor.</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Fatigue</li>\n	<li>Cough</li>\n	<li>Insomnia (difficulty in sleeping)</li>\n	<li>Rash</li>\n	<li>Joint pain</li>\n	<li>Hair loss</li>\n	<li>Fever</li>\n</ul>','[\"duovir-150-300-mg-170827396298.webp\"]','DU1530',1,'0','2024-02-18 16:33:47','2025-09-17 12:00:12'),(314,0,'Duovir N (150+200+300)mg Tablet','duovir-n-(150+200+300)mg-tablet','tablet','duovir-n-150-200-300-mg-tablet-170827405554.jpg','DU1223','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>It&#39;s possible to take the medication with or without food. The effectiveness of these drugs is increased by taking them consistently and at the same time. The recovery process may be hampered if a dose of this medication is missed. Until your doctor tells you to discontinue the therapy, it&#39;s crucial to finish the entire course. The potency of the medication could be impacted by abruptly stopping the treatment.</p>\n\n<p>As directed by your doctor, take this medication for the prescribed amount of time. Completely inhale it. Never eat, shatter, or crush it. Although the Duovir N Tablet can be taken with or without food, it is best to take it at a certain time each day.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Antiretroviral therapy: Duovir N is classified as an antiretroviral medication and is used as part of a combination therapy regimen for HIV. It helps to suppress the replication of the virus, reduce the viral load in the body, and slow down the progression of the disease.</p>\n\n<p>Effective against HIV: The three active ingredients in Duovir N work together to combat HIV infection. Lamivudine and zidovudine inhibit the reverse transcriptase enzyme, disrupting the viral replication process, while nevirapine inhibits the HIV reverse transcriptase and viral DNA integration. By targeting different stages of the viral lifecycle, Duovir N can help reduce the viral load and control the HIV infection.</p>\n\n<p>Delayed disease progression: Regular and appropriate use of Duovir N can help delay the progression of HIV infection to acquired immunodeficiency syndrome (AIDS) and related complications. It plays a crucial role in managing the disease and improving the quality of life for individuals living with HIV.</p>\n\n<p>Increased CD4 cell count: CD4 cells are a type of white blood cells that are specifically targeted and destroyed by HIV. Duovir N helps to increase the CD4 cell count, which is important for maintaining a healthy immune system. This helps the body fight off infections and reduces the risk of opportunistic infections associated with HIV.</p>\n\n<p>Convenience: Duovir N combines three active ingredients in a single tablet, which simplifies the treatment regimen for patients. This can make it easier to adhere to the prescribed medication schedule and ensure consistent and effective treatment.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Medical supervision: Duovir N should be taken under the supervision of a healthcare professional experienced in the treatment of HIV infection. They can provide appropriate dosing instructions, monitor your progress, and address any concerns or side effects that may arise.</p>\n\n<p>Allergies: Inform your healthcare provider if you have any known allergies to lamivudine, nevirapine, zidovudine, or any other components of Duovir N. Allergic reactions can range from mild to severe, and it&#39;s essential to avoid medications that may trigger an allergic response.</p>\n\n<p>HIV resistance: Duovir N may not be effective against strains of HIV that have developed resistance to lamivudine, nevirapine, or zidovudine. Regular monitoring of viral load and CD4 cell count is important to ensure the medication remains effective. If resistance is detected, alternative treatment options may be necessary.</p>\n\n<p>Liver function: Duovir N can affect liver function, and individuals with liver disease or a history of liver problems should exercise caution when taking this medication. Close monitoring of liver function may be required, and dose adjustments may be necessary in some cases.</p>\n\n<p>Other medications and interactions: Inform your healthcare provider about all the medications you are currently taking, including prescription drugs, over-the-counter medications, and herbal supplements. Some medications may interact with Duovir N, potentially reducing its effectiveness or increasing the risk of side effects.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>Antiretroviral medications are included in the Duovir N Tablet. It is a medication that is prescribed to treat HIV infection. It strengthens the immune system&#39;s ability to combat HIV in order to control or treat AIDS (acquired immunodeficiency syndrome).</p>\n\n<p>In order to extend a person&#39;s lifespan, Duovir N Tablet limits the growth of HIV in the body and lowers the chance of contracting diseases linked to HIV.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Insomnia (difficulty in sleeping)</li>\n	<li>Rash</li>\n	<li>Decreased white blood cell count (neutrophils)</li>\n	<li>Fever</li>\n</ul>','[\"duovir-n-150-200-300-mg-tablet-170827405554.jpg\"]','DU1223',1,'0','2024-02-18 16:35:42','2025-09-17 12:00:40'),(315,0,'Efavir 200 mg','efavir-200-mg','tablet','efavir-200-mg-170827418427.jpg','EF200','<p>How to use;</p>\n\n<p>It is administered in conjunction with other HIV medications and can be taken on an empty stomach or with food. All of these medications work much better when taken consistently and at the proper times, which also lessens the possibility that HIV will develop a resistance to them. It is crucial to continue taking them until your doctor advises you that stopping is safe.</p>\n\n<p>Follow your doctor&#39;s instructions for 