r if you have any known allergies to efavirenz or any other components of Efavir. Allergic reactions can range from mild to severe, and it&#39;s essential to avoid medications that may trigger an allergic response.</p>\n\n<p>HIV resistance: Efavir may not be effective against strains of HIV that have developed resistance to efavirenz. Regular monitoring of viral load and CD4 cell count is important to ensure the medication remains effective. If resistance is detected, alternative treatment options may be necessary.</p>\n\n<p>Central Nervous System (CNS) effects: Efavir may cause CNS-related side effects, such as dizziness, drowsiness, confusion, and vivid dreams. Exercise caution when performing tasks that require alertness and discuss any concerns with your healthcare provider.</p>\n\n<p>Mental health considerations: Some individuals taking efavirenz have reported psychiatric symptoms, including depression, anxiety, and suicidal thoughts. If you have a history of mental health disorders, discuss it with your healthcare provider, as they may consider alternative treatment options or closely monitor your mental well-being.</p>','<p>Efavir 200mg Tablet is a member of the antiretroviral drug class. HIV (human immunodeficiency virus), a virus that can lead to AIDS (acquired immunodeficiency syndrome), is treated with it. In order for your immune system to function better, it helps to suppress HIV infection.</p>\n\n<p>Efavir 200mg Tablet extends your life and lowers your risk of HIV-related problems.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Increased liver enzymes</li>\n	<li>Insomnia</li>\n</ul>','[\"efavir-200-mg-170827418427.jpg\"]','EF200',1,'0','2024-02-18 16:37:09','2025-09-17 12:01:14'),(316,0,'Efavir 600 mg','efavir-600-mg','tablet','efavir-600-mg-170827431458.jpg','EF600','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>It can be taken with food or on an empty stomach and is given along with other HIV drugs. When taken consistently and at the appropriate times, all of these medications perform significantly better, which also lowers the risk that HIV will build a resistance to them. It is critical to take them until your doctor tells you it is safe to quit.</p>\n\n<p>For the dosage and duration of this drug, according to your doctor&#39;s instructions. Observe everything at once. Avoid eating, smashing, or breaking it. It is best to take Efavir 600mg Tablets without food.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Efavir is categorized as an antiretroviral drug and is used as a component of a combination therapy program for HIV. It aids in preventing viral reproduction, lowering the body&#39;s viral load, and halting the spread of the illness.</p>\n\n<p>Efavir is effective against HIV because it targets the reverse transcriptase enzyme, which is essential for viral replication. Efavirenz reduces the amount of virus in the body by blocking this enzyme, which aids in stopping the virus from replicating.</p>\n\n<p>Delay in disease progression: Efavir, when used regularly and correctly, can help prevent HIV infection from developing into AIDS and its associated consequences. It is essential for controlling the illness and enhancing the lives of those who are HIV positive.</p>\n\n<p>A higher CD4 cell count is a sign of HIV infection because CD4 cells are a type of white blood cell that the virus preferentially targets and kills. Efavir aids in increasing CD4 cell count, vital for preserving a strong immune system. This lowers the danger of HIV-related opportunistic illnesses and aids the body&#39;s ability to fight off infections.</p>\n\n<p>Easy administration: Efavir is normally given once daily, making it an easy treatment option for those with HIV. The once-daily dose frequency can make taking medications easier to remember and increase adherence to the treatment plan.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Efavir should be taken under the guidance of a medical expert with knowledge of the treatment of HIV infection. They can give you the right dosage instructions, keep track of your development, and manage any issues or side effects that might come up.</p>\n\n<p>Allergies: Let your doctor know if you have ever had an allergic reaction to efavirenz or any other element of Efavir. It is important to avoid taking medications that could cause an allergic reaction because allergic reactions can range in severity from moderate to severe.</p>\n\n<p>HIV resistance: Efavir may not be effective against HIV strains that have evolved efavirenz resistance. It&#39;s crucial to regularly check viral load and CD4 cell count to make sure the treatment is still working. Alternative treatment methods may be required if resistance is found.</p>\n\n<p>Efavir may have negative effects on the central nervous system (CNS), including tiredness, disorientation, and vivid nightmares. When undertaking duties that call for attention, proceed with caution and bring up any problems with your healthcare physician.</p>\n\n<p>Considerations relating to mental health include the fact that some efavirenz users have had psychiatric symptoms like sadness, anxiety, and suicide thoughts. If you have a history of mental health issues, let your doctor know. They might look into other treatment options or keep a close eye on your mental health.</p>','<p>The antiviral medication class includes Efavir 600mg Tablet. It is used to treat HIV (human immunodeficiency virus), a virus that can cause AIDS (acquired immunodeficiency syndrome). HIV infection can be suppressed in order to improve the performance of your immune system.</p>\n\n<p>Your lifespan is prolonged and your danger of HIV-related issues is decreased by efavirenz 600 mg tablet.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Increased liver enzymes</li>\n	<li>Insomnia</li>\n</ul>','[\"efavir-600-mg-170827431458.jpg\"]','EF600',1,'0','2024-02-18 16:38:42','2025-09-17 12:16:54'),(317,0,'Eflora Cream 15gm','eflora-cream-15gm','Cream','eflora-cream-15gm-170827436979.jpg','EF15','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Use the 15 gm Eflora Cream exactly as directed by your doctor. As long as your doctor has recommended Eflora Cream 15 gm for you depending on your medical condition, you are urged to take it. Some people may have acne, bleeding, sore throats, itching, scaling, dry skin, minor tingling or pain where the product was applied, and fever. Most of these Eflora Cream 15 gm adverse effects subside with time without the need for medical intervention. However, please see a doctor if the adverse effects worsen or persist.</p>\n\n<p>Use clean, dry hands and the recommended dosage of 15 gm of Eflora Cream on the affected regions of the skin. Use your fingers to gently massage the Eflora Cream 15 gm into the skin. Before and after using 15 g of Eflora Cream, wash your hands. Avoid applying bandages or dressings to the afflicted areas. You should wait 4 hours before bathing the area where the 15 gm Eflora Cream was applied.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Eflornithine, found in Eflora Cream 15 gm, is used to stop the growth of unsightly facial hair in women, typically around the lips or beneath the chin. It functions by inhibiting the natural component ornithine decarboxylase, which is found in the hair follicle (the sac where each hair grows) and is important in the development of hair in the body. Eflora Cream 15 gm may also make hair finer and lighter while slowing hair growth. It neither removes hair nor makes hair fall out. Eflora Cream 15 gm is additionally used to treat African sleeping sickness, a condition brought on by the protozoan Trypanosoma brucei.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Avoid contact with the eyes, mouth, and other sensitive areas. Take care to avoid applying Eflora Cream near the eyes, mouth, or other sensitive areas of the face. If accidental contact occurs, rinse thoroughly with water.</p>\n\n<p>Patch test: Before applying Eflora Cream to larger areas of the skin, it is recommended to perform a patch test on a small area to check for any adverse reactions or skin sensitivity.</p>\n\n<p>Sun protection: Eflora Cream may increase the skin&#39;s sensitivity to sunlight. It is important to protect your skin from excessive sun exposure by using sunscreen, wearing protective clothing, and avoiding prolonged sun exposure.</p>\n\n<p>Pregnancy and breastfeeding: Consult with a healthcare professional before using Eflora Cream if you are pregnant, planning to become pregnant, or breastfeeding. They can provide guidance on the safety and suitability of the product during these periods.</p>\n\n<p>Allergic reactions: If you have a known allergy to any of the ingredients in Eflora Cream, avoid using the product. If you experience signs of an allergic reaction, such as a rash, itching, or swelling, discontinue use and seek medical attention.</p>','<p>Eflora Cream 15 gm is a member of the hair growth retardant medication class used to treat female facial hirsutism, which is the unwelcome overgrowth of facial hair. The protozoal illness known as African sleeping sickness is also treated with it. Women who suffer from the disorder known as facial hirsutism experience excessive facial hair development. Women who have unwanted facial hair may experience emotional discomfort and mental trauma in addition to an aesthetic issue.</p>\n\n<p>The 15 g of Eflora Cream includes A natural chemical called ornithine decarboxylase, an enzyme in the body involved in the development of hair, is located in the hair follicle (the sac where each hair grows), and eflornithine is an ornithine decarboxylase (ODC) inhibitor that blocks it. The parasite-infected illness known as African sleeping sickness is also treated with Eflora Cream 15 gm.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Acne</li>\n	<li>Itching</li>\n	<li>Skin redness</li>\n	<li>Hair loss</li>\n	<li>Burning sensation</li>\n	<li>Stinging sensation</li>\n	<li>Irritation</li>\n	<li>Fever</li>\n	<li>Sore throat</li>\n</ul>','[\"eflora-cream-15gm-170827436979.jpg\"]','EF115',1,'0','2024-02-18 16:40:30','2025-07-20 16:22:09'),(318,0,'Elocon 10gm Cream','elocon-10gm-cream','Cream','elocon-10gm-cream-170827447296.png','EL10','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Apply Elocon Cream 10 gm exactly as directed. As long as your doctor has prescribed Elocon Cream 10 gm for your ailment, you are urged to use it. Elocon Cream 10 gm should only be applied externally. Elocon Cream 10 gm should not be applied to the eyes, mouth, or nose. Rinse these areas carefully with water if Elocon Cream 10 gm unintentionally comes into contact with them. Inflamed hair follicles, acne, skin thinning, itching, stinging, tingling, or burning sensations are possible side effects for certain persons. Most of these adverse effects subside with time without the need for medical intervention. However, please see a doctor if the adverse effects worsen or persist.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Mometasone furoate, a strong corticosteroid included in Elocon Cream 10 gm, is used to treat dermatitis and psoriasis, two conditions that produce inflammation (swelling), itching, and redness. It works by inhibiting the release of specific inflammatory molecules in the body that produce swelling, itching, and redness in the skin cells. Normally, these chemicals are released when the skin reacts to allergens.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>If you are allergic to Mometasone furoate or any other medications, please inform your doctor.&nbsp; Before taking Elocon Cream 10 gm, please let your doctor know if you are pregnant or nursing. Children should not take Elocon Cream 10 grams for an extended period of time as it could cause sluggish growth. If your vision changes after using Elocon Cream 10 gm, call your doctor right away. If your skin becomes sensitive or inflamed, stop using Elocon Cream 10 gm and talk to your doctor. Your doctor may periodically assess your progress if you use Elocon Cream 10 gm for psoriasis. Do not resume taking Elocon Cream 10 gm without first visiting your doctor if your condition returns within two weeks of stopping therapy with the medication. If not directed otherwise by your doctor, do not bandage or cover the treated area. Elocon Cream 10 gm shouldn&#39;t be applied to the face or on youngsters for longer than five days. Elocon Cream 10 gm should not be applied to the eyelids or anywhere near the eyes. Use Elocon Cream 10 gm sparingly and not for an extended period of time.</p>','<p>Elocon Cream 10 gm is a member of the corticosteroid drug class used to treat dermatitis and psoriasis, two conditions that produce inflammation (swelling), itching, and redness. Itchy, dry, or swollen skin are symptoms of the common skin ailment dermatitis. Skin cells that multiply more quickly than usual in psoriasis cause white scales and dry, itchy spots on the skin.</p>\n\n<p>Mometasone furoate, a strong corticosteroid found in Elocon Cream 10 gm, prevents the release of specific inflammatory molecules in the body that cause inflammation-related symptoms including redness, itching, and swelling by acting inside skin cells. A normal release of these chemicals occurs as the skin reacts to allergens.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Inflamed hair follicles</li>\n	<li>Acne</li>\n	<li>Thinning of the skin</li>\n	<li>Itching</li>\n	<li>Stinging, tingling or burning sensation</li>\n</ul>','[\"elocon-10gm-cream-170827447296.png\"]','EL10',1,'0','2024-02-18 16:41:55','2025-09-17 12:17:37'),(319,0,'Eltroxin 100 mcg','eltroxin-100-mcg','tablet','eltroxin-100-mcg-170827460192.jpg','ELT100','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>It is crucial to follow your doctor&rsquo;s instructions when taking Eltroxin 100 mcg. Read and adhere to all the guidelines provided on the medication label. Take the medication exactly as prescribed, usually once a day on an empty stomach, at least 30 minutes to 1 hour before breakfast. Swallow the tablet whole with a glass of water and avoid crushing or chewing it.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Treatment of Hypothyroidism: Eltroxin 100 mcg is highly effective in managing hypothyroidism by providing the body with the necessary amount of thyroid hormone. It helps restore the balance of thyroid hormone levels, which is essential for maintaining normal metabolism, energy levels, and overall well-being.</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Improvement of Symptoms: By ensuring an adequate supply of thyroid hormone, Eltroxin 100 mcg can help alleviate the symptoms associated with hypothyroidism. These may include fatigue, weight gain, dry skin, hair loss, cold intolerance, and depression. With proper use, many individuals experience an improvement in their symptoms and a return to their normal daily activities.</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Maintenance of Vital Functions: Thyroid hormone plays a crucial role in regulating various bodily functions, including metabolism, heart rate, digestion, and brain development. Eltroxin 100 mcg helps ensure that these vital functions are adequately supported, promoting overall health and well-being.</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Prevention of Complications: By effectively managing hypothyroidism, Eltroxin 100 mcg can help prevent potential complications associated with the condition. These may include cardiovascular issues, fertility problems, and cognitive impairment. Consistent use of Eltroxin 100 mcg can help minimize the risk of these complications and maintain a healthier life.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before starting Eltroxin 100 mcg, it is important to inform your healthcare provider or pharmacist about any allergies you have, including to levothyroxine or any other substances. Discuss your medical history, especially if you have heart disease, adrenal gland problems, or diabetes, as dosage adjustments may be necessary.</p>\n\n<p>It Is essential to take Eltroxin 100 mcg consistently and not to miss any doses. Inform your healthcare professional if you experience any unusual symptoms or side effects while taking the medication.</p>','<p>Eltroxin 100 mcg, also known as levothyroxine 100 mcg, is a medication that is primarily used to treat hypothyroidism, a condition where the thyroid gland does not produce enough thyroid hormone. Levothyroxine is a synthetic form of the thyroid hormone, which is essential for regulating various bodily functions.</p>\n\n<p>Here Is some important information about Eltroxin 100 mcg:</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>Most individuals tolerate Eltroxin 100 mcg well, and any side effects are generally rare and temporary. However, it is important to be aware of potential side effects and consult your doctor if you have any concerns. Common side effects may include:</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Headache</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Nervousness</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Tremors</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Insomnia</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Increased appetite</p>','[\"eltroxin-100-mcg-170827460192.jpg\"]','ELT100',1,'0','2024-02-18 16:49:00','2025-09-17 12:56:50'),(320,0,'Emeset 4mg','emeset-4mg','tablet','emeset-4mg-170827502047.jpg','EM004','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Take 10 Emeset-4 Tablets exactly as directed. Depending on your health, your doctor will recommend a dosage schedule for Emeset-4 Tablets, 10 per day. A person taking Emeset-4 Tablet 10 frequently has the following side effects: a warm sensation, constipation, headache, diarrhea, headache, drowsiness, and a fatigued feeling. Even so, not everyone who takes Emeset-4 Tablet 10 has its negative side effects, and some of them don&#39;t even call for medical treatment.</p>\n\n<p>As directed by the doctor, it may be taken with or without food. With a glass of water, completely swallow the tablet. Never crush, break, or chew it.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Emeset-4 Tablet 10 is a member of a class of drugs known as anti-emetics that is used to treat nausea and vomiting in adults and kids over the age of four that are brought on by disorders such cancer chemotherapy, radiotherapy, surgery, pregnancy, and motion sicknes