ed proliferation of malignant tissue.</p>\n\n<p>A member of the class of drugs known as &quot;kinase inhibitors,&quot; &quot;erlotinib&quot; is found in Erlocip 150 Tablet 30&#39;s. It functions by preventing the aberrant protein that fuels the growth of malignant cells from doing its job. The spread of malignant cells is stopped in this way.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Stomach pain</li>\n	<li>Bone pain</li>\n	<li>Breathlessness</li>\n	<li>Constipation</li>\n	<li>Cough</li>\n	<li>Diarrhea</li>\n	<li>Loss of appetite</li>\n	<li>Edema (swelling)</li>\n</ul>','[\"erlocip-150mg-170827637216.jpg\"]','ER150',1,'0','2024-02-18 17:13:39','2025-09-18 08:06:05'),(329,0,'Erlonat 100mg','erlonat-100mg','tablet','erlonat-100mg-170827649421.jpg','ER100','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>It is crucial to follow your doctor&rsquo;s instructions and read the medication label carefully before using Erlonat 100mg. Take the medication exactly as prescribed, and do not exceed the recommended dosage or duration of treatment.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Effective treatment for non-small cell lung cancer (NSCLC): Erlonat 100mg has shown significant effectiveness in treating NSCLC, a type of lung cancer that accounts for the majority of lung cancer cases. It works by inhibiting the activity of certain proteins that are responsible for the growth and spread of cancer cells.</p>\n\n<p>Positive outcomes in pancreatic cancer treatment: Erlonat 100mg has also demonstrated promising results in the treatment of pancreatic cancer. It can help slow down the progression of the disease and improve overall survival rates for patients.</p>\n\n<p>Targeted therapy with fewer side effects: Erlonat 100mg belongs to a class of drugs known as targeted therapies. These drugs specifically target cancer cells and interfere with their growth signals, while causing fewer side effects compared to traditional chemotherapy.</p>\n\n<p>Oral administration: Erlonat 100mg is available in oral tablet form, which makes i