mber of the class of medications known as &quot;kinase inhibitors.&quot; It functions by halting the action of an aberrant protein that promotes the division of malignant cells. This stops malignant cells from spreading.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Stomach pain</li>\n	<li>Bone pain</li>\n	<li>Breathlessness</li>\n	<li>Constipation</li>\n	<li>Cough</li>\n	<li>Diarrhea</li>\n	<li>Loss of appetite</li>\n</ul>','[\"erlonat-150mg-170827667013.jpg\"]','ER150',1,'0','2024-02-18 17:20:04','2025-09-18 08:07:08'),(331,0,'Erytop 1% Gel 20gm','erytop-1-gel-20gm','Gel','erytop-1-gel-20gm-170827690139.jpg','ER20','<p>How To Use:</p>\n\n<p>Follow your physician&#39;s instructions when applying ERYTOP GEL, which is intended for external use exclusively. Prior to using, ensure that you wash your hands. Cleanse and dry the entire affected area, then apply a thin layer to the skin where acne lesions are present, using enough to cover the entire affected region. If the gel comes into contact with your eyes, mouth, or nostrils, promptly rinse it off thoroughly with water. The appropriate dosage and duration of treatment will be determined by your doctor, considering factors such as your age, body weight, and medical condition.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Acne Treatment: Erytop Gel contains an active ingredient called clindamycin, which is an antibiotic that helps combat the bacteria responsible for causing acne. It can effectively reduce the number of acne lesions, such as pimples, whiteheads, and blackheads.</li>\n	<li>Anti-Inflammatory Properties: Clindamycin in Erytop Gel also possesses anti-inflammatory properties. It helps reduce the redness, swelling, and inflammation associated with acne, providing relief and improving the appearance of the skin.</li>\n	<li>Prevents Future Breakouts: Erytop Gel not only treats existing acne but also helps prevent new breakouts. By targeting the underlying causes of acne, such as bacteria, it helps maintain clearer skin and reduces the likelihood of future flare-ups.</li>\n	<li>Easy Application: Erytop Gel comes in a convenient gel form, making it easy to apply and spread evenly over the affected skin areas. Its formulation ensures proper absorption and adherence to the skin, maximizing its effectiveness.</li>\n	<li>Suitable for Various Types of Acne: Erytop Gel is commonly prescribed for different types of acne, including mild to moderate acne vulgaris. It can be used on various body areas affected by acne, such as the face, chest, back, and shoulders.</li>\n	<li>Dermatologist Recommended: Erytop Gel is typically prescribed by dermatologists, who specialize in skin health. Being a widely used topical acne treatment, it has been tested and recommended by medical professionals with expertise in treating skin conditions.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Consultation with a Healthcare Professional: Before using Erytop Gel, it is recommended to consult with a healthcare professional, such as a dermatologist. They can evaluate your skin condition, provide a proper diagnosis, and determine if Erytop Gel is suitable for you.</li>\n	<li>External Use Only: Erytop Gel is intended for external use on the skin only. Avoid applying it to sensitive areas such as the eyes, mouth, nostrils, or open wounds. In the event of accidental contact, rinse the affected area with water immediately.</li>\n	<li>Allergies and sensitivities: Inform your healthcare professional about any known allergies or sensitivities you may have, especially to clindamycin or other related medications. They can assess the risks and suggest alternative treatment options if necessary.</li>\n	<li>Avoid Sun Exposure: Erytop Gel can increase your skin&#39;s sensitivity to sunlight. It is advisable to limit sun exposure during treatment and use appropriate sun protection measures, such as wearing protective clothing and applying sunscreen with a high SPF.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>Erytop Gel 20 gm is classified as an antibiotic medication primarily used for the treatment of acne (pimples). Acne occurs when hair follicles become clogged with oil and dead skin cells, resulting in symptoms such as blackheads, pus-filled pimples, and swollen red bumps.</p>\n\n<p>The active ingredient in Erytop Gel 20 gm is &#39;Clindamycin,&#39; which works by inhibiting the synthesis of bacterial proteins, thereby halting bacterial growth. It exhibits a bacteriostatic effect, preventing the multiplication of bacteria.</p>\n\n<p>Erytop Gel 20 gm is intended for external use on the skin. It is important to avoid contact with the eyes, eyelids, lips, and mouth during application. While Erytop Gel 20 gm, like all medicines, may cause side effects, not everyone experiences them. Common side effects include a burning sensation, itching, dryness, redness, oily skin, and skin peeling. Most of these side effects are mild and do not require medical attention, resolving gradually over time. However, if these side effects persist, it is advisable to consult your doctor.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>The common side effects are listed below:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Burning sensation</li>\n	<li>Itching</li>\n	<li>Dryness</li>\n	<li>Redness</li>\n	<li>Oily skin</li>\n</ul>','[\"erytop-1-gel-20gm-170827690139.jpg\"]','ER20',1,'0','2024-02-18 17:22:49','2025-09-18 08:07:43'),(332,0,'Esomeprazole 40mg','esomeprazole-40mg','tablet','esomeprazole-40mg-17082771193.png','ES40','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>You should take this medication by mouth exactly as instructed by your physician, which is often once daily at least an hour before a meal. If you are treating yourself at home, make sure to read and follow all of the instructions on the product packaging. Your current health status and how well you respond to treatment will determine the dosage that you take and how long the treatment will last. Do not use this medication more frequently or at higher doses than the manufacturer recommends. If you have any questions, you should consult with either your physician or your pharmacist.</p>\n\n<p>This drug should not be crushed or chewed in any way. Take the capsules with a full glass of water. If you have trouble swallowing this medication in its entirety, you can open the capsule and sprinkle the contents into one tablespoon of unheated applesauce. This should only be done if you have problems swallowing the capsule whole. Do not chew the apple sauce combination; rather, swallow it as quickly as possible. Do not make the mixture in advance in order to use it at a later time. It&#39;s possible that doing so will ruin the medicine.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Reduction of gastric acid production: Esomeprazole belongs to a class of medications called proton pump inhibitors (PPIs), which work by inhibiting the production of gastric acid in the stomach. By reducing the production of acid, Esomeprazole can help relieve symptoms associated with conditions such as gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD), acid reflux, and peptic ulcers.</p>\n\n<p>Relief of heartburn and acid reflux symptoms: Esomeprazole can provide relief from symptoms such as heartburn, regurgitation, and chest discomfort caused by excessive stomach acid refluxing into the esophagus. By lowering acid levels, Esomeprazole helps reduce the burning sensation and discomfort associated with these conditions</p>\n\n<p>Healing of esophageal damage: Esomeprazole may aid in the healing of esophageal tissue damage caused by chronic acid reflux. It can help reduce inflammation and irritation of the esophagus, allowing the damaged tissue to heal.</p>\n\n<p>Prevention of stomach ulcers: Esomeprazole is also used for the prevention of gastric ulcers associated with nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID) use. It helps reduce the risk of developing ulcers in individuals who require long-term NSAID treatment for conditions such as arthritis.</p>\n\n<p>Treatment of Helicobacter pylori infection: Esomeprazole is often used as part of a combination therapy to eradicate Helicobacter pylori (H. pylori) bacteria, which can cause gastric ulcers and other gastrointestinal issues. By reducing acid production, Esomeprazole creates a less favorable environment for the bacteria to survive, enhancing the effectiveness of antibiotic treatment.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Tell your doctor or pharmacist if you are allergic to esomeprazole, or to other medicines that are similar to it (such as omeprazole or lansoprazole), or if you have any additional allergies before beginning treatment with esomeprazole. This product may contain inactive ingredients, which can cause allergic reactions or other problems. For further information, speak with your pharmacist.</p>\n\n<p>Before beginning treatment with this drug, it is important that you discuss your medical history with your doctor or pharmacist, particularly if you have a history of liver illness or lupus.</p>\n\n<p>There is a possibility that certain symptoms are actually indicators of a more serious disease. You should seek immediate medical attention if you are experiencing any of the following symptoms: heartburn that is accompanied by lightheadedness, sweating, or dizziness; chest, jaw, arm, or shoulder discomfort; unexpected shortness of breath; or unexplained weight loss.</p>\n\n<p>In addition, before you self-treat with this medication, get medical help right away if you have any of these signs of a serious condition: trouble/pain swallowing food, bloody vomit, vomit that looks like coffee grounds, bloody/black stools, heartburn for over 3 months, frequent chest pain, frequent wheezing (especially with heartburn), nausea/vomiting, stomach pain.</p>','<p>Esomeprazole is used to treat a variety of conditions that affect the stomach and the esophagus, including ulcers and acid reflux. It accomplishes this by lowering the amount of acid that is produced by your stomach. Heartburn, difficulty swallowing, and cough are just few of the symptoms that can be alleviated. This medicine assists in the healing of acid damage to the esophagus and stomach, assists in the prevention of ulcers, and may assist in the prevention of esophageal cancer. Esomeprazole is a member of the proton pump inhibitor (PPI) medication class. PPI stands for &quot;proton pump inhibitor.&quot;</p>\n\n<p>If you are treating your heartburn on your own with this medication, you can utilize over-the-counter esomeprazole medications to treat frequent heartburn, which is defined as heartburn that occurs two or more times per week. These treatments do not immediately alleviate heartburn because it could take anywhere from one to four days for them to have their full impact.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<p>There may be headaches or abdominal discomfort. If any of these side effects persist or worsen, consult your doctor or pharmacist immediately.n</p>\n\n<p>Remember that your doctor prescribed this medication because he or she has judged that the benefit to you justifies the risk of adverse effects. Numerous users of this medication do not experience severe adverse effects.</p>','[\"esomeprazole-40mg-17082771193.png\"]','ES40',1,'0','2024-02-18 17:25:29','2025-09-18 08:08:46'),(333,0,'Esperal 250mg','esperal-250mg','tablet','esperal-250mg-170827728475.jpg','ES250','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>In order to prevent stomach discomfort and for optimal benefits, Esperal Tablet 10&#39;s should be taken as directed by your doctor, with or without food, at regular intervals throughout the day. Esperal Tablet 10 side effects include drowsiness, fatigue, headache, acne, flushing (warmth, redness, or tingly feeling), sweating, increased thirst, swelling, rapid weight gain, nausea, severe vomiting, neck pain, throbbing headache, blurred vision, fast or pounding heartbeats or fluttering in your chest, confusion, weakness, spinning sensation, feeling unsteady, or and metallic/garlic-like taste in your mouth may occur as your body gets used to The negative effects listed above don&#39;t necessarily apply to everyone. Consult a doctor if you have any significant discomfort after taking Esperal Tablets 10s.</p>\n\n<p>Never break, crush, or chew it; instead, swallow it whole with water.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Disulfiram, a component of the anti-alcohol drug Antabuse, is a component of Esperal Tablets 10 and is used to treat alcoholism. It functions by preventing an enzyme (acetaldehyde) that aids in the body&#39;s breakdown of alcohol. Esperal Tablets 10 assist alcoholics who have made the decision to give up drinking by preventing them from resuming their previous behavior.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Let your doctor know about all of your health issues, sensitivities, and medications you are taking before using the Esperal Tablet 10&#39;s. The following symptoms of an Esperal Tablet 10 overdose include feeling or being sick, stomach pain, diarrhea, drowsiness, mental disorders, fatigue, rapid heartbeat, rapid breathing, high body temperature, low blood pressure, loss of muscle control, high blood sugar, and changes in the blood (as seen in blood tests). Disulfiram tablets and alcohol can react negatively to several foods, liquid medications, cures, tonics, cosmetics, perfumes, and sprays. To prevent a &quot;aldehyde reaction,&quot; stay away from alcohol-containing medications, mouthwash, hand soap, and alcoholic beverages.</p>','<p>Esperal Tablets 10 are part of the Antabuse drug class, which is used to treat chronic alcoholism or alcohol dependence. Heavy alcohol consumption over an extended period of time can lead to addiction, which alters the way your brain functions. Long-term alcohol usage can seriously harm your liver and lead to fatty liver syndrome or liver cirrhosis.</p>\n\n<p>Disulfiram, an ingredient in Esperal Tablets 10 works by inhibiting an enzyme that breaks down alcohol in our bodies. Esperal Tablets 10 prevent the enzyme that converts alcohol into acetaldehyde, which is what happens when a patient drinks alcohol. Since there is more acetaldehyde in the blood as a result, pain and bodily reactions follow. Esperal Tablet 10s can assist alcoholics who have made the decision to stop drinking by discouraging them from doing so. As a result, it supports the treatment of alcoholism.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Drowsiness</li>\n	<li>Tiredness</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Acne</li>\n	<li>Metallic/garlic-like taste in the mouth</li>\n</ul>','[\"esperal-250mg-170827728475.jpg\"]','ES250',1,'0','2024-02-18 17:28:48','2025-09-18 08:09:48'),(334,0,'Evalon 15 gm','evalon-15-gm','tablet','evalon-15-gm-170832392982.jpg','EV15','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>To ensure optimal results, it is recommended to follow the instructions provided by your healthcare provider or pharmacist when using this product. It is important to read and adhere to all the instructions on the medication label. By using the medication as directed, you can maximize its effectiveness and safety.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Hormonal balance: Evalon 15 gm helps restore hormonal balance in women. It can be particularly beneficial during menopause or in cases where there is a deficiency of estrogen. By supplementing the body with estradiol, this cream helps alleviate symptoms associated with hormonal imbalances, such as hot flashes, night sweats, mood swings, and vaginal dryness.</p>\n\n<p>Vaginal health: Evalon 15 gm is primarily used for the treatment of vaginal atrophy, a condition characterized by the thinning, dryness, and inflammation of the vaginal walls. By applying the cream directly to the affected area, it helps to moisturize and rejuvenate the vaginal tissues. This can lead to increased comfort, reduced itching, and a decrease in painful intercourse.</p>\n\n<p>Preventing osteoporosis: Estradiol, the active ingredient in Evalon 15 gm, has been shown to have a protective effect on bone health. By supplementing the body with estrogen, this cream may help reduce the risk of osteoporosis, a condition characterized by weakened and brittle bones.</p>\n\n<p>Skin health: The application of Evalon 15 gm to the skin can have positive effects on its health and appearance. Estradiol helps to improve skin elasticity, reduce wrinkles, and promote a more youthful appearance. It can also aid in the healing of certain skin conditions.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before using Evalon 15 gm, it is important to consult with your healthcare provider or pharmacist. They can provide personalized advice based on your medical history and current health condition. It is particularly crucial to discuss any allergies you may have, as well as any medications or supplements you are currently taking.</p>','<p>Evalon 15 gm is a topical cream that offers several positive effects for women&rsquo;s health. It contains the active ingredient estradiol, which is a form of estrogen. This hormone plays a crucial role in maintaining the health and well-being of the female reproductive system.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>While side effects are possible with any medication, they are generally rare with Evalon 15 gm when used as directed. However, it is still important to be aware of potential side effects and contact your healthcare provider if you experience any unusual or bothersome symptoms. Some possible side effects may include mild skin irritation or redness at the application site. These effects are usually temporary and subside as your body adjusts to the medication.</p>\n\n<p>Remember to follow your healthcare provider&rsquo;s instructions and use Evalon 15 gm as prescribed. If you have any concerns or questions, do not hesitate to reach out to your healthcare provider for further guidance.</p>','[\"evalon-15-gm-170832392982.jpg\"]','EV15',1,'0','2024-02-19 06:25:37','2025-07-20 16:22:13'),(335,0,'Extra Super M Force','extra-super-m-force','tablet','extra-super-m-force-170832411180.jpg','EX','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>It is important to follow the instructions provided by your doctor or