sh it. Although the Ezedoc 10 Tablet can be taken any way, it is best to take it at a set time.</p>\n\n<p>Workings of Ezedoc Tablet</p>\n\n<p>An inhibitor of cholesterol absorption is Ezedoc 10 Tablet. It lowers blood levels of total cholesterol and &quot;bad&quot; cholesterol (LDL) by reducing the absorption of cholesterol from the gut.</p>\n\n<p>Advantages of the Ezedoc Tablet</p>\n\n<p>elevated cholesterol</p>\n\n<p>The elevated cholesterol levels in your body are successfully lowered by Ezedoc 10 Tablet. Lowering your cholesterol lowers your risk of developing heart disease and prolongs your lifespan. To get the most out of this medication, take it frequently and adopt the right lifestyle habits (such eating well and exercising regularly). Even if you feel good, keep taking it.</p>\n\n<p>Ezedoc Tablet side effects</p>\n\n<p>The majority of adverse effects are temporary and go away as your body becomes used to the medication. If they persist or you&#39;re concerned about them, speak with your doctor.</p>','<p>A medication called Ezedoc 10 Tablet is used to treat high cholesterol. This medication works by bringing down blood levels of &quot;bad&quot; cholesterol (LDL). A fatty substance called cholesterol causes your blood vessels to narrow as it accumulates, which can result in a heart attack or stroke.</p>\n\n<p>The doctor&#39;s recommended dose and duration for taking Ezedoc 10 Tablet should be followed. Although you can take it whenever you like, try to take it every day at the same time. Most people with high cholesterol don&#39;t have any symptoms, but your condition could worsen if you stop taking this medication. Your risk of heart disease and stroke may rise as a result, and your cholesterol levels may start to rise once more.</p>\n\n<p>It&#39;s critical to regularly monitor your cholesterol levels. This medication is just one element of a therapy plan that should also include a balanced diet, frequent exercise, quitting smoking, drinking alcohol in moderation, and weight loss. While taking this medication, you can eat normally, but try to stay away from meals that are high in fat.</p>\n\n<p>Joint discomfort and diarrhoea are two of this medication&#39;s frequent side effects. It is best to inform your doctor about all other medications you have been prescribed before taking this one. If you have a kidney or liver condition, you should use this medication with caution. Additionally, without first seeing a doctor, pregnant women and nursing moms should avoid using this medication.</p>','<p>Ezedoc common side effects</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; diarrhoea Joint discomfort</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Infection of the upper respiratory tract and sinuses</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Acute extremities pain</li>\n</ul>','[\"ezedoc-10mg-170832457194.jpg\"]','EZ10',1,'0','2024-02-19 06:37:36','2025-09-18 08:11:01'),(339,0,'Famocid 20mg','famocid-20mg','Tablet','famocid-20mg-170832473916.jpg','FA20','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Famocid 20 Tablet is also frequently prescribed to prevent gastric ulcers and heartburn brought on by the use of analgesics. It must be taken with a full glass of water before or after a meal. The medication must be consumed according to the doctor-recommended dosage and duration. This medication should alleviate reflux and indigestion within a few hours. If the symptoms persist or worsen after 14 days of treatment, you should immediately consult a physician. This medication is not recommended for patients with severe gastrointestinal disease. You can improve the effectiveness of your medication by consuming smaller meals more frequently and avoiding spicy or oily foods.</p>\n\n<p>Take this medication according to your doctor&#39;s prescribed dosage and duration. Swallow the pill whole. Not to be chewed, crushed, or broken. The Famocid 20 Tablet should be consumed with sustenance.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Acid reflux and heartburn relief: Famocid 20mg is commonly used to relieve symptoms of acid reflux and heartburn. It works by reducing the production of stomach acid, which can help alleviate the burning sensation, discomfort, and regurgitation associated with these conditions.</p>\n\n<p>Peptic ulcer treatment: Famocid 20mg is also used in the treatment of peptic ulcers, which are open sores that develop in the lining of the stomach or the upper part of the small intestine. By reducing stomach acid production, famotidine helps promote the healing of ulcers and prevents their recurrence.</p>\n\n<p>Gastric protection during NSAID use: Nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs) can sometimes cause irritation and damage to the stomach lining, leading to conditions such as gastritis or ulcers. Famocid 20mg can be used as a preventive measure to protect the stomach and reduce the risk of NSAID-induced gastric complications in individuals who require long-term NSAID therapy.</p>\n\n<p>Zollinger-Ellison syndrome: Famocid 20mg may be prescribed for individuals with Zollinger-Ellison syndrome, a rare condition characterized by the overproduction of stomach acid. By reducing acid secretion, famotidine can help manage the symptoms associated with this syndrome, such as abdominal pain, heartburn, and diarrhea.</p>\n\n<p>Reduced risk of gastrointestinal bleeding: By decreasing stomach acid production, Famocid 20mg can help reduce the risk of gastrointestinal bleeding in individuals who are at higher risk, such as those with a history of ulcers or certain medical conditions that predispose them to bleeding.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Allergies: Inform your healthcare provider if you have any known allergies to famotidine or any other components of Famocid 20mg. Allergic reactions can range from mild to severe, and it&#39;s essential to avoid medications that may trigger an allergic response.</p>\n\n<p>Kidney and liver function: Famocid is primarily eliminated from the body through the kidneys. If you have impaired kidney function, your healthcare provider may need to adjust the dosage of Famocid 20mg to prevent the accumulation of the medication in your body. Similarly, individuals with severe liver disease may require dosage adjustments as famotidine metabolism may be affected.</p>\n\n<p>Medication interactions: Inform your healthcare provider about all the medications you are currently taking, including prescription drugs, over-the-counter medications, and herbal supplements. Some medications may interact with Famocid 20mg, potentially reducing its effectiveness or increasing the risk of side effects. It&#39;s particularly important to mention medications such as antacids, H2 blockers, and proton pump inhibitors to avoid any potential interactions.</p>\n\n<p>Ongoing medical conditions: If you have any other underlying medical conditions, such as stomach cancer, gastrointestinal bleeding, or impaired immune function, discuss it with your healthcare provider before taking Famocid 20mg. They can assess the risks and benefits of the medication in relation to your specific condition.</p>','<p>Famocid 20 Tablet is a proton pump inhibitor. It reduces the quantity of stomach acid produced. It is used to treat and prevent acid reflux, indigestion, and other symptoms caused by excess gastric acid. Additionally, it is utilized to treat and prevent gastric ulcers, reflux disease, and a few other uncommon conditions.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n	<li>Diarrhea</li>\n	<li>Constipation</li>\n</ul>','[\"famocid-20mg-170832473916.jpg\"]','FA20',1,'0','2024-02-19 06:39:50','2025-09-18 08:15:12'),(340,0,'Famocid 40mg','famocid-40mg','tablet','famocid-40mg-170832483675.jpg','FA40','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>The prescribed dose and duration for taking Famocid 40 Tablet 14 must be followed. You may experience migraines, vertigo, constipation, and diarrhea on occasion. The majority of these unwanted effects of Famocid 40 Tablet 14&#39;s do not necessitate medical attention and subside with time. However, if the adverse effects persist, seek medical attention.</p>\n\n<p>Do not pulverize, break, or chew it; simply swallow it whole with water.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Famocid 40 Tablet 14&#39;s is a member of the class of drugs known as H2 receptor antagonists. Histamine stimulates the production of acid by binding to H2 receptors present in the parietal cells of the stomach. Famocid 40 Tablet 14&#39;s bind to these receptors and inhibit the action of histamine. Additionally, it reduces gastric secretion. Additionally, it decreases the amount of gastric secretion stimulated by food, caffeine, insulin, and pentagastrin. Caffeine, insulin (used to treat diabetes), and pentagastrin (a synthetic medication used to diagnose thyroid cancer) all stimulate gastric acid secretion.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Allergies: Inform your healthcare provider if you have any known allergies to famotidine or any other components of Famocid 40mg. Allergic reactions can range from mild to severe, and it&#39;s essential to avoid medications that may trigger an allergic response.</p>\n\n<p>Kidney and liver function: Famocid is primarily eliminated from the body through the kidneys. If you have impaired kidney function, your healthcare provider may need to adjust the dosage of Famocid 40mg to prevent the accumulation of the medication in your body. Similarly, individuals with severe liver disease may require dosage adjustments as famotidine metabolism may be affected.</p>\n\n<p>Medication interactions: Inform your healthcare provider about all the medications you are currently taking, including prescription drugs, over-the-counter medications, and herbal supplements. Some medications may interact with Famocid 40mg, potentially reducing its effectiveness or increasing the risk of side effects. It&#39;s particularly important to mention medications such as antacids, H2 blockers, and proton pump inhibitors to avoid any potential interactions.</p>\n\n<p>Ongoing medical conditions: If you have any other underlying medical conditions, such as stomach cancer, gastrointestinal bleeding, or impaired immune function, discuss it with your healthcare provider before taking Famocid 40mg. They can assess the risks and benefits of the medication in relation to your specific condition.</p>','<p>Famocid 40 Tablet 14 is a member of the class of drugs known as H2-receptor antagonists, which reduce acid secretion in the stomach. It is used for the treatment of stomach ulcers (gastric and duodenal ulcers), reflux oesophagitis, and Zollinger-Ellison syndrome. Ulcers of the stomach are painful sores on the interior lining of the stomach. The inflammation of the oesophagus (food conduit) caused by the reflux of stomach contents into the oesophagus is known as reflux esophagitis. Zollinger-Ellison syndrome is a condition in which the pancreas (which generates digestive enzymes) and duodenum (a portion of the small intestine) tumours increase stomach acids.</p>\n\n<p>Famocid 40 Tablet 14&#39;s contain the antacid &#39;Famotidine&#39;. It inhibits the H2-receptors present on the cells of the stomach. It decreases gastric acid production and gastric secretion volume. Due to the fact that excess acid can cause inflammation of the oesophagus, stomach, and intestine, a decrease in acid secretion improves the symptoms and condition.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n	<li>Constipation</li>\n	<li>Diarrhoea</li>\n</ul>','[\"famocid-40mg-170832483675.jpg\"]','FA40',1,'0','2024-02-19 06:41:20','2025-09-18 08:17:15'),(341,0,'Farobact 200mg','farobact-200mg','tablet','farobact-200mg-170832494027.jpg','FA200','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Take six Farobact 200 Tablets according to your doctor&#39;s instructions. Based on your medical condition, your doctor will advise you on how frequently to take your medication. In certain instances, you may experience nausea, diarrhea, stomach discomfort, and a rash. The majority of these adver