ract, respiratory tract, skin, ears, nasal, and gynecological tract. Bacterial infection is a condition in which pathogenic bacteria multiply and induce infection within the body. It can rapidly proliferate and can infect any part of the body.</p>\n\n<p>Farobact 200 Tablet 6&#39;s contain Faropenem, an antibiotic that destroys bacteria (bactericidal) by inhibiting the formation of the bacterial cell wall (a necessary covering for bacterial survival).</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Diarrhoea</li>\n	<li>Stomach pain</li>\n	<li>Rash</li>\n</ul>','[\"farobact-200mg-170832494027.jpg\"]','FA200',1,'0','2024-02-19 06:43:01','2025-09-18 11:35:11'),(342,0,'Farobact ER 300mg','farobact-er-300mg','tablet','farobact-er-300mg-170832508022.jpg','FA300','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>As prescribed, take six Farobact 300 ER tablets. Depending on your medical condition, your physician will advise you on how frequently to take your medications. Occasionally, you may experience nausea, diarrhea, stomach discomfort, and rash. The majority of these unwanted effects of Farobact 300 ER Tablet 6s do not necessitate medical attention and subside with time. Please consult your physician if side effects persist or worsen.</p>\n\n<p>Take 6s Farobact 300 ER tablets with or without sustenance, as directed by your doctor. With a glass of water, ingest the pill whole. Avoid crushing, chewing, and breaking.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Farobact 300 ER Tablet 6&#39;s are a broad-spectrum antibiotic that is effective against aerobic (grow in the presence of oxygen) and anaerobic (grow in the absence of oxygen) gram-negative and gram-positive bacteria. Farobact 300 ER Tablet 6&#39;s are used to treat a variety of bacterial infections of the urinary tract, respiratory tract, skin, ears, nasal, and gynecology. Farobact 300 ER Tablet 6s inhibits the formation of the bacterial cell wall (a required protective covering) that is essential for their survival. Kills microorganisms as a