ctor.</p>','<p>Femilon Tablet is a combination of two medications used to treat irregular periods and as a method of contraception (to prevent conception). It aids in stopping the egg from being released and the sperm from fertilising it. Additionally, it might aid in lowering the risk of ovarian cancer.</p>\n\n<p>You can take Femilon Tablet with or without food, but for maximum effect, take it at the same time each day. You should take it as prescribed by your doctor. You must start taking the pill on the first day of your menstrual cycle and keep doing so for the entire month. Start a fresh pack once the last one is finished. Take another tablet if you vomit within four hours after taking the dose. Use a condom during sexual activity for two days if you missed your dose and you were more than 12 hours late taking the missed dose.</p>\n\n<p>Some of the negative effects of this medication that are frequently observed are nausea, headaches, breast soreness, and weight gain. Tell your doctor if these concern you or seem serious. There might be techniques to lessen or stop them. You can encounter spotting, bleeding, or skipped periods in between menstrual intervals. If this happens regularly or lasts a long time, talk to your doctor. If you experience chest discomfort, shortness of breath, limb pain, vision problems, or any other symptoms that could indicate a blood clot, call your doctor right once.</p>\n\n<p>Inform your doctor before using this medication if you smoke, are over 35, have ever had a heart attack, have uterine/cervix cancer, or have vaginal cancer. Your other medications should be disclosed to your doctor as many of them may reduce or alter the effectiveness of this medication. If you are currently breastfeeding or pregnant, avoid using the medication. While receiving therapy, you could be required to undergo routine checks of your blood pressure, cholesterol, and blood sugar levels.</p>','<p>Femilon common side effects</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Nausea</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; abdominal pain</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Headache</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; uncontrollable uterine bleeding</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; gaining weight</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Breast ache</li>\n</ul>','[\"femilon-0-170832559663.jpg\"]','FE0205',1,'0','2024-02-19 06:54:27','2025-09-18 11:45:46'),(345,0,'Fenered 1mg','fenered-1mg','tablet','fenered-1mg-170832572692.jpg','FE001','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>It is important to follow your doctor&rsquo;s instructions and the directions on the medication label when taking Fenered 1mg. Typically, it is taken orally once a day, with or without food. Consistency is key, so it is recommended to take it at the same time each day to maintain steady levels of the medication in your body.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Fenered 1mg offers several benefits for individuals experiencing hair loss:</p>\n\n<p>Hair loss prevention: Fenered 1mg is effective in slowing down and even halting the progression of male pattern baldness. By inhibiting the production of DHT, it helps to maintain existing hair and prevent further hair loss.</p>\n\n<p>Hair regrowth: In addition to preventing hair loss, Fenered 1mg has been shown to promote hair regrowth in some men. It can stimulate the regrowth of hair follicles that have become miniaturized due to the effects of DHT.</p>\n\n<p>Convenient and easy to use: Fenered 1mg comes in a tablet form, making it simple to incorporate into your daily routine. It does not require any topical application or complex procedures, offering a hassle-free solution for hair loss treatment.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before starting Fenered 1mg, it is important to consult with your healthcare provider and inform them about any pre-existing medical conditions, allergies, or medications you are currently taking. This will help ensure the medication is suitable for you and minimize the risk of any potential complications.</p>','<p>Fenered 1mg is a medication that is commonly prescribed for the treatment of hair loss in men. It contains finasteride, which is the active ingredient responsible for its beneficial effects. Finasteride works by inhibiting the conversion of testosterone into dihydrotestosterone (DHT), a hormone that plays a key role in the development of male pattern baldness.</p>\n\n<p>Here Is some important information about Fenered 1mg:</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>Fenered 1mg is generally well-tolerated, and most men experience no or minimal side effects. However, it is important to be aware of potential side effects, which may include:</p>\n\n<p>Sensual side effects: In rare cases, some individuals may experience decreased libido, impotence, or changes in ejaculation. These side effects are generally reversible upon discontinuation of the medication.</p>\n\n<p>Other potential side effects: Some individuals may experience mild symptoms such as headache, dizziness, or rash. These side effects are usually temporary and resolve on their own.</p>\n\n<p>It Is important to note that the majority of men taking Fenered 1mg do not experience any significant side effects. If you have any concerns or questions about the medication, it Is always best to consult with your doctor.</p>','[\"fenered-1mg-170832572692.jpg\"]','FE001',1,'0','2024-02-19 06:57:13','2025-09-18 11:46:21'),(346,0,'Fenolip  145 mg','fenolip-145-mg','tablet','fenolip-145-mg-170832608085.jpg','FE145','<p>Fenolip common side effects</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; elevated liver enzyme levels</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Nausea</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Vomiting Gastric Discomfort</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Continent pain</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Diarrhea</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Headache</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; back ache</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Increased blood levels of creatine phosphokinase (CPK) Nasal inflammation</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>A medication called Fenolip 145 Tablet is used to treat high cholesterol