althcare provider or pharmacist about any allergies you have, including to trimetazidine or any other medications. Additionally, disclose your complete medical history, including any pre-existing heart conditions or other relevant health issues.</p>','<p>Flavedon 35mg is a medication that is used to treat certain heart conditions and improve cardiovascular health. It contains the active ingredient known as trimetazidine, which helps to improve the functioning of the heart muscle by increasing its efficiency in utilizing oxygen. Angina is a type of chest pain or discomfort that develops when a portion of your heart does not receive enough oxygen-rich blood. When the heart&rsquo;s blood arteries narrow, this can happen. The blood arteries are relaxed by Flavedon MR Tablet, allowing blood to flow more freely and ensuring that your heart receives enough oxygen. You are less prone to experience angina-related chest pain as a result of this. By lessening the frequency of angina attacks, Flavedon MR Tablet can also help you be more active and navigate daily life more easily. For it to be successful, you must take it consistently for the full duration of the recommended dosage.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>Flavedon 35mg is generally well-tolerated, and most people do not experience any significant side effects. However, as with any medication, there is a possibility of side effects. If you have any concerns, it is best to discuss them with your doctor. Some possible side effects may include:</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Gastrointestinal symptoms</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Allergic reactions</p>\n\n<p>Remember to consult your healthcare professional for personalized advice and guidance regarding the use of Flavedon 35mg. They can provide you with detailed information and address any specific concerns you may have.</p>','[\"flavedon-35mg-170849230461.jpg\"]','FL035',1,'0','2024-02-21 05:12:48','2025-09-18 11:52:59'),(358,0,'Flavocip 200mg','flavocip-200mg','tablet','flavocip-2