hes, sweating, and jitteriness. By consuming lots of water, the side effects may be prevented. It is advisable to wait until you know how it affects you before driving or performing any other tasks that call for concentration. It may also make you feel lightheaded or tired. Consult a doctor right away if any adverse effects disturb you or continue.</p>\n\n<p>If you are taking any medicine for a medical condition, let your doctor know before starting the treatment. Before receiving therapy, let your doctor know if you are breastfeeding or pregnant. Patients with glaucoma, a condition marked by elevated eye pressure, should take special precautions throughout therapy and should let their doctor know before starting it.</p>','<p>Common Flavocip side effects</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Nausea</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Vomiting</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; mouth feeling parched</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Headache</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Drowsiness</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Dizziness</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; distorted vision</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Nervousness</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Sweating</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','[\"flavocip-200mg-170849244070.jpg\"]','FL200',1,'0','2024-02-21 05:16:10','2025-09-18 11:53:29'),(359,0,'Flexura  400mg','flexura-400mg','tablet','flexura-400mg-170849261797.jpg','FL400','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>To ensure the safe and effective use of Flexura 400mg, it is essential to follow your doctor&rsquo;s instructions and read the information provided on the medication label. Take the medication exactly as prescribed, and avoid exceeding the recommended dosage or using it for an extended period without medical advice.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Flexura 400mg offers several benefits in the treatment of muscle spasms and related conditions:</p>\n\n<p>Muscle spasm relief: Flexura 400mg effectively relaxes muscles and relieves muscle spasms, providing significant relief from discomfort and pain.</p>\n\n<p>Improved muscle function: By relaxing muscles, Flexura 400mg helps restore normal muscle function, allowing for improved mobility and range of motion.</p>\n\n<p>Enhanced quality of life: With its ability to alleviate muscle spasms, Flexura 400mg can significantly enhance your overall quality of life by reducing pain and discomfort associated with musculoskeletal conditions.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before taking Flexura 400mg, it is important to inform your healthcare provider or pharmacist about any allergies you have, including allergies to metaxalone or any other substances. This will help ensure your safety and prevent any potential allergic reactions.</p>\n\n<p>Additionally, discuss your medical history with your healthcare professional, especially if you have any liver or kidney problems. It is important to disclose this information to determine if Flexura 400mg is suitable for you or if any adjustments to the dosage are necessary.</p>','<p>Flexura 400mg is a medication that provides relief from muscle spasms and helps improve muscle function. It contains the active ingredient called metaxalone, which belongs to a class of drugs known as muscle relaxants. Flexura 400mg is primarily used to alleviate discomfort and pain caused by acute musculoskeletal conditions.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Here is some important information about Flexura 400mg:</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>Flexura 400mg is generally well-tolerated, and most individuals experience minimal side effects, if any. However, like any medication, it is important to be aware of potential side effects. Common side effects associated with Flexura 400mg may include:</p>\n\n<p>Drowsiness: Some individuals may experience mild drowsiness, which is generally temporary and subsides as your body adjusts to the medication.</p>\n\n<p>Dizziness: In some cases, dizziness may occur. It is advisable to avoid activities that require mental alertness or coordination until you know how your body responds to the medication.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','[\"flexura-400mg-170849261797.jpg\"]','FL400',1,'0','2024-02-21 05:18:17','2025-09-18 11:54:10'),(360,0,'Flixotide Discus 250 mcg','flixotide-discus-250-mcg','tablet','flixotide-discus-250-mcg-170849295391.jpg','FL250','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Take this medication consistently for the best results, even when asymptomatic.</li>\n	<li>Take this medication as your doctor has advised. It is often advised to use this twice daily.</li>\n	<li>After each usage, rinse your mouth with warm water to avoid throat and mouth infections. Negative side effects like mouth thrush will be avoided.</li>\n	<li>Wipe the inhaler&#39;s mouthpiece as directed at least once a week.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Asthma control: Flixotide Discus helps control and manage asthma symptoms in individuals with persistent asthma. It is an inhaled corticosteroid that reduces inflammation in the airways, helping to prevent and relieve symptoms such as wheezing, shortness of breath, chest tightness, and coughing.</p>\n\n<p>Long-term management: Flixotide Discus is intended for long-term use to maintain asthma control. By reducing airway inflammation, it helps to prevent asthma exacerbations and improve overall respiratory function.</p>\n\n<p>Prevention of asthma attacks: Regular use of Flixotide Discus can help prevent asthma attacks by reducing the sensitivity of the airways to triggers such as allergens, exercise, or cold air. It helps to keep the airways open and reduces the likelihood of sudden asthma symptoms.</p>\n\n<p>Improved lung function: By reducing airway inflammation, Flixotide Discus can improve lung function and increase airflow in individuals with asthma. This can lead to better exercise tolerance and overall respiratory health.</p>\n\n<p>Reducing reliance on rescue medications: With proper use of Flixotide Discus, individuals may experience a decreased need for rescue inhalers or other quick-relief medications. This indicates improved asthma control and a reduced risk of asthma exacerbations.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Proper usage: Follow the instructions provided with the inhaler carefully to ensure proper administration of Flixotide Discus. Be familiar with the correct inhalation technique to maximize the effectiveness of the medication.</p>\n\n<p>Regular use: Flixotide Discus is intended for long-term use and should be used consistently as prescribed by your healthcare professional. Do not discontinue or adjust the dosage without consulting your healthcare professional.</p>\n\n<p>Underlying medical conditions: Inform your healthcare professional about any other medical conditions you may have, especially if you have a history of tuberculosis, fungal, or viral infections. They can assess whether Flixotide Discus is suitable for you or if any additional precautions are necessary.</p>\n\n<p>Interactions with other medications: Inform your healthcare professional about all the medications you are currently taking, including prescription and over-the-counter drugs, as well as any herbal supplements. Some medications may interact with Flixotide Discus, so it&#39;s important to disclose this information.</p>','<p>The main component of Flixotide Diskus 250 mcg, fluticasone propionate, relieves and prevents asthma symptoms and attacks.</p>\n\n<p>Asthma is a chronic condition in which inflammation and muscle tension cause the airways in the lungs to narrow. Additional mucus may be produced.</p>\n\n<p>It may cause coughing, wheezing, and shortness of breath as well as make breathing challenging.</p>\n\n<p>Additionally useful for treating Chronic Obstructive Pulmonary Disease (COPD), fluticasone propionate</p>\n\n<p>COPD is a lung condition that impairs breathing by obstructing airflow.</p>\n\n<p>For the treatment of COPD, Flixotide Diskus - 250 mcg is also advised in addition to long-acting bronchodilators (such as long-acting beta-agonists).</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Hoarseness of voice</li>\n	<li>Bruising</li>\n	<li>Swelling of face, mouth, lips, limbs, etc</li>\n	<li>Feeling Faint and lightheadedness</li>\n	<li>Bone Degradation</li>\n</ul>','[\"flixotide-discus-250-mcg-170849295391.jpg\"]','FL250',1,'0','2024-02-21 05:23:45','2025-09-18 11:56:15'),(361,0,'Flomist Nasal Spray 50 mcg 100 metered doses','flomist-nasal-spray-50-mcg-100-metered-doses','Nasal Spray','flomist-nasal-spray-50-mcg-100-metered-doses-170849308269.jpg','FL50','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Only with a prescription is 10 ml of Flomist Nasal Spray accessible. To receive the most advantage from Flomist Nasal Spray 10 ml, it must be used in accordance with the healthcare professional&#39;s instructions or the instructions on the leaflet. Very little of the medication in Flomist Nasal Spray 10 ml is absorbed into the body, thus it is unlikely to have any negative side effects. A few uncommon side effects include coughing, burning, itching, nosebleeds, headaches, nausea, vomiting, sore throat, and nosebleeds. The majority of these Flomist Nasal Spray 10 ml adverse effects go away over time without the need for medical intervention. However, please see a doctor if the adverse effects worsen or persist.</p>\n\n<p>Close one nostril while inserting the bottle&#39;s tip into the other, then spray in the direction of the nostril&#39;s sides. Straighten your back and take slow, deep breaths. For the second nostril, follow the same procedure.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Fluticasone is an ingredient in Flomist Nasal Spray 10 ml. Fluticasone functions by preventing the body&#39;s release of specific molecules that trigger inflammatory responses. As a result, symptoms including a runny or blocked nose, sneezing, itching, watery eyes, and an itchy nose are alleviated.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>In case you experience an allergic or hypersensitive reaction to fluticasone or any other medication, let your doctor know right away. If you are a woman who is pregnant or breastfeeding, avoid using Flomist Nasal Spray 10 ml without first visiting a doctor. A prescription will only be given if the advantages outweigh the dangers. Patients who recently had surgery, trauma, or nasal ulcers should refrain from using this medicine. Fluticasone nasal spray use has been linked to the emergence of eye diseases such cataracts and glaucoma. To screen for these diseases, you should get an annual eye checkup. Tell your doctor if you have ever had treatment for a fungal, bacterial, viral, or parasitic illness before using Flomist Nasal Spray 10 ml. Additionally, let your physician know if you have tuberculosis, a form of lung infection. The effectiveness and safety in children under the age of four have not been sufficiently demonstrated. Under the guidance of a medical practitioner, kids as old as four years old can take Flomist Nasal Spray 10 ml.</p>','<p>The corticosteroid drug class includes Flomist Nasal Spray 10 ml. It is prescribed for adult and pediatric patients four years of age and older to treat the nasal symptoms of seasonal, perennial, allergic, and non-allergic rhinitis. Exposure to airborne chemicals (like pollens) that are only present during particular seasons of the year causes seasonal allergies. Year-round indoor exposure to airborne contaminants (such house dust) is the main cause of perennial allergies. Vasomotor rhinitis, often referred to as perennial non-allergic rhinitis, is a chronic condition marked by symptoms that are similar to allergic rhinitis (runny nose, stuffy nose, sneezing, and nasal itching), but that endure for more than nine months each year.</p>\n\n<p>Fluticasone is an ingredient in Flomist Nasal Spray 10 ml. Fluticasone functions by preventing the body&#39;s release of specific molecules that trigger inflammatory responses. As a result, it relieves symptoms such as a runny or blocked nose, sneezing, itching, watery eyes, and an itchy nose.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Sore Throat</li>\n	<li>Nose Bleeds</li>\n	<li>Trouble Breathing</li>\n</ul>','[\"flomist-nasal-spray-50-mcg-100-metered-doses-170849308269.jpg\"]','FL50',1,'0','2024-02-21 05:26:04','2025-09-18 11:57:22'),(362,0,'Fluka 150 mg','fluka-150-mg','tablet','fluka-150-mg-170849322568.jpg','FL150','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Take this medication exactly as your doctor has advised. Fluka 150 Tablet 1s commonly cause adverse symptoms such as headache, diarrhoea, nausea, upset stomach, dizziness, and changing food tastes. These adverse effects differ from person to person and are not universally known. Please see your doctor if you experience any unavoidable side effects.</p>\n\n<p>Do not crush, break, or chew it; instead, swallow it whole with water.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>reatment of fungal infections: Fluka 150 mg is effective in treating a variety of fungal infections, including vaginal yeast infections (candidiasis), oral thrush, esophageal candidiasis, and systemic fungal infections. It works by inhibiting the growth and spread of the fungi responsible for these infections.</p>\n\n<p>Vaginal yeast infection relief: Fluka 150 mg is commonly prescribed for the treatment of vaginal yeast infections. It helps to alleviate symptoms such as itching, burning, abnormal discharge, and discomfort in the vaginal area.</p>\n\n<p>Oral thrush management: Fluka 150 mg can be used to treat oral thrush, a fungal infection of the mouth and throat caused by an overgrowth of Candida fungus. It helps to clear the infection and relieve symptoms such as white patches on the tongue and inner cheeks, pain, and difficulty swallowing.</p>\n\n<p>Prevention of fungal infections: In certain situations, Fluka 150 mg may be prescribed as a preventive measure against recurring fungal infections, particularly in individuals with weakened immune systems or those undergoing treatments that increase the risk of fungal infections.</p>\n\n<p>Convenient dosing: Fluka 150 mg is available in a single-dose oral tablet form, which makes it convenient and easy to take. A single dose is often sufficient to treat many fungal infections effectively.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before using Fluka 150 Tablet 1, please let your doctor know if you take any prescription or over-the-counter medications, including vitamin and herbal supplements. If you are allergic to Fluka 150 Tablet 1 or any of its ingredients, do not use it. Before taking Fluka 150 Tablet 1, let your doctor know if you have any liver, renal, or heart issues. Please seek medical counsel if you have diabetes, cancer, low blood magnesium or potassium levels, a weakened immune system, or any of the other conditions listed above. The Fluka 150 Tablet 1 should not be taken by women who are pregnant or nursing. If you feel lightheaded or have any other symptoms that could impair your ability to drive safely, do not operate machinery or drive. Avoid drinking alcohol while taking Fluka 150 Tablet 1 to prevent negative effects.</p>','<p>Fluka 150 Tablet 1s are part of a group of medications known as &quot;antifungals,&quot; which are used to treat a variety of illnesses brought on by fungi and yeast. A fungus can enter the body and affect any part of it, including the blood, lungs, bladder, genital region, mouth, throat, and oesophagus.</p>\n\n<p>Fluka 150 Tablet 1s include &quot;Fluconazole,&quot; which inhibits an enzyme in fungi that is necessary for their proper fat metabolism and prevents the creation of the fungal cell membrane. This inhibits the growth of fungi or yeast. As a result, yeast or fungus cells die or have their growth restrained.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Diarrhoea</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Stomach upset</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n	<li>Stomach pain</li>\n</ul>','[\"fluka-150-mg-170849322568.jpg\"]','FL150',1,'0','2024-02-21 05:27:57','2025-09-18 11:58:57'),(363,0,'Foligraf 150 IU','foligraf-150-iu','Injection','foligraf-150-iu-170849344860.jpg','FL150','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Under the direction of a doctor, Foligraf 150IU Injection is administered intravenously. Your doctor or nurse will assist you in learning the precise self-administration procedure. Always heed your doctor&#39;s recommendations, since they will determine when the injection should be administered. Depending on what you are using it for, you should adjust the dosage and frequency. Another medication may be administered to you as part of your treatment. As long as it has been prescribed for you, you should continue taking this medication.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>150IU Foligraf Injection encourages the release of a mature, healthy egg and aids in the correct development of an egg in a woman&#39;s ovary (the female reproductive organ). This improves the likelihood of a successful pregnancy while aiding in the treatment of female infertility. When a woman receives fertility treatment or in vitro fertilization (IVF), it is frequently used. It should not be self-administered and is administered by a doctor or nurse via injection. For the medicine to work, you must take it exactly as directed.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Pregnant women should not take PREGNANCY FOLIGRAF 150IU INJECTION. Therefore, before receiving it, talk to your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>It is not advised to use BREASTFEEDING FOLIGRAF 150IU INJECTION on nursing mothers. Therefore, before receiving it, talk to your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>FOLIGRAF 150IU INJECTION has no effect on your ability to drive or operate machines. However, if your capacity is impaired by FOLIGRAF 150IU INJECTION, avoid operating heavy machinery or operating a vehicle.</p>\n\n<p>ALCOHOL</p>\n\n<p>Prior to administering FOLIGRAF 150IU INJECTION, refrain from drinking.</p>\n\n<p>ALLERGY</p>\n\n<p>If you are allergic to urofollitropin, consult your doctor before getting FOLIGRAF 150IU INJECTION.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>Foligraf 150IU Injection is a medication used in assisted reproductive technology (ART) procedures to stimulate the development and maturation of eggs in women. It contains follicle-stimulating hormone (FSH), which plays a crucial role in the process of ovulation. By injecting Foligraf 150IU, it helps to promote the growth and development of ovarian follicles, which are sacs in the ovaries that contain the eggs.</p>\n\n<p>This medication is commonly used in fertility treatments such as in vitro fertilization (IVF) or intrauterine insemination (IUI). It is a part of a controlled ovarian hyperstimulation (COH) protocol, which involves carefully monitoring and stimulating the ovaries to produce multiple mature eggs for retrieval and fertilization.</p>\n\n<p>Foligraf 150IU Injection is personalized to each individual&#39;s needs, and the dosage can be adjusted based on the response to treatment. Regular monitoring through ultrasound scans and hormonal measurements is necessary to assess the growth and development of the follicles. This helps healthcare professionals to make any necessary adjustments to optimize the treatment and increase the chances of successful ovulation and conception.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Abdominal pain</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Bloating</li>\n	<li>Pelvic pain</li>\n	<li>Abdominal cramp</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n</ul>','[\"foligraf-150-iu-170849344860.jpg\"]','FL150',1,'0','2024-02-21 05:31:26','2025-10-06 05:56:08'),(364,0,'Foligraf 75 IU','foligraf-75-iu','Injection','foligraf-75-iu-170849354867.jpg','FL75','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Do not self-administer Foligraf 75Iu Injection 0.5 ml; seek medical attention instead.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Ovulation induction: Foligraf 75IU Injection contains follicle-stimulating hormone (FSH), which helps stimulate the growth and development of ovarian follicles in women who have difficulty ovulating or have irregular ovulation. This can increase the chances of successful ovulation and improve the chances of conception.</p>\n\n<p>Assisted reproductive technology (ART): Foligraf 75IU Injection is often used in conjunction with other fertility treatments, such as in vitro fertilization (IVF) or intrauterine insemination (IUI). It helps to promote the growth of multiple follicles, increasing the likelihood of obtaining multiple eggs for fertilization during these procedures.</p>\n\n<p>Controlled ovarian hyperstimulation: Foligraf 75IU Injection is used as part of a controlled ovarian hyperstimulation (COH) protocol. It helps to stimulate the growth of multiple follicles and increases the chances of obtaining a larger number of mature eggs for retrieval during fertility treatments.</p>\n\n<p>Personalized dosing: Foligraf 75IU Injection can be prescribed at different doses based on individual patient needs and response. The dosage can be adjusted by a healthcare professional to optimize follicle growth and maturation.</p>\n\n<p>Monitored treatment: When using Foligraf 75IU Injection, regular monitoring of the follicular development is necessary. This involves ultrasound scans and hormonal measurements to assess the response to treatment and make any necessary dosage adjustments. Close monitoring helps ensure the safety and effectiveness of the medication.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>A disorder called ovarian hyperstimulation syndrome (OHSS), in which ovarian follicles grow excessively and turn into big cysts, may be brought on by Foligraf 75Iu Injection 0.5 ml. Notify your doctor right once if you experience unusual pain, rapid weight gain, breathing problems, or general malaise as these symptoms could be indicators of OHSS. Foligraf 75Iu Injection 0.5 ml may raise the chance of miscarriage, ectopic pregnancy, birth abnormalities, and multiple pregnancies (carrying more than one child at once). In order to determine whether you have experienced any of the hazards related to Foligraf 75Iu Injection 0.5 ml, your doctor could urge you to get regular blood tests and ultrasounds throughout your therapy. If you have ever experienced a heart attack or blood clots in the legs, lungs, or veins, tell your doctor before receiving Foligraf 75Iu Injection 0.5 ml. It&#39;s possible that Foligraf 75Iu Injection 0.5 ml will make your blood clots worse or more likely to form. Additionally, let your doctor know if you&#39;ve had repeated infertility treatment regimens, since Foligraf 75Iu Injection 0.5 ml may make tumors in the ovaries and other sex organs more likely. After taking Foligraf 75Iu Injection 0.5 ml, notify your doctor right away if you notice any changes in your skin, including brittleness and blistering susceptibility. Women with primary ovarian failure (inadequate egg production from the ovaries) should not get the Foligraf 75Iu Injection 0.5 ml.</p>','<p>Foligraf 75Iu Injection 0.5 ml is a member of the class of pharmaceuticals known as &quot;fertility drugs&quot; that are used to treat infertility. It is a member of the group of hormones known as &quot;gonadotropins&quot; that play a role in fertilization and reproduction. Female infertility is the term used when a woman is unable to conceive after a year of trying. Infertility also includes pregnancies that end in miscarriages or stillbirths for the mother.</p>\n\n<p>&#39;Follitropin alfa&#39;, which is present in Foligraf 75Iu Injection 0.5 ml, works by maturing and forming a number of follicles (each holding an egg) and stimulating the ovulation process (the release of an egg from the ovary). To become pregnant, an egg must be released from the ovary and fertilized by a sperm cell. Foligraf 75Iu Injection 0.5 ml is used in conjunction with other medications to assist infertile men generate sperm.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Sacs of fluid within the ovaries (ovarian cysts)</li>\n	<li>Abdominal pain</li>\n	<li>Diarrhoea</li>\n	<li>Pain or redness at the injection site</li>\n</ul>','[\"foligraf-75-iu-170849354867.jpg\"]','FL75',1,'0','2024-02-21 05:36:53','2025-07-20 16:22:22'),(365,0,'Foracort Forte Inhaler 12/400 mcg (120 mdi)','foracort-forte-inhaler-12/400-mcg-(120-mdi)','Inhaler','foracort-forte-inhaler-12-400-mcg-120-mdi-170849390545.jpg','FO1240','<p>How to Use:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Do not swallow the rotacaps; they are meant for inhalation only.</li>\n	<li>Before use, refer to the label for specific directions.</li>\n	<li>Place the capsule at the base of the rotahaler, not in the mouthpiece.</li>\n	<li>Twist the mouthpiece completely until you hear a click.</li>\n	<li>Breathe in deeply through the mouthpiece.</li>\n	<li>Hold your breath for up to 10 seconds to ensure proper medication delivery.</li>\n	<li>If there is any powder remaining in the rotahaler, repeat the process.</li>\n	<li>Use FORACORT FORTE ROTACAP exactly as prescribed by your doctor.</li>\n	<li>Check the label carefully for directions before each use.</li>\n	<li>Your doctor will determine the appropriate dose and duration based on your age, body weight, and severity of your condition.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Foracort Forte Rotacap is a medication that helps keep the airways in your lungs open by relaxing the muscles in these airways. This allows air to flow in and out more easily, providing relief from symptoms such as chest tightness, shortness of breath, wheezing, and coughing. By improving your respiratory function, it enables you to carry out your daily activities with greater ease. This medicine is considered safe and effective, with its effects typically starting within a few minutes and lasting for several hours. It is important to continue using it as prescribed by your doctor and not discontinue it without their advice.</p>\n\n<p>Foracort Forte Rotacaps contains two active drugs, namely budesonide and formoterol. Budesonide belongs to the class of corticosteroids, which work by reducing inflammation and swelling within the nasal lining cells, thereby inhibiting the release of certain chemicals that trigger inflammatory reactions. This provides relief from symptoms such as sneezing, a runny or blocked nose, and sinus discomfort. Formoterol, on the other hand, belongs to the class of bronchodilators, which relax the muscles in the airways of the lungs and widen them, making breathing easier.</p>\n\n<p>Overall, Foracort Forte Rotacap is an effective combination medication used to treat symptoms of asthma and chronic obstructive pulmonary diseases (COPD), providing relief from respiratory distress and improving lung function.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Follow the instructions and use Foracort Forte Rotacaps (12 mcg + 400 mcg) as prescribed by your doctor.</li>\n	<li>Use the medication for inhalation only; do not swallow the capsules.</li>\n	<li>Use under medical supervision, preferably from a respiratory specialist.</li>\n	<li>Use it regularly, even if you have no immediate symptoms.</li>\n	<li>Avoid triggers that worsen respiratory symptoms.</li>\n	<li>Be aware of potential side effects and report any unusual reactions to your doctor.</li>\n	<li>Inform your doctor about all medications you are taking.</li>\n	<li>Inform your doctor about any underlying medical conditions you have.</li>\n</ul>','<p>Foracort Forte Rotacaps is a combination medication used primarily to treat symptoms of asthma and chronic obstructive pulmonary diseases (COPD). Asthma is a long-term respiratory condition characterized by narrowed airways, swelling, and excessive mucus production, resulting in breathing difficulties. COPD encompasses lung diseases like emphysema and chronic bronchitis, which cause shortness of breath and inflammation of the bronchial tubes.</p>\n\n<p>The medication contains two active ingredients: budesonide, a corticosteroid, and formoterol, a long-acting beta-agonist (LABA) or bronchodilator. Budesonide, belonging to the corticosteroid class, reduces irritation and swelling by acting on the cells lining the nasal passage and airways, preventing the release of certain inflammatory chemicals, and alleviating symptoms such as sneezing, nasal congestion, and sinus discomfort. Formoterol, as an LABA or bronchodilator, relaxes and widens the muscles of the respiratory airways, facilitating easier breathing for individuals with asthma and COPD.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Fungal infection in the mouth</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Sore throat, hoarse voice</li>\n	<li>Upper respiratory tract infection</li>\n	<li>Flu, cough</li>\n	<li>Back pain</li>\n	<li>Increased heart rate</li>\n</ul>','[\"foracort-forte-inhaler-12-400-mcg-120-mdi-170849390545.jpg\"]','FO1240',1,'0','2024-02-21 05:39:03','2025-10-06 05:56:26'),(366,0,'Foracort Forte Rotacaps 12mcg+400mcg','foracort-forte-rotacaps-12mcg+400mcg','Rotacaps','foracort-forte-rotacaps-12mcg-400mcg-170849405561.jpg','FO12','<p>How to Use:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Do not swallow the rotacaps; they are meant for inhalation only.</li>\n	<li>Before use, refer to the label for specific directions.</li>\n	<li>Place the capsule at the base of the rotahaler, not in the mouthpiece.</li>\n	<li>Twist the mouthpiece completely until you hear a click.</li>\n	<li>Breathe in deeply through the mouthpiece.</li>\n	<li>Hold your breath for up to 10 seconds to ensure proper medication delivery.</li>\n	<li>If there is any powder remaining in the rotahaler, repeat the process.</li>\n	<li>Use FORACORT FORTE ROTACAP exactly as prescribed by your doctor.</li>\n	<li>Check the label carefully for directions before each use.</li>\n	<li>Your doctor will determine the appropriate dose and duration based on your age, body weight, and severity of your condition.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Foracort Forte Rotacap is a medication that helps keep the airways in your lungs open by relaxing the muscles in these airways. This allows air to flow in and out more easily, providing relief from symptoms such as chest tightness, shortness of breath, wheezing, and coughing. By improving your respiratory function, it enables you to carry out your daily activities with greater e