ng, and excessive mucus production, resulting in breathing difficulties. COPD encompasses lung diseases like emphysema and chronic bronchitis, which cause shortness of breath and inflammation of the bronchial tubes.</p>\n\n<p>The medication contains two active ingredients: budesonide, a corticosteroid, and formoterol, a long-acting beta-agonist (LABA) or bronchodilator. Budesonide, belonging to the corticosteroid class, reduces irritation and swelling by acting on the cells lining the nasal passage and airways, preventing the release of certain inflammatory chemicals, and alleviating symptoms such as sneezing, nasal congestion, and sinus discomfort. Formoterol, as an LABA or bronchodilator, relaxes and widens the muscles of the respiratory airways, facilitating easier breathing for individuals with asthma and COPD.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Fungal infection in the mouth</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Sore throat, hoarse voice</li>\n	<li>Upper respiratory tract infection</li>\n	<li>Flu, cough</li>\n	<li>Back pain</li>\n	<li>Increased heart rate</li>\n</ul>','[\"foracort-forte-rotacaps-12mcg-400mcg-170849405561.jpg\"]','FO12',1,'0','2024-02-21 05:41:03','2025-10-06 05:56:43'),(367,0,'Foracort Inhaler 6/100 mcg (120 Doses)','foracort-inhaler-6/100-mcg-(120-doses)','Inhaler','foracort-inhaler-6-100-mcg-120-doses-170849423719.jpg','FO006','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Before using the inhaler, please refer to the instructions on the label. Shake the inhaler well. As you breathe in through your mouth, press down on the inhaler once to release the medication, and hold your breath for 10 seconds. Repeat this process until you have taken the recommended number of puffs, as advised by your doctor. Afterward, rinse your mouth thoroughly with water and spit it out.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Foracort 100 Inhaler 120 mdi is a combination medication containing two drugs, budesonide and formoterol, which are utilized for treating symptoms associated with asthma and chronic obstructive pulmonary diseases (COPD). Budesonide, a corticosteroid, reduces irritation and swelling within nasal lining cells and inhibits the release of certain inflammatory chemicals in the body. This provides relief from symptoms such as sneezing, nasal congestion, and sinus discomfort. Formoterol, a bronchodilator, relaxes and widens the muscles in the lungs&#39; airways, making breathing easier.</p>\n\n<p>By helping to keep the airways open, the Foracort 100 Inhaler assists in relaxing the muscles of the airways. This facilitates easier airflow in and out of the lungs, relieving symptoms like chest tightness, shortness of breath, wheezing, and coughing. It enables individuals to carry out their daily activities with greater ease. This medicine is both safe and effective, typically taking effect within a few minutes and providing relief that can last for several hours. It is important not to discontinue usage unless advised by a doctor.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>When using Foracort Inhaler (6/100 mcg), it is important to take certain precautions. Firstly, inform your doctor about any known allergies or hypersensitivity to the active ingredients, Budesonide or Formoterol, or any other medications. Additionally, disclose any medical conditions or history of certain conditions, such as heart problems, high blood pressure, diabetes, seizures, thyroid disorders, or liver or kidney diseases.</p>\n\n<p>Foracort inhaler may interact with other medications, including certain antibiotics, antifungal drugs, and certain heart medications. Inform your healthcare provider about all the medications you are currently taking, including prescription, over-the-counter, and herbal supplements, to avoid any potential drug interactions.</p>','<p>The primary purpose of the Foracort 100 Inhaler is to address symptoms related to asthma and chronic obstructive pulmonary diseases (COPD). Asthma is a long-term respiratory condition characterized by narrowed airways, swelling, and excessive mucus production, leading to breathing difficulties. COPD is a group of lung diseases that includes emphysema (shortness of breath) and chronic bronchitis (inflammation of the bronchial tube lining).</p>\n\n<p>Foracort 100 inhaler is a combination medication comprising two active substances: budesonide, a corticosteroid, and formoterol, a long-acting beta-agonist or bronchodilator. Budesonide, a corticosteroid, functions by reducing irritation and swelling within the nasal passages and airway linings. It inhibits the release of specific chemicals responsible for causing inflammation and allergic reactions, thus providing relief from symptoms like sneezing, nasal congestion, and sinus discomfort. On the other hand, formoterol, a long-acting beta-agonist or bronchodilator, relaxes and widens the muscles in the respiratory airways, making it easier for individuals with asthma and COPD to breathe.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<p>The majority of side effects do not need medical attention and typically subside as your body adapts to the medication. However, if you are concerned or if the side effects persist, it is recommended that you consult your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>The most common side effects are listed below:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Stomach discomfort</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n	<li>Cough</li>\n	<li>Nasopharyngitis (inflammation of the throat and nasal passages)</li>\n	<li>Upper respiratory tract infection</li>\n</ul>','[\"foracort-inhaler-6-100-mcg-120-doses-170849423719.jpg\"]','FO006',1,'0','2024-02-21 05:44:43','2025-10-06 05:56:56');
INSERT INTO `products` VALUES (368,0,'Foracort Inhaler 6/200 mcg (120 mdi)','foracort-inhaler-6/200-mcg-(120-mdi)','inhaler','foracort-inhaler-6-200-mcg-120-mdi-170849499030.jpg','FO620','<p>How to Use:</p>\n\n<p>Before using the inhaler, please refer to the instructions on the label. Shake the inhaler gently. While inhaling through your mouth, press the inhaler once to release the medication, and hold your breath for approximately 10 seconds. Repeat this process until you have taken the recommended number of puffs, as advised by your doctor. Afterward, thoroughly rinse your mouth with water and then spit it out.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Foracort 200 Inhaler 120 mdi combines two medications, budesonide and formoterol fumarate, which are used for the treatment of asthma and chronic obstructive pulmonary diseases (COPD). Budesonide, a corticosteroid, acts within the nasal lining cells to reduce irritation and swelling. It also inhibits the release of specific inflammatory chemicals in the body, providing relief from symptoms such as sneezing, a runny or blocked nose, and sinus discomfort. Formoterol fumarate, on the other hand, belongs to the class of bronchodilators. It works by relaxing the muscles and widening the airways of the lungs, making breathing easier.</p>\n\n<p>When treating chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD), Foracort Inhaler 200 helps keep the airways in your lungs open. It achieves this by relaxing the muscles in these airways, allowing for easier airflow. This medication alleviates symptoms such as chest tightness, shortness of breath, wheezing, and coughing, enabling you to carry out your daily activities with greater ease. It is both safe and effective, typically starting to take effect within a few minutes and providing relief that can last for several hours. It&#39;s important not to discontinue use unless advised to do so by your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Some precautions for Foracort 6/200mcg Box of 120md include avoiding its use if allergic to its components, regular monitoring for side effects, using it with caution in certain medical conditions, avoiding abrupt discontinuation, and following the prescribed dosage. Consult a healthcare professional for personalized advice and guidance.<br />\n&nbsp;</p>','<p>Foracort 200 Inhaler 120 mdi is a respiratory combination medication utilized primarily for the treatment of asthma symptoms and chronic obstructive pulmonary diseases (COPD). Asthma, a long-term respiratory condition characterized by narrowed airways, swelling, and excess mucus production, results in breathing difficulties. COPD encompasses a group of lung diseases, including emphysema (shortness of breath) and chronic bronchitis (inflammation of the bronchial tube lining).</p>\n\n<p>Comprised of two drugs, budesonide (a corticosteroid) and formoterol fumarate (a long-acting beta-agonist or bronchodilator), Foracort 200 Inhaler 120 mdi operates as follows: Budesonide, a corticosteroid, reduces irritation and swelling by acting directly on the nasal passage and airway lining cells. It inhibits the release of specific chemicals responsible for inflammatory reactions and allergies, thereby alleviating symptoms such as sneezing, a runny or blocked nose, and sinus discomfort. In contrast, formoterol fumarate, a long-acting beta-agonist or bronchodilator, relaxes and widens the muscles in the respiratory airways, facilitating easier breathing for individuals with asthma and COPD.</p>','<p>Fungal infection in the mouth</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Sore throat, hoarse voice</li>\n	<li>Upper respiratory tract infection</li>\n	<li>Flu, cough</li>\n	<li>Back pain</li>\n</ul>','[\"foracort-inhaler-6-200-mcg-120-mdi-170849499030.jpg\"]','FO620',1,'0','2024-02-21 05:57:20','2025-10-07 05:54:22'),(369,0,'Foracort Rotacaps 100 mcg 6 mcg','foracort-rotacaps-100-mcg-6-mcg','Rotacaps','foracort-rotacaps-100-mcg-6-mcg-170849510884.jpg','FO106','<p>How to Use:</p>\n\n<p>The majority of side effects do not need medical attention and typically subside as your body adapts to the medication. However, if you are concerned or if the side effects persist, it is recommended that you consult your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Foracort 100 Rotacap 30&#39;s is a combination medication that includes two drugs, namely budesonide and formoterol. It is specifically used for the treatment of asthma symptoms and chronic obstructive pulmonary diseases (COPD). Budesonide belongs to the corticosteroid class and acts by reducing irritation and swelling in the cells of the nasal lining. It also prevents the release of certain chemicals in the body that trigger inflammatory reactions. This helps alleviate symptoms such as sneezing, a runny or blocked nose, and sinus discomfort. On the other hand, formoterol belongs to the bronchodilator class and works by relaxing the muscles and widening the airways in the lungs, making breathing easier.</p>\n\n<p>When used for the treatment of chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD), Foracort 100 Rotacap helps keep the airways in the lungs open. It achieves this by relaxing the muscles in these airways, facilitating the entry and exit of air. This medication provides relief from symptoms such as chest tightness, shortness of breath, wheezing, and coughing, allowing individuals to engage in their daily activities more easily. Foracort 100 Rotacap is considered safe and effective, with a rapid onset of action within a few minutes and effects that can last for several hours. It is important not to discontinue the use of this medication unless advised to do so by your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Disclose any pre-existing medical conditions, such as heart problems, high blood pressure, diabetes, liver disease, thyroid disorders, or seizures.</li>\n	<li>Let your doctor know about all medications you are taking, including prescription, over-the-counter, and herbal supplements.</li>\n	<li>Consult your doctor if you are pregnant, planning to become pregnant, or breastfeeding.</li>\n	<li>Avoid using Foracort 100 Rotacap during respiratory infections.</li>\n	<li>Do not stop using Foracort 100 Rotacap suddenly without consulting your doctor.</li>\n	<li>Contact your doctor if you experience changes in vision or eye-related problems.</li>\n	<li>Be aware of potential side effects and report any unusual or severe reactions to your doctor.</li>\n	<li>Attend regular follow-up appointments with your doctor for monitoring and assessment of your condition while using Foracort 100 Rotacap.</li>\n</ul>','<p>Foracort 100 Rotacap 30&#39;s is a respiratory combination medication primarily used for the treatment of symptoms related to asthma and chronic obstructive pulmonary diseases (COPD). Asthma is a long-term respiratory condition characterized by the narrowing, swelling, and increased production of mucus in the airways, leading to breathing difficulties. COPD refers to a group of lung diseases, including emphysema (shortness of breath) and chronic bronchitis (inflammation of the bronchial tubes).</p>\n\n<p>Foracort 100 Rotacap 30&#39;s is composed of two drugs: budesonide, which is a corticosteroid, and formoterol, classified as a long-acting beta-agonist (LABA) or bronchodilator. Budesonide, as a corticosteroid, works by reducing inflammation and swelling in the nasal passage and airway lining cells. It inhibits the release of certain chemicals responsible for causing inflammatory reactions and allergies. This action provides relief from symptoms such as sneezing, a runny or blocked nose, and sinus discomfort. On the other hand, formoterol, a LABA or bronchodilator, relaxes and widens the muscles of the respiratory airways, making it easier for individuals with asthma and COPD to breathe.</p>','<p>The most common side effects are listed below:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Fungal infection in the mouth</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Sore throat, hoarse voice</li>\n	<li>Upper respiratory tract infection</li>\n	<li>Flu, cough</li>\n	<li>Back pain</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The majority of side effects do not need medical attention and typically subside as your body adapts to the medication. However, if you are concerned or if the side effects persist, it is recommended that you consult your doctor.</p>','[\"foracort-rotacaps-100-mcg-6-mcg-170849510884.jpg\"]','FO106',1,'0','2024-02-21 05:59:24','2025-10-07 05:54:33'),(370,0,'Foracort Rotacaps 200 mcg 6 mcg','foracort-rotacaps-200-mcg-6-mcg','Rotacaps','foracort-rotacaps-200-mcg-6-mcg-170849522420.jpg','FO206','<p>How to Use:</p>\n\n<p>It is important to avoid swallowing Rotacaps. Before using, refer to the instructions on the label. Position the capsule at the bottom of the rotahaler, not in the mouthpiece. Rotate the mouthpiece fully until you hear a click, then take a deep breath through the mouthpiece. Hold your breath for up to 10 seconds. If any powder is left in the rotahaler, repeat the process.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Foracort 200 Rotacap 30&#39;s combines two medications, budesonide and formoterol fumarate, which are used in the treatment of asthma and chronic obstructive pulmonary diseases (COPD). Budesonide, classified as a corticosteroid, functions by reducing irritation and swelling within the cells of the nasal lining. It also inhibits the release of specific chemicals in the body that trigger inflammatory reactions, providing relief from symptoms such as sneezing, nasal congestion, and sinus discomfort. On the other hand, formoterol fumarate belongs to the class of bronchodilators. It works by relaxing muscles and widening the airways in the lungs, making breathing easier for individuals with asthma and COPD.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>When using Foracort Rotacaps 200 mcg or 6 mcg, follow the instructions carefully. Inform your doctor about any allergies or medical conditions you have. Be cautious of potential drug interactions. If symptoms worsen or there is no improvement, contact your doctor. Discuss with your doctor if you are pregnant or breastfeeding. Store the rotacaps safely and check the expiration date. Consult your doctor for any concerns or questions.</p>','<p>Foracort 200 Rotacap is a respiratory combination medication primarily utilized for the treatment of symptoms related to asthma and chronic obstructive pulmonary diseases (COPD). Asthma, a long-term respiratory condition, is characterized by narrowing, swelling, and excess mucus production in the airways, resulting in breathing difficulties. COPD encompasses a group of lung diseases, including emphysema (shortness of breath) and chronic bronchitis (inflammation of the bronchial tube lining).</p>\n\n<p>Comprising two active drugs, Foracort 200 Rotacap&nbsp; consists of budesonide (a corticosteroid) and formoterol fumarate (a long-acting beta-agonist or bronchodilator). Budesonide, classified as a corticosteroid, functions by reducing irritation and swelling within the nasal passages and airway lining cells. It also inhibits the release of specific chemicals responsible for triggering inflammatory reactions and allergies. As a result, it provides relief from symptoms such as sneezing, nasal congestion, and sinus discomfort. On the other hand, formoterol fumarate, categorized as a long-acting beta-agonist or bronchodilator, relaxes and widens the muscles in the respiratory airways. This action makes breathing easier for individuals with asthma and COPD by facilitating improved airflow.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<p>The majority of side effects typically resolve on their own as your body adapts to the medication and do not require medical attention. However, if they persist or cause concern, it&#39;s recommended to consult with your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>The most common side effects are listed below:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Fungal infection in the mouth</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Sore throat, hoarse voice</li>\n	<li>Upper respiratory tract infection</li>\n	<li>Flu, cough</li>\n	<li>Back pain</li>\n</ul>','[\"foracort-rotacaps-200-mcg-6-mcg-170849522420.jpg\"]','FO206',1,'0','2024-02-21 06:01:21','2025-10-07 05:54:54'),(371,0,'Forcan 200 mg','forcan-200-mg','t','forcan-200-mg-170849542443.jpg','DO200','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>As directed by your physician, take this medication. Common side effects of Forcan-200 Tablet 4 include headache, diarrhoea, nausea, upset stomach, dizziness, and changing food tastes. These negative consequences are unique to each person and are not universal. Please see your doctor if you experience any side effects that are severe.</p>\n\n<p>It should be completely swallowed with water; do not break, crush, or chew it.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Forcan 200 mg is an effective antifungal medication that provides relief from a range of fungal infections. It works by inhibiting the growth and spread of fungi, helping to clear up infections and alleviate associated symptoms. This medication is commonly prescribed for conditions such as vaginal yeast infections (vulvovaginal candidiasis), oral thrush (a fungal infection in the mouth), esophageal candidiasis (fungal infection of the food pipe), and certain systemic fungal infections.</p>\n\n<p>One of the key benefits of Forcan 200 mg is its effectiveness in treating fungal infections. It targets the underlying cause of the infection and helps to eliminate the fungus responsible for the symptoms. This leads to symptom relief, including reduction in itching, redness, and discomfort associated with fungal infections. Forcan 200 mg can provide relief to individuals experiencing the distressing symptoms of fungal infections, allowing them to regain their comfort and well-being.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before using Forcan-200 Tablet 4&#39;s, please let your doctor know if you are taking any prescription or over-the-counter medications, including vitamin and herbal supplements. If you have a reaction to Forcan-200 Tablet 4s or any of its ingredients, do not take it. Before beginning treatment with Forcan-200 Tablet 4, let your doctor know if you have ever experienced liver, renal, or heart issues. Please seek medical counsel if you have diabetes, cancer, low blood magnesium or potassium levels, a weakened immune system, or any other condition that may make this medication inappropriate for you. Before using Forcan-200 Tablet 4s, pregnant or nursing women should talk to their doctor. If you develop lightheadedness or other symptoms that could impair your ability to drive safely, avoid operating machinery or driving if possible. Forcan-200 Tablet 4 should not be taken with alcohol to prevent negative effects.</p>','<p>The Forcan-200 Tablet 4s are part of a group of drugs known as &quot;antifungals,&quot; which are used to treat a variety of illnesses brought on by fungi and yeast. A fungus can enter the body and affect any part of it, including the blood, lungs, bladder, genital region, mouth, throat, and oesophagus.</p>\n\n<p>Fluconazole, a component of Forcan-200 Tablet 4, inhibits an enzyme necessary for the normal fat metabolism of fungi, preventing the growth of fungal cell membranes and killing or preventing the growth of fungi or yeast. As a result, yeast or fungus cells die or have their growth restrained.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Diarrhoea</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Stomach upset</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n	<li>Stomach pain</li>\n	<li>Altered food tastes</li>\n</ul>','[\"forcan-200-mg-170849542443.jpg\"]','FO200',1,'0','2024-02-21 06:04:25','2025-10-07 05:55:20'),(372,0,'Frusenex 100mg','frusenex-100mg','tablet','frusenex-100mg-17084957782.jpg','FR100','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>To ensure safe and effective use of Frusenex 100mg, it&rsquo;s important to follow the instructions provided by your doctor or pharmacist. Read the medication label carefully and adhere to the recommended dosage and timing. It&rsquo;s essential not to exceed the prescribed dose or use the medication for an extended period without medical guidance.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Edema Treatment: Frusenex 100mg is primarily used to manage edema, a condition characterized by fluid retention in various parts of the body. It can be particularly helpful in reducing swelling in the legs, ankles, and feet commonly associated with conditions like congestive heart failure, liver disease, kidney disorders, and certain lung diseases.</p>\n\n<p>Hypertension Management: Frusenex 100mg may be prescribed as part of a comprehensive treatment plan for hypertension (high blood pressure). By promoting the removal of excess fluid and reducing blood volume, it can help lower blood pressure levels and contribute to better cardiovascular health.</p>\n\n<p>Congestive Heart Failure: Frusenex 100mg is often used as a key component in managing congestive heart failure. It can help alleviate the symptoms associated with fluid buildup in the lungs and other parts of the body, improving breathing and overall comfort.</p>\n\n<p>Kidney Conditions: For individuals with certain kidney conditions, such as nephrotic syndrome or renal impairment, Frusenex 100mg may be prescribed to regulate fluid balance and reduce the workload on the kidneys.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before starting Frusenex 100mg, it&rsquo;s important to disclose your complete medical history and any allergies to your healthcare provider. Inform them about any existing conditions, such as diabetes, gout, or electrolyte imbalances, as well as any medications or supplements you are currently taking.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>Frusenex 100mg, also known as Furosemide 100, is a medication that offers several beneficial uses and can be a helpful treatment option when used appropriately. It belongs to a class of drugs called diuretics, which work by increasing urine production and promoting the elimination of excess fluid from the body. Here are some key points about Frusenex 100mg:</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>Like any medication, Frusenex 100mg can have potential side effects, but they are typically temporary and resolve as your body adjusts. It&rsquo;s important to note that not everyone experiences side effects, and they may vary in severity. Common side effects associated with Frusenex 100mg may include increased urination, dizziness, mild muscle cramps, and low blood pressure. However, it&rsquo;s crucial to consult your doctor if you experience any persistent or severe side effects.</p>\n\n<p>Overall, Frusenex 100mg can be a valuable medication for managing edema, hypertension, congestive heart failure, and certain kidney conditions. When used as directed and under the supervision of a healthcare professional, it can contribute to improved health and well-being. It&rsquo;s important to maintain open communication with your doctor to ensure optimal treatment and address any concerns or questions you may have.</p>','[\"frusenex-100mg-17084957782.jpg\"]','FR100',1,'0','2024-02-21 06:11:10','2025-10-07 05:55:06'),(373,0,'Furamist Nasal Spray 120 metered doses','furamist-nasal-spray-120-metered-doses','Nasal Spray','furamist-nasal-spray-120-metered-doses-170849597571.jpg','FU120','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Only those with a prescription can purchase Furamist Nasal Spray 6 gm. To receive the full benefits of Furamist Nasal Spray 6 gm, it must be used as instructed by a healthcare practitioner or in accordance with the instructions on the package. Very little of the medication in Furamist Nasal Spray 6 gm is absorbed into the body, so it is unlikely to have any negative side effects. A few uncommon side effects include coughing, burning, itching, nosebleeds, headaches, nausea, vomiting, sore throat, and nosebleeds. The majority of these Furamist Nasal Spray 6 gm adverse effects go away over time without the need for medical intervention. However, please see a doctor if the adverse effects worsen or persist.</p>\n\n<p>Close one nostril while inserting the bottle&#39;s tip into the other, then spray in the direction of the nostril&#39;s sides. Straighten your back and take slow, deep breaths. For the second nostril, follow the same procedure.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Allergy symptom relief: Furamist Nasal Spray contains the active ingredient fluticasone furoate, which is a corticosteroid. It helps to reduce inflammation and swelling in the nasal passages, providing relief from common allergy symptoms such as sneezing, itching, nasal congestion, and runny nose.</p>\n\n<p>Long-lasting action: Furamist Nasal Spray offers extended relief from allergy symptoms due to its long-lasting effect. It provides sustained relief throughout the day, allowing individuals to go about their daily activities without the constant discomfort of allergic rhinitis.</p>\n\n<p>Prevention of allergy symptoms: Furamist Nasal Spray can also be used as a preventive measure for individuals who are prone to frequent or seasonal allergies. By using it regularly, especially before the allergy season or exposure to allergens, it can help prevent the onset of symptoms or minimize their severity.</p>\n\n<p>Targeted treatment: The nasal spray formulation allows for direct administration of the medication to the nasal passages, where the allergic inflammation occurs. This targeted treatment approach helps to minimize systemic side effects and provides localized relief.</p>\n\n<p>Non-drowsy: Furamist Nasal Spray is a non-drowsy medication, which means it does not typically cause sedation or interfere with daily activities. It allows individuals to function normally without feeling excessively tired or sleepy.</p>\n\n<p>Well-tolerated: Furamist Nasal Spray is generally well-tolerated when used as directed. However, it&#39;s important to follow the recommended dosage and usage instructions provided by a healthcare professional to ensure safe and effective use of the medication.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>If you have ever experienced an allergic or hypersensitive reaction to fluticasone or any other medication, tell your doctor. Furamist Nasal Spray 6 gm should not be used by women who are pregnant or nursing since a doctor will only prescribe it if the advantages outweigh the hazards. Avoid using this product if you recently had surgery, trauma, or nasal ulcers. There have been reports of cataract and glaucoma development in association with fluticasone nasal spray use. A yearly eye exam should be done to look for these issues. Please let your doctor know if you have ever received treatment for a fungal, bacterial, viral, or parasitic illness before using Furamist Nasal Spray 6 gm. Additionally, let your doctor know if you have a lung infection like tuberculosis. Children under the age of four have not been adequately tested for safety and efficacy. Furamist Nasal Spray 6 gm can be administered to kids as old as four with a doctor&#39;s supervision.</p>','<p>The corticosteroid drug class includes Furamist Nasal Spray 6 gm. It is prescribed for adult and pediatric patients four years of age and older to treat the nasal symptoms of seasonal, perennial, allergic, and non-allergic rhinitis. Exposure to airborne chemicals (like pollens) that are only present during particular seasons of the year causes seasonal allergies. Year-round indoor exposure to airborne contaminants (such house dust) is the main cause of perennial allergies. Vasomotor rhinitis, often referred to as perennial non-allergic rhinitis, is a chronic condition marked by symptoms that are similar to allergic rhinitis (runny nose, stuffy nose, sneezing, and nasal itching), but that endure for more than nine months each year.</p>\n\n<p>Fluticasone is an ingredient in Furamist Nasal Spray 6 gm. Fluticasone functions by preventing the body&#39;s release of specific molecules that trigger inflammatory responses. As a result, it relieves symptoms such as a runny or blocked nose, sneezing, itching, watery eyes, and an itchy nose.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Sore Throat</li>\n	<li>Nose Bleeds</li>\n	<li>Trouble Breathing</li>\n</ul>','[\"furamist-nasal-spray-120-metered-doses-170849597571.jpg\"]','FU120',1,'0','2024-02-21 06:13:31','2025-10-07 05:56:05'),(374,0,'Furosemide 40mg','furosemide-40mg','tablet','furosemide-40mg-170849614072.jpg','FU40','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>Follow your doctor&rsquo;s instructions and carefully read the medication label for proper usage of Furosemide 40mg. It is important to take the medication as directed and avoid taking more or less than prescribed. Take the tablets with a glass of water and try to take them at the same time each day to maintain a consistent level of the drug in your body.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Furosemide 40mg offers several benefits in the treatment of various conditions:</p>\n\n<p>Edema Management: Furosemide is highly effective in reducing excess fluid retention in the body, providing relief from edema (swelling) in conditions such as congestive heart failure, liver disease, kidney disease, and certain lung conditions.</p>\n\n<p>Congestive Heart Failure: Furosemide is commonly used to manage congestive heart failure by reducing fluid buildup in the lungs and other parts of the body. This can help improve breathing, reduce fatigue, and enhance overall well-being.</p>\n\n<p>Hypertension Management: Furosemide can be used as part of a comprehensive treatment plan for high blood pressure. By reducing excess fluid in the body, it helps lower blood pressure levels and improve cardiovascular health.</p>\n\n<p>Kidney Disease: Furosemide is often prescribed to manage fluid retention associated with kidney disease, helping to alleviate symptoms and maintain kidney function.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Electrolyte Imbalance: Furosemide can cause electrolyte imbalances, such as low potassium levels. Your doctor may recommend regular monitoring and, if necessary, prescribe supplements to maintain the balance.</p>\n\n<p>Dehydration: Furosemide increases urine production, which can lead to dehydration if adequate fluid intake is not maintained. It is important to drink enough water and follow your doctor&rsquo;s recommendations.</p>\n\n<p>Interactions: Furosemide may interact with other medications, including certain antibiotics, anti-inflammatory drugs, and blood pressure medications. Inform your doctor about all the medications you are taking to avoid potential interactions.</p>','<p>Furosemide 40mg is a medication that is commonly prescribed to treat conditions related to excess fluid accumulation in the body, such as edema and congestive heart failure. It belongs to a class of drugs known as loop diuretics, which work by increasing urine production and promoting the excretion of excess water and salt from the body.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Here is some information about Furosemide 40mg:</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>While Furosemide 40mg is generally well-tolerated, some individuals may experience mild side effects. Most side effects are temporary and resolve on their own. Common side effects may include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Frequent urination</li>\n	<li>Dizziness or lightheadedness</li>\n	<li>Muscle cramps</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n</ul>','[\"furosemide-40mg-170849614072.jpg\"]','FU40',1,'0','2024-02-21 06:15:48','2025-10-07 05:56:18'),(375,0,'Galamer 4mg','galamer-4mg','tablet','galamer-4mg-170849639758.jpg','GA004','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Depending on the severity of your disease and how it responds to therapy, your doctor will determine the dose and length. Nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, headaches, dizziness, tiredness, shakiness (tremor), weakness, depression, and loss of appetite are typical adverse effects of Galamer 4 Tablet 10s. These negative consequences are unique to each person and are not universal. Please see your doctor if you experience any side effects that are severe.</p>\n\n<p>With a glass of water, swallow it whole; do not chew, break, or crush it.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Cognitive improvement: Galamer 4 Tablet is known as a cholinesterase inhibitor, which means it helps increase the levels of a neurotransmitter called acetylcholine in the brain. Acetylcholine is involved in memory, learning, and cognitive functions. By inhibiting the breakdown of acetylcholine, Galamer 4 Tablet can help improve cognitive functions and slow down the decline in memory and thinking abilities associated with Alzheimer&#39;s disease.</p>\n\n<p>Symptom management: Alzheimer&#39;s disease can cause various symptoms such as memory loss, confusion, difficulty with language and communication, and problems with daily activities. Galamer 4 Tablet may help alleviate some of these symptoms and improve overall quality of life for individuals with Alzheimer&#39;s disease.</p>\n\n<p>Stabilization of symptoms: While Galamer 4 Tablet cannot cure Alzheimer&#39;s disease or reverse its progression, it may help slow down the decline in cognitive functions and stabilize symptoms for a period of time. This can allow individuals with Alzheimer&#39;s disease to maintain their independence and engage in activities for a longer duration.</p>\n\n<p>Potential functional improvement: Some individuals taking Galamer 4 Tablet may experience a modest improvement in their ability to perform daily activities such as dressing, eating, and bathing. This can enhance their independence and reduce the burden on caregivers.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>If you have any liver or kidney conditions, heart issues (chest pain, sick sinus syndrome, heart attack, heart failure, and a slow or irregular heartbeat), electrolyte imbalance (potassium), stomach ulcers, fits, Parkinson&#39;s disease, breathing issues (asthma, chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD)), or urination issues, please mention them in your medical history. Tell your doctor if you recently have surgery on your stomach, intestines, or bladder. Before taking Galamer 4 Tablet 10, please talk to your doctor if you are pregnant, trying to conceive, or nursing a baby. Galamer 4 Tablet 10 shouldn&#39;t be used with alcohol because doing so could exacerbate negative effects like sleepiness and dizziness. Avoid operating machinery or driving because Galamer 4 Tablet 10s may cause you to feel drowsy or dizzy and may lower your mental awareness. Children under the age of 18 should not use Galamer 4 Tablet 10&#39;s since its safety and efficacy have not been shown.</p>','<p>A class of drugs known as &quot;anti-dementia agents&quot; known as Galamer 4 Tablet 10s is used to treat mild to moderate dementia brought on by Alzheimer&#39;s disease. A neurological condition called Alzheimer&#39;s disease results in dementia (memory loss) and gradually erodes one&#39;s capacity for thought, learning, communication, and managing daily tasks. Memory, communication, and thought impairment are all symptoms of dementia.</p>\n\n<p>The ingredient &quot;Galantamine,&quot; which is in the category of &quot;Acetylcholinesterase Inhibitors,&quot; is present in Galamer 4 Tablets 10s. The cholinesterase enzyme, which degrades acetylcholine, is blocked by galantamine. Acetylcholine is a chemical messenger known as a neurotransmitter that carries messages from one nerve cell to another, as well as between nerve cells, muscle cells, and gland cells. As a result, Galamer 4 Tablet 10 raises acetylcholine levels, enabling nerve cells to connect. It improves brain function, including memory and thought, by restoring the equilibrium of neurotransmitters.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n	<li>Drowsiness</li>\n	<li>Shakiness (tremor)</li>\n	<li>Weakness</li>\n	<li>Loss of appetite</li>\n</ul>','[\"galamer-4mg-170849639758.jpg\"]','GA004',1,'0','2024-02-21 06:21:16','2025-10-07 05:56:30'),(376,0,'Galamer 8mg','galamer-8mg','tablet','galamer-8mg-170849663369.jpg','GA008','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Your doctor will choose the dose and duration based on the severity of your condition and how it responds to treatment. The most common side effects of Galamer 8 Tablet 10s include nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, headaches, dizziness, fatigue, shakiness (tremor), weakness, depression, and lack of appetite. Everybody experiences these negative effects differently; they are not a universal phenomenon. If you encounter any serious side effects, please visit your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>Do not chew, break, or crush it; rather, consume it whole with a glass of water.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Enhancement of cognition: Acetylcholine, a neurotransmitter, is produced in greater quantities in the brain thanks to Galamer 8 Tablet, a cholinesterase inhibitor. Acetylcholine plays a role in cognitive processes such as memory and learning. Galamer 8 Tablet works to enhance cognitive processes and decrease the deterioration of memory and thinking skills brought on by Alzheimer&#39;s disease by preventing the breakdown of acetylcholine.</p>\n\n<p>Management of symptoms: Alzheimer&#39;s disease can result in a variety of symptoms, including memory loss, disorientation, issues with language and communication, and difficulties doing daily tasks. For people with Alzheimer&#39;s disease, Galamer 8 Tablet may help reduce some of these symptoms and enhance general quality of life.</p>\n\n<p>Stabilization of symptoms: Although Galamer 8 Tablet cannot reverse the advancement of Alzheimer&#39;s disease or cure it, it may help slow down the loss of cognitive abilities and stabilize symptoms for a while. As a result, people with Alzheimer&#39;s disease may be able to maintain their independence and participate in activities for longer.</p>\n\n<p>Potential functional improvement: Some people taking Galamer 8 Tablet might notice a slight improvement in their capacity to carry out regular tasks like getting dressed, eating, and taking a shower. They may become more independent as a result, and carers may have less work.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Indicate in your medical history if you have any liver or kidney conditions, heart problems (chest pain, sick sinus syndrome, heart attack, heart failure, and a slow or irregular heartbeat), electrolyte imbalance (potassium), stomach ulcers, fits, Parkinson&#39;s disease, breathing problems (asthma, chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD)), or urination problems. If you recently had surgery on your stomach, intestines, or bladder, let your doctor know. Please consult your doctor if you are pregnant, trying to conceive, or nursing a child before using Galamer 8 Tablet 10. Alcohol shouldn&#39;t be consumed while taking Galamer 8 Tablet 10 because doing so could make side effects like drowsiness and nausea worse. Galamer 8 Tablet 10s may make you feel sleepy or lightheaded and may impair your mental awareness. Avoid operating heavy machinery or operating a vehicle while using them. Since the safety and effectiveness of Galamer 8 Tablet 10 have not been established, children under the age of 18 shouldn&#39;t use it.</p>','<p>Galamer 8 Tablet 10s, a member of the &quot;anti-dementia agents&quot; class of medications, are used to treat mild to moderate dementia brought on by Alzheimer&#39;s disease. Alzheimer&#39;s disease is a neurological ailment that causes dementia (memory loss) and gradually impairs one&#39;s ability to think, learn, communicate, and manage daily chores. Dementia is characterized by impairments in cognition, memory, and communication.</p>\n\n<p>The ingredient &quot;Galantamine,&quot; which belongs to the class of &quot;Acetylcholinesterase Inhibitors,&quot; may be found in Galamer 8 Tablets 10s. Galantamine inhibits the cholinesterase enzyme, which breaks down acetylcholine. Acetylcholine, a neurotransmitter, is a chemical messenger that transmits information between nerve cells as well as between nerve cells, muscle cells, and gland cells. Galamer 8 Tablet 10 increases the level of acetylcholine as a result, allowing nerve cells to interact. It enhances mental processes, such as memory and cognition, by reestablishing the balance of neurotransmitters.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n	<li>Drowsiness</li>\n	<li>Shakiness (tremor)</li>\n	<li>Weakness</li>\n	<li>Loss of appetite</li>\n</ul>','[\"galamer-8mg-170849663369.jpg\"]','GA008',1,'0','2024-02-21 06:25:08','2025-10-07 05:56:43'),(377,0,'Gliclazide Tab  80mg','gliclazide-tab-80mg','tablet','gliclazide-tab-80mg-170849725846.jpg','GL80','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>It is important to follow your doctor&rsquo;s instructions regarding the usage and dosage of Gliclazide Tab 80mg. Typically, the medication is taken once or twice a day, preferably with meals to ensure proper absorption. It is important to take the medication regularly and at the prescribed times for optimal results.</p>\n\n<p>Benefit:</p>\n\n<p>Gliclazide Tab 80mg offers several benefits in the management of type 2 diabetes:</p>\n\n<p>Blood sugar control: Gliclazide helps lower blood glucose levels by stimulating the release of insulin from the pancreas. This helps to regulate blood sugar levels and keep them within the target range.</p>\n\n<p>Improved glycemic control: By enhancing insulin sensitivity, Gliclazide assists in improving the body&rsquo;s response to insulin. This leads to better utilization of glucose by the body&rsquo;s cells, resulting in improved glycemic control.</p>\n\n<p>Reduced risk of complications: By effectively controlling blood sugar levels, Gliclazide can help reduce the risk of long-term complications associated with diabetes, such as cardiovascular diseases, kidney problems, and nerve damage.</p>\n\n<p>Convenience and ease of use: Gliclazide Tab 80mg is available in tablet form, making it convenient and easy to incorporate into your daily routine. It allows for effective diabetes management without the need for frequent insulin injections.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>While Gliclazide Tab 80mg is generally safe and well-tolerated, there are a few precautions to keep in mind:</p>\n\n<p>Hypoglycemia: Gliclazide can occasionally cause low blood sugar levels (hypoglycemia). It is important to monitor your blood sugar regularly, especially when starting the medication, and to be aware of the symptoms of low blood sugar. Promptly treating hypoglycemia by consuming a source of glucose, such as fruit juice or glucose tablets, can help alleviate symptoms.</p>\n\n<p>Allergies and interactions: Inform your healthcare provider about any allergies you have, including allergies to sulfonylureas or other medications. It is also important to disclose all medications, including over-the-counter drugs and supplements, to avoid potential interactions.</p>\n\n<p>Pregnancy and breastfeeding: If you are pregnant, planning to become pregnant, or breastfeeding, it is important to consult with your healthcare provider before taking Gliclazide Tab 80mg, as the safety of the medication during these periods may need to be evaluated.</p>','<p>Gliclazide Tab 80mg is a medication that is commonly prescribed to manage blood sugar levels in individuals with type 2 diabetes. It belongs to the class of drugs known as sulfonylureas, which work by stimulating the pancreas to produce more insulin and increasing the body&rsquo;s sensitivity to insulin.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Here Is some important information about Gliclazide Tab 80mg:</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>Gliclazide Tab 80mg is generally well-tolerated, and most side effects are mild and temporary. It is important to discuss any concerns with your doctor. Common side effects may include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Nausea or upset stomach</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n	<li>Hypoglycemia (low blood sugar) in some cases</li>\n</ul>','[\"gliclazide-tab-80mg-170849725846.jpg\"]','GL80',1,'0','2024-02-21 06:38:12','2025-10-07 05:57:28'),(378,0,'Glinate 120 mg','glinate-120-mg','tablet','glinate-120-mg-170849774752.jpg','GL120','<p>Gli