cting source of glucose on hand, such as sweet foods or fruit juice. Alcohol use should be avoided because it increases the risk of low blood sugar levels. With this medication, some individuals may gain weight.</p>\n\n<p>If you have type 1 diabetes mellitus, diabetic ketoacidosis (high amounts of acid in your blood), or severe kidney or liver damage, you shouldn&#39;t use Glypride 4 Tablet. If you have ever had heart disease, thyroid illness, or any hormonal disorders, let your doctor know before taking this medication since it might not be appropriate for you. Before using it, women who are pregnant or nursing should also visit their doctor. Regular blood sugar checks are advised, and your doctor may also suggest blood tests to evaluate your liver and blood cell counts.</p>','<p>Glypride common side effects</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Low blood glucose, or hypoglycemia</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Headache</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Nausea</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Dizziness</li>\n</ul>','[\"glypride-4mg-170850084221.jpg\"]','GL004',1,'0','2024-02-21 07:34:58','2025-10-07 06:04:06'),(394,0,'Hepcinat 400 mg','hepcinat-400-mg','tablet','hepcinat-400-mg-17085009694.jpg','HE400','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>The dosage and duration of Hepcinat Tablet should be followed as prescribed by your doctor. Even if you feel better, do not miss any doses and complete the entire course of treatment. It should be taken preferably at a set time and with food. Take the missed dose as soon as you remember. If your next dose is approaching, skip the missing one and resume your regular regimen. Don&#39;t increase the dosage.</p>\n\n<p>Follow your doctor&#39;s instructions for this medication&#39;s dosage and duration. Take it all in at once. Don&#39;t eat it, break it, or crush it. Hepcinat Tablet should be consumed alongside food.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>High cure rates: Hepcinat 400 mg, when used in combination with other antiviral medications, has shown high rates of sustained virologic response (SVR) in the treatment of chronic hepatitis C. SVR means that the virus is undetectable in the blood six months after completing the treatment, indicating a cure for the infection. This can help prevent the progression of liver disease and reduce the risk of complications associated with chronic HCV infection.</p>\n\n<p>Improved liver health: Chronic hepatitis C infection can lead to liver damage, including inflammation and fibrosis. By effectively treating the HCV infection with Hepcinat 400 mg, it can help slow down or halt the progression of liver disease. This can lead to improved liver health and reduce the risk of developing cirrhosis, liver failure, or liver cancer.</p>\n\n<p>Convenience and shorter treatment duration: Hepcinat 400 mg, along with certain combination therapies, offers the advantage of shorter treatment durations compared to older treatment regimens for hepatitis C. Some treatment regimens with Hepcinat 400 mg can last as short as 8 to 12 weeks, depending on the specific genotype of the HCV infection. This shorter treatment duration can improve treatment adherence and patient convenience.</p>\n\n<p>Well-tolerated: Hepcinat 400 mg is generally well-tolerated, and most side effects associated with the medication are mild. Common side effects may include fatigue, headache, nausea, and insomnia. Serious side effects are rare but can occur, and it&#39;s important to consult with a healthcare professional if any concerning symptoms arise.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>When using Hepcinat 400 mg for the treatment of chronic hepatitis C, it&#39;s important to follow certain precautions. Firstly, it should be used under the supervision of a healthcare professional specializing in hepatitis C treatment. Inform your healthcare professional about any allergies or sensitivities you have. Discuss any other medical conditions or medications you are taking, as they may interact with Hepcinat 400 mg. If you are pregnant, planning to become pregnant, or breastfeeding, consult with your healthcare professional regarding the risks and benefits. Be aware of potential side effects such as fatigue, headache, nausea, and insomnia, and report any persistent or severe symptoms. Adhere to the prescribed treatment regimen and attend follow-up appointments for monitoring and assessment. Remember, personalized advice from your healthcare professional is essential for safe and effective use of Hepcinat 400 mg.</p>','<p>Hepcinat Tablet is a drug that fights viruses. It is utilized in conjunction with other drugs to treat chronic hepatitis C virus (HCV) infection. It functions by gradually reducing the amount of hepatitis C virus in the body and eradicating the infection from the blood.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Fatigue</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Insomnia (difficulty in sleeping)</li>\n	<li>Anemia (low number of red blood cells)</li>\n</ul>','[\"hepcinat-400-mg-17085009694.jpg\"]','HE400',1,'0','2024-02-21 07:36:53','2025-10-07 06:04:20'),(395,0,'Herpex Cream 5 gm cream','herpex-cream-5-gm-cream','Cream','herpex-cream-5-gm-cream-170850107997.jpg','HE005','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Only external usage is permitted for Herpex 5% Cream 5 gm. As directed by your doctor, place a tiny amount on the tip of your finger and apply a thin coating to the clean, dry affected region. Avoid making contact with the mouth, eyes, or nose. Rinse with water liberally if you come into contact with these areas by accident. In order to stop the transmission of infection, wash your hands both before and after applying.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Antiviral activity: Herpex 5% Cream contains the active ingredient acyclovir, which is an antiviral agent. Acyclovir works by inhibiting the replication and spread of the herpes simplex virus. By reducing the viral activity, Herpex 5% Cream can help alleviate the symptoms and shorten the duration of herpes outbreaks.</p>\n\n<p>Symptom relief: Herpex 5% Cream can provide relief from the symptoms associated with herpes outbreaks. These symptoms may include pain, itching, tingling, and the appearance of blisters or sores. By applying the cream topically to the affected area, it can help soothe discomfort and promote healing.</p>\n\n<p>Faster healing: By inhibiting the replication of the herpes virus, Herpex 5% Cream can contribute to faster healing of herpes lesions. It may help reduce the duration of outbreaks and promote the formation of scabs, leading to the eventual healing of the sores.</p>\n\n<p>Preventive effect: Herpex 5% Cream can also be used as a preventive measure in individuals who experience recurrent herpes outbreaks. By applying the cream at the first signs of an impending outbreak (such as tingling or itching), it may help reduce the severity and duration of the outbreak or even prevent it from fully developing.</p>\n\n<p>Convenient topical application: Herpex 5% Cream comes in a tube for easy and convenient topical application. The cream should be applied directly to the affected area, following the recommended dosage and frequency as prescribed by a healthcare professional.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Allergic reactions: Before using Herpex 5% Cream, it&#39;s essential to check if you are allergic to acyclovir or any other ingredients in the cream. If you experience any signs of an allergic reaction such as rash, itching, swelling, or difficulty breathing, discontinue use and seek medical attention immediately.</p>\n\n<p>Avoid contact with eyes and mucous membranes: Herpex 5% Cream is meant for external use only. Avoid getting the cream in your eyes, mouth, or other mucous membranes. If accidental contact occurs, rinse thoroughly with water.</p>\n\n<p>Hygiene and handwashing: Ensure that your hands are clean before and after applying Herpex 5% Cream to prevent the spread of the herpes virus or potential secondary infections.</p>\n\n<p>Do not share: Do not share your Herpex 5% Cream with others, as this may lead to the transmission of the herpes virus.</p>\n\n<p>Use as directed: Follow the instructions provided by your healthcare professional or the product label regarding the application frequency, duration of use, and recommended dosage. Do not exceed the prescribed dose or apply the cream for longer than recommended.</p>','<p>A member of the &quot;antivirals&quot; class, Herpex 5% Cream 5 gm is primarily used to treat herpes simplex virus infections of the skin. Herpes labialis/cold sores (herpes simplex virus infections of the lips and face) and genital herpes are both treated with it.</p>\n\n<p>Aciclovir, an antiviral medication, is present in Herpex 5% Cream 5 gm. Herpes simplex virus proliferation is halted and killed as a result of its action.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Dry/cracked lips</li>\n	<li>Flaky skin</li>\n	<li>Temporary burning or stinging sensation</li>\n</ul>','[\"herpex-cream-5-gm-cream-170850107997.jpg\"]','HE005',1,'0','2024-02-21 07:38:50','2025-10-07 06:04:37'),(396,0,'Ibugesic 200mg','ibugesic-200mg','tablet','ibugesic-200mg-170850180773.jpg','IB200','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>To ensure safe and effective use of Ibuprofen 200mg, it is important to carefully read and follow the instructions provided on the medication label or as advised by your healthcare professional. The usual recommended dosage for adults is 200mg taken orally every 4 to 6 hours, as needed. It is best to take the medication with food or milk to minimize the chance of stomach irritation.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Pain relief: Ibuprofen 200mg is effective in reducing mild to moderate pain, such as headaches, menstrual cramps, dental pain, muscle aches, and joint pain. It provides relief by inhibiting the production of certain chemicals in the body that contribute to pain and inflammation.</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Fever reduction: Ibuprofen 200mg helps lower fever by targeting the underlying cause of elevated body temperature. It can be particularly useful in managing fevers associated with common colds, flu, or other infections.</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Anti-inflammatory effects: Ibuprofen 200mg possesses anti-inflammatory properties, making it helpful in reducing inflammation associated with conditions such as arthritis, sprains, strains, and other musculoskeletal injuries.</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Ease of availability: Ibuprofen 200mg is readily available over the counter without the need for a prescription, allowing individuals to quickly and conveniently access temporary relief for their pain and discomfort.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>While Ibuprofen 200mg is generally considered safe when used as directed, it is important to exercise caution and consider the following precautions:</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Allergies and sensitivities: Inform your healthcare provider or pharmacist about any known allergies to ibuprofen or other NSAIDs, as well as any other substances, to prevent potential allergic reactions or adverse effects. Seek medical attention if you experience any signs of an allergic reaction, such as rash, itching, swelling, dizziness, or difficulty breathing.</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Medical conditions: If you have a history of stomach ulcers, gastrointestinal bleeding, kidney or liver disease, high blood pressure, heart conditions, asthma, or any other chronic medical condition, consult with your healthcare professional before using Ibuprofen 200mg to ensure its safe use and discuss potential interactions or risks.</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Drug interactions: It is important to inform your healthcare provider about all medications, supplements, or herbal products you are currently taking to avoid potential drug interactions or adverse effects.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>Ibuprofen 200mg is a commonly used medication that belongs to the class of nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs). It is widely recognized for Its analgesic (pain-relieving), antipyretic (fever-reducing), and anti-inflammatory properties. Ibuprofen 200mg is available over the counter and can help alleviate a variety of conditions.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>Ibuprofen 200mg is generally well-tolerated, and most side effects are mild and temporary. However, it is important to be aware of possible side effects and seek medical attention if any severe or persistent symptoms occur. Common side effects of Ibuprofen 200mg may include:</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Upset stomach or indigestion</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Nausea or vomiting</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Mild headache</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Dizziness or drowsiness</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Allergic reactions (rare)</p>','[\"ibugesic-200mg-170850180773.jpg\"]','IB200',1,'0','2024-02-21 07:51:27','2025-10-07 06:04:47'),(397,0,'Imatib 100mg','imatib-100mg','tablet','imatib-100mg-170850195292.jpg','IM100','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Depending on your medical condition, it is advisable that you continue taking Imatib 100 Tablet 10&#39;s for the duration of the prescription your doctor has given you. You might occasionally develop oedema, exhaustion, muscle cramps, musculoskeletal discomfort, diarrhea, rash, and stomach pain in addition to nausea, vomiting, nauseousness, and abdominal pain. The majority of these adverse effects subside gradually and do not need medical intervention. If you have these side effects frequently, you are urged to speak with your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>With a glass of water, swallow the pill completely. Not to be chewed, broken, or crushed.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Cancer treatment: Imatib 100 Tablet is commonly used in the treatment of chronic myeloid leukemia (CML), a type of blood cancer, as well as gastrointestinal stromal tumors (GIST), a type of tumor found in the digestive tract. It works by inhibiting the growth and division of cancer cells, helping to control the progression of the disease.</p>\n\n<p>Targeted therapy: Imatib 100 Tablet belongs to a class of medications called tyrosine kinase inhibitors. It specifically targets and inhibits the activity of abnormal proteins, such as BCR-ABL in CML and c-KIT in GIST, which play a crucial role in the development and progression of these cancers. By targeting these specific proteins, Imatib 100 Tablet can help slow down or stop the growth of cancer cells.</p>\n\n<p>Increased survival rates: Imatib 100 Tablet has shown significant benefits in improving overall survival rates and progression-free survival in patients with chronic myeloid leukemia and gastrointestinal stromal tumors. It has revolutionized the treatment of CML, providing patients with a targeted therapy that can effectively control the disease and extend their life expectancy.</p>\n\n<p>Reduced side effects: Compared to traditional chemotherapy, Imatib 100 Tablet is generally associated with fewer and less severe side effects. This is because it specifically targets cancer cells without affecting healthy cells to the same extent, resulting in a more tolerable treatment experience for patients.</p>\n\n<p>Convenience of oral administration: Imatib 100 Tablet is taken orally, usually once or twice daily, which offers convenience and ease of administration compared to other forms of cancer treatment. This allows patients to take the medication at home without the need for frequent hospital visits for injections or infusions.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>If you have a reaction to any of the chemicals in Imatib 100 Tablet 10, avoid taking it. Do not drive or operate any equipment that demands attention while taking Imatib 100 Tablet 10 since these medications may induce blurred vision and dizziness. It is necessary to cover your skin with a high sun protection factor (SPF) when going outside because it can result in a skin rash if you are not using a strong SPF. This is because while taking Imatib 100 Tablet 10&#39;s, you might become more susceptible to sunlight. Imatib 100 Tablet 10&#39;s can result in water retention (oedema) and limb swelling, therefore if you experience an unanticipated rapid weight increase, please see your doctor. Imatib 100 Tablet 10&#39;s can reactivate hepatitis B, therefore please let your doctor know if you have ever had an infection. Imatib 100 Tablet 10s may increase your susceptibility to infections; if you experience any symptoms of an infection, such as fever, sore throat, dyspnea, jaundice, unexplained bleeding, or bruising, call your doctor right once.</p>','<p>Imatib 100 Tablet 10s are part of a group of medications known as &quot;anti-cancer medications,&quot; which are primarily used to treat different types of cancer. It is used to treat gastrointestinal stromal tumors as well as cancers of the blood (chronic myeloid leukemia and acute lymphocytic leukemia). A genetic mutation known as cancer causes cells to divide uncontrolled and invade nearby tissues. There are more than 100 different forms of cancer, including breast, lung, and blood cancers.</p>\n\n<p>Imatinib, which is mostly used to treat cancer, is present in Imatib 100 Tablet 10&#39;s. It functions by preventing an enzyme that promotes the growth of cancer cells and causes cell death (apoptosis). As a result, cancer cell growth and dissemination are inhibited or slowed down.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Fatigue</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Diarrhoea</li>\n	<li>Muscle cramp</li>\n	<li>Abdominal pain</li>\n	<li>Musculoskeletal pain</li>\n</ul>','[\"imatib-100mg-170850195292.jpg\"]','IM100',1,'0','2024-02-21 07:53:26','2025-10-07 06:05:04'),(398,0,'Imdur 30mg','imdur-30mg','tablet','imdur-30mg-17085022193.jpg','IM30','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>It is important to follow your doctor&rsquo;s instructions and read the medication label carefully when taking Imdur 30mg. Typically, the tablets are taken orally once daily, with or without food. It is recommended to swallow the tablet whole, without crushing or chewing it, to ensure the proper release of the medication.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Imdur 30mg provides several benefits for individuals with