o adequately pump blood throughout the body, which causes the heart to become dysfunctional. Heart failure may result from a number of diseases, such as high blood pressure or clogged arteries.</p>\n\n<p>Ivabradine, which is present in Ivabrad 7.5 Tablet 10&#39;S, acts by lowering heart rate by a few beats per minute.&nbsp; This reduces the heart&#39;s need for oxygen, which is especially beneficial when an angina attack is possible. All of these actions prevent or lessen the likelihood of additional angina attacks.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Feeling tired</li>\n	<li>Irregular or rapid feeling heartbeat</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n	<li>Visual impairment or blurry vision</li>\n</ul>','[\"ivabrad-7-170860001352.jpg\"]','IV075',1,'0','2024-02-22 11:07:08','2025-10-07 06:10:31'),(408,0,'Ivecop 6 mg','ivecop-6-mg','tablet','ivecop-6-mg-170860020461.jpg','IV006','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>As directed by your doctor, take this medication. Do not change the dosage without consulting your doctor beforehand. Headache, wooziness, muscle discomfort, nausea, and upset stomach are typical Ivecop 6 Tablet 10 side effects. Additionally, you can develop orthostatic hypotension, which causes dizziness when you stand up too rapidly from a resting or sitting posture. The majority of these adverse effects of Ivecop 6 Tablet 10s gradually go away over time without the need for medical intervention. Contact your doctor, nevertheless, if the adverse effects are severe.</p>\n\n<p>Do not crush, break, or chew it; instead, swallow it whole with water.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Effective against parasitic infections: Ivecop 6 mg is highly effective in treating various parasitic infections caused by roundworms, threadworms, and other parasites. It works by paralyzing and killing the parasites, preventing them from reproducing and spreading further in the body.</p>\n\n<p>Wide range of applications: Ivecop 6 mg is used to treat a variety of parasitic infections, including strongyloidiasis (intestinal infection), onchocerciasis (river blindness), and scabies (skin infestation). It is also used in the treatment of certain off-label conditions, such as head lice and rosacea.</p>\n\n<p>Easy administration: Ivecop 6 mg is taken orally, typically as a single dose or as directed by a healthcare professional. The oral administration makes it convenient and easy to use, without the need for injections or topical applications.</p>\n\n<p>High safety profile: Ivecop 6 mg is generally safe and well-tolerated when used as directed. Serious side effects are rare, but as with any medication, there is a possibility of mild side effects such as dizziness, headache, or gastrointestinal discomfort. It is important to consult with a healthcare professional if any concerns or unexpected reactions arise.</p>\n\n<p>Cost-effective treatment: Ivecop 6 mg is available as a generic medication, making it more affordable and accessible to a larger population. This affordability ensures that patients can receive necessary treatment without excessive financial burden.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>If you have any pharmaceutical allergies, including those to Ivecop 6 Tablet 10s or antiparasitic drugs, let your doctor know. Inform your doctor if you take any vitamins, nutritional supplements, prescription or over-the-counter medications, herbal items, or other medications. If you have ever been treated for meningitis, HIV, or human African trypanosomiasis (a disease brought on by the tsetse fly), let your doctor know. If you are breas