rought on by the tsetse fly), let your doctor know. If you are breastfeeding, pregnant, or intend to become pregnant, let your doctor know. If you have ever had a loa loa infection (a worm infection) or have ever lived in West or Central Africa, let your doctor know. If you have headaches, neck discomfort, seizures, or difficulties walking, call your doctor right away.</p>','<p>Ivermectol 12 Tablet 2s are a type of anti-parasitic medication also referred to as an anthelmintic. Strongyloidiasis (a roundworm infection) and onchocerciasis (a worm infection that affects the skin and eyes) are two parasitic illnesses that are commonly treated with this medicine. If untreated, these parasite infections can lower quality of life and can result in fatal diseases, especially in those with compromised immune systems.</p>\n\n<p>Ivermectin, which is present in Ivermectol 12 Tablet 2, operates by adhering to the parasite&#39;s inside. Finally, it paralyzes and kills the parasite, or it temporarily stops adult parasites from producing larvae. Thus, parasitic infections are successfully treated.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Muscle pain</li>\n	<li>Diarrhoea</li>\n	<li>Orthostatic hypotension</li>\n	<li>Head or neck pain</li>\n</ul>','[\"ivermectol-12mg-170860044348.bmp\"]','IV012',1,'0','2024-02-22 11:14:21','2025-10-08 08:53:06'),(410,0,'Izra 40 mg','izra-40-mg','tablet','izra-40-mg-170910827499.jpg','IZ40','<p>Using the Izra Tablet</p>\n\n<p>Follow your doctor&#39;s instructions for this medication&#39;s dosage and duration. Take it all in at once. Don&#39;t eat it, break it, or crush it. Izra 40 Tablet should be taken without food.</p>\n\n<p>Izra Tablet operation</p>\n\n<p>Proton pump inhibitor (PPI) Izra 40 Tablet. It functions by lowering the amount of stomach acid, which relieves acid-related indigestion and heartburn.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits of Izra Tablet for the Treatment of Acid Reflux Disease (Gastroesophageal Reflux Disease)</p>\n\n<p>GERD is a chronic (long-term) disorder that feels more like ongoing heartburn than intermittent heartburn. It occurs when a muscle above your stomach relaxes excessively, allowing stomach contents to reflux into your mouth and oesophagus. Izra 40 Tablet is a member of the class of drugs known as proton pump inhibitors. It lessens the amount of acid your stomach produces and lessens the discomfort brought on by acid reflux and heartburn. For it to work, you must take it exactly how it is intended.</p>\n\n<p>The signs of GERD might be lessened with a few straightforward lifestyle adjustments. Eat smaller, more frequent meals; consider what foods make you feel heartburny and try to avoid them; if you are overweight, attempt to lose weight; and look for ways to relax. Eat nothing three to four hours before bedtime.</p>\n\n<p>Peptic ulcer disease treatment</p>\n\n<p>Izra 40 Tablet is a member of the class of drugs known as proton pump inhibitors. As the ulcer heals spontaneously, it avoids additional damage by lowering the amount of acid your stomach produces. Depending on what caused the ulcer, you might also be prescribed other medications in addition to this one. Even if the symptoms appear to go away, you must continue taking the medication as directed for it to be successful.</p>','<p>Izra 40 Tablet is a medication that lessens the quantity of acid your stomach produces. It is used to treat peptic ulcer disease, acid reflux, and other issues with your food pipe. Stomach ulcers can also be prevented and treated with it.</p>\n\n<p>Izra 40 Tablet should be taken as prescribed by your doctor. The dosage will depend on the ailment you are treating, but it is often the lowest dose for the shortest amount of time that is required to cure your illness. It is typically consumed without food. Even if your symptoms go away right away, keep taking it as directed. Your doctor may perform routine tests to assess your levels of magnesium, which can drop with this medication, if you use it for a long time.</p>\n\n<p>Headache, diarrhoea or constipation, stomach pain, and nausea are typical adverse effects. These are often minor, but if they annoy you or do not go away, consult your doctor. The longer you use this medication, the greater the chance of negative effects may be. If you take it for a long time, you can be more prone to break a bone. It is recommended to stay away from things like fatty, spicy, and rich foods that seem to exacerbate your symptoms. Limiting alcohol and caffeinated beverages like tea, coffee, and cola may also be beneficial.</p>\n\n<p>Some people should not take this medication. You must inform your doctor if you have serious liver issues, are taking HIV medications, have ever had an allergic reaction to a medication similar to this one, or have osteoporosis before using this medication. Izra 40 Tablet doesn&#39;t affect how well alcohol works. Alcohol consumption, however, causes your stomach to create more acid than usual. This medication may cause you to feel lightheaded, drowsy, or have vision problems. In such a case, refrain from operating any machinery or tools until you feel better. It is typically not advised when breastfeeding or pregnant.</p>','<p>Izra&#39;s usual side effects</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Headache</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Dizziness</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; mouth feeling parched</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Nausea</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Continent pain</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Constipation</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Flatulence</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Diarrhea</li>\n</ul>','[\"izra-40-mg-170910827499.jpg\"]','I0Z',1,'0','2024-02-28 08:18:03','2025-10-07 06:15:23'),(411,0,'Janumet 50/500 mg','janumet-50/500-mg','tablet','janumet-50-500-mg-170921272355.jpg','JA50','<p>Utilising the Janumet Tablet</p>\n\n<p>Follow your doctor&#39;s instructions for this medication&#39;s dosage and duration. Take it all in at once. Don&#39;t ea