requent exercise. Your illness, blood sugar levels, and other medications you are taking will all affect the dose that is prescribed to you. It helps to lower the possibility of getting an upset stomach if taken with meals.</p>\n\n<p>To maximise the benefits, you should take it consistently at the same time each day, and you shouldn&#39;t stop taking it until your doctor advises you to. While taking this medication, it&#39;s crucial to stick to the diet and exercise regimen advised by your doctor. Controlling diabetes involves changing your lifestyle significantly.</p>\n\n<p>Janumet 50mg/500mg Tablet side effects most frequently reported include nausea, vomiting, upset stomach, headache, and sore throat. If you are using other diabetic medications, such as insulin or sulfonylurea, you may experience the side effect of low blood sugar (hypoglycemia), therefore you should be aware of how to identify and manage it.</p>\n\n<p>Not everyone should take this medication. If you have ever experienced heart, kidney, liver, or pancreas issues, or if you drink a lot of alcohol, you should tell your doctor before taking it. Women who are pregnant or nursing should also speak with their doctor before taking this medication. In order to ensure your safety while using Janumet 50mg/500mg Tablet, inform your doctor of all the medications you are now taking. Since alcohol lowers blood glucose, you should make an effort to avoid drinking it. Before and during therapy, your doctor will check your blood sugar levels and kidney function.</p>','<p>Janumet common side effects</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Low blood glucose, or hypoglycemia</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Nausea</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Vomiting</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Diarrhea</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; a diminished appetite</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; stomach bloating</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; infection of the upper respiratory tract</li>\n</ul>','[\"janumet-50-500-mg-170921272355.jpg\"]','JA50',1,