els and improves how well the body reacts to insulin. To get better outcomes while taking JANUMET, patients must continue to follow their doctor&#39;s recommendations for a carbohydrate-regularized diet.</p>\n\n<p>If you have type 1 diabetes, severe liver or kidney illness, or cardiac issues, let your doctor know before using JANUMET. For women who are pregnant or nursing, JANUMET is not advised. Nausea, vomiting, diarrhoea, stomach pain, and taste alterations are typical JANUMET side effects. If any of the symptoms trouble you, talk to your doctor.</p>','<p>JANUMET SIDE EFFECTS:</p>\n\n<p>COMMON</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; low amounts of blood sugar</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; nausea and vomit</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; diarrhoea, constipation, stomach pain, and farts</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; the hands or legs swelling</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; upper respiratory infection and headache</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; leg discomfort or joint pain along with a runny or stuffy nose and a painful throat</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; reduced appetite</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; tongue flavour of metal</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>UNCOMMON</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; grogginess and sleepiness</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; tongue feeling dry and itchy</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>RARE</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>&nbsp; &nbsp; Decreased platelet count, which could lead to infections or an increased tendency to bleed</li>\n</ul>','[\"janumet-50-850mg-170921297053.jpg\"]','JA850',1,'0','2024-02-29 13:24:44','2025-10-07 06:16:29'),(414,0,'Januvia 100mg','januvia-100mg','tablet','januvia-100mg-170921325720.jpg','JA100','<p><strong>How to use:</strong></p>\n\n<p>Take this medicine in the dose and duration as advised by your doctor. Swallow it as a whole. Do not chew, crush or break it. Januvia 100mg Tablet may be taken with or without food, but it is better to take it at a fixed time.</p>\n\n<p><strong>How it works:</strong></p>\n\n<p>Januvia 100mg Tablet is an antidiabetic medi