ow to use:</p>\n\n<p>Your physician will recommend the best medications for you and determine the appropriate dosage. Carefully adhere to the instructions for all prescribed medications. The medication may be consumed with or without food. Regularly taking all of these medications at the appropriate times increases their efficacy and decreases the likelihood that HIV will develop resistance to them. It is essential not to miss doses and to continue taking medications until your physician informs you it is safe to stop.</p>\n\n<p>Take this medication according to your doctor&#39;s prescribed dosage and duration. Swallow the pill whole. Not to be chewed, crushed, or broken. The Lamivir HBV Tablet may be taken with or without sustenance, but it is preferable to take it at a set time each day.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>In patients with chronic hepatitis B virus (HBV) infection, Lamivir HBV Tablet prevents the HBV virus from replicating within the body. It assists in infection control and enhances immune function. This decreases the likelihood of complications and enhances the quality of life. This medication is always administered with other antiretroviral medications. It is neither a cure nor a preventative measure against HBV infection. It is essential that you take this medication exactly as prescribed, per your doctor&#39;s dosage instructions. The effectiveness of the medication is significantly enhanced when all dosages are taken at the correct times and in the correct amounts.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>supervision of a healthcare professional who can determine the appropriate dosage and duration of treatment based on your specific condition.</p>\n\n<p>Hepatitis B testing: Before starting Lamivir HBV Tablet, your healthcare provider may perform tests to confirm the diagnosis of HBV infection and to assess the severity of the infection. This information will help guide the appropriate treatment plan.</p>\n\n<p>Allergies: Inform your healthcare provider if you have any known allergies to Lamivir HBV Tablet or any other medications. Allergic reactions to Lamivir HBV Tablet can occur and may require immediate medical attention.</p>\n\n<p>Resistance: Over time, the hepatitis B virus may develop resistance to Lamivir HBV Tablet. Regular monitoring of your viral load and liver function is important to ensure the effectiveness of the medication. If resistance occurs, your healthcare provider may need to adjust the treatment plan.</p>\n\n<p>Other medical conditions: Inform your healthcare provider about any other medical conditions you have, such as kidney disease, liver disease (other than hepatitis B), or HIV infection. These conditions may affect the use of Lamivir HBV Tablet and require special monitoring or dose adjustments.</p>','<p>HIV infection and chronic hepatitis B virus (HBV) infection are treated with Lamivir HBV Tablet. It prevents pathogen replication within human cells. This eliminates your infection by preventing the virus from producing new copies of itself.</p>\n\n<p>Lamivir HBV Tablet is not a cure for HIV or AIDS; it merely reduces the volume of HIV in the body. This reduces your likelihood of developing HIV-related complications and increases your lifespan. It is prescribed alongside additional HIV medications.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<p>The majority of adverse effects do not necessitate medical attention and subside as the body adjusts to the medication. Consult your physician if they persist or if they cause you concern.</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Diarrhea</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Fatigue</li>\n</ul>','[\"lamivir-100-mg-170947403822.jpg\"]','LA100',1,'0','2024-03-03 13:54:40','2025-10-07 06:19:21'),(430,0,'Lan 15mg','lan-15mg','Capsule','lan-15mg-170947424467.jpg','LA15','<p>Use of LAN Capsule</p>\n\n<p>Follow your doctor&#39;s instructions for this medication&#39;s dosage and duration. It is best to consume LAN 15 Capsule on an empty stomach.</p>\n\n<p>Worki