nt of chronic hepatitis C infection. This combination therapy has proven to be highly effective in curing hepatitis C and improving the overall health of patients. Here is some important information about LediHep 90/400mg:</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>Like any medication, LediHep 90/400mg may cause some side effects, although they are generally well-tolerated. It&rsquo;s important to note that not everyone will experience these side effects, and they are usually temporary. Some common side effects include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Fatigue</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Diarrhea</li>\n	<li>Insomnia</li>\n</ul>','[\"ledihep-90-400mg-170948140734.jpg\"]','LH94',1,'0','2024-03-03 15:58:01','2025-10-07 06:19:55'),(433,0,'Latoprost RT BKC Free Eye Drop .005% (2.5 ml)','latoprost-rt-bkc-free-eye-drop-.005-(2.5-ml)','Drops','latoprost-rt-bkc-free-eye-drop-170948161771.webp','LA005','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Latoprost RT BKC-Free Eye Drops, 2.5 ml are intended solely for ophthalmic use. You are advised to use Latoprost RT BKC Free Eye Drops 2.5 ml for as long as your physician has prescribed. Before using, remove the seal and cleanse your hands to prevent contamination. If you wear contact lenses, you must remove them prior to applying Latoprost RT BKC Free Eye Drops 2.5 ml and wait 15 minutes before reinserting them. Changes in eye color, vision blurring, changes in the thickness, length, or color of eyelashes, irritation, and dehydrated eyes may occur in some cases. The majority of these side effects of Latoprost RT BKC Free Eye Drops 2.5 ml are transient, do not necessitate medical attention, and subside progressively over time. However, if the adverse effects persist, consult your physician.</p>\n\n<p>Wash your hands prior to and following use. Shake the bottle vigorously prior to each use. Instill the eye drops by forming a pocket between the eyelid and the eye by drawing down the lower eyelid. Do not contact the dropper&#39;s tip, as doing so could contaminate the solution.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Latanoprost, which is contained in Latoprost RT BKC Free Eye Drops 2.5 ml, is a prostaglandin inhibitor. To reduce ocular pressure, Latoprost RT BKC Free ocular Drops 2.5 ml are used alone or in combination with other medications. It is primarily used to treat elevated intraocular pressure. It enhances the passage of aqueous humor from the eye into the bloodstream. As a consequence, the eye&#39;s pressure is reduced. In addition, if the pressure is too high and is not treated, permanent vision loss can result. Latoprost RT BKC Free Eye Drops 2.5 ml should only be applied to the afflicted eye; normal eye contact should be avoided.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>If you have an allergy or hypersensitivity to latanoprost or prostaglandin inhibitors, do not use Latoprost RT BKC Free Eye Drops, 2.5 ml. Inform your physician of all prescription and over-the-counter medications you are taking, particularly eye medications, aspirin-containing products, and vitamins. Inform your doctor before using Latoprost RT BKC Free Eye Drops 2.5 ml if you have a kidney condition, uveitis, asthma, dry eye, herpes simplex eye infection, if you are pregnant or breastfeeding, or if you have any of the above conditions, as a dose adjustment may be necessary. Please inform your physician if you are taking additional eye medications. If you wear contact lenses, you must remove them prior to using Latoprost RT BKC Free Eye Drops 2.5 ml and wait 15 minutes before reapplying. To prevent infection, wash your hands thoroughly before applying Latoprost RT BKC Free Eye Drops 2.5 ml. Never combine two eye medications; wait at least 5 minutes before administering the second medication. It is contraindicated to combine Latoprost RT BKC Free Eye Drops 2.5 ml with other prostaglandin inhibitors.</p>','<p>Latoprost RT BKC Free Eye Drops, 2.5 ml belong to the class of ophthalmic medications prescribed to reduce intraocular pressure in patients with glaucoma or ocular hypertension. Glaucoma is an eye disease that damages the optic nerve and leads to impaired vision. Ocular hypertension is increased pressure in the eye caused by inadequate discharge of aqueous humor (eye fluid that maintains normal pressure through its continuous flow).</p>\n\n<p>Latoprost RT BKC Free Eye Drops 2.5 ml contain Latanoprost, which increases the natural outflow of fluid from the eye into the circulation. This reduces intraocular pressure and prevents the deterioration of vision.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Change in eye colour</li>\n	<li>Redness of the eye</li>\n	<li>Inflamed eyelid</li>\n	<li>Eye infection (conjunctivitis)</li>\n	<li>Irritated eye</li>\n	<li>Burning,</li>\n</ul>','[\"latoprost-rt-bkc-free-eye-drop-170948161771.webp\"]','LA005',1,'0','2024-03-03 16:02:57','2025-10-07 06:20:10'),(434,0,'Levipil 250mg','levipil-250mg','tablet','levipil-250mg-170948189934.jpg','LE250','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Take 10 Levipil 250 mg Tablets as directed. Your doctor will determine the frequency of Levipil 250 Tablet 10 administration based on your medical condition. In some instances, you may experience daytime lethargy, disturbed sleep, lightheadedness or vertigo, sleepiness, general weakness, and infections that cannot be explained. The majority of these adverse effects of Levipil 250 Tablet 10&#39;s do not necessitate medical attention and subside over time. However, if the side effects persist, please consult your physician.</p>\n\n<p>Take it as directed by your doctor. It should be ingested whole with a glass of water. Do not shatter, chew, or crush it.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Seizure control: Levipil 250 is effective in reducing the frequency and severity of seizures in individuals with epilepsy. It works by stabilizing electrical activity in the brain, preventing abnormal and excessive neuronal firing that leads to seizures.</p>\n\n<p>Broad spectrum: Levipil 250 is considered a broad-spectrum antiepileptic drug, meaning it is effective against various types of seizures, including partial seizures, generalized tonic-clonic seizures, myoclonic seizures, and absence seizures. It can be used as a monotherapy or in combination with other antiepileptic medications.</p>\n\n<p>Well-tolerated: Levipil 250 is generally well-tolerated by most individuals. It has a favorable side effect profile compared to some other antiepileptic drugs. Common side effects, such as dizziness, drowsiness, and headache, are usually mild and transient.</p>\n\n<p>Flexible dosing: Levipil 250 offers flexible dosing options, allowing for individualized treatment based on the specific needs of the patient. The dosage can be adjusted according to the severity of seizures and the patient&#39;s response to the medication.</p>\n\n<p>Extended release formulation: Levipil 250 is available in an extended-release formulation, which allows for once-daily dosing convenience. This can improve medication adherence and simplify the treatment regimen for individuals with epilepsy.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Combining Levipil 250 Tablet 10&#39;s with other anti-epileptic drugs can result in extreme drowsiness, breathing difficulties, coma, and mortality. Patients with a history of alcoholism or substance addiction should take Levipil 250 Tablet 10&#39;s with extreme caution. Taking Levipil 250 Tablet 10&#39;s with alcohol may impair your ability to drive or operate heavy machinery because you may become disoriented and unable to concentrate. Inform your doctor if you experience excessive suicidal ideation, difficulty concentrating, sleep disturbances, dizziness, or drowsiness. Pregnant or lactating women should consult a physician before taking this pregnancy medication of category C. Do not take Levipil 250 Tablet 10&#39;s if you are allergic to any of its active constituents, have lung disease, liver disease, glaucoma, or sleep apnea.</p>','<p>Levipil 250 Tablet 10&#39;s belongs to the &#39;anticonvulsant&#39; class of drugs, which are primarily used to treat epilepsy-related convulsions (fits). Epilepsy is a chronic condition characterized by recurrent convulsions (fits). Levipil 250 Tablet 10&#39;s is used to treat a form of epilepsy in which seizures affect only one side of the brain, but may spread to broader regions on both sides.</p>\n\n<p>Levetiracetam, which is present in Levipil 250 Tablet 10&#39;s, is used alone or in combination to treat epilepsy symptoms. It works by slowing down the abnormal signals that the brain sends out, which result in epilepsy episodes. It inhibits specific brain regions responsible for aberrant activity and prevents the spread of electrical signals that cause seizures. It reduces the frequency of seizures but is not a panacea for epilepsy.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Daytime drowsiness</li>\n	<li>Disturbed sleep</li>\n	<li>Light-headedness</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n	<li>Sleepiness</li>\n	<li>General weakness</li>\n	<li>Unexplained infections</li>\n</ul>','[\"levipil-250mg-170948189934.jpg\"]','LE250',1,'0','2024-03-03 16:05:42','2025-10-07 06:20:22'),(435,0,'Levipil 500mg','levipil-500mg','tablet','levipil-500mg-170948200173.jpg','LE500','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Take 10 Levipil XR 500 mg tablets as directed. Your doctor will determine the frequency of Levipil XR 500 Tablet 10 administration based on your medical condition. In some instances, you may experience daytime lethargy, disturbed sleep, lightheadedness or vertigo, sleepiness, general weakness, and infections that cannot be explained. The majority of these adverse effects of Levipil XR 500 Tablet 10&#39;s do not necessitate medical attention and subside with time. However, if the side effects persist, please consult your physician.</p>\n\n<p>Take as directed by your doctor. It should be ingested whole with a glass of water. Do not shatter, chew, or crush it.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Levetiracetam, which is present in Levipil XR 500 Tablet 10&#39;s, is used alone or in