3-24 16:38:51','2025-10-08 05:20:58'),(447,0,'Lipril 10mg','lipril-10mg','tablet','lipril-10mg-171129849154.jpg','LI10','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Take 15 tablets of Lipril 10 with or without sustenance. Do not chew, crush, or break the tablet; instead, consume it with a glass of water. Take 15 Lipril 10 Tablets daily at the same time. Occasionally, you may experience common adverse effects such as headache, vertigo, fatigue, and congestion. The majority of these adverse effects do not necessitate medical attention and subside over time. Consult your physician if you continue to experience these side effects.</p>\n\n<p>Swallow it whole with water; do not pulverize, chew, or dissolve it.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Relaxing and dilating the blood vessels makes it simpler for the heart to pump blood to all body parts. This aids in reducing blood pressure and the likelihood of a heart attack or stroke. Lipril 10 Tablet 15&#39;s reduces standing and lying blood pressure with no orthostatic effect (a sudden drop in blood pressure that can occur when a person immediately stands up). However, Lipril 10 Tablet 15&#39;s may exhibit an orthostatic effect when dehydrated. Continued use of Lipril 10 Tablet 15s reduces the severity of heart failure, the rate of hospitalization, and symptoms including weakness and shortness of breath. Lipril 10 Tablet 15&#39;s may be administered alone or in conjunction with other medications to treat hypertension.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Lipril 10 Tablet 15&#39;s should not be taken if you are allergic to Lipril 10 Tablet 15&#39;s or any of its ingredients. Consult your physician if you have issues with your heart, kidneys, or liver. Lipril 10 Tablet 15&#39;s may occasionally cause lower than normal blood pressure, particularly in dehydrated patients taking diuretics (medicines used to treat edema) and low sodium levels. Check your blood pressure regularly to avoid potential hazards. If you are pregnant or breastfeeding, avoid consuming Lipril 10 Tablet 15&#39;s. Consult your doctor. They may recommend an alternate medication. Children under the age of 18 should not take Lipril 10 Tablet 15&#39;s because efficacy and safety have not been established. Inform your physician of your medications and health condition in order to rule out the possibility of disagreeable side effects. Consult your physician if you have lost a significant amount of body fluids due to vomiting, diarrhoea, or excessive perspiration, if you are taking low water tablets to treat edema (diuretics), or if you undergo dialysis. Stop taking Lipril 10 Tablet 15s one day before undergoing surgery or dental work requiring anesthesia. Inform your physician that you are taking 15 Lipril 10 Tablets. Regular monitoring of blood pressure, electrolyte levels, and kidney function is recommended while using Lipril 10 Tablet 15s.</p>','<p>Angiotensin-Converting Enzyme (ACE) Inhibitors are a class of blood pressure-lowering medications used predominantly to treat high blood pressure (hypertension) and reduce the risk of having a heart attack, stroke, or heart failure. High blood pressure is a chronic condition characterized by elevated blood vessel pressure. Blood exerts excessive pressure on the walls of blood vessels (arteries), resulting in hypertension. Heart failure can occur when the heart cannot adequately circulate the blood required by the body. The occurrence of a heart attack or stroke is the obstruction of blood supply to the heart muscle. The blockage is typically caused by a buildup of fat and cholesterol in the coronary artery (which supplies blood to the heart).</p>\n\n<p>Lipril 10 Tablet 15&#39;s contain lisinopril, which reduces the production of substances in the body that could increase blood pressure. Lipril 10 Tablet 15&#39;s relaxes and enlarges the blood vessels, making it simpler for the heart to pump blood to all parts of the body, thereby lowering the elevated blood pressure and decreasing the risk of heart failure, heart attack, or stroke.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n	<li>Weakness</li>\n	<li>Hypotension (low blood pressure)</li>\n	<li>Sinusitis (inflammation of the sinus)</li>\n	<li>Shortness of breath</li>\n	<li>Stomach pain</li>\n	<li>Diarrhea</li>\n</ul>','[\"lipril-10mg-171129849154.jpg\"]','LI10',1,'0','2024-03-24 16:42:31','2025-10-08 05:21:18'),(448,0,'Lipril H  5 12.5 mg','lipril-h-5-12.5-mg','tablet','lipril-h-5-12-171129863564.jpg','LI12.5','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>Lisinopril is an angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) inhibitor that works by relaxing blood vessels, thereby lowering blood pressure. This helps to reduce the strain on the heart and improve its efficiency. Hydrochlorothiazide is a diuretic that helps to eliminate excess fluid and sodium from the body, further lowering blood pressure.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Effective blood pressure management: Lipril H 5/12.5 mg is highly effective in controlling high blood pressure, which is a major risk factor for various cardiovascular diseases such as heart attack and stroke. By maintaining optimal blood pressure levels, this medication helps reduce the strain on the heart and blood vessels, promoting better heart health.</p>\n\n<p>Combination therapy: The combination of lisinopril and hydrochlorothiazide in Lipril H 5/12.5 mg offers the advantage of dual action. Lisinopril works to widen the blood vessels, while hydrochlorothiazide helps remove excess fluid from the body. Together, they provide a more comprehensive approach to blood pressure control compared to using a single medication.</p>\n\n<p>Convenience: Lipril H 5/12.5 mg simplifies the treatment regimen for individuals with hypertension by combining two medications into a single tablet. This can make it easier to manage and adhere to the prescribed treatment plan, promoting better long-term blood pressure control.</p>\n\n<p>Potential kidney protection: Lisinopril, as an ACE inhibitor, has 