nce. Don&#39;t eat it, break it, or crush it. It is preferable to take Lipvas 20 Tablet at a set time rather than with or without food.</p>\n\n<p>Functions of Lipvas Tablet</p>\n\n<p>Lipvas 20 Tablet is a statin that lowers cholesterol. It functions by inhibiting the HMG-CoA-reductase enzyme, which the body needs to produce cholesterol. As a result, it reduces triglycerides and &quot;bad&quot; cholesterol (LDL), while increasing &quot;good&quot; cholesterol (HDL).</p>\n\n<p>The advantages of Lipvas Tablet</p>\n\n<p>elevated cholesterol</p>\n\n<p>Lipvas 20 Tablet is a member of the statin drug class. It functions by lowering your blood&#39;s level of &quot;bad&quot; cholesterol (LDL) and increasing the level of &quot;good&quot; cholesterol (HDL). Lowering your cholesterol lowers your risk of developing heart disease and prolongs your lifespan.</p>\n\n<p>To get the most out of this medication, take it frequently and adopt the right lifestyle habits (such eating well and exercising regularly). Even if you feel good, keep taking it.</p>\n\n<p>In order to prevent heart attacks</p>\n\n<p>High cholesterol levels can lead to atherosclerosis, which narrows your blood vessels and increases your risk of heart attack and stroke. Reducing this fat helps you stay healthier for longer by lowering the likelihood of this happening. Despite feeling fine, continue taking this medication.</p>','<p>Lipvas 20 Tablet is a member of the statin drug class. It lowers cholesterol and lowers the chance of developing heart disease. A fatty substance called cholesterol causes your blood vessels to narrow as it accumulates, which can result in a heart attack or stroke.</p>\n\n<p>When taken as directed by a doctor, Lipvas 20 Tablet is a frequently prescribed medication that is thought to be safe for long-term usage. It may be consumed either before or after food. You can take it whenever you like, but try to take it daily at roughly the same time. However, quitting your medication may cause your c