hing, and swelling associated with various skin conditions.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Before using Melamet Cream, it is advisable to consult with a healthcare professional, such as a dermatologist or physician.</li>\n	<li>Allergic Reactions: Individuals with known allergies to any of the active ingredients in Melamet Cream (Hydroquinone, Mometasone, and Tretinoin) or any other similar medications should avoid using this cream. It is important to inform your doctor about any known allergies or sensitivities.</li>\n	<li>Avoid Contact with Sensitive Areas: Melamet Cream should not come into contact with sensitive areas such as the eyes, mouth, nose, ears, or vagina. If accidental contact occurs, rinse thoroughly with water.</li>\n	<li>Pregnancy and Breastfeeding: The safety of using Melamet Cream during pregnancy and breastfeeding has not been established conclusively. It is essential to consult with your doctor if you are pregnant, planning to become pregnant, or breastfeeding before using this cream.</li>\n	<li>Skin Irritation: Some individuals may experience skin irritation, redness, dryness, or a burning sensation when using Melamet Cream. If these symptoms become severe or persistent, discontinue use and consult your doctor.</li>\n</ul>','<p>Melamet cream contains active ingredients such as mometasone, tretinoin, and hydroquinone, which work together as a depigmenting agent for the skin. Its primary purpose is to address moderate-to-severe melasma, which manifests as dark and discolored patches on the skin, known as hyperpigmentation. Additionally, it assists in brightening the complexion and treating senile lentigines, which are dark spots or age spots resulting from sun exposure in older individuals.</p>\n\n<p>Melasma, also referred to as hyperpigmentation, is a condition characterized by the appearance of brown patches on the face, particularly on the nose, cheeks, chin, and forehead. Factors such as hormonal changes during pregnancy or sun exposure contribute to its development. This condition is more commonly observed in women compared to men. Eukroma Plus, Melabest, Melacare cream, and Clear Skin are other medications that contain a combination of mometasone, tretinoin, and hydroquinone as their active components.</p>\n\n<p>By combining mometasone, tretinoin, and hydroquinone, Melamet cream works by inhibiting the metabolic processes responsible for pigmentation, thereby aiding in the lightening of the skin tone.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>The majority of side effects do not necessitate medical attention and tend to resolve as your body adapts to the medication. However, if these side effects persist or cause concern, it is recommended to consult your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>The most coomon side effects are listed below:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Skin pain</li>\n	<li>Acne</li>\n	<li>Redness, irritation, burning, itching or stinging sensation of the skin</li>\n</ul>','[\"melamet-cream-15-gm-171134066880.jpg\"]','ME15',1,'0','2024-03-25 04:42:54','2025-10-08 05:27:00'),(469,0,'Metolar 100mg','metolar-100mg','tablet','metolar-100mg-171134187318.jpg','ME100','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>To ensure optimal results, it is recommended to follow the instructions provided by your healthcare provider or pharmacist when taking this medication. It is important to read and adhere to all the instructions on the medication label. By using the medication as directed, you can maximize its effectiveness and safety.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Hypertension management: Metolar 100mg is widely prescribed for the treatment of high blood pressure. It helps to lower blood pressure and reduce the strain on the heart, thereby reducing the risk of heart attacks, strokes, and other cardiovascular complications.</p>\n\n<p>Angina relief: Metolar 100mg is effective in managing angina, a condition characterized by chest pain or discomfort caused by reduced blood flow to the heart. It helps to relieve the frequency and intensity of angina epis