, such as atrial fibrillation or ventricular tachycardia, by regulating the heart&rsquo;s rhythm and preventing rapid or irregular heartbeats.</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Migraine prevention: Some individuals may find relief from migraines with the use of Metolar 25mg, as it can help reduce the frequency and intensity of migraine headaches.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before starting Metolar 25mg, it is essential to inform your healthcare provider or pharmacist about any allergies you have, including allergies to this medication or other beta-blockers. This information is crucial to ensure your safety and prevent any adverse reactions.</p>\n\n<p>Inform your doctor about your medical history, especially if you have a history of certain conditions such as asthma, diabetes, liver disease, or heart failure. They will consider these factors when determining the appropriate dosage and monitoring your response to the medication.</p>\n\n<p>If you are scheduled to undergo surgery, including dental procedures, it is important to inform your healthcare professional that you are taking Metolar 25mg. They may advise you on whether to temporarily discontinue the medication before the procedure.</p>','<p>Metolar 25mg, also known as Metoprolol 25, is a medication that offers numerous benefits in the management of certain cardiovascular conditions. Metoprolol belongs to a class of medications called beta-blockers, which work by blocking the action of certain natural substances in the body, such as adrenaline, that can increase heart rate and blood pressure.</p>\n\n<p>Here Is some information about Metolar 25mg in a similar format:</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>Most side effects associated with Metolar 25mg are temporary and generally well-tolerated. If you have any concerns or experience any persistent or severe side effects, it is recommended to consult your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>Common side effects may include:</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Fatigue or tiredness</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Dizziness or lighthead