stem.</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Symptom relief: Metolar XR 100mg can alleviate symptoms such as chest pain, shortness of breath, and fatigue, enabling individuals to engage in daily activities with greater comfort and ease.</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Enhanced quality of life: By effectively managing cardiovascular conditions, Metolar XR 100mg can contribute to an improved quality of life, allowing individuals to lead more active and fulfilling lives.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before starting Metolar XR 100mg, it is important to inform your healthcare provider about any allergies or medical conditions you have. Also, disclose any medications you are currently taking, including over-the-counter drugs and herbal supplements, to avoid potential interactions.</p>','<p>Metolar XR 100mg, also known as Metoprolol Succinate Extended-Release 100, is a medication that offers several positive benefits in the treatment of cardiovascular conditions. It belongs to a class of drugs called beta-blockers and is commonly prescribed by doctors to manage various heart-related conditions. Below is some important information about Metolar XR 100mg:</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>While most individuals tolerate Metolar XR 100mg well, some may experience mild and temporary side effects. These side effects may include dizziness, fatigue, slow heartbeat, and mild digestive issues. It is important to discuss any concerns or persistent side effects with your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>Remember, this information is intended for general knowledge and should not replace professional medical advice. It&rsquo;s essential to consult with your healthcare provider for personalized guidance and to address any specific questions or concerns you may have regarding Metolar XR 100mg</p>','[\"metolar-xr-100mg-171134443779.jpg\"]','ME100',1,'0','2024-03-25 05:29:18','2025-10-08 05:27:53'),(473,0,'Micogel 0.02 (15gm)','micogel-0.02-(15gm)','Gel','micogel-0-171134466512.jpg','MI15','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Utilize Micogel Cream 15 g as prescribed by your doctor. Micogel Cream 15 gm may cause erythema, rash, itching, or blister formation at the application site, impaired sense of taste (dysgeusia), headache, itching or burning, stomach/abdominal pain, nausea, vomiting, and diarrhea. Inform your physician if the side effects persist or worsen after a few days.</p>\n\n<p>Micogel Cream 15 g is intended solely for topical use. As directed by your doctor, place a small volume of Micogel Cream 15 gm on your fingertip and apply it as a thin layer to the clean and dry affected area. Avoid getting Micogel Cream 15 g in your sinuses or eyes. In the event of accidental contact with these areas, thoroughly cleanse with water. If your hands are not the afflicted area, wash your hands before and after applying 15 g of Micogel Cream to prevent the spread of infection.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Micogel Cream 15 g is used to treat infections caused by fungi or yeast. It inhibits the proliferation of fungi by targeting the membranes of fungal cells. It can be utilized to treat candidiasis, athlete&#39;s foot, ringworm, and jock itch. The symptoms improve within three to four days of the initial treatment.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Inform your doctor if you are averse to miconazole or any other antifungal agents before using Micogel Cream 15 g. Micogel Cream 15 g should be used with caution in patients with a compromised immune system due to chronic conditions such as HIV or AIDS, as well as those undergoing chemotherapy. Inform your physician if you have previously been diagnosed with diabetes, if you are pregnant, or if you are breastfeeding. Avoid getting this medication in your eyes. If you get any cream in your eyes, promptly rinse with water. Maintain your eyes open while rinsing. Micogel Cream 15 gm is contraindicated in patients with a history of hypersensitivity (e.g., anaphylaxis) to miconazole, milk protein concentrate, or any other component of the product.</p>','<p>Micogel Cream 15 g belongs to the antifungal medication category. It is used to treat skin infections caused by fungi or yeast, such as athlete&#39;s foot (affects toes), jock itch (affects groin), candidiasis (affects mouth, throat, stomach, and vagina), and ringworm (affects skin or scalp) &shy;&shy;&shy;&shy;. Ringworm, athlete&#39;s foot, and jock itch are closely related fungal infections, whereas candidiasis is a yeast infection caused by Candida albicans. These infections are typically found in individuals with a compromised immune system. They can disseminate through contact with the skin.</p>\n\n<p>Micogel Cream 15 gm contains miconazole. Micogel Cream 15 g can reduce infection and inhibit fungal growth. In general, it may take four to seven days for Micogel Cream 15 g to alleviate symptoms. Your doctor will determine the appropriate dosage based on your health condition. Continue using 15 g of Micogel Cream even if the symptoms improve. A relapse of the infection (reappearance of the symptoms) may result from abruptly discontinuing the medication. Therefore, continue treatment as prescribed by your physician to eliminate the infection.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Rashes</li>\n	<li>Redness</li>\n	<li>Itching</li>\n	<li>Burning sensation</li>\n	<li>Blistering at the site of application</li>\n	<li>Diarrhoea</li>\n	<li>Abdominal pain</li>\n</ul>','[\"micogel-0-171134466512.jpg\"]','MI15',1,'0','2024-03-25 05:32:03','2025-10-08 05:25:34'),(474,0,'Mignar 25mg','mignar-25mg','tablet','mignar-25mg-171135234081.webp','MI25','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>It is important to follow your doctor&rsquo;s instructions and the dosage guidelines provided on the medication label when taking Mignar 25mg. Typically, it is taken orally with the first bite of each main meal. Make sure to take the medication exactly as prescribed and avoid skipping doses. It is recommended to continue with a well-balanced diet and regular exercise regimen while using Mignar 25mg.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Mignar 25mg offers several benefits for individuals with type 2 diabetes:</p>\n\n<p>Blood sugar control: Mignar 25mg helps regulate blood sugar levels by delaying the breakdown and absorption of carbohydrates in the body. This can help prevent spikes in blood glucose after meals, leading to better overall glycemic control.</p>\n\n<p>Postprandial glucose management: By slowing down carbohydrate digestion, Mignar 25mg specifically targets post-meal glucose levels, reducing the risk of hyperglycemia and helping to maintain stable blood sugar levels throughout the day.</p>\n\n<p>Adjunct to lifestyle changes: Mignar 25mg is often prescribed alongside lifestyle modifications, such as a healthy diet and regular exercise. It can complement these efforts by providing additional support in managing blood sugar levels.</p>\n\n<p>Weight management: Unlike some other diabetes medications, Mignar 25mg is not associated with weight gain. In fact, it may even help with weight management as it reduces the&nbsp; rise in blood glucose that can contribute to weight gain.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before starting Mignar 25mg, it is important to inform your healthcare provider about any existing medical conditions, allergies, or medications you are currently taking. This will help ensure the medication is suitable for you and minimize the risk of any potential interactions or adverse effects.</p>','<p>Mignar 25mg is a medication that is commonly prescribed to help manage blood sugar levels in individuals with type 2 diabetes. It contains the active ingredient miglitol, which belongs to a class of drugs called alpha-glucosidase inhibitors. Mignar 25mg works by slowing down the digestion and absorption of carbohydrates in the body, thereby helping to control blood glucose levels after meals.</p>\n\n<p>Here Is some important information about Mignar 25mg:</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>Mignar 25mg is generally well-tolerated, but like any medication, it can cause side effects in some individuals. Common side effects may include:</p>\n\n<p>Gastrointestinal symptoms: Mignar 25mg may cause mild gastrointestinal discomfort, such as bloating, flatulence, or diarrhea. These symptoms are often temporary and tend to improve as your body adjusts to the medication.</p>\n\n<p>Hypoglycemia: While Mignar 25mg is less likely to cause hypoglycemia compared to some other diabetes medications, it is still important to monitor your blood sugar levels regularly. If you experience symptoms of low blood sugar, such as dizziness, sweating, or confusion, consult your healthcare provider for appropriate management.</p>','[\"mignar-25mg-171135234081.webp\"]','MI25',1,'0','2024-03-25 07:39:09','2025-10-08 05:28:01'),(475,0,'Mignar 50mg','mignar-50mg','tablet','screenshot-2024-03-25-183144-171137179747.png','MI50','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>It is important to follow your doctor&rsquo;s instructions and read the medication label carefully before taking Mignar 50mg. Typically, the recommended starting dose is 50mg. The dosage may be adjusted by your healthcare provider based on your individual needs and response to the medication.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Managing blood sugar levels: Mignar 50mg plays a crucial role in controlling blood sugar levels in individuals with type 2 diabetes. By slowing down the digestion of carbohydrates, it helps prevent increases in blood sugar levels after meals, leading to better overall glycemic control.</p>\n\n<p>Maintaining a balanced lifestyle: By helping to regulate blood sugar levels, Mignar 50mg can assist individuals with diabetes in maintaining a more balanced lifestyle. Stable blood sugar levels can contribute to improved energy levels, reduced fatigue, and enhanced overall well-being.</p>\n\n<p>Positive impact on long-term health: By effectively managing blood sugar levels, Mignar 50mg can help reduce the risk of complications associated with diabetes, such as cardiovascular disease, nerve damage, kidney problems, and eye-related issues. It is an important component of a comprehensive diabetes treatment plan aimed at preserving long-term health.</p>\n\n<p>Fewer hypoglycemic episodes: Unlike some other diabetes medications, Mignar 50mg is less likely to cause low blood sugar levels (hypoglycemia). This is because it does not stimulate the release of insulin from the pancreas but instead works on slowing down carbohydrate absorption in the gut.</p>\n\n<p>Well-tolerated and safe: Mignar 50mg is generally well-tolerated, and most side effects, if any, are mild and temporary. Common side effects may include flatulence, diarrhea, or stomach discomfort. It is important to discuss any concerns or side effects with your healthcare provider.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before starting Mignar 50mg, inform your healthcare provider about any allergies or sensitivities you may have, as well as your medical history, including any liver or kidney conditions. It is important to disclose all other medications, including over-the-counter and herbal supplements, to avoid potential interactions.</p>\n\n<p>Compliance with dietary recommendations: To maximize the benefits of Mignar 50mg, it is crucial to adhere to a healthy diet plan recommended by your healthcare provider or a registered dietitian. This may involve portion control, balanced meal composition, and timing of carbohydrate intake.</p>\n\n<p>Regular monitoring: Regular monitoring of blood sugar levels, as advised by your doctor, is important to ensure the effectiveness of Mignar 50mg and to make any necessary dosage adjustments. It is essential to maintain open communication with your healthcare team and report any changes or concerns.</p>\n\n<p>Remember to consult your healthcare provider for personalized advice and guidance regarding the use of Mignar 50mg. They can provide the most accurate information based on your specific medical condition and needs.</p>','<p>Mignar 50mg is a medication that is used to help manage and control blood sugar levels in individuals with type 2 diabetes. It contains the active ingredient miglitol, which belongs to a class of drugs called alpha-glucosidase inhibitors. Mignar 50mg works by slowing down the digestion and absorption of carbohydrates in the body, which helps prevent spikes in blood sugar levels after meals.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Here are some important points to know about Mignar 50mg:</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Skin rashes</li>\n	<li>Stomach Pain</li>\n	<li>Diarrhoea</li>\n	<li>Flatulence</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','[\"screenshot-2024-03-25-183144-171137179747.png\"]','MI50',1,'0','2024-03-25 13:03:37','2025-10-08 05:28:13'),(476,0,'Milflox 0.5% 5 ml','milflox-0.5-5-ml','Drops','milflox-0-171137198229.jpg','MI005','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Employ Milflox Eye Drops 5 ml according to the dosage and duration prescribed by your physician. In certain instances, you may experience common eye side effects such as dry eyes, watery eyes, eye pain or discomfort, impaired vision, redness, itching, and irritation. The majority of these adverse effects do not necessitate medical attention and subside over time. However, if the adverse effects persist, consult your physician.</p>\n\n<p>Lie on your stomach and tilt your head rearward. With your index finger, gently pull your lower eyelid to form a compartment. Instill the prescribed number of eyedrops into the crevice of the lower eyelid. Close your eyelids for a minute or two.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Before using Milflox Eye Drops 5 ml, inform your doctor if you have a history of eye surgery or eye conditions such as dry eye syndrome and corneal issues. Avoid touching the dropper with bare hands or bringing it near to the eyelids when administering eye drops, as this could contaminate the dropper tip and solution. Inform your doctor if you are using other eye medications prior to beginning Milflox Eye Drops 5 ml. If you are expectant or breastfeeding, it is recommended to consult your doctor. Milflox Eye Drops 5 ml may cause temporary vision blurring, so avoid driving or operating heavy machinery after use.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Allergies: If you have a known allergy or hypersensitivity to Moxifloxacin or any other fluoroquinolone antibiotics, inform your healthcare provider. Allergic reactions to Milflox can include rash, itching, swelling, severe dizziness, or difficulty breathing. Seek immediate medical attention if you experience any signs of an allergic reaction.</p>\n\n<p>Contact Lenses: Remove contact lenses before instilling Milflox 0.5% eye drops, as the product may contain preservatives or other ingredients that can be absorbed by the lenses. Wait at least 15 minutes after using the eye drops before reinserting contact lenses.</p>\n\n<p>Other Eye Medications: Inform your healthcare provider about all other eye medications or ointments you are using, including prescription, non-prescription, or herbal products. Certain medications may interact with Milflox, affecting its effectiveness or increasing the risk of side effects.</p>','<p>Milflox Eye Drops 5 ml belongs to the class of &#39;antibiotics&#39;, which are primarily used to treat bacterial eye infections, such as bacterial conjunctivitis. A bacterial eye infection occurs when bacteria invade any part of the eyeball or its adjacent tissues, such as the cornea (the transparent front surface of the eye) and the conjunctiva (the thin membrane lining the outer eye and inner eyelids).</p>\n\n<p>Milflox Eye Drops 5 ml contain Moxifloxacin, a bactericidal agent that destroys bacteria responsible for a variety of infections. It prevents bacteria from copying their genetic material (DNA), which prevents them from reproducing and destroys them.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Dry eyes</li>\n	<li>Watery eyes</li>\n	<li>Eye pain or discomfort</li>\n	<li>Blurred vision</li>\n	<li>Redness, itching and irritation of the eyes</li>\n</ul>','[\"milflox-0-171137198229.jpg\"]','MI005',1,'0','2024-03-25 13:06:34','2025-10-08 05:28:23'),(477,0,'Minoz  100mg','minoz-100mg','tablet','minoz-100mg-171138781286.jpg','MI100','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Take 10 tablets of Minoz 100 as prescribed by your doctor. Depending on your medical condition, you should take Minoz 100 Tablet 10s for as long as your physician prescribes. Headache, photosensitivity (extreme sensitivity to ultraviolet (UV) rays from the sun and other light sources), vertigo, vomiting, itching, nausea, dizziness, and diarrhea may occur. The majority of these adverse effects of Minoz 100 Tablet 10s do not necessitate medical attention and subside with time. However, if the adverse effects persist, you should contact your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>Do not crush, chew, or split the capsule; swallow it whole with water.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Minoz 100 Tablet 10&#39;s is an antibiotic belonging to the tetracycline class that is effective against a wide spectrum of bacteria, including gram-negative and gram-positive bacteria, anaerobes, and certain parasites (such as Balantidium coli and Entamoeba species). It is prescribed for the treatment of a variety of bacterial infections of the respiratory tract, urinary tract, gastrointestinal tract, and sexually transmitted infections (such as gonorrhea and syphilis). In addition to this, it is also observed in Rickettsia-caused tick-borne infections (typhus fever) transmitted by ticks. Off-label uses of the medication include acne treatment.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Iron and antacids (such as magnesium hydroxide and aluminum hydroxide) may adhere to and reduce the effectiveness of Minoz 100 Tablet 10 in the gastrointestinal tract. Therefore, at least two hours should pass between the consumption of Minoz 100 Tablet 10s and iron supplements and antacids. Prolonged use of Minoz 100 Tablet 10s during tooth development (pregnancy, infancy, and adolescence up to the age of 8 years) may result in yellow-grey-brown discoloration of the teeth. Do not drink alcohol while taking Minoz 100 Tablet 10&#39;s because it may cause excessive drowsiness. Before using Minoz 100 Tablet 10&#39;s, inform your doctor if you have ever had an allergy to Minoz 100 Tablet 10&#39;s or if you have kidney, liver, or respiratory problems. Use effective birth control to prevent pregnancy while taking these Minoz 100 Tablet 10&#39;s, regardless of your gender. Alcohol should not be consumed while taking Minoz 100 Tablet 10&#39;s, as it may exacerbate the disagreeable side effects. In addition, the use of Minoz 100 Tablet 10&#39;s can occasionally result in antibiotic-associated diarrhea. The Minoz 100 Tablet 10s may make the epidermis more sensitive to sunlight and ultraviolet rays, leading to a more severe sunburn reaction. Therefore, it is recommended to apply sunscreen before venturing outdoors.</p>','<p>Minoz 100 Tablet 10&#39;s belongs to the class of antibiotics known as tetracycline, which is used to treat a variety of bacterial infections. Minoz 100 Tablet 10&#39;s treats urinary tract infections, intestinal infections, respiratory infections, sexually transmitted infections (such as gonorrhea and syphilis), cutaneous infections, and other infections. In addition, Minoz 100 Tablet 10&#39;s treats acne-like lesions resulting from rosacea. The bacterial infection is a condition in which bacteria multiply and induce infection within the body. It can target any part of the body and multiply rapidly. Antibiotics inhibit the proliferation of the microorganisms that cause such infections.</p>\n\n<p>Minoz 100 Tablet 10&#39;s contain the antibiotic Minocycline, which is used to treat a variety of gram-negative, gram-positive, anaerobic, and other bacterial infections. It is a derivative of the tetracycline class of antibiotics that inhibits the process of protein synthesis necessary for bacterial cell proliferation. Consequently, bacterial cells cannot reproduce and develop. It is a bacteriostatic antibiotic, meaning that it inhibits the growth of bacteria but does not necessarily destroy them.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Photosensitivity (extreme sensitivity to ultraviolet (UV) rays from the sun and other light sources)</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Itching</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Diarrhea</li>\n</ul>','[\"minoz-100mg-171138781286.jpg\"]','MI100',1,'0','2024-03-25 17:30:29','2025-10-08 05:28:36'),(478,0,'Mintop Solution 2% (60 ml)','mintop-solution-2-(60-ml)','Solution','mintop-solution-2-60-ml-171138805578.jpg','Mi002','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>The dosage and duration will be recommended by your doctor based on your situation. Changes in the color or texture of the hair, excessive hair growth, headaches, itching, skin irritation, dryness, shortness of breath, scaling of the skin, and redness are a few of the side effects of Mintop 2% Solution 60 ml that are frequently reported. Most of the time, these adverse effects subside during the course of treatment without the need for medical attention. Consult a doctor if the negative effects continue or get worse.</p>\n\n<p>The solution/spray form often includes an extended spray-tip applicator and a spray pump applicator. One pump the spray pump while aiming it at the scalp&#39;s bald spots. Use your fingertips to spread the solution after that. Avoid inhaling the spray mist, and after use, wash your hands thoroughly. To apply the solution to broad areas of skin, use the spray pump applicator; for smaller areas, use the spray-tip applicator.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Solution Mintop 2% A vasodilator used to treat alopecia (hair loss) is 60 ml. It promotes hair growth and guards against balding. Solution Mintop 2% In order to enhance blood flow, 60 ml activates potassium channels and expands blood vessels. By encouraging blood flow to the hair follicles, this vasodilation process ensures that the hair cells receive enough nutrients and oxygen. By giving the hair cell oxygen and nutrients, this mechanism both delays cell death and promotes hair growth.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Use as directed: Mintop 2% Solution should be used as directed by a healthcare professional or as indicated on the packaging. Follow the recommended dosage and application instructions carefully.</p>\n\n<p>Avoid contact with eyes and sensitive areas: Take care to avoid contact with eyes, mucous membranes, and other sensitive areas of the body. If accidental contact occurs, rinse thoroughly with water.</p>\n\n<p>Do not use on broken or irritated scalp: Mintop 2% Solution should not be applied to a scalp that is irritated, sunburned, or has any open wounds or cuts. Wait for the scalp to heal before using the solution.</p>\n\n<p>Consult a healthcare professional for underlying conditions: If you have any underlying medical conditions, such as heart disease, low blood pressure, or any scalp or skin disorders, it is important to consult with a healthcare professional before using Mintop 2% Solution.</p>\n\n<p>Allergic reactions: If you have a known allergy to minoxidil or any other ingredients in Mintop 2% Solution, avoid using the product. If you experience any signs of an allergic reaction, such as rash, itching, or swelling, discontinue use and seek medical attention.</p>','<p>Solution Mintop 2% 60 ml is categorized as a &quot;vasodilator,&quot; which is a drug used to treat alopecia (hair loss). Hair growth is stimulated and the balding process is slowed down by Mintop 2% Solution 60 ml. Alopecia refers to hair loss or thinning on the scalp or any other part of the body.</p>\n\n<p>The vasodilator &quot;Minoxidil,&quot; which opens blood vessels, is present in Mintop 2% Solution 60 ml. By supplying the hair follicles with oxygen, blood, and nutrients, this vasodilation process aids in preventing the death of hair cells and fostering the creation of new hair.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Changes in the colour/texture of the hair</li>\n	<li>Excessive hair growth</li>\n	<li>Heada