lergy-causing agents) such as pollen, grit, etc. Certain foods have been identified as allergens. Avoid combining Montair-10 Tablet 15s with alcohol or other antidepressants in order to maintain mental acuity. Even if you are symptom-free and feeling well, do not abruptly cease taking Montair-10 Tablet 15s, as doing so could trigger an asthma attack.</p>','<p>Montair-10 Tablet 15&#39;s contain an anti-allergic medication that is used primarily to treat seasonal allergies and asthma. An allergy is the immune system&#39;s response to normally harmless foreign substances. These foreign substances are referred to as &#39;allergens&#39; Asthma is a local inflammatory disease of the lungs and airways characterized by excessive airway constriction and the production of excess mucus in response to specific stimuli such as viruses, allergens, and exercise.</p>\n\n<p>Montair-10 Tablet 15&#39;s contains a leukotriene antagonist, Montelukast. It reduces inflammation and swelling of the airways in the lungs by inhibiting a chemical messenger (leukotriene). This facilitates respiration and prevents asthma attacks. When you have an allergic reaction to dust or pollen, your body also produces leukotrienes. Montair-10 Tablet 15 helps reduce leukotriene levels and prevents the onset of symptoms.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Diarrhoea</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Abdominal cramp</li>\n	<li>Flu-like symptoms</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n</ul>','[\"montaire-10-171138938675.jpg\"]','MO10',1,'0','2024-03-25 17:56:34','2025-10-08 05:31:01'),(485,0,'Montair Chewable Tablets 4mg','montair-chewable-tablets-4mg','Chewable Tablets','montair-chewable-tablets-4mg-171145742041.webp','MO004','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Give your child one Montair 4mg Chewable Tablet at a fixed time before or after sustenance, according to the prescribed dose, time, and method. You may need to administer the medication to your child for a few weeks prior to the onset of asthma symptoms. For asthma, it is recommended to administer Montair 4mg Chewable Tablet in the evening or two hours prior to physical activity. Depending on the timing of symptom onset, allergy medication is best administered in the evening. If your child has both, consider administering it in the evening. If your child vomits within 30 minutes of taking this medication, administer the same dose again, but forego the dose if it is time for the next dose.</p>\n\n<p>Use as directed by your physician or consult the product&#39;s label prior to administration. Use this medication orally. Completely chew it before ingesting, or as directed by your physician. Montair 4mg Chewable Tablets may be consumed with or without food, but it is best to adhere to a regular schedule.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Asthma Control: Montair Chewable Tablets 4mg can help in controlling and preventing asthma symptoms in children. It works by reducing airway inflammation and constriction, making it easier for children to breathe and reducing symptoms such as wheezing, coughing, shortness of breath, and chest tightness.</p>\n\n<p>Allergic Rhinitis Relief: These chewable tablets can provide relief from symptoms of allergic rhinitis in children, including sneezing, runny or itchy nose, and nasal congestion. It helps to alleviate inflammation and the release of certain chemicals responsible for allergy symptoms.</p>\n\n<p>Exercise-Induced Asthma Prevention: Montair Chewable Tablets 4mg can be beneficial in preventing exercise-induced bronchoconstriction, a condition where physical activity triggers asthma symptoms in children. By taking the medication before exercise, it helps to keep the airways open and prevent asthma symptoms during physical exertion.</p>\n\n<p>Reduction in Allergy-Related Symptoms: Montair Chewable Tablets 4mg may also help reduce other allergy-related symptoms in children, such as itchy and watery eyes and skin reactions.</p>\n\n<p>Once-Daily Dosage: These chewable tablets are typically taken once daily, making it convenient for children to take their medication consistently.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Allergies: If your child has a known allergy or hypersensitivity to Montelukast or any other ingredients in the medication, it is important to inform your healthcare provider. Allergic reactions may include rash, itching, swelling, severe dizziness, or difficulty breathing. Seek immediate medical attention if your child experiences any signs of an allergic reaction.</p>\n\n<p>Asthma Attacks: Montair Chewable Tablets 4mg should not be used to relieve acute asthma attacks. It is not a rescue medication and does not provide immediate relief. Ensure your child has a separate rescue inhaler or medication for the treatment of asthma attacks.</p>\n\n<p>Regular Use: Montair Chewable Tablets 4mg are typically used for long-term management and prevention of asthma and allergic rhinitis symptoms. It is important to administer the medication regularly as prescribed by your healthcare provider, even if your child&#39;s symptoms improve or they are free from symptoms.</p>\n\n<p>Drug Interactions: Inform your healthcare provider about all the medications, supplements, or herbal products your child is currently taking. Montelukast can interact with certain medications, such as phenobarbital, phenytoin, rifampin, and certain antifungal drugs. These interactions may affect the effectiveness or safety of Montair Chewable Tablets 4mg.</p>','<p>Children are given Montair 4mg Chewable Tablet to prevent asthma attacks. Additionally, it may be used to alleviate respiratory difficulties brought on by strenuous physical activity. This medication also assists in the treatment of skin and seasonal allergy symptoms, including runny nose, sneezing, itching, puffiness, congestion, and watery eyes.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Diarrhea</li>\n	<li>Abdominal pain</li>\n</ul>','[\"montair-chewable-tablets-4mg-171145742041.webp\"]','MO004',1,'0','2024-03-26 12:50:33','2025-10-08 05:30:29'),(486,0,'Montair LC Kid (4+2.5mg)','montair-lc-kid-(4+2.5mg)','tablet','montair-lc-kid-4-2-171145760277.jpg','MO2.5','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Montair LC Kid Tablet 10&#39;s are consumed with or without food, according to the doctor-prescribed dosage and duration. Your dosage will be based on your medical condition and response to Montair LC Kid Tablet 10&#39;s. Occasionally, you may experience nausea, rash, diarrhea, vomiting, parched mouth, headache, rash, and fatigue. The majority of these side effects of Montair LC Kid Tablet 10&#39;s are transient, do not necessitate medical attention, and resolve progressively over time. However, if the adverse effects persist, consult your physician.</p>\n\n<p>Swallow it whole with water; do not pulverize, chew, or dissolve it.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>The anti-allergic medication Montair LC Kid Tablet 10&#39;s contains Levocetirizine and Montelukast. Levocetirizine is an antihistamine (allergy medication) that inhibits the effects of a naturally occurring chemical messenger (histamine) implicated in allergic reactions. Consequently, it alleviates allergy symptoms such as sneezing, runny nose, watery eyes, itching, puffiness, congestion, and stiffness. Montelukast, on the other hand, is a leukotriene antagonist that inhibits a chemical messenger (leukotriene) and reduces inflammation and swelling in the nose and lungs, making it easier to breathe. Together, they help to alleviate symptoms and treat a wide variety of allergic conditions, thereby reducing symptoms such as sneezing, runny nose, wheezing, etc.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Inform your doctor if you are expectant, breastfeeding, or planning to become pregnant. If you have kidney disease, your doctor may need to modify your dosage based on the severity of your condition. Before taking Montair LC Kid Tablet 10&#39;s, you should inform your doctor if you have difficulty discharging urine and epilepsy (fits). If you are scheduled for a skin test, your doctor may advise you to cease taking Montair LC Kid Tablet 10&#39;s 72 hours prior to the test, as it reduces skin prick test response. After taking Montair LC Kid Tablet 10&#39;s, patients should avoid engaging in activities that require excessive mental alertness, such as operating apparatus or driving a motor vehicle. If you experience aggression, anxiety, or depression after taking Montair LC Kid Tablet 10&#39;s, please contact your doctor immediately. It is recommended to avoid allergens (allergy-causing agents) such as pollen, grit, etc. Certain foods are known to cause you to develop allergies.</p>','<p>Levocetirizine belongs to the antihistamine or anti-allergic drug class. It treats sneezing, a runny nose, and itchy skin caused by numerous allergies and hay fever (seasonal allergy). An allergy is the immune system&#39;s response to normally harmless foreign substances. These foreign substances are known as &#39;allergens.&#39; The allergic condition varies between individuals. Some individuals may be allergic to particular foods and seasonal allergens, such as hay fever, pollen, and pet dander. Coughing, which occurs as a reflex action in the pharynx when mucus or a foreign irritant enters the respiratory system, is one of the most prominent allergy symptoms.</p>\n\n<p>Montair LC Kid Tablet 10&#39;s is a combination of two anti-allergic medications, Levocetirizine and Montelukast, used predominantly to treat allergic symptoms. Levocetirizine inhibits the effects of histamine, a naturally occurring chemical messenger implicated in allergic reactions. It alleviates allergy symptoms including sneezing, a runny nose, watery eyes, itching, swelling, congestion, and fatigue. Montelukast is a leukotriene antagonist that diminishes inflammation and swelling in the nose by blocking a chemical messenger (leukotriene). Together, they serve to ameliorate symptoms and alleviate allergic symptoms.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Skin rash</li>\n	<li>Diarrhoea</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Dry mouth</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Skin rash</li>\n</ul>','[\"montair-lc-kid-4-2-171145760277.jpg\"]','MO2.5',1,'0','2024-03-26 12:53:32','2025-10-08 05:30:38'),(487,0,'Mysoline 250mg','mysoline-250mg','tablet','mysoline-250mg-171145856481.jpg','MY250','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Take 10 tablets of Mysoline 250 with or without sustenance. Depending on your medical condition, you should take Mysoline 250 Tablet 10&#39;s for as long as your doctor has prescribed. You may experience nausea, headache, vomiting, fatigue, vertigo, visual impairment, low energy, impaired coordination, and nystagmus (involuntary eye movement) in some cases. The majority of these adverse effects do not necessitate medical attention and will subside over time. However, you should consult your physician if you experience these side effects frequently.</p>\n\n<p>It should be swallowed whole with water; it should not be crushed or chewed.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Mysoline 250 Tablet 10&#39;s belongs to the class of drugs known as anticonvulsants. Primidone is used to control epilepsy (fits) symptoms. Mysoline 250 Tablet 10&#39;s are also used to prevent and control convulsions during or after severe head trauma or brain surgery. Trigeminal neuralgia (facial nerve pain) can also be treated with Mysoline 250 Tablet 10s. Mysoline 250 Tablet 10 works by inhibiting the brain&#39;s hyperactivity, which causes seizures. Consequently, Mysoline 250 Tablet 10 aids in the control of epileptic fits characterized by muscle spasms and twitching.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Avoid taking Mysoline 250 Tablet 10&#39;s if you have an allergy to any of its ingredients. Do not skip doses or abruptly cease taking Mysoline 250 Tablet 10&#39;s without consulting your doctor, as doing so may increase your risk of seizures. Consult your physician if you have heart, kidney, or liver issues. Avoid ingesting Mysoline 250 Tablet 10&#39;s unless prescribed by your doctor if you are pregnant or breastfeeding. Alcohol consumption should be avoided while taking Mysoline 250 Tablet 10&#39;s, as it may cause undesirable adverse effects. Children should not use Mysoline 250 Tablet 10&#39;s unless prescribed. Inform your physician if you have diabetes, as Mysoline 250 Tablet 10&#39;s ingestion affects blood sugar levels. Mysoline 250 Tablet 10s may cause vertigo; therefore, caution should be exercised while driving or operating heavy machinery.</p>','<p>Mysoline 250 Tablet 10&#39;s is a type of anticonvulsant medication used to control numerous epileptic conditions (fits), prevent seizures, and treat attacks of shaking (essential tremor). Epilepsy is a disorder of the central nervous system characterized by an abrupt surge of electrical activity in the brain, which results in seizures, abnormal behavior, and loss of consciousness. The absence (petit mal) seizure medication Mysoline 250 Tablet 10&#39;s is ineffective.</p>\n\n<p>Mysoline 250 Tablet 10&#39;s contain &#39;Primidone&#39;, which increases the activity of a chemical messenger (GABA) that suppresses the brain&#39;s excessive and aberrant nerve cell activity. Our brain cells (neurons) function normally by discharging at a specific rate. During an epileptic attack or seizure, however, our neurons are forced to function more quickly than under normal circumstances. Mysoline 250 Tablet 10s prevents neurons from operating at a rapid rate, thereby preventing all brain cells from rapidly and uncontrollably discharging in unison. As a consequence, only the onset of epileptic seizures is stopped.</p>','<p>Side eefects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n	<li>Drowsiness</li>\n	<li>Low energy</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Vertigo</li>\n</ul>','[\"mysoline-250mg-171145856481.jpg\"]','MY250',1,'0','2024-03-26 13:09:34','2025-10-08 05:30:45'),(488,0,'Naltima 50 mg','naltima-50-mg','tablet','naltima-50-mg-171145871618.jpg','NA50','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Take Naltima 50 Tablet 10&#39;s as prescribed by your physician. Nausea, vomiting, injection site reactions (including induration, pruritus, nodules and swelling), muscle cramps, dizziness or syncope, drowsiness or sedation, anorexia (eating disorder), decreased appetite or other appetite disorders, hepatic enzyme abnormalities, cold, insomnia, and toothache may occur in some cases. Not everyone will experience the aforementioned side effects. Consult a doctor if Naltima 50 Tablet 10&#39;s causes severe discomfort.</p>\n\n<p>Naltima 50 Tablet 10&#39;s contains naltrexone. It is a member of the &#39;opioid-antagonist&#39; class of drugs used to treat alcohol dependence (chronic alcoholism) and opioid dependence. It functions by inhibiting the effect of opioid receptors and decreasing alcohol and opioid cravings. Nonetheless, it is used in conjunction with counseling and social support to assist alcoholics in abstaining from alcohol.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Naltima 50 Tablet 10&#39;s contains naltrexone. It pertains to the class of drugs known as &#39;opioid-antagonist&#39; that are used to treat alcohol dependence (chronic alcoholism) and opioid dependence. It works by inhibiting the effect of opioid receptors and reducing alcohol and opioid cravings and impulses. Still, it is used in conjunction with counseling and social support to assist alcohol-dependent patients abstain from drinking.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Inform your doctor of all your medical conditions (especially hepatitis or liver failure), allergic reactions (to food and medications), and medications you are currently taking (especially opioid analgesics) prior to receiving a prescription for Naltima 50 Tablet 10&#39;s. Also, inform your doctor if you are pregnant, breastfeeding, or intending to become pregnant. The use of Naltima 50 Tablet 10 is contraindicated in patients with current physiologic opioid dependence, patients in acute opioid withdrawal, or anyone who has failed the naloxone challenge test or a urine opioid screen. If you experience vertigo or sedation while taking Naltima 50 Tablet 10s, do not drive or operate heavy machinery until you have returned to normal. Do not use other medications, especially those containing opioids, without the doctor&#39;s approval.</p>','<p>Naltima 50 Tablet 10&#39;s belong to the class of drugs known as &#39;opioid-antagonist&#39; that are used to treat alcohol dependence (chronic alcoholism) and opioid dependence. Alcohol dependence is a chronic medical condition characterized by a current or past history of excessive drinking, a strong craving for alcohol, continued use despite recurrent drinking-related problems, and an inability to control alcohol consumption. Opioid dependence is a condition in which an individual becomes physiologically dependent on a substance; their body requires the substance to prevent withdrawal.</p>\n\n<p>Naltima 50 Tablet 10&#39;s contains &#39;naltrexone&#39;. It functions by inhibiting the effect of opioid receptors and decreasing alcohol and opioid cravings. Nonetheless, it is used in conjunction with counseling and social support to assist alcoholics in abstaining from alcohol.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Injection site reactions (induration, pruritus, nodules and swelling)</li>\n	<li>Muscle cramps</li>\n	<li>Dizziness or syncope</li>\n	<li>Somnolence or sedation</li>\n	<li>Anorexia (eating disorder)</li>\n</ul>','[\"naltima-50-mg-171145871618.jpg\"]','NA50',1,'0','2024-03-26 13:12:05','2025-10-08 05:30:53'),(489,0,'Naprosyn 250 +','naprosyn-250-+','tablet','naprosyn-250-171145896510.jpg','NA250','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Take 15 tablets of Naprosyn 250 as prescribed. Based on your medical condition, your physician will advise you on how frequently to take Naprosyn 250 Tablet 15&#39;s. In some instances, side effects may include indigestion, heartburn, stomach discomfort, nausea, headache, vertigo, drowsiness, bruising, itching, rash, and ringing in the ears. The majority of these adverse effects of Naprosyn 250 Tablet 15&#39;s do not require medical attention and subside with time. However, if side effects persist or worsen, consult your physician.</p>\n\n<p>Take it with or after food to prevent gastric upset, or as directed by your doctor. It should be ingested whole with a glass of water. Do not chew it or pulverize it.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>In conditions such as osteoarthritis, rheumatoid arthritis, ankylosing spondylitis (pain and stiffness in the backbone), cervical spondylitis (wear and tear of spinal discs in neck), and acute gout (severe pain due to excess uric acid), Naprosyn 250 Tablet 15&#39;s are used to reduce pain and swelling in muscles and joints. In addition, it is utilized to treat fibrositis (muscle pain and rigidity), tenosynovitis (tendonitis), low back pain, strains, and sprains.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Please inform your doctor if you are allergic to Naprosyn 250 Tablet 15&#39;s or any other medications. Pregnant women should not take Naprosyn 250 Tablet 15&#39;s, particularly in the third trimester, because it may harm the baby. Therefore, pregnant or nursing women should consult a physician prior to ingesting Naprosyn 250 Tablet 15&#39;s. The risk of gastrointestinal hemorrhage is greater in elderly patients, so the doctor may reduce their dosage. Consuming alcohol while taking 15 tablets of Naprosyn 250 may increase the risk of gastrointestinal bleeding. Naprosyn 250 Tablet 15&#39;s may increase the risk of fatal cardiac complications such as myocardial infarction and stroke. If you observe bleeding from your back passage as black, sticky motions or bloody stools, blood in vomit, or stomach pain spreading to your back, stop taking Naprosyn 250 Tablet 15&#39;s immediately and contact your doctor. It should not be administered to patients who have recently undergone or are about to undergo cardiac bypass surgery. Naprosyn 250 Tablet 15&#39;s increases the risk of fatal gastrointestinal complications such as gastrointestinal hemorrhage, ulceration, and perforation of the stomach or intestines. If you experience weight loss, diarrhea, pain, or vomiting, please cease taking Naprosyn 250 Tablet 15&#39;s and consult a doctor immediately, as these could be indications of Crohn&#39;s disease or ulcerative colitis (swelling in the digestive tract).</p>','<p>Non-steroidal anti-inflammatory medications (NSAIDs) are the class of analgesics to which Naprosyn 250 Tablet 15 belongs. In conditions such as osteoarthritis, rheumatoid arthritis, ankylosing spondylitis (pain and stiffness in the backbone), cervical spondylitis (wear and tear of spinal discs in neck), and acute gout (severe pain due to excess uric acid), Naprosyn 250 Tablet 15&#39;s are used to reduce pain and swelling in muscles and joints. Arthritis is a condition that produces inflammation of one or more joints, resulting in progressive joint pain and stiffness.</p>\n\n<p>The Naproxen in Naprosyn 250 Tablet 15&#39;s functions by inhibiting the cyclo-oxygenase (COX) enzyme in the body, which is involved in the production of certain chemical substances, such as prostaglandins, that cause pain and inflammation. Consequently, it alleviates the pain and edema associated with various types of arthritis.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Indigestion</li>\n	<li>Heartburn</li>\n	<li>Stomach pain</li>\n	<li>Constipation</li>\n	<li>Gas</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n</ul>','[\"naprosyn-250-171145896510.jpg\"]','NA250',1,'0','2024-03-26 13:16:16','2025-10-08 05:32:11'),(490,0,'Naprosyn 500 +','naprosyn-500-+','tablet','naprosyn-500-171145913181.jpg','NA500','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Take 15 tablets of Naprosyn 500 as prescribed. Depending on your medical condition, your doctor will advise you on how frequently to take 15 Naprosyn 500 Tablets. In some instances, side effects may include indigestion, heartburn, stomach discomfort, nausea, headache, vertigo, drowsiness, bruising, itching, rash, and ringing in the ears. The majority of these adverse effects of Naprosyn 500 Tablet 15&#39;s do not necessitate medical attention and subside with time. However, if side effects persist or worsen, consult your physician.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;Take it with or after food to prevent gastric upset, or as directed by your doctor. It should be ingested whole with a glass of water. Do not chew it or pulverize it.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>In conditions such as osteoarthritis, rheumatoid arthritis, ankylosing spondylitis (pain and stiffness in the backbone), cervical spondylitis (wear and tear of spinal discs in neck), and acute gout (severe pain due to excess uric acid), Naprosyn 500 Tablet 15&#39;s are used to reduce pain and swelling in muscles and joints. In addition, it is utilized to treat fibrositis (muscle pain and rigidity), tenosynovitis (tendonitis), low back pain, strains, and sprains.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Please inform your physician if you are allergic to Naprosyn 500 Tablet 15&#39;s or any other drugs. Naprosyn 500 Tablet 15&#39;s is contraindicated for pregnant women, particularly in the third trimester, as it may affect the fetus. Women who are pregnant or lactating should consult a physician prior to taking Naprosyn 500 Tablet 15&#39;s. Because elderly patients are at a greater risk for gastrointestinal hemorrhage, the doctor may reduce their dosage. Alcohol may increase the risk of gastrointestinal bleeding while taking Naprosyn 500 Tablet 15&#39;s. Naprosyn 500 Tablet 15&#39;s may increase the risk of life-threatening cardiac conditions, such as myocardial infarction and stroke. If you observe bleeding from your back passage as black sticky motions or bloody stools, blood in vomit, or stomach pain that spreads to your back, please stop taking Naprosyn 500 Tablet 15&#39;s immediately and contact your doctor. Patients who have recently undergone or are about to undergo heart bypass surgery should not use this medication. Naprosyn 500 Tablet 15&#39;s increases the risk of life-threatening gastrointestinal conditions such as gastrointestinal hemorrhage, ulceration, and perforation of the stomach or intestines. If you experience weight loss, diarrhea, pain, or vomiting, please cease taking Naprosyn 500 Tablet 15&#39;s and consult a doctor immediately, as these could be signs of worsening Crohn&#39;s disease or ulcerative colitis (inflammation of the digestive tract).</p>','<p>Naprosyn 500 Tablet 15&#39;s belong to the class of analgesics known as nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory medications (NSAIDs). Naprosyn 500 Tablet 15&#39;s is primarily used to reduce pain and inflammation in muscles and joints in conditions such as osteoarthritis, rheumatoid arthritis, ankylosing spondylitis (pain and stiffness in the backbone), cervical spondylitis (wear and tear of spinal discs in neck), and acute gout (severe pain caused by an excess of uric acid). Arthritis is a condition that produces swelling of one or more joints, resulting in progressive pain and stiffness of the affected joints.</p>\n\n<p>Naproxen is contained in Naprosyn 500 Tablet 15&#39;s. It functions by inhibiting the cyclo-oxygenase (COX) enzyme in the body, which is involved in the production of pain- and inflammation-causing chemical substances such as prostaglandins. As a result, it alleviates the pain and swelling caused by various varieties of arthritis.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Indigestion</li>\n	<li>Heartburn</li>\n	<li>Stomach pain</li>\n	<li>Constipation</li>\n	<li>Gas</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n</ul>','[\"naprosyn-500-171145913181.jpg\"]','NA500',1,'0','2024-03-26 13:19:41','2025-10-08 05:32:32'),(491,0,'Naturogest 200mg','naturogest-200mg','Capsule','naturogest-200mg-171145936355.jpg','NA200','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>To ensure optimal results, it is recommended to follow the instructions provided by your healthcare provider or pharmacist when taking this medication. It is important to read and adhere to all the instructions on the medication label. By using the medication as directed, you can maximize its effectiveness and safety.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Hormone Replacement Therapy (HRT): Naturogest 200mg is often used as part of hormone replacement therapy for women who are experiencing menopausal symptoms. It helps alleviate symptoms such as hot flashes, night sweats, mood swings, and vaginal dryness, promoting overall well-being during this transitional phase.</p>\n\n<p>Support in Assisted Reproductive Techniques (ART): Naturogest 200mg is frequently prescribed in assisted reproductive techniques, such as in vitro fertilization (IVF) or intrauterine insemination (IUI). Progesterone plays a vital role in preparing the uterus for implantation and maintaining a pregnancy. Naturogest helps support the growth of the uterine lining, making it a valuable aid in fertility treatments.</p>\n\n<p>Prevention of Miscarriage: In certain cases, Naturogest 200mg may be prescribed to women with a history of recurrent miscarriages. Progesterone supplementation helps support the early stages of pregnancy and may reduce the risk of miscarriage in some individuals.</p>\n\n<p>Menstrual Irregularities: Naturogest 200mg can also be used to regulate menstrual cycles in women with irregular periods or conditions such as polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS). By balancing hormonal levels, it promotes more regular and predictable menstruation.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before starting Naturogest 200mg, it is important to discuss your medical history, current medications, and any allergies with your healthcare provider. Your doctor will consider potential interactions or contraindications, ensuring the medication is safe and suitable for you.</p>','<p>Naturogest 200mg is a medication that contains progesterone, a hormone naturally produced in the body. It is commonly prescribed to women for various gynecological conditions and hormonal imbalances. This medication comes in the form of soft gelatin capsules and is typically taken orally or inserted vaginally.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>Naturogest 200mg is generally well-tolerated, and most women experience minimal side effects. However, like any medication, it may cause some temporary and mild side effects. It&rsquo;s important to remember that not everyone will experience these side effects, and they usually resolve on their own. Common side effects may include:</p>\n\n<p>Breast Tenderness: Some women may experience mild breast tenderness while taking Naturogest. This is usually temporary and subsides with continued use.</p>\n\n<p>Mild Drowsiness or Fatigue: Occasionally, Naturogest can cause mild drowsiness or fatigue. If you experience these symptoms, it is advisable to take the medication at bedtime to minimize any potential discomfort.</p>','[\"naturogest-200mg-171145936355.jpg\"]','NA200',1,'0','2024-03-26 13:24:03','2025-10-08 05:32:50'),(492,0,'Nebicard 2.5 mg','nebicard-2.5-mg','tablet','nebicard-2-171147127650.jpg','NE2.5','<p>Utilising the Nebicard Tablet</p>\n\n<p>Follow your doctor&#39;s instructions for this medication&#39;s dosage and duration. Take it all in at once. Don&#39;t eat it, break it, or crush it. While the Nebicard 2.5 Tablet can be taken any way, it is preferable to take it at a set time.</p>\n\n<p>Procedure for Nebicard Tablet</p>\n\n<p>A beta blocker with a focus on the heart is Nebicard 2.5 Tablet. It functions by reducing heart rate and improving the heart&#39;s ability to pump blood throughout the body.</p>\n\n<p>Nebicard Tablet Uses</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hypertension (high blood pressure) treatment</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Avoiding heart attacks</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Defending against stroke</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Avoiding migraines</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Advantages of the Nebicard Tablet</p>\n\n<p>Hypertension (high blood pressure) treatment</p>\n\n<p>Nebicard 2.5 Tablet is a member of the long-acting beta-blocker class of medications. It functions by obstructing the impact of particular substances on your blood vessels and heart. Your heart beats more gently and more slowly as a result of it. By doing so, you lower your blood pressure and lessen your chance of experiencing a stroke, heart attack, other cardiac conditions, or renal issues in the future. Continue taking this medication even if you feel OK because it must be taken consistently to be successful. Do not quit without consulting your physician.</p>\n\n<p>In order to prevent heart attacks</p>\n\n<p>Nebicard 2.5 Tablet lowers blood pressure and facilitates the easier circulation of blood throughout the body via the heart. You are less likely to experience a heart attack as a result. If administered right away following a heart attack, it can also lower the risk of dying. Continue taking this medication even if you feel OK because it must be taken consistently to be successful. Do not quit without consulting your physician.</p>\n\n<p>Nebicard 2.5 Tablet lowers the risk of future strokes when used in stroke prevention. Your blood pressure is lowered, and your heart has an easier time pumping blood throughout your body. You have a lower likelihood of getting a stroke as a result. For the most advantage, follow the doctor&#39;s instructions exactly.</p>\n\n<p>Nebicard 2.5 Tablet for Migraine Prevention aids in enhancing blood flow to the brain and stops the aberrant muscle activity that causes migraines. Although it is a very effective medication for avoiding migraines, an attack that has already begun cannot be treated with it. The medication can assist you in getting through your daily tasks and enhancing your quality of life by preventing and minimising the frequency of migraine attacks.</p>','<p>Nebicard 2.5 Tablet is a member of the beta-blocker class of drugs. Hypertension, or high blood pressure, is treated with it. Additionally, it aids in the prevention of migraines, heart attacks, and stroke in the future.</p>\n\n<p>The Nebicard 2.5 Tablet can also be used to treat symptoms brought on by an overactive thyroid. It may be prescribed both on its own and in combination with other drugs. The dosage and frequency depend on the ailment you are treating and how serious it is. You can take it on an empty stomach or with food, but for the best results, take it consistently at the same time every day. Before you experience the full benefits of this medication, it could take a few weeks, and you might need to take it for the rest of your life. Even if you feel fine, it&#39;s still crucial to keep taking the medication. Most people with high blood pressure don&#39;t feel sick, and your condition could get worse if you stop taking your medication. Lifestyle modifications include a low-fat diet, regular exercise, and quitting smoking improve how well this medication works.</p>\n\n<p>This medication&#39;s primary side effects are weariness, headaches, slow heartbeat, feeling lightheaded, and nausea. These are often minor and transient. Some persons may experience low blood pressure or shortness of breath as a result. Your doctor will likely start the medication at a low dose and gradually raise it to limit the risk of side effects. If the adverse effects worry you or do not go away, speak with your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>If you have any liver issues, let your doctor know before taking it. Additionally, it might not be appropriate for those who have low blood pressure, significant circulation issues, severe heart failure, or a slow heartbeat. Before using it, women who are pregnant or nursing should also visit their doctor. To determine whether this medication is appropriate for you to use, you must speak with your doctor. To ensure that this medication is working as intended, you should routinely have your blood pressure monitored. Avoid consuming alcohol since it may make some adverse effects worse.</p>','<p>Side Effects</p>\n\n<p>The majority of adverse effects are temporary and go away as your body becomes used to the medication. If they persist or you&#39;re concerned about them, speak with your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>Nebicard common side effects</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Nausea</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Headache</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; sluggish heartbeat</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tiredness Constipation</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Diarrhea</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Dizziness</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>','[\"nebicard-2-171147127650.jpg\"]','NE2.5',1,'0','2024-03-26 16:41:27','2025-10-08 05:33:08'),(493,0,'Nevanac Eye Drop 5ml','nevanac-eye-drop-5ml','Drops','nevanac-eye-drop-5ml-171147148484.jpg','NE005','<p>How to Use:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Thoroughly wash your hands before and after using Nevanac Ophthalmic Suspension (5 ml).</li>\n	<li>Lie down and tilt your head backward.</li>\n	<li>Gently pull your lower eyelid with your index finger to create a small pocket.</li>\n	<li>Following your doctor&#39;s guidance, instill the prescribed number of drops into the pocket formed by the lower eyelid.</li>\n	<li>Close your eyes and keep them shut for 1-2 minutes to allow the medication to distribute.</li>\n	<li>After use, securely replace the outer cap of the container.</li>\n	<li>Avoid touching the tip of the container to your eye, eyelids, or surrounding areas to prevent any potential contamination of Nevanac Ophthalmic Suspension 5 ml.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Nevanac Ophthalmic Suspension 5 ml falls under the category of nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs) and is prescribed to prevent and alleviate pain and inflammation following cataract surgery. It is also used to reduce the risk of macular edema after cataract surgery. The active ingredient in Nevanac Ophthalmic Suspension 5 ml is nepafenac. This medication works by blocking the action of prostaglandin H synthase (cyclooxygenase), an enzyme necessary for the production of prostaglandins. Prostaglandins are responsible for causing pain, redness, and inflammation in the eyes. By inhibiting prostaglandins, Nevanac Ophthalmic Suspension (5 ml) provides relief from these conditions.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Use Nevanac eye drops only as directed for eye-related conditions.</p>\n\n<p>Wash your hands before and after using the drops to maintain cleanliness.</p>\n\n<p>Remove contact lenses before applying the drops, and wait 15 minutes before reinserting them.</p>\n\n<p>Follow the prescribed dosage and avoid touching the dropper tip to prevent contamination.</p>\n\n<p>Inform your doctor about any allergies or medications you are taking.</p>\n\n<p>Seek medical attention for severe eye pain, worsening redness, or vision changes.</p>\n\n<p>Consult your doctor if you are pregnant or breastfeeding.</p>\n\n<p>Store the drops in a cool, dry place, away from sunlight, and out of reach of children.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>Nevanac Ophthalmic Suspension 5 ml is classified as a nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID) and is primarily prescribed to alleviate eye irritation, pain, and redness following cataract surgery. Additionally, this medication is indicated to reduce the risk of macular edema, a swelling at the back of the eye that can occur after cataract surgery in patients with diabetes. Common symptoms experienced by patients include redness, itching, and inflammation in the eyes, which typically subside within a few weeks. Macular edema is a serious eye condition that can lead to permanent vision loss and arises when blood vessels in the light-sensitive part of the retina leak.</p>\n\n<p>The active ingredient in Nevanac Ophthalmic Suspension 5 ml is Nepafenac, which acts by inhibiting the action of prostaglandin H synthase (cyclooxygenase), an enzyme necessary for prostaglandin production. Prostaglandins are responsible for inducing pain, redness, and inflammation in the eyes. By blocking prostaglandins, Nevanac provides relief from these discomforting eye conditions.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<p>The majority of side effects do not need medical attention and typically subside as your body adapts to the medication. However, if you are concerned or if the side effects persist, it is recommended that you consult your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>The most common side effects are listed below:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Blurred vision</li>\n	<li>Change in vision</li>\n	<li>Decrease in vision</li>\n</ul>','[\"nevanac-eye-drop-5ml-171147148484.jpg\"]','NE005',1,'0','2024-03-26 16:44:52','2025-10-08 05:33:31'),(494,0,'Nevimune 200mg','nevimune-200mg-','tablet','nevimune-200mg-tablets-171147168314.jpg','NE200','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>It can be consumed on an empty stomach or with food, and is prescribed alongside other HIV medications. Regularly taking all of these medications at the appropriate times increases their efficacy and decreases the likelihood that HIV will develop resistance to them. It is essential to continue taking them until your doctor tells you it&#39;s safe to cease.</p>\n\n<p>Take this medication according to your doctor&#39;s prescribed dosage and duration. Swallow the pill whole. Not to be chewed, crushed, or broken. Nevimune Tablet may be taken with or without sustenance, but it is preferable to take it at a set time each day.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Nevimune Tablet prevents the spread of HIV within the body. It helps control the infection and strengthens the immune system. This reduces the likelihood of complications such as new infections and enhances your quality of life.</p>\n\n<p>Nevimune Tablet is not a cure for HIV or AIDS and should not be used to prevent HIV infection following accidental exposure. Importantly, this medication must be consumed exactly as prescribed by the doctor. Taking all doses at the correct times and in the correct amounts significantly improves the efficacy of the medication and decreases the likelihood of HIV infection developing resistance to antiretroviral drugs. Although taking this medication will not prevent the spread of HIV to others, it will reduce the likelihood of contracting the virus.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>HIV Treatment: Nevimune 200mg Tablets are primarily used for the treatment of HIV infection. It should only be used under the guidance and supervision of a healthcare professional experienced in the treatment of HIV.</p>\n\n<p>Medical History: Inform your healthcare provider about any existing medical conditions, including liver or kidney problems, hepatitis, or any other significant medical history. This information will help the healthcare provider determine the appropriate dosage and monitor the safety of the medication.</p>\n\n<p>Allergies: If you or the person taking Nevimune 200mg Tablets has a known allergy or hypersensitivity to nevirapine or any other components of the medication, inform your healthcare provider. Allergic reactions may include rash, itching, swelling, severe dizziness, or difficulty breathing. Seek immediate medical attention if any signs of an allergic reaction occur.</p>\n\n<p>Drug Interactions: Nevimune 200mg Tablets can interact with other medications, including prescription drugs, over-the-counter medicines, and herbal supplements. Some drugs may decrease the effectiveness of Nevimune, while others may increase the risk of side effects. Inform your healthcare provider about all the medications being taken to avoid potential interactions.</p>','<p>Nevimune Tablet belongs to the class of drugs known as antiretrovirals. HIV (human immunodeficiency virus), the virus that can induce AIDS (acquired immunodeficiency syndrome), is treated with this drug. It helps control HIV infection so that your immune system can function more effectively.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Abdominal pain</li>\n	<li>Fatigue</li>\n	<li>Increased liver enzymes</li>\n</ul>','[\"nevimune-200mg-tablets-171147168314.jpg\"]','NE200',1,'0','2024-03-26 16:48:12','2025-10-08 05:36:46'),(495,0,'Nexpro 20 mg','nexpro-20-mg','tablet','nexpro-20-mg-171147197740.jpg','NE20','<p>Nexpro Tablet uses</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Acid reflux treatment for gastroesophageal reflux disease</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Peptic ulcer disease treatment</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Benefits of Nexpro Tablet in the Treatment of Gastroesophageal Reflux Disease (Acid Reflux) GERD is a chronic (long-term) disorder that feels more like chronic heartburn than occasional heartburn. It occurs when a muscle above your stomach relaxes excessively, allowing stomach contents to reflux into your mouth and oesophagus. Proton pump inhibitors are a class of medications that includes Nexpro 20 Tablet. It lessens the amount of acid your stomach produces and lessens the discomfort brought on by acid reflux and heartburn. For it to work, you must take it exactly how it is intended.</p>\n\n<p>The signs of GERD might be lessened with a few straightforward lifestyle adjustments. Eat smaller, more frequent meals; consider what foods make you feel heartburny and try to avoid them; if you are overweight, attempt to lose weight; and look for ways to relax. Eat nothing three to four hours before bedtime.</p>\n\n<p>Peptic ulcer disease treatment</p>\n\n<p>Proton pump inhibitors are a class of medications that includes Nexpro 20 Tablet. As the ulcer heals spontaneously, it avoids additional damage by lowering the amount of acid your stomach produces. Depending on what caused the ulcer, you might also be prescribed other medications in addition to this one. Even if the symptoms appear to go away, you must continue taking the medication as directed for it to be successful.</p>','<p>A medication called Nexpro 20 Tablet lowers the quantity of acid your stomach produces. It is used to treat peptic ulcer disease, acid reflux, and other issues with your food pipe. Stomach ulcers can also be prevented and treated with it.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>You must take Nexpro 20 Tablet as prescribed by your physician. The dosage will depend on the ailment you are treating, but it is often the lowest dose for the shortest amount of time that is required to cure your illness. It is typically consumed without food. Even if your symptoms go away right away, keep taking it as directed. Your doctor may perform routine tests to assess your levels of magnesium, which can drop with this medication, if you use it for a long time.</p>\n\n<p>Headache, diarrhoea or constipation, stomach pain, and nausea are typical adverse effects. These are often minor, but if they annoy you or do not go away, consult your doctor. The longer you use this medication, the greater the chance of negative effects may be. If you take it for a long time, you can be more prone to break a bone. It is recommended to stay away from things like fatty, spicy, and rich foods that seem to exacerbate your symptoms. Limiting alcohol and caffeinated beverages like tea, coffee, and cola may also be beneficial.</p>\n\n<p>Some people should not take this medication. You must inform your doctor if you have serious liver issues, are taking HIV medications, have ever had an allergic reaction to a medication similar to this one, or have osteoporosis before using this medication. Nexpro 20 Tablet does not interact negatively with alcohol. Alcohol consumption, however, causes your stomach to create more acid than usual. This medication may cause you to feel lightheaded, drowsy, or have vision problems. In such a case, refrain from operating any machinery or tools until you feel better. It is typically not advised when breastfeeding or pregnant.</p>','<p>Common Nexpro side effects</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Headache</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Dizziness</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; mouth feeling parched</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Nausea</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Continent pain</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Constipation</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Flatulence</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Diarrhea</li>\n</ul>','[\"nexpro-20-mg-171147197740.jpg\"]','NE20',1,'0','2024-03-26 17:21:28','2025-10-08 05:36:58'),(496,0,'Nicardia 20mg','nicardia-20mg','tablet','nicardia-20mg-171147385681.jpg','NI20','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>Nicardia 20mg should be taken exactly as prescribed by your doctor. It is important to follow the instructions provided and read the medication label carefully. Make sure to take the medication regularly and do not exceed the recommended dosage.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Nicardia 20mg offers several benefits in the treatment of cardiovascular conditions:</p>\n\n<p>High blood pressure management: Nicardia 20mg helps lower high blood pressure, also known as hypertension. By relaxing the blood vessels, it improves blood flow and reduces the workload on the heart, promoting healthy blood pressure levels.</p>\n\n<p>Angina treatment: Nicardia 20mg is effective in managing angina, a condition characterized by chest pain or discomfort. It helps relax and widen the blood vessels in the heart, allowing for improved blood flow and reduced chest pain.</p>\n\n<p>Raynaud&rsquo;s disease management: Nicardia 20mg is often prescribed for individuals with Raynaud&rsquo;s disease, a condition that causes blood vessels in the fingers and toes to constrict. By dilating the blood vessels, it helps alleviate symptoms such as cold fingers or toes and reduces the frequency and severity of attacks.</p>\n\n<p>Prevention of preterm labor: Nicardia 20mg is sometimes used to prevent preterm labor by relaxing the uterine muscles and improving blood flow to the placenta.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before taking Nicardia 20mg, it is important to discuss your medical history and any existing health conditions with your doctor. Inform them about any allergies or sensitivities you may have to this medication or any other substances.</p>\n\n<p>It Is essential to take Nicardia 20mg exactly as prescribed and not to stop or adjust the dosage without consulting your doctor. Abruptly discontinuing the medication can have adverse effects on your condition.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>Nicardia 20mg, also known as Nifedipine 20mg, is a medication that is commonly used to treat various cardiovascular conditions. It belongs to a class of drugs known as calcium channel blockers. Nicardia 20mg is prescribed to help manage certain heart conditions and promote overall cardiovascular health. Here is some important information about Nicardia 20mg:</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>Most people tolerate Nicardia 20mg well, and any side effects are generally mild and temporary. However, it is important to be aware of potential side effects and seek medical attention if they become severe or persistent. Some common side effects include:</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Headache</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Dizziness or lightheadedness</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Flushing</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Swelling in the ankles or feet</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Nausea or upset stomach</p>\n\n<p>Remember that your doctor has prescribed Nicardia 20mg because they have determined that the benefits outweigh the potential risks. If you experience any concerning side effects, do not hesitate to consult your doctor for further guidance.</p>\n\n<p>Overall, Nicardia 20mg is an effective medication used to manage various cardiovascular conditions. When taken as directed, it can help improve heart health and enhance overall well-being.</p>','[\"nicardia-20mg-171147385681.jpg\"]','NI20',1,'0','2024-03-26 17:26:18','2025-10-08 05:37:24'),(497,0,'Nimodip 30mg','nimodip-30mg','tablet','nimodip-30mg-17114750117.jpg','NI30','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>It is crucial to follow your doctor&rsquo;s instructions and carefully read the medication label when taking Nimodi