jpg','NI200','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Please consume the prescribed dose and duration of NIZONIDE DT 200MG TABLET based on your medical condition. In general, NIZONIDE DT 200MG TABLET is a safe medication to take. However, adverse effects such as nausea, vomiting, stomach pain, fever, hair loss, dizziness, giddiness, and headache are possible. The majority of these adverse effects of NIZONIDE DT 200MG TABLET are non-serious and resolve on their own over time. Consult your physician if these adverse effects persist for an extended period.</p>\n\n<p>Do not crush, chew, or split the capsule; swallow it whole with water.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>NIZONIDE DT 200MG TABLET contains Nitazoxanide, a member of the thiazolide class of medications. Nitazoxanide is a broad-spectrum antiparasitic, antiprotozoal, and antiviral drug used primarily for the treatment of diarrhea. It inhibits the production of chemical substances necessary for the energy metabolism and growth of protozoa, helminths, anaerobic, microaerophilic, and viruses. Nitazoxanide is an effective treatment for parasitic infections of the gastrointestinal tract, such as Cryptosporidium parvum and Giardia lamblia.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before taking NIZONIDE DT 200MG TABLET, tell your doctor if you have liver or kidney disease, asthma, diabetes, or a weakened immune system. Please inform your doctor if you are allergic to NIZONIDE DT 200MG TABLET or any other medications. Do not take NIZONIDE DT 200MG TABLET on your own, as it may result in antibiotic-resistance, rendering antibiotics ineffective against certain infections. Do not abruptly discontinue this medication to avoid disagreeable side effects and withdrawal symptoms. Before starting NIZONIDE DT 200MG TABLET, you should consult your doctor if you are pregnant or intending to become pregnant. Due to the possibility of dizziness, do not drive or operate heavy machinery after consuming NIZONIDE DT 200MG TABLET. Children younger than one year are not advised to take NIZONIDE DT 200MG TABLETS.</p>','<p>NIZONIDE DT 200MG TABLET belongs to the class of &#39;antiprotozoal and antiviral&#39; medications, which are used predominantly to treat diarrhea caused by parasite infections of the intestines (Cryptosporidium parvum and Giardia lamblia). NIZONIDE DT 200MG TABLET is also used to treat protozoa infections caused by single-celled parasites that thrive in moist environments such as lakes, streams, and soil. Diarrhea is a condition characterized by frequent passage of loose or liquid feces.</p>\n\n<p>Nitazoxanide, the active ingredient in NIZONIDE DT 200MG TABLET, is a thiazolide-class drug. Nitazoxanide is a broad-spectrum antiparasitic drug. It inhibits the production of chemical substances necessary for the energy metabolism and growth of protozoa, helminths (parasites resembling worms), anaerobic (microbes that survive without oxygen), and microaerophilic (requiring little oxygen to survive) microbes and viruses. Nitazoxanide is useful for treating gastrointestinal infections.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Stomach pain</li>\n	<li>Fever</li>\n	<li>Hair loss</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n</ul>','[\"nizonide-dt-200mg-171147631632.jpg\"]','NI200',1,'0','2024-03-26 18:05:50','2025-10-08 05:33:51'),(501,0,'Nizral Cream  2% 30gm','nizral-cream-2-30gm','Cream','nizral-cream-2-30gm-171147640867.jpg','NI30','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>Nizral Cream is specifically designed to treat fungal infections of the skin, including ringworm, athlete&rsquo;s foot, jock itch, and yeast infections. It effectively combats the growth and spread of the fungi, providing rapid relief from itching, redness, and inflammation associated with these conditions.</p>\n\n<p>It is important to follow the instructions provided by your healthcare professional or the product label when using Nizral Cream. Cleanse and dry the affected area before applying a thin layer of the cream, gently massaging it into th