event infectious diarrhea in individuals who are at risk, such as those traveling to areas with a high incidence of bacterial infections or individuals with compromised immune systems. It can help reduce the risk of developing diarrhea caused by certain bacterial pathogens.</p>\n\n<p>Broad Spectrum Antibiotic: Norflox-200 Tablet belongs to the fluoroquinolone class of antibiotics, which exhibits a broad spectrum of activity against a wide range of bacteria. This means it can be effective against many types of bacterial infections, providing versatility in its treatment capabilities.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>If you are allergic to antibiotics, you must not use Norflox-200 Tablet 10&#39;s. Inform your doctor if you have liver/kidney disease, heart rhythm disorders, tendon problems, convulsions, diabetes, hypokalaemia/low potassium levels, or muscle/nerve disorders prior to taking this medication. Before taking Norflox-200 Tablet 10&#39;s, pregnant and lactating women should consult a physician. Avoid or limit alcohol consumption during treatment, as it can cause dizziness. Do not drive or operate machinery because it can cause dizziness and impair your ability to drive. The safety and efficacy of Norflox-200 Tablet 10&#39;s in minors have not been established; for more information, please consult a physician.</p>','<p>Norflox-200 Tablet 10&#39;s belong to the class of &#39;antibiotics&#39;, which are utilized predominantly to treat bacterial infections. A bacterial infection occurs when pathogenic bacteria multiply within the body and cause disease. It is capable of infecting any region of the body and can rapidly multiply. It is not recommended to use Norflox-200 Tablet 10&#39;s to treat viral infections, such as the common cold and flu.</p>\n\n<p>Norfloxacin and Lactic acid bacillus are included in Norflox-200 Tablet 10&#39;s. Norfloxacin belongs to the class of antibiotics known as quinolones. It is bactericidal and inhibits bacterial DNA gyrase, an enzyme 