he infection, it alleviates symptoms such as frequent urination, pain or warmth during urination, and urinary urgency.</p>\n\n<p>Frequently caused by a bacterial infection, prostatitis is an inflammation of the prostate organ. Norflox-800 Tablet is effective in the treatment of bacterial prostatitis by targeting and eliminating the causative bacteria, thereby reducing the associated pain, urinary symptoms, and inflammation.</p>\n\n<p>Norflox-800 Tablet is efficacious against bacterial gastroenteritis and traveler&#39;s diarrhea. It aids in the eradication of the microorganisms responsible for the infection, thereby alleviating symptoms such as diarrhea, abdominal pain, and vertigo.</p>\n\n<p>Avoiding Infectious Diarrhea: Individuals at risk for infectious diarrhea, such as those traveling to regions with a high incidence of bacterial infections or those with compromised immune systems, may be prescribed Norflox-800 Tablet under certain conditions. It can decrease the likelihood of contracting gastroenteritis caused by particular bacterial pathogens.</p>\n\n<p>Norflox-800 Tablet belongs to the class of fluoroquinolone antibiotics, which exhibit broad-spectrum activity against a wide range of microorganisms. This means that it can be used to treat a wide range of bacterial infections, granting it flexible treatment capabilities.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Antibiotic-sensitive individuals cannot consume Norflox-800 Tablet 10s. Inform your doctor if you have liver or kidney disease, cardiac rhythm disorders, tendon problems, convulsions, diabetes, hypokalemia/low potassium levels, or muscle/nerve disorders prior to taking this medication. Before taking Norflox-800 Tablet 10s, women who are expectant or breastfeeding should consult a physician. Avoid or limit alcohol consumption during treatment, as it can cause vertigo. Because it can cause vertigo and impair driving ability, you should not drive or operate machinery while under the influence of alcohol. The safety and effectiveness of Norflox-800 Tablet 10&#39;s in minors have not been determined; please consult a physician for more information.</p>','<p>Norflox-800 Tablet 10&#39;s belong to the class of &#39;antibiotics&#39;, which are used predominantly to treat bacterial infections. When pathogenic bacteria proliferate and cause disease within the body, a bacterial infection occurs. It can infect any region of the body and reproduces rapidly. Norflox-800 Tablet 10s should not be used to treat viral infections such as the common cold and influenza.</p>\n\n<p>The Norflox-800 Tablet 10 contains both Norfloxacin and Lactic acid bacillus. Norfloxacin belongs to the class of antibiotics known as quinolones. It inhibits the bacterial DNA gyrase necessary for DNA replication, transcription, and repair. Lactic acid bacillus, a probiotic (beneficial live bacteria), restores healthy intestinal bacteria.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Diarrhoea</li>\n	<li>Heartburn</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Trouble sleeping</li>\n</ul>','[\"norflox-800-mg-1-171147814065.jpg\"]','NO800',1,'0','2024-03-26 18:36:37','2025-10-08 05:35:08'),(507,0,'Norflox Eye Drop 0.3% (10 ml)','norflox-eye-drop-0.3-(10-ml)','Drops','norflox-eye-drop-0-171147828318.jpg','NO10','<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Treatment of Bacterial Conjunctivitis: Norflox Eye Drop 0.3% is commonly prescribed for bacterial conjunctivitis, also known as &quot;pink eye.&quot; It helps eliminate the bacteria causing the infection, reducing symptoms such as redness, itching, discharge, and discomfort in the eyes.</p>\n\n<p>Management of Corneal Ulcers: Norflox Eye Drop 0.3% can be beneficial in the treatment of corneal ulcers caused by susceptible bacteria. By targeting and eradicating the bacteria, it aids in the healing process and reduces the risk of complications.</p>\n\n<p>Prevention of Eye Infections: In some cases, Norflox Eye Drop 0.3% may be prescribed prophylactically to prevent eye infections, particularly in individuals who are at risk, such as those undergoing eye surgery or trauma. It helps prevent bacterial growth and reduces the likelihood of infection.</p>\n\n<p>Broad Spectrum Antibiotic: Norfloxacin, the active ingredient in Norflox Eye Drop 0.3%, belongs to the fluoroquinolone class of antibiotics, which exhibit a broad spectrum of activity against various bacteria. This means it can be effective against many types of bacterial eye infections, providing versatility in its treatment capabilities.</p>\n\n<p>Convenience and Ease of Use: Norflox Eye Drop 0.3% is an ophthalmic solution that can be easily applied directly to the affected eye. Its formulation allows for targeted delivery of the medication, ensuring effective treatment of the infection.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>If you are allergic to any of its components or if you have viral or fungal eye/ear infections, do not use Norflox Eye/Ear Drops 10ml. Inform your doctor if you have glaucoma, high blood pressure, ocular hypertension, diabetes, eye/ear infection or injury, or heart, kidney or liver problems. If you are pregnant or breastfeeding, talk to your doctor before using Norflox Eye/Ear Drops 10ml. Norflox Eye/Ear Drops 10ml should only be administered to minors with a doctor&#39;s prescription.</p>','<p>Norflox Eye Drop 0.3% (10 ml) is an ophthalmic solution used for the treatment of bacterial eye infections. It contains the active ingredient norfloxacin, which belongs to the fluoroquinolone class of antibiotics. This eye drop is specifically formulated for topical application to the eye.</p>\n\n<p>The primary purpose of Norflox Eye Drop 0.3% is to eliminate bacteria that cause eye infections. It is effective against a wide range of bacteria that can lead to conditions such as bacterial conjunctivitis (pink eye) and corneal ulcers.</p>\n\n<p>Norflox Eye Drop 0.3% comes in a 10 ml bottle with a dropper tip for easy administration. The sterile solution is designed for direct application to the affected eye(s) as directed by a healthcare professional.</p>\n\n<p>To use Norflox Eye Drop 0.3%, you typically need to tilt your head back slightly and gently pull down the lower eyelid to create a small pocket. Holding the dropper close to the eye, squeeze the prescribed number of drops into the pocket without touching the eye or eyelid with the dropper tip. After administering the drops, close your eyes gently and blink a few times to spread the medication evenly over the eye surface.How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Eye drops: Lie on your back with your head tilted backwards. With your index finger, gently pull your lower eyelid to form a compartment. Instill the prescribed number of eyedrops into the crevice of the lower eyelid. Close your eyes for one to two minutes.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Discomfort</li>\n	<li>Burning sensation</li>\n</ul>','[\"norflox-eye-drop-0-171147828318.jpg\"]','NO10',1,'0','2024-03-26 18:38:11','2025-10-08 05:35:17'),(508,0,'Norvasc 10mg','norvasc-10mg','tablet','norvasc-10mg-171147847276.jpg','NO10','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Dosage: Take Norvasc 10mg exactly as prescribed by your healthcare professional. The recommended dose may vary based on your medical condition and response to treatment. Do not change the dose without consulting your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>Timing: Take Norvasc 10mg once daily, preferably at the same time each day. It can be taken with or without food.</p>\n\n<p>Swallowing: Swallow the tablet whole with a glass of water. Do not crush, chew, or break the tablet unless directed by your healthcare professional.</p>\n\n<p>Compliance: Take Norvasc 10mg regularly to get the most benefit from it. It is important to continue taking it even if you feel well, as high blood pressure and other conditions often have no symptoms. If you stop taking Norvasc abruptly, your blood pressure may rise, increasing the risk of complications.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Lowering Blood Pressure: Norvasc 10mg helps relax and widen the blood vessels, allowing for easier blood flow. This can lead to a reduction in blood pressure, helping to manage and control hypertension. By controlling high blood pressure, Norvasc 10mg may help reduce the risk of complications such as heart attack, stroke, and kidney problems.</p>\n\n<p>Treatment of Angina: Norvasc 10mg can be used to treat certain types of angina, such as stable angina. By dilating the coronary arteries and improving blood flow to the heart, it can help reduce the frequency and severity of angina episodes. This can result in decreased chest pain and improved exercise tolerance.</p>\n\n<p>Prevention of Coronary Artery Disease Progression: Norvasc 10mg may be used as part of a comprehensive treatment plan to help slow down the progression of coronary artery disease. By improving blood flow and reducing the workload on the heart, it can help prevent further damage to the coronary arteries and decrease the risk of complications.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Inform your doctor if you have congestive heart failure or liver disease prior to taking Norvasc.</p>\n\n<p>Consuming alcohol can further reduce blood pressure and may exacerbate certain amlodipine side effects.</p>\n\n<p>If you are being treated for hypertension, continue taking Norvasc even if you feel fine. Frequently, high blood pressure has no symptoms. You might require blood pressure medication for the remainder of your life.</p>\n\n<p>Norvasc is only one component of a comprehensive treatment plan that may also include diet, exercise, and weight management. Strictly adhere to your diet, medication, and exercise regimens.</p>\n\n<p>Inform your physician of any additional heart or blood pressure medications you are taking.</p>\n\n<p>Your chest pain may worsen when you begin taking Norvasc or when you increase your dose. Consult a physician if your chest pain is severe or persistent.</p>','<p>Norvasc is used with or without additional medications to treat hypertension. Reducing hypertension helps prevent strokes, heart attacks, and kidney issues. Amlodipine is a member of the class of medications known as calcium channel blockers. It functions by relaxing blood vessels so that blood flow is facilitated. Amlodipine is also used to prevent angina. It may improve your exercise capacity and reduce the frequency of your angina attacks. It should not be utilized to treat episodes of chest discomfort. Use other medications (such as sublingual nitroglycerin) as prescribed by your doctor to alleviate attacks of chest discomfort.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>headache,</li>\n	<li>swelling (edema) of the ankles or feet,</li>\n	<li>dizziness,</li>\n	<li>lightheadedness,</li>\n	<li>drowsiness,</li>\n	<li>tired feeling,</li>\n	<li>nausea,</li>\n</ul>','[\"norvasc-10mg-171147847276.jpg\"]','NO10',1,'0','2024-03-26 18:42:07','2025-10-08 05:35:25'),(509,0,'Ns Aid 5 ml Eye drop','ns-aid-5-ml-eye-drop','Drops','ns-aid-5-ml-eye-drop-171147875831.jpg','NS05','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Only ophthalmic usage is permitted for Nsaid N Eye Drop, 5 ml. Use Nsaid N Eye Drop (5 ml) only after thoroughly washing your hands. Tilt your head back when lying down. With your index finger, gently pull your lower eyelid to create a pocket. Put the recommended number of drops into the lower eyelid&#39;s pocket, per the doctor&#39;s instructions. For a few minutes, shut your eyes. After use, put the outer cap back on. The 5 ml of Nsaid N Eye Drop may be contaminated if the container&#39;s tip is touched to the eye, eyelids, or surrounding skin.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory medications (NSAIDs) are used to treat and prevent pain and inflammation following cataract surgery. Nsaid N Eye Drop, 5 ml, falls into this group. The risk of macular oedema following cataract surgery is also decreased with its use. Nepafenac is the main ingredient in Nsaid N Eye Drop (5 ml). The prostaglandin synthase (cyclooxygenase) enzyme, which is necessary for prostaglandin production, is blocked by Nsaid N Eye Drop (5 ml). By preventing prostaglandins, these diseases are alleviated because these prostaglandins are what cause the pain, redness, and inflammation in the eyes.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Use NS Aid Eye Drop as directed by your doctor or healthcare professional.</p>\n\n<p>Avoid touching the dropper tip to prevent contamination.</p>','<p>The nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID) class of medications includes Nsaid N Eye Drop (5 ml), which is primarily recommended to reduce eye irritation, discomfort, and redness following cataract surgery. Additionally, this medication is suggested to lower the risk of macular oedema, or swelling in the back of the eye, in diabetic individuals undergoing cataract surgery. Patients frequently feel redness, itching, and inflammation in their eyes for a week before these symptoms go away. Macular oedema, an eye disorder that might even result in permanent blindness, is brought on by blood vessels in the retina&#39;s light-sensitive area leaking blood.</p>\n\n<p>Nepafenac, an ingredient in Nsaid N Eye Drop 5 ml, inhibits prostaglandin H synthase (cyclooxygenase), an enzyme needed to produce prostaglandin. The pain associated with painful eye disorders can be relieved by suppressing the prostaglandins that are responsible for the pain, redness, and inflammation in the eyes.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<p>The majority of side effects do not need medical attention and typically subside as your body adapts to the medication. However, if you are concerned or if the side effects persist, it is recommended that you consult your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>The most common side effects are listed below:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Eye discomfort</li>\n	<li>Burning eyes</li>\n	<li>Edema (swelling)</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n</ul>','[\"ns-aid-5-ml-eye-drop-171147875831.jpg\"]','NS05',1,'0','2024-03-26 18:46:05','2025-10-08 05:35:34'),(510,0,'Nucoxia 120 mg','nucoxia-120-mg',