bull; Nausea</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Diarrhea or constipation</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Headache</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Dizziness or drowsiness</p>','[\"nucoxia-90-mg-171147946978.jpg\"]','NU90',1,'0','2024-03-26 18:57:58','2025-10-08 05:36:10'),(513,0,'Nuvaring 2.7mg/ 11.2mg','nuvaring-2.7mg/-11.2mg','Medication','nuvaring-2-171147985188.webp','NU04','<p>Examples and Uses</p>\n\n<p>A tiny, flexible vaginal ring called Nuvaring is used to avoid getting pregnant. This item is a vaginal ring that combines two hormones&mdash;Etonogestrel, also known as Progestin, and Ethinyl Estradiol, also known as Estrogen&mdash;in one convenient package. It primarily functions by preventing ovulation&mdash;the release of an egg&mdash;during your menstrual cycle. Additionally, it thickens the vaginal fluid to aid in inhibiting fertilisation by preventing sperm from reaching an egg, and it alters the uterine lining to prevent a fertilised egg from adhering to the wall of the uterus (womb). A fertilised egg leaves the body if it does not adhere to the uterus. HIV infection or other sexually transmitted diseases are not prevented by this medication. When used as an emergency contraceptive, such as during unprotected sexual encounter, it will not be of any assistance.</p>\n\n<p>Administration and Dosage - Recommended dosage:</p>\n\n<p>Every month for three weeks, nuvaring is inserted and then taken out. After a seven-day pause, a fresh ring is installed. For seven days, refrain from wearing rings. Within two to three days of the ring being removed, you ought to start your period. Whether or whether you have your period, put in a new ring on the same day of the week that the old one was taken out after 1 ring-free week. It is recommended that you take this medication exactly as prescribed by your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>-Administration Method:</p>\n\n<p>A ring called Nuvaring is designed to go within your vagina. Take the ring out of the pouch after washing and drying your hands. Make sure your hands are dry because the ring turns slick when they are damp. As instructed, carefully insert the folded ring into your vagina until it feels cosy. Rarely, some women have unintentionally placed the ring in their bladder. Never place the ring within your bladder. The vagina should receive the ring. Women occasionally report not feeling the ring after it has been put on. If you experience pain, the ring is probably not put into your vagina far enough. The ring can be softly pushed into your vagina by using your finger. There is no risk of the ring slipping or moving too far up the vagina. It can only be inserted all the way to the vaginal end. It will be prevented from moving farther by the cervix. Sexual activity should not be hampered by the ring. Due to bowel motions, coughing, constipation, or straining, some women have reported the ring gliding or moving within the vagina. If this happens, use your finger to reposition it. When using this medication, it is important to carefully read the directions in the booklet and to use the application in accordance with your doctor&#39;s recommendations.</p>\n\n<p>missing a dosage</p>\n\n<p>If you forget to put the replacement ring in on the designated day, do it as soon as you remember. Until the new ring has been worn for seven days, you must utilise a backup method of birth control. Use an additional method of birth control, such as condoms, if you are unsure what to do or forget to put the fresh ring in on the appointed day. It&#39;s also advisable to visit your doctor if you missed taking the medicine.</p>\n\n<p>-Overdose:</p>\n\n<p>Never wear two rings at once. Before putting the new ring on, you should take the old one off. Consult your doctor about the situation if you accidentally took more than one ring at a time.</p>\n\n<p>Contraindications</p>\n\n<p>Patients who have demonstrated hypersensitivity to any of the formulation&#39;s ingredients shouldn&#39;t use Nuvaring.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pregnant women shouldn&#39;t take this medication.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; If you have a smoking habit and are older than 35, you should not use this drug.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Male patients should not use this medication.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions and warnings</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Keep in mind that patients who are allergic to the active ingredient or any of the compounds in Nuvaring cannot use it. Researching the contents of Nuvaring 2.7 mg/ 11.2 mg is essential before making an online purchase.</li>\n	<li>Patients with cardiac conditions like angina, high blood pressure, or a heart attack should not take this medication. If you have a cardiac condition of any kind before using this medicine, talk to your doctor first.</li>\n	<li>Before taking this medication, if the patient has unexplained vaginal bleeding, you should visit your doctor.</li>\n	<li>Patients with asthma, diabetes, migraines, or epilepsy issues should not take this medication. Consult your doctor before using this medication if you have any of these symptoms.</li>\n	<li>The use of this medication is not recommended for anyone with kidney or liver disease of any type. Before beginning to take this medication, it is important that you speak with your doctor and discuss your medical history.</li>\n	<li>If a patient has ever experienced brain bleeding, a stroke, a heart attack, or other major blood vessel issues, they should not use this medication. Consult your doctor before taking this medication in this situation.</li>\n	<li>Women who have a history of breast nodules, fibrocystic disease of the breast, an abnormal breast x-ray or mammography, or irregular or sparse menstrual cycles should not take this medication. Before using this medication, speak with your doctor.</li>\n	<li>Before using this medication, speak with your doctor if the patient has previously mentioned experiencing any type of allergic response to any foods, colours, or medications.</li>\n	<li>If the patient has any type of blood issue, this medication is not recommended.</li>\n	<li>Be sure to thoroughly wash your hands before taking this medication.</li>\n	<li>HIV/AIDS and other sexually transmitted infections are not protected from by nuvaring. Only when it is used properly may it prevent pregnancy.</li>\n</ul>','<p>Nuvaring 2.7/11.2mg Rings&#39; primary active ingredients are etonogestrel and ethinyl estradiol. The mixture is used to stop pregnancies. It is a versatile vaginal birth control ring made of two hormones: etonogestrel and ethinyl estradiol. It prevents the release of eggs from the ovaries, preventing conception as a result.</p>','<p>Negative effects</p>\n\n<p>If you experience any side effects that annoy you or do not go away, let your doctor know:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Itching Minor annoyance</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Throwing Up Hives</li>\n	<li>Rash, headache, and lightheadedness</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>There are several uncommon but major side effects that could happen:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Fever</li>\n	<li>breathing difficulty</li>\n	<li>distorted vision</li>\n	<li>Jaundice</li>\n	<li>Mood changes</li>\n	<li>Virulent discharge</li>\n	<li>Gaining weight</li>\n	<li>unpleasant menstrual period</li>\n	<li>Acne</li>\n	<li>lowered sex lust</li>\n	<li>Migraine</li>\n	<li>Blood clot warning signs</li>\n	<li>Skin irritation or itching in the vagina or vicinity.</li>\n	<li>Breasts swell, become tender, or hurt.</li>\n	<li>removing flesh with a flame</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Adverse drug reactions</p>\n\n<p>Etonogestrel and ethinyl estradiol&#39;s pharmacological effects can be changed by the following medications:</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tamoxifen, exemestane, ospemifene, tizanidine, and transamic acid</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ritonavir, Ombitasvir, Paritaprevir, Casabuvir, and Anastrozole</p>\n\n<p>Avoid using other medications while using this one or speak with your doctor about it to avoid any potential interactions.</p>\n\n<p>Get the complete list of medications from your doctor that can make drug interactions more likely or reduce Nuvaring&#39;s effectiveness.</p>\n\n<p>Ingredients</p>\n\n<p>Etonogestrel and ethinyl estradiol are the two medicinal components that make up Nuvaring. This contraceptive is a vaginal ring that contains a mixture of hormone medications. It prevents the release of eggs from the ovaries, preventing conception as a result.</p>\n\n<p>Keeping information</p>\n\n<p>Nuvaring should be kept secure and out of the way of heat and moisture. Refrigerate not. Keep it out of children&#39;s and animals&#39; reach. Do not leave this medicine unattended.</p>','[\"nuvaring-2-171147985188.webp\"]','NU04',1,'0','2024-03-27 02:59:22','2025-10-08 05:36:18'),(514,0,'Obelit 120mg','obelit-120mg','tablet','obelit-120mg-171150842379.jpg','OB120','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>Obelit 120mg should be taken orally with water, usually three times a day, during each main meal that contains fat. It is important to follow the dosage instructions provided by your healthcare professional. To maximize the effectiveness of the medication, it is recommended to consume a well-balanced, low-calorie diet while taking Obelit 120mg.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Weight management support: Obelit 120mg can assist individuals in managing their weight by reducing the absorption of dietary fats. It can be particularly helpful for those who have struggled to lose weight through diet and exercise alone.</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Improved health outcomes: By promoting weight loss, Obelit 120mg can potentially improve overall health and reduce the risk of obesity-related conditions such as type 2 diabetes, high blood pressure, and cardiovascular disease.</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Long-term weight maintenance: Obelit 120mg can also be used to help individuals maintain their weight after successfully achieving their weight loss goals. It can be a valuable tool in preventing weight regain and promoting a healthier lifestyle.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before starting Obelit 120mg, it is important to c