irected on a regular basis. Usually, taking this medication does not result in any immediate benefits for you, but over time, it keeps you healthy.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>While side effects are possible with any medication, most individuals tolerate Olmesar A 5 20mg well. It is important to be aware of potential side effects and consult your doctor if you have any concerns. Common side effects may include:</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Headache</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Dizziness</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Swelling in the ankles or feet</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Flushing</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Stomach pain</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Nausea</p>','[\"olmesar-a-5-20mg-171151097351.bmp\"]','OL20',1,'0','2024-03-27 03:47:14','2025-10-08 05:41:43'),(523,0,'Olopat 0.1% (5 ml )','olopat-0.1-(5-ml-)','Solution','olopat-0-17115115204.jpg','OL05','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>Based on your medical situation, your doctor will advise you on how frequently you should take Olopat Eye Drops 5 ml. Olopat Eye Drops 5 ml commonly cause side effects such as eye pain, eye irritation, headaches, blurred vision, burning/stinging/redness/dryness of the eyes, eyelid swelling, and uncomfortable eye conditions. These side effects gradually go away over time without the need for medical care. Consult a doctor if any of the negative effects last or get worse.</p>\n\n<p>Pull your lower eyelid outward and downward as you tilt your head back. Instill the eye drops into the affected eye(s) with a light squeeze of the dropper. To disperse the medication inside your eye, blink a few times.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Allergy Relief: Olopat 0.1% provides relief from symptoms associated with allergic conjunctivitis, such as itching, redness, watering, and swelling of the eyes. It works by inhibiting the release of histamines, which are responsible for triggering allergic reactions.</p>\n\n<p>Symptom Control: By reducing the symptoms of allergic conjunctivitis, Olopat 0.1% helps improve comfort and quality of life for individuals experienc