:</p>\n\n<p>Your physician will determine the dosage and length of treatment based on the severity of your infection. PENTIDS 200MG TABLET can cause adverse effects, but not everyone will experience them. Common PENTIDS 200MG TABLET side effects include stomach pain, headache, nausea, vomiting, diarrhoea, skin rash, yellow eyes and skin, fatigue, and muscle/joint pain. If any of these side effects persist or worsen, consult a doctor immediately. It should be ingested whole with a glass of water. Do not crush, chew or break it.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Bacterial Infection Treatment: PENTIDS 200mg is effective against a wide range of bacterial infections caused by susceptible organisms. It works by inhibiting the growth of bacteria and preventing them from multiplying, thus helping to control and eliminate the infection.</p>\n\n<p>Streptococcal Infections: PENTIDS 200mg is commonly used in the treatment of streptococcal infections, including strep throat, scarlet fever, and other streptococcal skin and soft tissue infections. It helps in eradicating the bacteria responsible for these infections and promoting recovery.</p>\n\n<p>Syphilis: PENTIDS 200mg is also used in the treatment of syphilis, a sexually transmitted infection caused by the bacterium Treponema pallidum. It is effective in killing the bacteria and preventing the progression of the disease.</p>\n\n<p>Other Bacterial Infections: PENTIDS 200mg may be prescribed for various other bacterial infections, such as respiratory tract infections, skin and soft tissue infections, urinary tract infections, and certain types of meningitis. It helps to combat the specific bacteria causing the infection and aids in resolution.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Inform your doctor if you have a history of asthma, kidney disease, stomach problems (nausea, vomiting, digestive issues), or heart or liver disease before taking PENTIDS 200MG TABLET. Clostridium difficile-associated diarrhea (CDAD) has been reported in patients taking antibiotics such as PENTIDS 200MG TABLET. If you develop diarrhea while taking PENTIDS 200MG TABLET, you should undergo an examination to rule out the possibility of CDAD. Inform your physician if you are undergoing vaccinations with live bacterial vaccines (such as typhoid vaccine), as PENTIDS 200MG TABLET may affect the effectiveness of vaccines. Please seek medical advice before consuming PENTIDS 200MG TABLET if you are pregnant or breastfeeding. Consuming alcohol while taking PENTIDS 200MG TABLET may result in unwanted adverse effects; therefore, please limit or avoid alcohol consumption. PENTIDS 200MG TABLET should only be administered to minors when prescribed by a physician.</p>','<p>PENTIDS 200MG TABLET belongs to the class of medications known as &#39;antibiotics&#39;, which are primarily used to treat bacterial infections of the respiratory tract, throat, lungs, nose, and skin. It is effective against infections caused by streptococci and staphylococci, as well as diphtheria, meningitis, gonorrhea, and syphilis. Bacterial infection occurs when harmful bacteria proliferate in the body and causes illness. It can infect any part of the body and multiply very quickly.</p>\n\n<p>PENTIDS 200MG TABLET contains the antibacterial agent Penicillin G Potassium. It has bactericidal activity against aerobic (requires oxygen to survive) and anaerobic (survives with little or no oxygen) gram-positive and gram-negative bacteria. PENTIDS 200MG TABLET inhibits bacterial cell wall synthesis by binding to penicillin-binding proteins (PBPs) within the bacterial cell wall.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Stomach pain</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Diarrhoea</li>\n	<li>Weakness</li>\n	<li>Muscle/joint pain</li>\n</ul>','[\"pentids-200mg-171152378285.jpg\"]','PE200',1,'0','2024-03-27 07:17:18','2025-10-08 05:45:23'),(548,0,'Pentids 400mg','pentids-400mg','tablet','pentids-400mg-171152662199.jpg','PE400','<p>How to use:</p>