s such as PENTIDS 400MG TABLET. If you develop diarrhea while taking PENTIDS 400MG TABLET, you should undergo an examination to rule out the possibility of CDAD. Inform your physician if you are undergoing vaccinations with live bacterial vaccines (such as typhoid vaccine), as PENTIDS 400MG TABLET may affect the effectiveness of vaccines. Please seek medical advice before consuming PENTIDS 400MG TABLET if you are pregnant or breastfeeding. Consuming alcohol while taking PENTIDS 400MG TABLET may result in unwanted adverse effects; therefore, please limit or avoid alcohol consumption. PENTIDS 400MG TABLET should only be administered to minors when prescribed by a physician.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>PENTIDS 400MG TABLET belongs to the class of medications known as &#39;antibiotics&#39;, which are primarily used to treat bacterial infections of the respiratory tract, throat, lungs, nose, and skin. It is effective against infections caused by streptococci and staphylococci, as well as diphtheria, meningitis, gonorrhea, and syphilis. A bacterial infection occurs when pathogenic bacteria multiply within the body and cause disease. It is capable of infecting any region of the body and can rapidly multiply.</p>\n\n<p>PENTIDS 400MG TABLET contains the antibacterial agent Penicillin G Potassium. It has bactericidal activity against aerobic (requires oxygen to survive) and anaerobic (survives with little or no oxygen) gram-positive and gram-negative bacteria. PENTIDS 400MG TABLET inhibits bacterial cell wall synthesis by binding to penicillin-binding proteins (PBPs) within the bacterial cell wall.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Stomach pain</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Diarrhoea</li>\n	<li>Weakness</li>\n</ul>','[\"pentids-400mg-171152662199.jpg\"]','PE400',1,'0','2024-03-27 08:04:41','2025-10-08 05:43:53'),(549,0,'Permite Cream 5% (60gm)','permite-cream-5-(60gm)','Cream','permite-cream-5-60gm-171152711623.jpg','PE5','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Permite 5% Cream, 60 grams, is intended solely for external use. Some individuals may experience side effects including redness, rash, searing sensation, and itching.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;It is for external use only. As instructed, place a tiny amount on a fingertip and apply a thin layer to the clean, dry affected area. Avoid touching your nostrils or eyes. In the event of accidental contact with these areas, thoroughly cleanse with water. If they are not the infected area, wash your hands before and after using them to prevent the spread of infection.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Scabies Treatment: Permite 5% Cream is highly effective in killing the scabies mites and their eggs that cause the infestation. It helps to alleviate the symptoms associated with scabies, such as intense itching, rash, and skin irritation.</p>\n\n<p>Mite Infestations: In addition to scabies, Permite 5% Cream may also be used for the treatment of other mite infestations, such as pediculosis (lice infestation) and crab lice infestation. It works by disrupting the nervous system of the parasites, leading to their elimination.</p>\n\n<p>Convenience: Permite 5% Cream is easy to apply and is typically applied topically to the affected areas of the skin. It is a convenient and non-invasive treatment option for scabies and other mite infestations.</p>\n\n<p>Broad-Spectrum Activity: Permite 5% Cream exhibits broad-spectrum activity against various types of mites and insects. It is effective against both the adult parasites and their eggs, ensuring comprehensive treatment and preventing re-infestation.</p>\n\n<p>Relief from Symptoms: By eliminating the underlying cause of the infestation, Permite 5% Cream provides relief from the intense itching, redness, and discomfort associated with scabies and other mite infestations. It helps to improve the overall skin condition and promote healing.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Inform your physician if you are allergic to permethrin, chrysanthemum, or any other medications. Please inform your physician if you have any additional skin conditions or chronic ailments. If prescribed by a physician, Permite 5% Cream 60 g is recommended for children under six years of age, the elderly, expectant women, and nursing mothers. Take the dosage prescribed by your doctor. Consult a physician if you develop any unusual symptoms or indications while using permethrin.</p>','<p>Permite 5% Cream 60 g belongs to the pyrethroids category. It is used to treat infections caused by eggs, parasites, and mites. It is primarily utilized to treat pediculosis and mange. Pediculosis is an infestation of lice on the cranium and other hairy areas of the body. It is most prevalent in children older than five and is transmitted through head-to-head contact. Mites cause the cutaneous infection scabies. It is contagious and spreads through physical contact between individuals. Patients with pediculosis and scabies experience rashes and persistent itching that intensifies at night in the infected area.</p>\n\n<p>Permite 5% Cream 60 grams contain the antiparasitic drug Permethrin. It eliminates the scabies-causing small insects (mites) and their larvae. Additionally, it eliminates head lice, which adhere to the epidermis and cause irritation.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Skin irritation</li>\n	<li>Redness</li>\n	<li>Rash</li>\n	<li>Burning or tingling sensation</li>\n	<li>numbness</li>\n</ul>','[\"permite-cream-5-60gm-171152711623.jpg\"]','PE5',1,'0','2024-03-27 08:12:05','2025-10-08 05:44:02'),(550,0,'Persol Gel 2.5% (30 gm)','persol-gel-2.5-(30-gm)','Gel','persol-gel-2-17115292298.jpg','PE30','<p>How to Use:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Persol AC 2.5 gel is designed for external use exclusively.</li>\n	<li>Prior to applying the gel, cleanse your skin and gently dry it.</li>\n	<li>Apply Persol AC 2.5 gel in a thin layer either once or twice a day, following the instructions given by your doctor.</li>\n	<li>While using this product, it is advisable to minimize sun exposure. If exposure to sunlight is unavoidable, it is recommended to use the gel in the evening.</li>\n	<li>Ensure that you adhere to your doctor&#39;s instructions regarding the quantity and frequency of product application. Avoid using more or less of the gel or applying it more frequently than directed by your doctor.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Persol AC 2.5 Gel 30 gm contains the active ingredient &quot;Benzoyl Peroxide,&quot; which is an antibacterial medication utilized for treating bacterial skin infections such as acne (pimples). It is an organic compound that possesses several beneficial properties, including being an irritant, keratolytic (removing warts and calluses), comedolytic (inhibiting blemish formation), and anti-inflammatory agent.</p>\n\n<p>The gel effectively eliminates bacteria, reduces inflammation, and unclogs blocked pores. When applied to the skin, Persol AC 2.5 Gel 30 gm undergoes decomposition, leading to the release of oxygen. This oxygen acts as a bactericidal agent, targeting and eliminating Propionibacterium acnes, the bacteria responsible for causing acne.</p>\n\n<p>Furthermore, Persol AC 2.5 Gel 30 gm enhances the turnover rate of epithelial cells, which are the surface cells lining the skin. This increased turnover facilitates skin peeling and aids in the treatment of comedones, which are small skin-colored bumps associated with acne.</p>\n\n<p>In addition, Persol AC 2.5 Gel 30 gm has a mild drying effect, promoting the removal of excess oils and dirt from the skin, resulting in a cleaner and healthier skin appearance.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>External Use Only: Persol AC 2.5 Gel 30 gm is meant for external use on the skin only. Avoid contact with the eyes, mouth, nose, and other sensitive areas. If accidental contact occurs, rinse thoroughly with water. Skin Sensitivity: Some individuals may experience skin irritation, redness, dryness, or a burning sensation when using Persol AC 2.5 Gel 30 gm. If these symptoms become severe or persistent, discontinue use and consult your doctor.</li>\n	<li>Sun Exposure: It is advisable to minimize sun exposure while using Persol AC 2.5 Gel 30 gm. This medication can increase the skin&#39;s sensitivity to sunlight, making it more prone to sunburn. Apply sunscreen and wear protective clothing when exposed to the sun.</li>\n	<li>Pregnancy and Breastfeeding: The safety of using Persol AC 2.5 Gel 30 gm during pregnancy or while breastfeeding is not well-established. It is advisable to consult your doctor before using this medication if you are pregnant, planning to become pregnant, or breastfeeding.\n	<ul>\n		<li>Other Medications: Inform your doctor about any other topical or oral medications you are using, as certain medications may interact with Persol AC 2.5 Gel 30 gm and result in adverse effects. This includes prescription medications, over-the-counter products, and herbal supplements.</li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n</ul>','<p>Persol AC 2.5 Gel 30 gm is classified as an &quot;antibacterial agent&quot; medication primarily utilized for the treatment of bacterial skin infections, specifically acne, which is characterized by the clogging of hair follicles with oil and dead skin cells.</p>\n\n<p>The active ingredient in Persol AC 2.5 Gel 30 gm is &quot;Benzoyl Peroxide,&quot; which serves multiple purposes in acne treatment. It effectively eliminates bacteria, reduces inflammation, and unclogs blocked pores. When applied to the skin, Persol AC 2.5 Gel 30 gm undergoes decomposition, releasing oxygen. This oxygen acts as a bactericidal agent, targeting and killing Propionibacterium acnes, the bacteria responsible for causing acne.</p>\n\n<p>Additionally, Persol AC 2.5 Gel 30 gm enhances the turnover rate of epithelial cells, which are the outermost skin cells. This increased turnover facilitates skin exfoliation, aiding in the treatment of comedones, which are small skin-colored bumps associated with acne.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>The majority of side effects do not necessitate medical attention and typically resolve as your body adapts to the medication. However, if these side effects persist or cause you concern, it is advisable to consult your doctor for further guidance.</p>\n\n<p>The common side effects are listed below:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Dry skin</li>\n	<li>Erythema (skin redness)</li>\n	<li>Burning sensation</li>\n	<li>Itching</li>\n	<li>Skin peeling</li>\n</ul>','[\"persol-gel-2-17115292298.jpg\"]','PE30',1,'0','2024-03-27 08:48:37','2025-10-08 05:44:11'),(551,0,'Persol Gel 5% 30gm','persol-gel-5-30gm','Tube','persol-gel-5-30gm-171152952128.jpg','PE5','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Cleanse the affected area with a gentle skin cleanser and water, then gently dry the skin by patting it.</p>\n\n<p>Once a day, apply a thin layer of Persol AC gel to the affected areas. Leave it on the skin for 2 hours, then rinse it off with water and gently pat the skin dry.</p>\n\n<p>Use a non-comedogenic moisturizer that is lightweight and does not clog pores.</p>\n\n<p>Note: Alternatively, you can apply Persol AC gel in the evening and leave it on overnight.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Persol AC 5 Gel 30 g contains the active ingredient &quot;Benzoyl Peroxide,&quot; an antibacterial medication prescribed for treating bacterial skin infections like acne (pimples). It is an organic compound that possesses various beneficial properties, such as being an irritant, keratolytic (removing warts and calluses), comedolytic (inhibiting blemish formation), and anti-inflammatory agent.</p>\n\n<p>Persol AC 5 Gel (30 g) effectively combats bacteria, reduces inflammation, and unclogs blocked pores. When applied to the skin, it undergoes decomposition, releasing oxygen. This oxygen acts as a bactericidal agent, eliminating Propionibacterium acnes, the bacteria responsible for causing acne. Moreover, Persol AC 5 Gel 30 g promotes the turnover rate of epithelial cells, which are the cells that form the skin&#39;s surface. This process aids in skin exfoliation and the treatment of comedones, which are small, skin-colored bumps resulting from acne. Additionally, Persol AC 5 Gel (30 g) has a mild drying effect, facilitating the removal of excess oils and dirt from the skin through cleansing.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Consultation with a Healthcare Professional: Before using Persol Gel 5% (30 g), it is advisable to consult with a healthcare professional, preferably a dermatologist. They can assess your skin condition, provide an accurate diagnosis, and determine if Persol Gel is suitable for your specific needs.</p>\n\n<p>Follow Instructions: Carefully follow the instructions provided by your healthcare professional and the product labeling. Use the recommended amount of Persol Gel 5% (30 g) and apply it as directed. Adhere to the prescribed dosage and duration of treatment.</p>\n\n<p>Avoid Sensitive Areas: Avoid applying Persol Gel 5% (30 g) to sensitive areas such as the eyes, mouth, nostrils, or open wounds. If accidental contact occurs, rinse the affected area with water immediately.</p>\n\n<p>Skin Irritation: Some individuals may experience skin dryness, redness, itching, or a burning sensation when using Persol Gel 5% (30 g). If these side effects become severe or persistent, consult your healthcare professional.</p>\n\n<p>Pregnancy and Breastfeeding: If you are pregnant, planning to become pregnant, or breastfeeding, inform your healthcare professional before using Persol Gel 5% (30 g). They can assess the potential risks and benefits and provide guidance on safe usage during this period.</p>\n\n<p>Avoid Harsh Skin Products: To prevent skin irritation, it is recommended to avoid using harsh or abrasive skin products, such as exfoliants or alcohol-based cleansers, while using Persol Gel 5% (30 g). These can exacerbate dryness and irritation.</p>','<p>Persol AC 5 Gel 30 g falls under the category of medications known as &quot;antibacterial agents&quot; and is primarily utilized to address bacterial skin infections such as acne, commonly known as pimples. Acne occurs when oil and dead skin cells clog the hair follicles.</p>\n\n<p>Persol AC 5 Gel 30 g consists of &quot;Benzoyl Peroxide,&quot; which has multiple effects. It eliminates bacteria, reduces inflammation, and unclogs blocked pores. When applied to the skin, Persol AC 5 Gel (30 g) breaks down and releases oxygen. This oxygen acts as a bactericidal agent, effectively killing the acne-causing bacteria called Propionibacterium acnes. Additionally, Persol AC 5 Gel (30 g) accelerates the turnover of epithelial cells, which are the surface cells of the skin. This process aids in skin peeling and the treatment of comedones, which are small skin-colored bumps caused by acne. Furthermore, Persol AC 5 Gel (30 g) possesses a mild drying effect that helps eliminate excess oils and dirt from the skin when washed away.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>The most common side effects are listed below:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Itching</li>\n	<li>Skin irritation</li>\n	<li>Swelling</li>\n	<li>Blistering</li>\n	<li>Crusting</li>\n	<li>Skin rash</li>\n</ul>','[\"persol-gel-5-30gm-171152952128.jpg\"]','PE5',1,'0','2024-03-27 08:53:07','2025-10-08 05:44:20'),(552,0,'Phexin 250mg','phexin-250mg','Capsule','phexin-250mg-171152989765.jpg','PH250','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Depending on your condition and the severity of the infection, the dosage and duration of Phexin 250 Capsule 10&#39;s can vary. Also, as it is an antibiotic, it is recommended to finish the entire course of treatment even if you feel improved. Antibiotic resistance can occur when an infection becomes so severe that it no longer responds to treatment with an antibiotic. In some instances, you may experience diarrhea, nausea, vomiting, indigestion, gastrointestinal pain, and rashes. The majority of these adverse effects do not necessitate medical attention and will subside over time. However, you should consult your physici