 10&#39;s are utilized to treat dental infections. Infections induced by bacteria are caused by the multiplication of harmful bacteria within or on the body. Infectious or hazardous bacteria can cause illness and proliferate rapidly within the body. These pathogenic bacteria generate chemicals known as toxins, which can cause tissue injury and illness. Phexin 250 Capsule 10 is ineffective against viral infections, including the common cold and influenza.</p>\n\n<p>The essence of Phexin 250 Capsule 10&#39;s is bactericidal. Phexin 250 Capsule 10 functions by inhibiting the enzymes responsible for the production of peptidoglycan, an essential component of bacterial cell wall. This aids in treating and preventing the spread of infections by eliminating microorganisms.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Diarrhoea</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Indigestion</li>\n	<li>Stomach pain</li>\n	<li>Skin rashes</li>\n</ul>','[\"phexin-250mg-171152989765.jpg\"]','PH250',1,'0','2024-03-27 08:58:26','2025-10-08 05:44:29'),(553,0,'Posid 50mg','posid-50mg','Capsule','posid-50mg-171153034453.jpg','PO50','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Take eight Capsules of Posid 50 mg with a full glass of water on an empty stomach or as directed by your doctor. Depending on your medical condition, you should take Posid 50 mg Capsule 8 for as long as your physician prescribes. You may occasionally experience transient hair loss, nausea and vomiting, loss of appetite, diarrhoea, irregular heartbeat, and skin issues such as itchiness or rash. The majority of these adverse effects do not necessitate medical attention and will subside over time. However, you should consult your physician if you experience these side effects frequently.Completely swallow the tablet with a glass of water. Do not chew it or pulverize it. Do not use this tablet if it has been fractured by accident, as ingesting medicine from a broken tablet can be hazardous if it enters the eyes, mouth, or nose.</p>\n\n<p>Ben