 aids in reducing the rate at which they deteriorate.</p>\n\n<p>Regarding Heart Failure Treatment</p>\n\n<p>Ramipres 1.25 Tablet helps your heart work less hard by facilitating blood circulation throughout your body. This can enhance heart health and lessen heart failure symptoms. Your quality of life will be enhanced, and you&#39;ll be able to do your everyday tasks more quickly. For the medication to work, it must be taken consistently for the whole duration of the doctor&#39;s prescription.</p>','<p>Ramipres 1.25 Tablet is frequently prescribed after a heart attack to treat heart failure and excessive blood pressure. Additionally, it reduces your risk of suffering a heart attack or stroke.</p>\n\n<p>One may be prescribed Ramipres 1.25 Tablet alone or in conjunction with other medications. It may be consumed with food or on an empty stomach. To receive the most effect from this medication, it is best to take it every day at the same time. Even if you feel OK or if your blood pressure is under control, it&#39;s crucial to keep measuring it periodically. The majority of people who have high blood pressure do not have any symptoms, but your condition could worsen if you stop taking this medication. This medication is often used and is regarded as safe for long-term use.</p>\n\n<p>Making some lifestyle adjustments will also aid in lowering blood pressure. These can include getting regular exercise, lowering weight, quitting smoking, consuming less alcohol, and altering your diet to consume less salt in accordance with your doctor&#39;s recommendations. Feeling lightheaded or sleepy, headache, dry cough, lethargy, nausea, vomiting, diarrhoea, stomach discomfort, and low blood pressure are among of this medication&#39;s most frequent side effects. The majority of symptoms are transient and go away with time. If any of the adverse effects annoy you or do not go away, speak with your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>Inform your doctor if you have any renal or liver issues before using this medication. Before using it, women who are pregnant or nursing should also visit their doctor. While you are taking this medication, your doctor may perform routine checks on your blood pressure, potassium levels in your blood, and kidney function.</p>','<p>Ramipres Tablet side effects</p>\n\n<p>The majority of adverse effects are temporary and go away as your body becomes used to the medication. If they persist or you&#39;re concerned about them, speak with your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>Ramipres common side effects</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Dizziness</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Drowsiness</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; wet cough</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Headache</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Fatigue</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Nausea</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Vomiting</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; reduction in blood pressure</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','[\"ramipres-1-171161258822.jpg\"]','RA1.25',1,'0','2024-03-28 07:56:37','2025-10-08 05:49:51'),(572,0,'Ramipres 5 mg','ramipres-5-mg','tablet','ramipres-5-mg-171161529716.jpg','RA05','<p>Utilising the Ramipres Tablet</p>\n\n<p>Follow your doctor&#39;s instructions for this medication&#39;s dosage and duration. Take it all in at once. Don&#39;t eat it, break it, or crush it. It is preferable to take the Ramipres 5 Tablet at a set time rather than with or without food.</p>\n\n<p>Procedure for Ramipres Tablet</p>\n\n<p>Angiotensin converting enzyme (ACE) inhibitors include Ramipres 5 Tablet. It works by lowering the heart&#39;s workload and relaxing blood vessels to improve blood flow and the heart&#39;s ability to pump blood effectively.</p>\n\n<p>Ramipres Tablet Uses</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hypertension (high blood pressure) treatment</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Heart attack and stroke prevention</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Heart failure therapy</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Advantages of the Ramipres Tablet</p>\n\n<p>Ramipres 5 Tablet is a member of the class of drugs known as ACE inhibito