ected by your doctor, take 10 Rasalect 1 Tablets. Rasalect 1 Tablet 10&#39;s most frequent side effects include nausea, headaches, abdominal pain, and elevated blood pressure. The majority of these Rasalect 1 Tablet 10 side effects subside over time without the need for medical intervention. However, please see a doctor if the adverse effects worsen or persist.It should be completely swallowed with water; do not break, crush, or chew it.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Rasalect 1 is a selective monoamine oxidase-B (MAO-B) inhibitor that aids in the treatment of Parkinson&#39;s disease symptoms. It functions by elevating dopamine levels in the brain, a neurotransmitter that is depleted in people with Parkinson&#39;s disease. Rasalect 1 improves motor function, eases muscle stiffness, tremors, and other movement-related symptoms linked to the illness by increasing dopamine activity.</p>\n\n<p>Rasalect 1 has been demonstrated to potentially have neuroprotective properties, which can slow the progression of disease. The dopamine-producing neurons may be preserved, preventing additional harm, and slowing the progression of Parkinson&#39;s disease. Improved quality of life and long-term disease management may result from this.</p>\n\n<p>Rasalect 1 is frequently used as an adjunct therapy in conjunction with other Parkinson&#39;s disease drugs, such as levodopa. In advanced stages of the illness, when levodopa alone might not be sufficient, it can assist increase the effectiveness of levodopa and offer further symptom relief.</p>\n\n<p>Rasalect 1 aids in the management of a number of Parkinson&#39;s disease symptoms, including bradykinesia (slowness of movement), rigidity, and postural instability. It can increase general mobility, coordination, and functionality by treating these symptoms.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Inform your doctor of all of your allergies or food or medication sensitivities before to using Rasalect 1 Tablet 10s. Before taking Rasalect 1 Tablet 10&#39;s, be sure to discuss your medical history with your doctor in order to rule out any potential adverse effects. If you have hepatic impairment, psychosis (psychotic disease), or hypotension, let your doctor know. Caffeine and alcohol should be consumed in moderation or not at all.</p>','<p>Rasalect 1 Tablet 10s is an antiparkinson medication. It is used alone or in combination with another medication to treat Parkinson&#39;s disease symptoms. Parkinson&#39;s disease is a condition in which brain regions progressively deteriorate over time. Symptoms of Parkinson&#39;s disease include tremors, sluggish movement, and rigid and inflexible muscles. As the nerve cells that produce dopamine begin to perish, the levels of dopamine (a chemical messenger that is essential for movement control) decrease in Parkinson&#39;s patients.</p>\n\n<p>Rasalect 1 Tablet 10&#39;s contains Rasagiline. It functions by increasing the quantity of dopamine, a chemical messenger required to regulate brain movement. Thus, it aids in the treatment of Parkinson&#39;s disease symptoms.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Feeling sick</li>\n	<li>Headaches</li>\n	<li>Lightheadedness</li>\n	<li>Abdominal pain</li>\n	<li>High blood pressure</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Joint or neck pain</li>\n	<li>Heartburn</li>\n</ul>','[\"rasalect-1-mg-171161575545.jpg\"]','RA01',1,'0','2024-03-28 08:50:11','2025-10-08 05:50:13'),(574,0,'Raxitid 150 mg','raxitid-150-mg','tablet','raxitid-150-mg-17116161616.jpg','RA150','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Raxitid 150 mg Tablets, 10 per prescription only. Certain typical side-effects, such as nausea, headaches, dizziness, stomach upset, diarrhea, rashes, and stomachaches, may occasionally occur. The majority of these adverse effects go away gradually over time without the need for medical care. However, if you have these side effects frequently, you should consult your doctor.Take 10 Raxitid 150mg Tablets either before a meal or on an empty stomach. Tablet/capsule: The tablet shouldn&#39;t be chewed or mashed; it should be swallowed whole with water. Before using an oral liquid, shake the bottle vigorously. Utilizing the measuring cup included in the kit, take the recommended dosage orally.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>A broad-spectrum antibiotic, Raxitid 150 mg Tablet 10&#39;s work against both gram-positive and gram-negative bacteria. Raxitid 150mg Tablet 10&#39;s inhibits the bacteria&#39;s ability to synthesize proteins, which is essential for their existence. thereby aids in the treatment of infections and their prevention.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>If you are allergic to any of the ingredients in Raxitid 150 mg Tablet 10s, consuming ergot alkaloids (used to treat migraines), terfenadine or astemizole (used to treat allergies), cisapride (used to cure acidity), or pimozide (used to treat psychosis), you should not consume it. Self-medication with Raxitid 150 mg Tablet 10 may result in antibiotic resistance, which makes medications ineffective against certain bacterial infections. Before taking Raxitid 150mg Tablet 10s, let your doctor know if you have any heart, kidney, or liver issues, hypokalaemia (low potassium levels), diarrhea, or if you weigh less than 60 kilograms. Avoid taking antacid medications at the same time as Raxitid 150mg Tablet 10s; leave a gap of two hours between the two. If you are using contraceptives, talk to your doctor before taking Raxitid 150mg Tablet 10s because it may lessen their effectiveness. If not prescribed by a doctor, avoid using Raxitid 150mg Tablet 10s while you are pregnant or nursing. To avoid unpleasant side effects, refrain from drinking alcohol when taking Raxitid 150mg Tablet 10. Being woozy after taking Raxitid 150mg Tablet 10s should make you careful behind the wheel. To rule out any undesirable side effects, tell your doctor about all the medications you are taking as well as your health.</p>','<p>Raxitid 150 mg Tablet 10 is a member of the macrolide class of antibiotics. A broad-spectrum antibiotic called Raxitid 150mg Tablet 10s is used to treat infections of the gastrointestinal tract, skin, and soft tissues. The proliferation of dangerous bacteria inside or on the body results in bacterial illnesses. You can get sick from harmful or contagious bacteria, and they can proliferate swiftly in your body. Toxins, which are substances produced by these hazardous bacteria, can injure tissue and make you ill.</p>\n\n<p>Raxitid 150mg Tablet 10&#39;s inhibits the bacteria&#39;s ability to synthesize proteins, which is essential for their existence. thereby aids in the treatment of infections and their prevention. The effects of Raxitid 150 mg Tablet 10&#39;s are ineffective against viral infections including the common cold and the flu.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n	<li>Stomach upset</li>\n	<li>Diarrhoea</li>\n	<li>Rash</li>\n</ul>','[\"raxitid-150-mg-17116161616.jpg\"]','RA150',1,'0','2024-03-28 08:57:08','2025-10-08 05:50:24'),(575,0,'Razo 10mg','razo-10mg','tablet','razo-10mg-171161661587.webp','RA10','<p>Instructions for the Razo Tablet</p>\n\n<p>Take this medication at the prescribed dose and for the prescribed amount of time as directed by your doctor. Take it in one complete bite. Do not chew on it, crush it, or break it in any way. It is important to take the Razo 10 Tablet on an empty stomach.</p>\n\n<p>The operation of the Razo Tablet</p>\n\n<p>An example of a proton pump inhibitor (PPI) is the Razo 10 Tablet. It accomplishes this by lessening the amount of acid produced by the stomach, which, in turn, provides relief from acid-related symptoms such as indigestion and heartburn.</p>\n\n<p>Advantages of Utilising a Razo Tablet</p>\n\n<p>When you have gastroesophageal reflux disease, also known as acid reflux, you may have heartburn on a more frequent rather than sporadic basis. This is because GERD is a chronic ailment that lasts for a long time. It occurs when a muscle above your stomach relaxes too much, which makes it possible for the contents of your stomach to go backwards through your oesophagus and into your mouth. The medication known as a proton pump inhibitor is one of the class of drugs known as the Razo 10 Tablet. It does this by lowering the amount of acid that your stomach produces and alleviating the pain that is linked with acid reflux and heartburn. In order for it to have the desired effect, it is imperative that you follow the directions for use to the letter.</p>\n\n<p>Some straightforward adjustments to one&#39;s lifestyle can be helpful in alleviating the symptoms of GERD. Consider which foods cause heartburn and make an effort to steer clear of those items; consume meals that are smaller and more frequently spaced out; make an effort to shed weight if you are overweight; and make an effort to discover ways to relax. Avoid eating anything within three to four hours of going to bed.</p>\n\n<p>In the treatment of the illness known as peptic ulcer</p>\n\n<p>The medication known as a proton pump inhibitor is one of the class of drugs known as the Razo 10 Tablet. It lowers the amount of acid that your stomach produces, so preventing any additional harm to the ulcer while it is healing on its own. Depending on the underlying cause of the ulcer, you might also be prescribed certain other medications in addition to this one. Even if your symptoms appear to be improving, it is imperative that you continue taking the medication exactly as directed in order for it to be effective.</p>','<p>One of the effects of the medication known as Razo 10 Tablet is to lower the quantity of acid that is produced in the stomach. It is utilised in the treatment of acid-related disorders of the stomach and intestine such as acid reflux, peptic ulcer disease, and various other stomach conditions that are associated with excessive production of stomach acid.</p>\n\n<p>In addition, the use of painkillers for an extended period of time can lead to stomach ulcers and acidity, both of which can be prevented by using Razo 10 Tablet. It is classified as a proton pump inhibitor (PPI), which is a type of medication in its own right. This medication should be used once daily, ideally in the morning, one hour prior to eating a meal. Your current health and how well you react to the medication will both play a role in determining the appropriate dosage. As directed by your physician, make an effort to administer it daily at around the same time. Even if your symptoms improve more rapidly, you should not stop taking it unless specifically directed to do so by your doctor. If you consume more frequent, smaller meals, stay away from caffeinated beverages like coffee and tea, and limit your intake of foods that are spicy or greasy, you may be able to alleviate some of your symptoms.</p>\n\n<p>Nausea, vomiting, headache, dizziness, flatulence, diarrhoea, and stomach discomfort are the most typical adverse reactions that might be caused by taking this medication. Although they are typically not severe, you should consult your physician if you have any discomfort or if the symptoms do not disappear. The longer you take this medication, the higher your risk of experiencing adverse effects may become. Using this product for a prolonged period of time (more than a year), and especially at larger doses, may increase your risk of bone fractures. Talk to your primary care physician about osteoporosis prevention strategies, such as taking calcium and vitamin D supplements, to reduce your risk of bone loss.</p>\n\n<p>Some persons taking this medication for three months or more have developed low magnesium levels in their blood, which is medically referred to as hypomagnesemia. This could result in feelings of exhaustion and bewilderment, as well as dizziness, twitching muscles, and an erratic pulse. Your magnesium levels might be monitored by your doctor as a preventative measure.</p>\n\n<p>There are certain individuals who should not use the Razo 10 Tablet. If you have serious liver issues, are currently taking medications for HIV, have ever had an allergic response to medicines that are similar to this one in the past, or suffer from bone loss (osteoporosis), you are required to inform your doctor before beginning treatment with this medication. Women who are pregnant or breastfeeding should also discuss it with their primary care physician before taking it. Avoid drinking alcohol since it stimulates your stomach to create an abnormally high amount of acid and can make your symptoms much worse. If this medication causes you to feel sleepy or dizzy, you should avoid driving and should avoid operating any machinery or tools.</p>','<p>Razo Tablet&#39;s Potentially Adverse Effects</p>\n\n<p>The majority of adverse effects may be managed without medical intervention and will go away as your body becomes used to the medication. If they continue or if you are concerned about them, you should make an appointment with your primary care physician.</p>\n\n<p>Common adverse reactions to the drug Razo</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Diarrhea</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Dizziness</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Flatulence</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Headache</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Nausea</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A sore throat and discomfort in the stomach</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Vomiting</li>\n</ul>','[\"razo-10mg-171161661587.webp\"]','RA10',1,'0','2024-03-28 09:04:33','2025-07-21 05:31:13'),(576,0,'Razo 20mg','razo-20mg','tablet','razo-20mg-171163643676.jpg','RA20','<p>Using the Razo Tablet</p>\n\n<p>Follow your doctor&#39;s instructions for this medication&#39;s dosage and duration. Take it all in at once. Don&#39;t eat it, break it, or crush it. The Razo 20 Tablet should be taken without food.</p>\n\n<p>How the Razo Tablet operates</p>\n\n<p>Proton pump inhibitor (PPI) Razo 20 Tablet. It functions by lowering the amount of stomach acid, which re