 acidity, which Razo 20 Tablet helps to prevent. It is a member of the proton pump inhibitor (PPI) drug class. Preferably in the morning, this medication should be taken one hour before a meal. Your response to the medication and your underlying condition will determine the dose. As directed by your doctor, attempt to take it regularly at the same time each day. Even if your symptoms go away right away, you should continue taking it as directed. By eating smaller meals more frequently and staying away from caffeinated beverages like tea and coffee as well as spicy or fatty foods, you may be able to reduce the severity of your symptoms.</p>\n\n<p>The most frequent side effects of this medication are stomach pain, nausea, vomiting, headaches, dizziness, and flatulence. These are often minor, but if they annoy you or do not go away, consult your doctor. The longer you use this medication, the greater the chance of negative effects may be. With higher doses and prolonged use (more than a year), bone fracture risk may increase. You can prevent osteoporosis by taking calcium and vitamin D supplements, so discuss this with your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>Some patients taking this medication for three months or more have experienced low blood levels of magnesium (hypomagnesemia). An erratic heartbeat, fatigue, confusion, dizziness, and muscular twitching could result from this. To avoid this, your doctor might keep an eye on your magnesium levels.</p>\n\n<p>Some persons should not take Razo 20 Tablet. If you have serious liver issues, are taking HIV medications, have ever had an allergic reaction to a medication similar to this one, or have osteoporosis, you should let your doctor know before using this medication. Before using it, women who are pregnant or nursing should also visit their doctor. Avoid drinking alcohol as it can worsen your symptoms by causing your stomach to create too much acid. If this medication causes you to feel drowsy or dizzy, do not drive or operate machinery or tools.</p>','<p>Effects of the drug Razo</p>\n\n<p>The majority of adverse effects are temporary and go away as your body becomes used to the medication. If they persist or you&#39;re concerned about them, speak with your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>Razo common side effects</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Diarrhea</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Dizziness</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Flatulence</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Headache</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Nausea</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; throat discomfort stomach pain</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Vomiting</li>\n</ul>','[\"razo-20mg-171163643676.jpg\"]','RA20',1,'1','2024-03-28 14:34:58','2024-03-28 14:34:58'),(577,0,'Relpax 40mg','relpax-40mg','tablet','relpax-40mg-171163663335.jpg','RE40','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>It is important to follow your doctor&rsquo;s instructions when taking Relpax 40mg. Read and carefully follow the directions on the medication label. Take the medication as soon as you feel a migraine attack coming on, but not before the symptoms begin. You can take the tablet with or without food, but it is recommended to take it with water.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Relpax 40mg offers several benefits for individuals suffering from migraines:</p>\n\n<p>Migraine relief: Relpax 40mg is highly effective in providing relief from the debilitating symptoms of migraines, including severe headache, nausea, vomiting, and sensitivity to light and sound. It works by narrowing the blood vessels in the brain and reducing inflammation, which helps alleviate the pain and discomfort associated with migraines.</p>\n\n<p>Fast-acting: Relpax 40mg is known for its rapid onset of action, meaning it starts working quickly to provide relief but it can take upto 2 hours. This can be particularly beneficial for individuals who experience migraine attacks, allowing them to resume their daily activities sooner.</p>\n\n<p>Convenient dosage: The 40mg dosage of Relpax is designed to provide optimal efficacy while minimizing the risk of side effects. It is available in a tablet form, making it easy to take and carry with you for prompt migraine relief when needed.</p>\n\n<p>Improved quality of life: By effectively managing migraines, Relpax 40mg can significantly improve the quality of life for individuals who experience frequent or severe migraine attacks. It can help reduce the frequency, duration, and intensity of migraines, allowing for better daily functioning and productivity.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before taking Relpax 40mg, it is important to consider the following precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Medical history: Inform your healthcare provider about any pre-existing medical conditions, such as heart disease, high blood pressure, liver or kidney problems, as these factors may affect the suitability of using Relpax 40mg.</p>\n\n<p>Drug interactions: Certain medications, such as monoamine oxidase inhibitors (MAOIs) and selective serotonin reuptake inhibitors (SSRIs), may interact with Relpax 40mg and cause adverse effects. Inform your doctor about all the medications you are currently taking to ensure there are no potential interactions.</p>\n\n<p>Allergies: Discuss any known allergies or sensitivities with your healthcare provider before starting Relpax 40mg, as it contains inactive ingredients that could trigger allergic reactions.</p>','<p>Relpax 40mg, also known as Eletriptan 40mg, is a medication commonly prescribed for the treatment of migraines. It belongs to a class of drugs called triptans, which are specifically designed to relieve migraine symptoms and help restore normal functioning.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Here is some Information about Relpax 40mg:</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>While most people tolerate Relpax 40mg well, it is essential to be aware of potential side effects. Remember that not everyone experiences these side effects, and they are typically temporary. Common side effects of Relpax 40mg may include:</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Mild dizziness</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Fatigue or drowsiness</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Nausea</p>\n\n<p>&bull; Dry mouth</p>','[\"relpax-40mg-171163663335.jpg\"]','RE40',1,'0','2024-03-28 14:38:29','2025-10-08 05:50:42'),(578,0,'Renodapt S 360mg','renodapt-s-360mg','tablet','renodapt-s-360mg-17116441313.jpg','RE360','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>As directed, take 10 Renodapt S 360 mg tablets. Based on your medical situation, your doctor will advise you on how frequently to take Renodapt S 360mg Tablet 10s. Diarrhoea, vomiting, a drop in white blood cell and red blood cell counts, infections, and diarrhea are some of the side effects of Renodapt S 360mg Tablet 10&#39;s most frequently reported. If any of these side effects linger or get worse, speak with your doctor right away.Take the tablet as directed by your doctor. With a glass of water, swallow it whole. Do not chew, shatter, or crush it. Suspension: It comes in dry powder form and is combined with liquid (usually boiling and cooled water) until the desired consistency is reached. Take the recommended dose and give the bottle a good shake before each use.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>The ingredient &quot;Mycophenolate Mofetil,&quot; which is an immunosuppressant, is found in Renodapt S 360mg Tablet 10&#39;s. It is employed in order to avoid organ transplant rejection. It lessens immune system activity by obstructing the body&#39;s white blood cells, which are in charge of immunological responses. Since it has shorter-term negative effects than steroids, it is favored.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>If you have any unusual bleeding or bruising, a history of digestive issues like a stomach ulcer, are planning to become pregnant, become pregnant while taking Renodapt S 360mg Tablet 10s, or have a rare hereditary disorder like Lesch-Nyhan or Kelley-Seegmiller syndrome (conditions brought on by a deficiency of the enzyme hypoxanthine-g), consult your doctor before taking Renodapt S 360mg Tablet 10s. Reduce your sun exposure because it raises the risk of skin cancer. Renodapt S 360mg Tablet 10. Don&#39;t give blood while using Renodapt S 360 mg Tablet 10 and for at least 60 days after stopping the medication. Men who are taking Renodapt S 360mg Tablet 10s shouldn&#39;t donate sperm for at least 90 days after stopping the medication. Please refrain from getting any vaccinations (especially live vaccines) as they won&#39;t be very effective. Patients with phenylketonuria, a birth condition or congenital impairment that results in a reduced metabolism of phenylalanine, should use caution when using the oral solution because it contains aspartame, a sweetener and a source of phenylalanine.</p>','<p>Renodapt S 360mg Tablet 10s is a member of the group of drugs known as &quot;immunosuppressants,&quot; which are used to stop the body from rejecting transplanted organs like the kidney, heart, or liver. When the transplant recipient&#39;s immune system perceives the transplanted organ as a &quot;foreign object&quot; and fights it, transplant rejection happens. It can result in irreparable harm if it is not addressed right away.</p>\n\n<p>Mycophenolate mofetil, a medication used to treat organ transplant rejection, is one of the immunosuppressants and anti-inflammatory ingredients found in Renodapt S 360mg Tablet 10s. It prevents the creation of antibodies, which recognize and eliminate foreign cells, as well as T and B lymphocytes, a type of white blood cell that assaults foreign cells. The immune system is suppressed by these actions, preventing the transplanted graft from being rejected.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Diarrhoea</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Infections</li>\n	<li>Low white blood cell (WBC) count</li>\n	<li>Red blood cell (RBC) count</li>\n</ul>','[\"renodapt-s-360mg-17116441313.jpg\"]','RE360',1,'0','2024-03-28 16:42:19','2025-10-08 05:50:59'),(579,0,'Repace 100mg','repace-100mg','tablet','repace-100mg-171164467672.jpg','RE100','<p>Repace Tablet Uses</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nb