nisms even further.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Diarrhoea</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n</ul>','[\"restecline-500mg-171169946352.jpg\"]','RE500',1,'0','2024-03-29 08:04:34','2025-10-08 05:51:39'),(582,0,'Retino A Cream  0.025% (20gm)','retino-a-cream-0.025-(20gm)','tube','retino-a-cream-171169974697.jpg','RE0.25','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>When using Retino-A Cream 0.025%, it is important to follow your doctor&rsquo;s instructions and read the information provided on the medication label. Apply a thin layer of the cream to the affected areas of the skin, avoiding contact with the eyes, lips, and mucous membranes. Gently massage the cream into the skin until it is fully absorbed. It is generally recommended to use Retino-A Cream 0.025% once daily, preferably at bedtime, to maximize its benefits.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Retino-A Cream 0.025% offers several positive benefits for the skin, including:</p>\n\n<p>Acne treatment: One of the primary uses of Retino-A Cream 0.025% is in the treatment of acne. Tretinoin, the active ingredient, helps to unclog pores and prevent the formation of new acne lesions. It also promotes the shedding of dead skin cells, which can further improve the appearance of acne-prone skin.</p>\n\n<p>Skin rejuvenation: Retino-A Cream 0.025% is also known for its ability to promote skin rejuvenation. It can help reduce the appearance of fine lines, wrinkles, and age spots, giving the skin a smoother and more youthful appearance. Regular use of the cream can improve overall skin texture and tone.</p>\n\n<p>Hyperpigmentation treatment: The cream is effective in treating hyperpigmentation, including melasma and post-inflammatory hyperpigmentation. It can help lighten dark spots and even out the skin tone, leading to a more balanced complexion.</p>\n\n<p>Sun damage repair: Tretinoin in Retino-A Cream 0.025% has been shown to help repair sun-damaged skin. It can stimulate collagen production and improve skin elasticity, leading to a healthier and more resilient skin barrier.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before using Retino-A Cream 0.025%, it is important to consider the following precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Sensitivity to sunlight: Tretinoin can increase the skin&rsquo;s sensitivity to sunlight. It is advisable to limit sun exposure and use sunscreen with a high SPF while using this cream.</p>\n\n<p>Pregnancy and breastfeeding: It is recommended to consult with a healthcare professional before using Retino-A Cream 0.025% during pregnancy or while breastfeeding, as its safety in these situations has not been extensively studied.</p>\n\n<p>Skin irritation: Some individuals may experience mild skin irritation, redness, or peeling when starting treatment with Retino-A Cream 0.025%. This is usually temporary and can be managed by adjusting the frequency of application or using a moisturizer as directed by your doctor.</p>','<p>Retino-A Cream 0.025% (20g) is a medication that is primarily used for the treatment of various skin conditions. It contains tretinoin, a form of vitamin A, which has been proven effective in improving the appearance and texture of the skin. This cream is commonly prescribed by dermatologists and is available in a 20g tube.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>While using Retino-A Cream 0.025%, some individuals may experience temporary side effects that typically subside as the skin adjusts to the medication. These side effects can include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Mild skin dryness or flaking</li>\n	<li>Temporary skin redness or irritation</li>\n	<li>Increased sensitivity to sunlight</li>\n</ul>','[\"retino-a-cream-171169974697.jpg\"]','RE0.25',1,'0','2024-03-29 08:10:36','2025-07-21 05:37:43'),(583,0,'Retino A Cream 0.05% (20gm)','retino-a-cream-0.05-(20gm)','Tube','retino-a-cream-0-171170047769.webp','RE05','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>To begin with, it is essential to wash your hands thoroughly before and after using Retino A 0.5% Cream 20 gm. Prior to application, make sure to clean and dry the area of the skin that needs treatment. It&#39;s advisable not to apply the cream to wet skin, as it may cause skin irritation. After applying Retino A 0.5% Cream 20 gm, refrain from using any other skin products for at least an hour.</p>\n\n<p>When washing your face, use a mild soap and pat your skin dry. Take a small amount of Retino A 0.5% Cream 20 gm, about the size of a pearl, and apply it to the affected area that is clean and dry. Only apply the cream once a day, in the evening.</p>\n\n<p>It is important to avoid contact with Retino A 0.5% Cream 20 gm with your nose, mouth, eyes, ears, or vagina. If it is accidentally applied to these areas, rinse them thoroughly with water.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Retino-A 0.05% Cream is a synthetic form of vitamin A that is effective in treating acne. It works by unclogging pores on the skin and preventing the formation of pimples and spots. While it may take a few weeks to see visible results, it is important to continue using it as directed.</p>\n\n<p>It is possible for acne to worsen before it improves when using Retino-A 0.05% Cream. However, consistent use can result in clearer skin. Starting treatment early can also reduce the risk of scarring.</p>\n\n<p>Using this medication can improve your mood and self-esteem as it helps clear acne. However, it is not recommended for use on eczema or sunburned skin.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>If you are allergic to tretinoin, vitamin A, or any other ingredient present in this medication, it is essential to inform your doctor. Make sure to disclose any known allergies to drugs and describe the symptoms you experienced, such as rash, hives, itching, shortness of breath, wheezing, coughing, swelling of the face, lips, tongue, or throat, or any other signs.</p>\n\n<p>If you are pregnant or suspect that you might be pregnant, it is crucial to inform your doctor. Similarly, if you are nursing, let your doctor know before using this medication.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>Retino A 0.5% Cream 20 gm falls under the category of retinoids, which are artificial or man-made forms of vitamin A. Its main purpose is to treat acne (pimples) and skin damage caused by sun exposure. Acne is a prevalent skin condition that occurs when hair follicles become clogged with dead skin cells and oil.</p>\n\n<p>The active ingredient in Retino A 0.5% Cream 20 gm is tretinoin, also known as retinoic acid, which is a type of vitamin A. This substance works by reducing the production of oil in the skin, which helps to loosen and unblock pores on the skin&#39;s surface. This, in turn, prevents the formation of whiteheads, blackheads, and pimples.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>In most cases, the side effects of this medication will go away on their own as your body becomes accustomed to the treatment. However, if you are concerned about any persistent side effects, it is advisable to seek medical attention and consult your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>The common side effects are listed below:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Erythema (skin redness)</li>\n	<li>Skin irritation</li>\n	<li>Dry skin</li>\n	<li>Dry lips</li>\n	<li>Pale red skin</li>\n</ul>','[\"retino-a-cream-0-171170047769.webp\"]','RE05',1,'1','2024-03-29 08:21:30','2024-03-29 08:21:30'),(584,0,'Retino A Micro Gel 0.04% (15 gm)','retino-a-micro-gel-0.04-(15-gm)','gel','retino-a-micro-gel-0-171177688330.jpg','RE004','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>It is important to follow your doctor&rsquo;s instructions and read the information provided on the medication label carefully. Apply Retino-A Micro Gel as directed and avoid using more or less than the prescribed amount. Typically, a pea-sized amount of gel is sufficient to cover the affected area of the skin.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Acne Treatment: Retino-A Micro Gel is highly effective in the treatment of acne. It works by unclogging pores, reducing inflammation, and promoting the turnover of skin cells. With consistent use, it can help clear existing acne lesions and prevent new ones from forming, leading to smoother and clearer skin.</p>\n\n<p>Skin Texture Improvement: This gel helps improve skin texture by promoting the renewal of skin cells. It stimulates collagen production, which can lead to a more youthful and healthier-looking complexion. It can reduce the appearance of fine lines, wrinkles, and rough skin patches, resulting in a smoother and more even skin tone.</p>\n\n<p>Hyperpigmentation Reduction: Retino-A Micro Gel is known for its ability to reduce hyperpigmentation, including dark spots, melasma, and post-inflammatory hyperpigmentation. It inhibits the production of melanin, the pigment responsible for skin color, leading to a more even and brighter complexion.</p>\n\n<p>Treatment of Sun Damage: The use of Retino-A Micro Gel can help repair and minimize the damage caused by excessive sun exposure. It aids in the removal of dead skin cells and stimulates the production of new, healthier skin cells, reducing the appearance of sunspots and photodamage.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>It is essential to discuss your medical history and any current medications or treatments with your healthcare provider before using Retino-A Micro Gel. They can provide guidance on the appropriate usage and potential interactions.</p>','<p>Retino-A Micro Gel 0.04% (15gm) is a medication that offers several positive benefits for the treatment of various skin conditions. It contains tretinoin, a derivative of vitamin A, which is known for its beneficial effects on the skin. This gel is primarily used topically and can be prescribed by a healthcare professional.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Here Is some information about Retino-A Micro Gel 0.04% (15gm):</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>While Retino-A Micro Gel is generally well-tolerated, some individuals may experience mild side effects that usually subside as the skin adjusts to the treatment. These side effects may include temporary redness, dryness, and mild irritation. It is crucial to inform your doctor if you experience any severe or persistent side effects.</p>\n\n<p>Remember to consult your healthcare professional for personalized advice and recommendations regarding the use of Retino-A Micro Gel 0.04% (15gm). They can assess your specific skin condition and guide you through the treatment process, ensuring the best possible outcomes for your skin health.</p>','[\"retino-a-micro-gel-0-171177688330.jpg\"]','RE004',1,'0','2024-03-30 05:36:06','2025-07-21 05:37:51'),(585,0,'Retino A Micro Gel 0.1% (15 gm)','retino-a-micro-gel-0.1-(15-gm)','Gel','retino-a-micro-gel-0-171177716060.jpg','RE001','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>To ensure optimal results, it is recommended to follow the instructions provided by your healthcare provider or pharmacist when using this product. It is important to read and adhere to all the instructions on the medication label. By using the medication as directed, you can maximize its effectiveness and safety.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Acne Treatment: Retino-A Micro Gel 0.1% is highly effective in treating acne, including both inflammatory and non-inflammatory types. It works by reducing the formation of comedones (clogged pores) and promoting the shedding of dead skin cells, helping to unclog pores and prevent new acne lesions from forming. It also helps to reduce inflammation associated with acne, resulting in clearer and smoother skin.</p>\n\n<p>Skin Rejuvenation: The use of Retino-A Micro Gel 0.1% can promote skin rejuvenation. It stimulates collagen production, which helps to improve skin texture and elasticity. This can lead to a reduction in the appearance of fine lines, wrinkles, and other signs of aging, giving the skin a more youthful and vibrant look.</p>\n\n<p>Hyperpigmentation Treatment: The gel can also help in reducing hyperpigmentation, such as dark spots, melasma, and post-inflammatory hyperpigmentation. It works by increasing cell turnover and accelerating the fading of pigmented areas, resulting in a more even and uniform skin tone.</p>\n\n<p>Smoother Skin Texture: Retino-A Micro Gel 0.1% helps to improve the overall texture of the skin. It exfoliates the outer layer of dead skin cells, revealing fresher and smoother skin underneath. This can give the skin a softer and more refined appearance.</p>\n\n<p>Prevention of New Acne Breakouts: Regular use of Retino-A Micro Gel 0.1% can help prevent new acne breakouts by keeping the pores clear and reducing the production of sebum (oil) in the skin. This can be particularly beneficial for individuals who are prone to recurring acne.</p>\n\n<p>Non-Greasy and Easily Absorbed: The gel formulation of Retino-A Micro makes it non-greasy and easily absorbed into the skin. It does not leave a heavy or sticky residue, allowing for a comfortable and convenient application.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>While Retino-A Micro Gel 0.1% offers numerous benefits, it is important to take certain precautions when using it:</p>\n\n<p>Sun Protection: Tretinoin can increase the skin&rsquo;s sensitivity to sunlight. Therefore, it is recommended to use sunscreen with a high SPF and avoid excessive sun exposure to protect the skin from harmful UV rays.</p>\n\n<p>Gradual Introduction: It is advisable to start with a lower concentration of tretinoin and gradually increase the frequency and strength of application as tolerated by your skin. This helps to minimize potential initial skin irritation.</p>\n\n<p>Avoid Irritating Products: Harsh cleansers, exfoliants, or products containing alcohol may increase skin irritation when used in combination with Retino-A Micro Gel. It is best to avoid such products or consult a dermatologist for suitable skincare recommendations.</p>\n\n<p>Pregnancy and Nursing: It is important to consult with a healthcare professional before using Retino-A Micro Gel 0.1% during pregnancy or while breastfeeding, as it may not be recommended for use during these periods.</p>','<p>Retino-A Micro Gel 0.1% (15 gm) is a topical medication that contains tretinoin, a form of vitamin A. It is primarily used for the treatment of acne and certain other skin conditions. This gel has been widely recognized for its positive effects on the skin, offering several benefits to individuals seeking clearer and healthier skin.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>While side effects may occur with the use of Retino-A Micro Gel 0.1%, they are generally mild and transient. These may include:</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Temporary skin redness or irritation</li>\n	<li>Dryness or flakiness of the skin</li>\n	<li>Mild itching or stinging sensation</li>\n	<li>Increased sensitivity to sunlight</li>\n</ul>','[\"retino-a-micro-gel-0-171177716060.jpg\"]','RE001',1,'0','2024-03-30 05:39:28','2025-07-21 05:37:54'),(586,0,'Retino AC Gel 0.025% 1% (15 gm)','retino-ac-gel-0.025-1-(15-gm)','Gel','retino-ac-gel-0-171177726261.jpg','RE025','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Take the 15 gm Retino Ac Gel as directed by your doctor. Depending on your medical conditions, you are encouraged to use Retino Ac Gel 15 gm for as long as your doctor has prescribed it for you. Dermatitis, skin peeling, dryness, and application site responses (burning, itchiness, itching, and redness) are possible. The majority of these Retino Ac Gel 15 gm adverse effects are temporary and go away on their own. However, contact your doctor if the adverse effects continue to bother you.Before and after using the 15 gm Retino Ac Gel, wash your hands. As directed by the doctor, use Retino Ac Gel 15 gm to the afflicted region. If Retino Ac Gel 15 gm accidently gets in your eyes, thoroughly rinse them out with water.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Combining two medications, Tretinoin (vitamin A) and Clindamycin (antibiotic), Retino Ac Gel 15 gm is primarily used to treat acne (pimples). A vitamin A derivative called retinol replenishes the skin, lowers oil production, and aids in maintaining open pores. Clindamycin is a member of the group of antibiotics that prevents bacteria from producing vital proteins needed for growth, multiplication, and population expansion. Together, they prevent the development of acne and block or slow down bacterial growth.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Please let your doctor know if you have ever had an adverse reaction to Retino Ac Gel 15 gm or any other medication. if you suffer from an inflammatory bowel condition that is chronic (like Crohn&#39;s disease or ulcerative colitis). if you have folliculitis or other acute inflammatory skin diseases, particularly perioral dermatitis around the mouth. Retino Ac Gel 15 gm should not be used in the sun as it may increase skin sensitivity to sunlight and result in sunburn. When going outside, wear sun protection clothes and apply sunscreen to avoid becoming sunburned. if you have a history of colitis, a chronic digestive condition marked by substantial or persistent diarrhoea and/or cramping in the abdomen. Applying Retino Ac Gel 15 gm on broken, sunburned, or sensitive skin shouldn&#39;t be done. Retino Ac Gel 15 gm should not be used in the sun as it may increase skin sensitivity to sunlight and result in sunburn. When going outside, wear sun protection clothes and apply sunscreen to avoid becoming sunburned. Before using Retino Ac Gel 15 gm, please let your doctor know if you have intestinal issues or eczema. Before using Retino Ac Gel 15 gm, please let your doctor know if you are pregnant or nursing.</p>','<p>Retino Ac Gel 15 gm is a member of the group of antiacne dermatological treatments used to treat acne (pimples). When oil and dead skin cells clog hair follicles, acne, a common skin disorder, develops. The bacterium that causes acne feeds on sebum, the natural oil generated by skin, producing inflammation and redness.</p>\n\n<p>Tretinoin (vitamin A) and Clindamycin (antibiotic) are the two medications included in Retino Ac Gel 15 gm. A vitamin A derivative called retinol replenishes the skin, lowers oil production, and aids in maintaining open pores. Clindamycin is a member of the group of antibiotics that prevents bacteria from producing vital proteins needed for growth, multiplication, and population expansion. Together, they prevent the development of acne and block or slow down bacterial growth.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Application site reactions (burning, irritation, itching and redness)</li>\n	<li>Dermatitis</li>\n	<li>Skin peeling</li>\n	<li>Dryness</li>\n</ul>','[\"retino-ac-gel-0-171177726261.jpg\"]','RE25',1,'0','2024-03-30 05:42:39','2025-10-08 07:00:44'),(587,0,'Revize Micro Gel 0.025% (20gm)','revize-micro-gel-0.025-(20gm)','Gel','revize-micro-gel-0-171177748350.webp','RE025','<p>How to Use:</p>\n\n<p>Before applying Revize Micro 0.025% Gel (20 g), it is important to wash your hands thoroughly. Clean and dry the affected area of the skin before using the gel. Avoid applying the gel to wet skin as it may cause skin irritation, and do not wash the treated area immediately after application. Wait for at least one hour before using any other skin products. After washing your face with mild soap and patting it dry, take a small, pearl-sized amount of the gel on your fingertip and apply it to the affected area once a day in the evening. Do not let the gel come into contact with your eyes, mouth, nose, ears, or vagina. If this happens accidentally, rinse thoroughly with water.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Revize Micro 0.025% Gel is a retinoid medication that contains a form of vitamin A. It is primarily used to treat acne by unclogging skin pores and preventing the formation of pimples or spots. Although it may take a few weeks to see results, it is important to continue using the medication as directed. In some cases, acne may worsen before it improves, but with consistent use, your skin should become clearer. Starting treatment early can also help prevent scarring. An improved skin condition can boost your confidence and enhance your mood. However, this medication should not be used if you have eczema or sunburned skin.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before using Revize Micro 0.025% Gel, it is important to inform your doctor if you have any sunburn, sun sensitivity, eczema, or any other skin problems. This medication should not be used on sunburned skin or on skin that is eczematous. Revize Micro 0.025% Gel should be used with caution by pregnant and breastfeeding women. It should not be applied to the nose, mouth, eyes, ears, or vagina. In case the medication comes in contact with these areas accidentally, rinse thoroughly with water. Also, avoid applying other skin products for at least 1 hour after applying Revize Micro 0.025% Gel.</p>','<p>Revize Micro 0.025% Gel belongs to the retinoid group of drugs and is primarily used to treat acne. It may also be used to treat wrinkles, skin spots, and rough skin. Acne is a skin condition that involves inflammation of the sebaceous follicles of the face and upper body, leading to lesions on the face, back, upper chest, and shoulders.</p>\n\n<p>Before using Revize Micro 0.025% Gel, it is important to inform your doctor if you have any sunburn, sun sensitivity, or other skin problems. If you are pregnant, Revize Micro 0.025% Gel should only be used if specifically directed by your doctor. Use Revize Micro 0.025% Gel with caution if you are breastfeeding.</p>\n\n<p>It is important to consult your doctor before using Revize Micro 0.025% Gel in children under 12 years old, as its safety and effectiveness in this age group have not been established. The most common side effect of using REVIZE MICRO 0.025% GEL is skin irritation, such as redness, burning, stinging, dryness, and peeling. If any of these side effects worsen, contact your doctor.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>The majority of side effects do not necessitate medical attention and tend to subside as your body becomes accustomed to the medication. However, if the side effects persist or cause concern, it is recommended to consult yo