ant or nursing. While taking Ribavin 200 Capsule 4s and for 7 months after stopping therapy with Ribavin 200 Capsule 4s, it is advised to utilize effective contraceptive methods to prevent pregnancy. If you have the hepatitis C virus infection, you are urged to take the necessary precautions to stop the infection from spreading to other people. Please get medical attention right away if you suffer nausea, vomiting, or stomach pain while taking Ribavin 200 Capsule 4s since these could be signs of the rare but serious side effect known as lactic acidosis (excess lactic acid in the blood).</p>','<p>The medicine Ribavin 200 Capsule 4 is a member of the antiviral drug class used to treat chronic hepatitis C virus (HCV) infection. It is used in conjunction with other medications to take Ribavin 200 Capsule 4s. The hepatitis C virus (HCV) is the primary cause of hepatitis C, a serious liver infection. It spreads through contact with the blood of the sick individual and is infectious (spreads from one person to another).</p>\n\n<p>Ribavirin, an antiviral medication found in Ribavin 200 Capsule 4s, blocks the function of viral RNA (genetic material), which is necessary for the virus to grow. As a result, it helps to lower the level of hepatitis C virus in the body and prevents the virus from producing new viruses.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n	<li>Fever</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Tiredness</li>\n</ul>','[\"ribavin-200mg-171177768733.jpg\"]','RI200',1,'0','2024-03-30 05:48:51','2025-10-08 07:01:10'),(589,0,'Rivamer 1.5 mg','rivamer-1.5-mg','Capsule','rivamer-1-17117779229.webp','Ri1.5','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>It is important to follow your doctor&rsquo;s instructions and the instructions on the medication label when taking Rivamer 1.5mg. Take the medication exactly as prescribed and do not exceed the recommended dosage. Typically, Rivamer is taken orally once or twice a day with or without food. It is importan