ine, or if you have any additional allergies before beginning treatment with metronidazole. There is a possibility that this product contains inactive substances, which, if present, could result in allergic responses or other complications. Discuss the matter further with your pharmacist for further information.</p>\n\n<p>Before you begin using this medicine, it is important that you discuss your medical history with your doctor or pharmacist, specifically focusing on any blood problems (blood dyscrasias).</p>\n\n<p>During pregnancy, it is important to only use this drug when it is absolutely necessary. Talk to your healthcare provider about the potential drawbacks and advantages.</p>\n\n<p>There is no evidence to suggest that this medicine makes its way into breast milk. Before starting to breastfeed, you should talk to your healthcare provider.</p>','<p>A skin condition known as rosacea, which is a form of adult acne, can be remedied by applying this drug topically to the affected area. It is possible that it will assist in reducing the amount of redness, edema, and acne that are produced by rosacea.Antibiotic treatment is provided by this drug. Metronidazole is thought to be effective in the treatment of rosacea by bringing about a reduction in inflammation and edema. There are also formulations of this drug that include sunscreens (for more information, see the Notes section).</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Stinging</li>\n	<li>burning</li>\n	<li>skin irritation</li>\n	<li>dryness</li>\n	<li>redness</li>\n	<li>metallic taste</li>\n	<li>nausea</li>\n</ul>','[\"roza-gel-30-gm-171178554382.jpg\"]','RO30',1,'0','2024-03-30 07:59:44','2025-10-08 07:03:18'),(603,0,'Rozavel 40mg','rozavel-40mg','tablet','rozavel-40mg-171178586739.jpg','RO40','<p>Utilising the Rozavel Tablet</p>\n\n<p>Follow your doctor&#39;s instructions for this medication&#39;s dosage and duration. Take it all in at once. Don&#39;t eat it, break it, or crush it. Although the Rozavel 40 Tablet can be taken any way, it is best to take it at a set time.</p>\n\n<p>Workings of Rozavel Tablet</p>\n\n<p>Rozavel 40 Tablet is a statin that lowers cholesterol. It works by inhibiting an enzyme called HMG-CoA-reductase, which the body needs to produce cholesterol. As a result, &quot;bad&quot; cholesterol (LDL) and triglycerides are reduced, while &quot;good&quot; cholesterol (HDL) is increased.</p>\n\n<p>Rozavel Tablet Uses</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>High cholesterol treatment</li>\n	<li>Heart attack and stroke prevention</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Rozavel Tablet Benefits in the Treatment of High Cholesterol</p>\n\n<p>The drug Rozavel 40 Tablet is a member of the statin drug class. It functions by lowering your blood&#39;s level of &quot;bad&quot; cholesterol (LDL) and increasing the level of &quot;good&quot; cholesterol (HDL). Lowering your cholesterol lowers your risk of developing heart disease and prolongs your lifespan.</p>\n\n<p>To get the most out of this medication, take it frequently and adopt the right lifestyle habits (such eating well and exercising regularly). Even if you feel good, keep taking it.</p>\n\n<p>Regarding Heart Attack and Stroke Prevention</p>\n\n<p>High cholesterol levels can lead to atherosclerosis, which narrows your blood vessels and increases your risk of heart attack and stroke. Reducing this fat helps you stay healthier for longer by lowering the likelihood of this happening. Despite feeling fine, continue taking this medication.</p>','<p>The drug Rozavel 40 Tablet is a member of the statin drug class. It lowers cholesterol and lowers the chance of developing heart disease. A fatty substance called cholesterol causes your blood vessels to narrow as it accumulates, which can result in a heart attack or stroke.</p>\n\n<p>The drug Rozavel 40 Tablet is frequently prescribed and is thought to be secure for long-term use. It may be consumed either before or after food. Although you can take it whenever you like, try to take it at the same time every day. The majority of people with high cholesterol are not sickly most of the time, but quitting your medication may cause your cholesterol levels to rise, worsening your health and raising your risk of heart disease and stroke.</p>\n\n<p>It&#39;s critical to regularly monitor your cholesterol levels. This medication is just one element of a therapy plan that should also include a balanced diet, frequent exercise, quitting smoking, drinking alcohol in moderation, and weight loss. While taking this medication, you can eat normally, but try to stay away from meals that are high in fat.</p>\n\n<p>This medication frequently causes adverse effects such muscle soreness, weakness, nausea, headaches, and stomach pain. These are typically minor and go away quickly. If they continue, you notice any yellowing of your eyes, or you experience recurring or inexplicable muscle problems, see a doctor.</p>\n\n<p>Conditions like liver disease should not be treated with this medication. Additionally, this medication should not be taken by women who are pregnant or nursing because it could harm the unborn child. Patients with diabetes should keep an eye on their blood sugar levels while taking this medication because it may cause an increase.</p>','<p>The majority of adverse effects are temporary and go away as your body becomes used to the medication. If they persist or you&#39;re concerned about them, speak with your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>Rozavel common side effects</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>muscle ache</li>\n	<li>Weakness</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Continent pain</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n	<li>aching joints</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n</ul>','[\"rozavel-40mg-171178586739.jpg\"]','RO40',1,'0','2024-03-30 08:05:13','2025-10-08 07:03:26'),(604,0,'Rozavel EZ 10/10mg','rozavel-ez-10/10mg','tablet','rozavel-ez-10-10mg-171178604385.jpg','RO10','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Rozavel EZ Tablet 10s should be taken as directed by your attending physician. It is recommended that you continue taking the Rozavel EZ Tablet 10s for the duration of time that your physician has prescribed for you, taking into account the various aspects of your health. Nausea, muscular discomfort, joint pain, weakness, headache, abdominal pain, diarrhea, upper respiratory tract infection, and the common cold are all possible side effects of using this medication. The majority of these unwanted effects of Rozavel EZ Tablet 10s can be managed without medical intervention and will go away on their own over time. However, you should consult your physician if the adverse effects continue even after treatment has been discontinued.Rozavel EZ Tablet 10s should be taken as a whole with a glass of water; they should not be crushed, broken, or chewed.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>In cases when initial dietary efforts have not been successful in bringing down cholesterol levels, additional treatment with Rozavel EZ Tablet 10s can be helpful in treating excessive cholesterol. This is especially true for heart patients. The use of Rozavel EZ Tablet 10&#39;s reduces the risk of cardiovascular disease as well as the risk of coronary events such as heart attack, stroke, and chest pain associated with the heart (angina). Rosuvastatin is the active ingredient in Rozavel EZ Tablet 10&#39;s. Rosuvastatin is a lipid-lowering drug that prevents your body from producing &#39;bad&#39; cholesterol (LDL) while simultaneously boosting levels of &#39;good&#39; cholesterol (HDL). It does this by inhibiting liver enzymes, which in turn leads to the liver producing less cholesterol. Therefore, taking Rozavel EZ Tablet 10s will result in a greater uptake and breakdown of cholesterol already present in the blood by the liver. Ezetimibe, on the other hand, is a cholesterol absorption inhibitor that stops the body from absorbing cholesterol from the intestines. This happens when cholesterol is consumed with food. When combined, they produce a more effective reduction in the amount of cholesterol found in your body.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>If you have ever experienced an unusual or adverse reaction to this medication or any other medication, let your doctor know right away. If you have diabetes, severe lung disease, thyroid gland issues, or musculoskeletal disorders (including myopathy and rhabdomyolysis), you should see a doctor before taking any medications. If you regularly take Rozavel EZ Tablet 10s, it is advised that you have a liver enzyme test performed. Before consuming alcohol, a person who has liver disease or drinks excessively should visit a doctor.&nbsp; If a person consistently takes Rozavel EZ Tablet 10&#39;s, higher HbA1c and fasting glucose readings may be seen. Therefore, before undergoing these diabetes tests, you should let your doctor know. Inform your doctor right away if you are pregnant, trying to get pregnant, or nursing because Rozavel EZ Tablet 10s contain rosuvastatin, which can be harmful to an unborn child. A sugar called lactose is present in Rozavel EZ Tablets, 10 of them. Before taking these Rozavel EZ Tablet 10&#39;s, see your doctor if you have been told by your health care provider that you have a sensitivity to certain sugars.</p>','<p>The medication known as HMG-CoA reductase inhibitors (statins) and&#39;sterol absorption inhibitor&#39; is classified as a member of the Rozavel EZ Tablet 10&#39;s family. The primary application for Rozavel EZ Tablet 10s is the management of elevated cholesterol levels. The accumulation of unhealthy levels of fats (lipid) in the blood is known medically as dyslipidaemia (high cholesterol level). When a person has this condition, their levels of low-density lipoprotein (LDL, also known as &quot;bad cholesterol&quot;) and triglycerides (TG) are consistently elevated, while their levels of high-density lipoprotein (HDL, also known as &quot;good cholesterol&quot;) are much lower.</p>\n\n<p>Rosuvastatin, which belongs to a class of drugs known as HMG-CoA reductase inhibitors (statins), and ezetimibe, which blocks the body&#39;s ability to absorb cholesterol, are both included in Rozavel EZ Tablet 10&#39;s. Rosuvastatin is the active ingredient in Rozavel EZ Tablet 10&#39;s. Rosuvastatin is a lipid-lowering drug that prevents your body from producing &#39;bad&#39; cholesterol (LDL) while simultaneously boosting levels of &#39;good&#39; cholesterol (HDL). It does this by inhibiting liver enzymes, which in turn leads to the liver producing less cholesterol. Therefore, taking Rozavel EZ Tablet 10s will result in a greater uptake and breakdown of cholesterol already present in the blood by the liver. Ezetimibe, on the other hand, is a cholesterol absorption inhibitor that stops the body from absorbing cholesterol from the intestines. This happens when cholesterol is consumed with food. When combined, they produce a more effective reduction in the amount of cholesterol found in your body.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Muscle pain</li>\n	<li>Weakness</li>\n	<li>Joint pain</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Abdominal pain</li>\n</ul>','[\"rozavel-ez-10-10mg-171178604385.jpg\"]','RO10',1,'0','2024-03-30 08:08:01','2025-10-08 07:03:33'),(605,0,'Salicylix 6% (50gm)','salicylix-6-(50gm)','Tube','salicylix-6-50gm-17117866168.jpg','SA06','<p>How to Use:</p>\n\n<p>Follow your physician&#39;s instructions when using SALICYLIX SF 6% OINTMENT. Remember that it is intended for external use only. Prior to use, wash your hands and create a lather by adding water. Apply a thin layer of the ointment to the affected or wet skin area and gently massage it in. Avoid using this medication around your eyes, including on your eyelids. Your doctor will determine the appropriate dose and duration of treatment based on your age, body weight, and medical condition.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Acne treatment: The ointment contains salicylic acid, which helps to unblock clogged pores and reduce inflammation, thereby treating acne.</li>\n	<li>Psoriasis treatment: salicylic acid helps to reduce the thickening of the skin and scaling caused by psoriasis.</li>\n	<li>Exfoliation: The medication increases the turnover rate of skin cells, which aids in the shedding of dead skin cells, thereby providing exfoliation benefits.</li>\n	<li>Comedolytic: Salicylix SF 6% Ointment also has comedolytic properties that prevent the formation of blemishes.</li>\n	<li>Anti-inflammatory: The ointment has anti-inflammatory properties that can help reduce the redness and swelling associated with certain skin conditions.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Salicylix 6% (50 g) is meant for external use only and should not be ingested.</li>\n	<li>It should not be applied to broken, irritated, or infected skin.</li>\n	<li>Avoid using Salicylix 6% (50 g) around the eyes, including the eyelids.</li>\n	<li>Do not use this medication if you are allergic to salicylic acid or any of its ingredients.</li>\n	<li>Inform your doctor if you have any underlying medical conditions or are currently taking any medications.</li>\n	<li>Salicylix 6% (50 g) should not be used by pregnant or breastfeeding women without consulting a doctor.</li>\n	<li>It is important to follow the dosage and duration recommended by your doctor to avoid any adverse effects.</li>\n	<li>Do not apply Salicylix 6% (50 g) in larger amounts or for a longer duration than prescribed by your doctor.</li>\n	<li>If you experience any severe side effects or allergic reactions, such as difficulty breathing, hives, or swelling of the face, lips, tongue, or throat, stop using the medication and seek immediate medical attention.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>Salicylix SF 6% Ointment 50 g falls under the category of keratolytic agents that are mainly used to peel and shed the outer layer of the skin in psoriasis and acne conditions. Salicylix SF 6% Ointment, 50 g, is known for its comedolytic (prevents blemish formation) and anti-inflammatory properties. Acne is caused when hair follicles are obstructed by oil and dead skin cells.</p>\n\n<p>Salicylix SF 6% Ointment 50 g contains salicylic acid, which helps treat psoriasis and acne by reducing inflammation and unplugging blocked pores to reduce pimple size. Moreover, it enhances the turnover rate of upper skin cells, which helps in peeling and shedding the dead skin, leading to the treatment of comedones.</p>\n\n<p>This ointment is meant for external use only, and its usage should be as per the dosage and duration advised by your doctor. Dry skin, erythema, burning sensation, skin irritation, and skin rash are some common side effects of Salicylix SF 6% Ointment 50 g, which generally resolve on their own. However, if these side effects persist, it is recommended that you consult your doctor.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Dry skin</li>\n	<li>Erythema (skin redness)</li>\n	<li>Skin irritation</li>\n	<li>Slight tingling sensation</li>\n	<li>Skin rash</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n</ul>','[\"salicylix-6-50gm-17117866168.jpg\"]','SA06',1,'0','2024-03-30 08:17:38','2025-10-08 07:03:42'),(606,0,'Sebifin 250mg','sebifin-250mg','tablet','sebifin-250mg-171178684760.jpg','SE250','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>As directed, use Sebifin Tablets, 15 mg. Based on your medical situation, your doctor will advise you on how frequently you should take Sebifin Tablet 15&#39;s. Diarrhoea, tummy aches, headaches, and changes in or a lack of taste are all possible symptoms for some people. Most of these Sebifin Tablet 15 adverse effects subside over time without the need for medical intervention. However, please see a doctor if the adverse effects worsen or persist. Take it as directed by the doctor, either with or without food. With a glass of water, swallow the entire tablet. Do not chew, shatter, or crush it.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Antifungal treatment is provided by Sebifin Tablet 15&#39;s. Tablets are the most common form of treatment for fungal infections of the fingernails and toenails. Tinea capitis, often known as ringworm of the scalp, can be treated using oral granules.&nbsp; The fungal cell membranes that are important for their survival are destroyed by Sebifin Tablet 15, which prevents the entry of undesired substances into the cells and stops the leakage of cell contents. Consequently, this eliminates the illness and destroys the fungi.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Do not take Sebifin Tablet 15&#39;s if you have ever had an allergic reaction to terbinafine. Before beginning treatment with Sebifin Tablet 15&#39;s, it is strongly suggested that you speak with a medical professional, especially if you are pregnant or a nursing mother. While using Sebifin Tablet 15&#39;s, you should try to avoid or at least restrict your exposure to the sun because it may make your skin more sensitive to the sun. When you go outside, make sure to protect your skin from sunburn by donning protective clothing and using sunscreen. Before taking Sebifin Tablet 15&#39;s, you should consult your physician if you suffer from lupus, which is an autoimmune illness, a weakened immune system, renal difficulties, or liver problems. Inform your physician as soon as possible if you have depressive symptoms such as a feeling of worthlessness or sadness, a loss of interest or energy in everyday activities, changes in mood, restlessness, or a change in the manner in which you sleep.</p>','<p>The antifungals medication class includes Sebifin Tablet 15&#39;s. Toenail and fingernail fungal infections are treated with tablets. Treatment for tinea capitis (scalp ringworm) involves oral granules. Onychomycosis, or fungal nail infections, are frequent infections of the toenails or fingernails that make the nail thick, discolored, or more prone to breaking. Tinea capitis is a contagious fungal infection of the scalp that results in ring-shaped hairless, itchy, and scaly regions.</p>\n\n<p>Terbinafine, an antifungal included in Sebifin Tablet 15, inhibits the growth of fungi by attacking the cell membranes that are necessary for their existence because they block the entry of outside substances and restrict cell leakage. eliminates the fungal infection and kills the fungi as a result.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Diarrhoea</li>\n	<li>Indigestion</li>\n	<li>Stomach pain</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Taste disturbance</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n</ul>','[\"sebifin-250mg-171178684760.jpg\"]','SE250',1,'0','2024-03-30 08:23:14','2025-10-08 07:03:51'),(607,0,'Sefdin 300 mg','sefdin-300-mg','Capsule','sefdin-300-mg-171180368091.jpg','SE300','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Follow your doctor&#39;s instructions when taking Sefdin 300 mg Capsule 6s. As long as your doctor has recommended Sefdin 300 mg Capsule 6s for you depending on your medical condition, you are urged to take them. You might occasionally have nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, stomach pain, rash, headache, or vaginal itching or discharge. Most of these Sefdin 300 mg Capsule 6 adverse effects subside over time without the need for medical intervention. However, please see a doctor if the adverse effects worsen or persist. With a glass of water, swallow it whole. Do not chew, break, or chew it.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Sefdin 300 mg Capsule 6&#39;s includes Cefdinir is an antibiotic belonging to the cephalosporin class that is used to treat a variety of bacterial infections. Cefdinir is an antibiotic with a wide range of activity, meaning that it is effective against gram-negative and gram-positive bacteria that are both aerobic (grow in the presence of oxygen) and anaerobic (grow in the absence of oxygen). It prevents the production of the bacterial cell wall, which is essential for the bacteria&#39;s continued existence because it acts as a protective coating. This causes damage to the bacterial cell wall, which ultimately results in the death of the bacteria.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Please let your doctor know if you are allergic to Sefdin 300 mg Capsule 6, cephalosporin antibiotics, or any other medications. Inform your doctor if you have kidney issues or inflammation of the large intestine before taking Sefdin 300 mg Capsule 6s. Before using Sefdin 300 mg Capsule 6s, talk to a doctor if you are pregnant or nursing. Babies younger than 6 months of age should not use Sefdin 300 mg Capsule 6s since their safety and efficacy have not been shown. Sefdin 300 mg Capsule 6s may produce dizziness, therefore drive only if you are aware. For best benefits, it is advised that you take Sefdin 300 mg Capsules 6 for the entire suggested course. Sefdin 300 mg Capsule 6s may interfere with particular tests, like the coombs test and urine glucose (sugar) test, causing false-positive findings. Therefore, before having any tests, let your doctor know that you are taking Sefdin 300 mg Capsule 6. The recommended time interval between taking Sefdin 300 mg Capsule 6 and antacids containing aluminum, magnesium, iron supplements, or multivitamins containing iron is at least two hours. These could reduce the body&#39;s ability to absorb Sefdin 300 mg Capsule 6s.</p>','<p>The prescription known as antibiotics, of which Sefdin 300 mg Capsule 6&#39;s are a member, is prescribed for the treatment of a wide variety of bacterial infections that can affect the urinary tract, bones and joints, heart, lungs, brain, chest, ears, skin, or other soft tissues. A bacterial infection is a situation in which pathogenic bacteria proliferate inside the body and create an infection. Bacteria can be both beneficial and destructive. It has the ability to infect any region of the body and can quickly reproduce itself. Infections brought on by a virus, such the flu or the common cold, are resistant to the antiviral effects of Sefdin 300 mg Capsule 6s.</p>\n\n<p>Cefdinir is a cephalosporin antibiotic that is contained within Sefdin 300 mg Capsule 6s. This antibiotic works by inhibiting the production of the bacterial cell wall, which is essential for the bacteria&#39;s continued existence. This causes damage to the bacterial cell wall, which ultimately results in the death of the bacteria.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Diarrhoea</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Stomach pain</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Rash</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n</ul>','[\"sefdin-300-mg-171180368091.jpg\"]','SE300',1,'0','2024-03-30 14:34:36','2025-10-08 07:03:58'),(608,0,'Selgin 5 mg','selgin-5-mg','tablet','selgin-5-mg-171181775579.png','Se05','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>As directed by your doctor, take one Selgin Tablet 10 with a glass of water, with or without food. Swallow the tablet whole. Do not chew, break, or chew it. Based on your medical situation, your doctor will advise you on how frequently to take Selgin Tablet 10&#39;s. Some persons may develop a sore mouth, swollen gums, dizziness, nausea, sleep difficulties, mouth ulcers, constipation, loss of balance, and difficulty controlling their movements. The majority of these Selgin Tablet 10 adverse effects gradually go away over time without the need for medical intervention. However, please see a doctor if the adverse effects worsen or persist.As directed by the doctor, take Selgin Tablets, 10 each. With a glass of water, swallow it whole. Don&#39;t eat, shatter, or crush it.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>The antiparkinson medication known as Selgin Tablet 10s is what doctors reach for when treating patients with Parkinson&#39;s disease. Parkinson&#39;s disease is characterized by the gradual death of nerve cells that are responsible for the production of dopamine, an essential chemical messenger in the regulation of movement. As a result, there is a drop in the amount of dopamine. The mechanism of action of Selgin Tablet 10 is the inhibition of the action of the enzyme known as monoamine oxidase-B, which is responsible for the natural breakdown of dopamine. Dopamine levels in the brain are so increased, and their levels are restored. As a result, the signs and symptoms of Parkinson&#39;s disease are alleviated. In order to lessen the severity of uncontrollable movements, Selgin Tablet 10s can be used by themselves or in conjunction with other medications like levodopa.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Please let your doctor know if you have a history of allergies to Selgin Tablets 10 or any other medications. If you are pregnant or nursing, avoid taking Selgin Tablet 10s and talk to a doctor. For children, Selgin Tablet 10&#39;s are not advised. Please let your doctor know if you are taking Selgin Tablet 10s if you are going to have any type of surgery because it may interact with other medications used during general anesthesia. Avoid taking Selgin Tablet 10&#39;s if you have stomach or duodenal ulcers, angina (chest pain), high blood pressure, major heart or blood vessel problems, hyperthyroidism (overactive thyroid gland), fast or irregular heartbeat, narrow-angle glaucoma, pheochromocytoma (tumour of the adrenal gland), prostatic adenoma (tumour of the prostate gland), schizophrenia, advanced dementia (loss of memory and other thinking abilities). Before taking Selgin Tablet 10s, let your doctor know if you experience sleep issues, anxiety, a history of stomach ulcers, kidney or liver issues, or strange desires like excessive gambling or increased sexual behavior.</p>','<p>Selgin Tablet 10s are a member of the monoamine oxidase-B inhibitor class of antiparkinson medications used to treat Parkinson&#39;s disease. Parkinson&#39;s disease is a condition of the central nervous system that impairs movement. It impairs balance, coordination, and balance, as well as causes stiffness and tremors. Dopamine levels in Parkinson&#39;s patients fall when dopamine-producing nerve cells start to die off. Dopamine is a chemical messenger that is crucial for controlling movement.</p>\n\n<p>The active ingredient in Selgin Tablet 10s is selegiline, which blocks the function of the monoamine oxidase-B enzyme that normally breaks down dopamine. Dopamine is so increased and its level in the brain is restored, relieving Parkinson&#39;s disease symptoms.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Sore mouth</li>\n	<li>Swollen gums</li>\n	<li>Loss of balance</li>\n	<li>Difficulty in controlling movements</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n</ul>','[\"selgin-5-mg-171181775579.png\"]','SE05',1,'0','2024-03-30 16:56:10','2025-10-08 07:04:05'),(609,0,'Seretide Diskus 100 mcg / 50 mcg (60 Doses)','seretide-diskus-100-mcg-/-50-mcg-(60-doses)','Accuhaler','seretide-diskus-100-mcg-50-mcg-60-doses-1711818187100.webp','SE60','<p>How to Use:</p>\n\n<p>To use Seretide 50 mcg or 100 mcg Accuhaler, follow these steps: Open the device by pushing the lever, breathe out gently, place the mouthpiece in your mouth, and inhale slowly while pressing down the lever. Hold your breath for about 10 seconds, then exhale. Close the Accuhaler by sliding the lever back. Use as prescribed by your healthcare professional. If unsure, consult your healthcare provider or pharmacist for guidance.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Seretide 50mcg/100mcg Accuhaler is a medication that helps keep your lung airways open by relaxing the muscles. This allows air to flow in and out more easily, relieving symptoms like chest tightness, shortness of breath, wheezing, and coughing. It is safe and effective, starting to work within minutes and providing relief for several hours.</p>\n\n<p>It is used to treat and prevent respiratory disorders such as asthma attacks and chronic obstructive pulmonary diseases (COPD). Specifically, it helps improve lung function and prevents the worsening of conditions like emphysema and chronic bronchitis. Seretide 50mcg/100mcg Accuhaler is a combination of two drugs: salmeterol, a bronchodilator that widens the airways, and fluticasone, a corticosteroid that reduces airway inflammation.</p>\n\n<p>Fluticasone blocks the production of inflammatory chemicals, while salmeterol relaxes the airway muscles, resulting in easier breathing. This combination provides effective relief and helps you carry out your daily activities more comfortably. It is important to follow your doctor&#39;s advice and not stop using the medication without their guidance.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Take the medication as prescribed and do not exceed the recommended dose.</li>\n	<li>Use Seretide Diskus regularly as a maintenance medication, even if you&#39;re not experiencing symptoms.</li>\n	<li>Do not stop using it suddenly without consulting your doctor.</li>\n	<li>Inform your healthcare provider about any existing medical conditions and allergies.</li>\n	<li>Monitor for side effects and contact your doctor if you experience any persistent or severe reactions.</li>\n	<li>Keep track of your asthma symptoms and report any changes to your doctor.</li>\n	<li>Take precautions to avoid triggers that can worsen your respiratory symptoms.</li>\n	<li>Consult your doctor if you are pregnant, planning to become pregnant, or breastfeeding.<br />\n	&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>','<p>Seretide 50mcg/100mcg Accuhaler is a respiratory medication used to treat and prevent asthma attacks and chronic obstructive pulmonary diseases (COPD). Asthma and COPD are conditions that cause difficulty breathing due to narrowed airways, swelling, and excess mucus production.</p>\n\n<p>This medication combines two drugs: salmeterol, a long-acting bronchodilator that relaxes airway muscles and improves airflow, and fluticasone, a corticosteroid that reduces airway inflammation by blocking the production of certain chemicals.</p>\n\n<p>By widening the airways and reducing inflammation, Seretide 50 mg/100 mg Accuhaler helps make breathing easier for individuals with respiratory disorders like asthma and COPD.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Respiratory tract infection</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Sore throat</li>\n	<li>Cough</li>\n	<li>Bone, muscle or joint pain</li>\n</ul>','[\"seretide-diskus-100-mcg-50-mcg-60-doses-1711818187100.webp\"]','SE60',1,'0','2024-03-30 17:03:59','2025-10-08 07:04:13'),(610,0,'Seretide Diskus 250 mcg / 50 mcg (60 Doses)','seretide-diskus-250-mcg-/-50-mcg-(60-doses)','Accuhaler','seretide-diskus-250-mcg-50-mcg-60-doses-171186957760.jpg','SE250','<p>How to Use:</p>\n\n<p>To utilize Seretide 50 mcg/250 mcg Accuhaler 60&#39;s, it is important to administer it through inhalation with the provided inhaler. Your doctor or nurse will provide instructions on how to correctly use the inhaler. Position the inhaler in an upright position within your mouth, and place the mouthpiece between your teeth. Be careful not to bite down on it. As you begin to inhale through your mouth, press the top of the inhaler to release a puff of medication while continuing to breathe. Subsequently, hold your breath for as long as is comfortable before gently removing the inhaler. Exhale slowly. If an additional puff is required, wait for a minute before repeating the aforementioned steps. To prevent dust or debris from accumulating, remember to close the mouthpiece with the cover after each use.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Seretide 50 mcg/250 mcg Accuhaler 60 is an effective medication for treating and preventing respiratory disorders such as asthma and chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD). It significantly improves lung function and effectively manages conditions like emphysema and chronic bronchitis, which are characterized by shortness of breath and inflammation of the bronchial tubes.</p>\n\n<p>This medication combines two active ingredients, salmeterol and fluticasone propionate, which are specifically formulated to address asthma symptoms and COPD. Salmeterol belongs to the class of bronchodilators, which work by relaxing the muscles and widening the airways in the lungs. This mechanism facilitates easier and smoother breathing. Fluticasone propionate, on the other hand, is classified as a corticosteroid. It acts on the inner cells of the nasal lining to inhibit the release of certain inflammatory chemicals responsible for allergic reactions. By doing so, it provides relief from symptoms such as sneezing, a runny or blocked nose, and sinus discomfort.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Follow the prescribed dosage and instructions provided by your doctor.</li>\n	<li>Inform your doctor about any other medications you are taking.</li>\n	<li>Do not use Seretide Diskus if you are allergic to its components.</li>\n	<li>Keep a fast-acting rescue inhaler handy for sudden asthma attacks.</li>\n	<li>Monitor and report any changes in symptoms to your doctor.</li>\n	<li>Inform your doctor about any medical conditions you have.</li>\n	<li>Use caution when switching from oral corticosteroids to Seretide Diskus.</li>\n	<li>Do not abruptly stop using Seretide Diskus without consulting your doctor.</li>\n	<li>Keep the Diskus device clean, dry, and stored properly.</li>\n	<li>Seek medical attention if you experience new or worsening symptoms while using Seretide Diskus.</li>\n</ul>','<p>Seretide 50 mcg/250 mcg Accuhaler 60&#39;s is a respiratory medication used to treat and prevent asthma and chronic obstructive pulmonary diseases (COPD) such as bronchitis and emphysema. Asthma is a chronic respiratory condition characterized by narrowed airways and excess mucus production, leading to breathing difficulties. COPD encompasses a group of lung diseases that obstruct airflow from the lungs.</p>\n\n<p>This medication combines two drugs, namely salmeterol (a bronchodilator) and fluticasone propionate (a corticosteroid). Salmeterol is a long-acting bronchodilator that relaxes the muscles in the airways, allowing easier breathing by widening the airways. Fluticasone propionate, a corticosteroid, acts on the inner cells of the nasal lining to reduce the release of certain inflammatory chemicals in the body. It provides relief from symptoms like sneezing, a runny or blocked nose, and sinus discomfort.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<p>The majority of side effects typically resolve on their own as your body adapts to the medication and do not require medical attention. However, if they persist or cause concern, it&#39;s recommended to consult with your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>The most common side effects are listed below:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Low fever</li>\n	<li>Chest tightness</li>\n	<li>Fungal infection in the mouth</li>\n	<li>Sinus pain</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Stomach upset</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n</ul>','[\"seretide-diskus-250-mcg-50-mcg-60-doses-171186957760.jpg\"]','SE250',1,'0','2024-03-31 07:19:58','2025-10-08 07:04:19'),(611,0,'Seretide Diskus 500 mcg / 50 mcg (60 Doses)','seretide-diskus-500-mcg-/-50-mcg-(60-doses)','Accuhaler','seretide-50-mcg-500-mcg-171186987265.jpg','SE500','<p>How to Use:</p>\n\n<p>To use Seretide 50 mcg or 500 mcg Accuhaler, follow these inhalation instructions. Your doctor or nurse will demonstrate the correct technique. Hold the inhaler upright, placing the mouthpiece between your teeth without biting it. As you start to breathe in through your mouth, press the top of the inhaler to release a puff of medication. Continue inhaling while doing so. Hold your breath for as long as is comfortable, then gently remove the inhaler. Exhale slowly. If another puff is required, wait for a minute before repeating the steps. After use, close the mouthpiece with the cover to prevent dust or debris accumulation.</p>','<p>Seretide 50 mcg/500 mcg Accuhaler is a respiratory medication primarily prescribed for the treatment and prevention of asthma and chronic obstructive pulmonary diseases (COPD) such as bronchitis and emphysema. Asthma is a chronic respiratory condition characterized by narrowed airways, swelling, and excessive mucus production, resulting in breathing difficulties. COPD is a group of lung diseases that obstruct airflow from the lungs.</p>\n\n<p>Seretide 50 mcg/500 mcg Accuhaler contains two active ingredients: salmeterol (a bronchodilator) and fluticasone propionate (a corticosteroid). Sal