 for individuals with asthma or COPD to breathe and reduces symptoms such as wheezing, shortness of breath, and chest tightness</p>\n\n<p>Prevention of Asthma Attacks: By using Serobid Rotacaps 50 mcg regularly as prescribed, it can help prevent asthma attacks and reduce the frequency and severity of symptoms. It provides long-lasting bronchodilation, which helps to keep the airways open and reduces the risk of sudden asthma exacerbations.</p>\n\n<p>Maintenance Therapy: Serobid Rotacaps 50 mcg is often used as a maintenance therapy to manage chronic respiratory conditions such as asthma and COPD. It can be part of a comprehensive treatment plan to control symptoms and improve overall lung function.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Asthma Control: Serobid Rotacaps 50 mcg should not be used as a rescue medication for sudden asthma attacks. It is intended for regular maintenance therapy to control asthma symptoms and prevent asthma attacks. It is important to have a separate rescue inhaler or medication available for immediate relief during an asthma attack.</p>\n\n<p>Follow Prescribed Dosage: Use Serobid Rotacaps 50 mcg exactly as prescribed by your healthcare professional. Do not exceed the recommended dosage or change the frequency of use without medical advice</p>\n\n<p>Allergies: Inform your healthcare professional about any known allergies or hypersensitivity reactions to Salmeterol or any other medications. It is important to avoid Serobid Rotacaps 50 mcg if you have had an allergic reaction to it or any similar medications in the past.</p>\n\n<p>Other Medications: Inform your healthcare professional about all the medications, including prescription drugs, over-the-counter medications, and supplements, that you are currently taking. Certain medications may interact with Serobid Rotacaps 50 mcg, potentially affecting its effectiveness or increasing the risk of side effects. It is important to discuss potential drug interactions with your healthcare professional.</p>','<p>Asthma and chronic obstructive pulmonary disorder (also known as COPD), which is a lung disorder in which the flow of air to the lungs is restricted, can both be treated and prevented with the help of Serobid Rotacaps. It helps to relax the muscles of the air passages, which leads to a widening of those airways and an ease in breathing as a result.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Tremors</li>\n	<li>Insomnia (difficulty in sleeping)</li>\n	<li>Dryness in mouth</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Restlessness</li>\n	<li>Palpitations</li>\n	<li>Muscle cramp</li>\n</ul>','[\"serobid-rotacaps-50-mcg-171187388185.jpg\"]','SE50',1,'0','2024-03-31 08:32:02','2025-10-08 07:04:32'),(613,0,'Seroflo Inhaler 25 mcg 125 mcg (120 mdi)','seroflo-inhaler-25-mcg-125-mcg-(120-mdi)','Inhaler','seroflo-inhaler-25-mcg-125-mcg-120-mdi-171187701969.jpg','SE25','<p>How to Use:</p>\n\n<p>Inhaler Usage: The Seroflo 125 Inhaler is administered through inhalation using an inhaler device. Your doctor or nurse will demonstrate the proper technique for using the inhaler.</p>\n\n<p>Positioning: Hold the inhaler in an upright position. Place the mouthpiece between your teeth, but avoid biting it.</p>\n\n<p>Inhalation: Start breathing in through your mouth and simultaneously press the top of the inhaler to release a puff of medication. Continue inhaling deeply.</p>\n\n<p>Breath Holding: After taking the medication, hold your breath for as long as it feels comfortable. This allows the medication to reach deep into your lungs.</p>\n\n<p>Exhalation: Slowly exhale out.</p>\n\n<p>Repeat Dosage: If another dose is needed, wait for approximately one minute before repeating the above steps.</p>\n\n<p>Mouthpiece Protection: After use, close the mouthpiece with the provided cover to protect it from dust or debris.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Seroflo 125 Inhaler is prescribed for the treatment and prevention of respiratory conditions such as asthma and chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD). By improving pulmonary function, Seroflo 125 Inhaler effectively manages and prevents the exacerbation of symptoms associated with emphysema (breathing difficulties) and chronic bronchitis (inflammation of the bronchial tubes). This inhaler contains a combination of two drugs, namely salmeterol and fluticasone propionate, which are utilized for alleviating asthma symptoms and managing COPD. Salmeterol, classified as a bronchodilator, relaxes the muscles and widens the airways in the lungs, promoting easier breathing. Fluticasone propionate, categorized as a corticosteroid, acts on the inner cells of the nasal lining to suppress the release of specific chemicals responsible for triggering inflammatory reactions. Consequently, it provides relief from symptoms such as sneezing, a runny or congested nose, and sinus discomfort.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Seek medical guidance and use under supervision.</li>\n	<li>Inform your doctor about any allergies or hypersensitivity reactions.</li>\n	<li>Use a separate rescue inhaler for sudden asthma attacks.</li>\n	<li>Be aware of the potential systemic effects of corticosteroids.</li>\n	<li>Inform your doctor about any infections or exposure to contagious diseases.</li>\n	<li>Monitor growth in children using the inhaler.</li>\n	<li>Long-term corticosteroid use may affect adrenal gland function.</li>\n	<li>Regular eye check-ups may be necessary due to potential eye disorders.</li>\n	<li>Consult your doctor if you are pregnant, planning to become pregnant, or breastfeeding.</li>\n</ul>','<p>Seroflo 125 Inhaler is a respiratory medication that is mainly used for the treatment and prevention of asthma and chronic obstructive pulmonary diseases (COPD), such as bronchitis (inflammation of the bronchial tubes) and emphysema (breathing difficulties). Asthma is a long-term respiratory condition characterized by narrowed and swollen airways along with excessive mucus production, resulting in breathing difficulties. COPD refers to a group of lung diseases that obstruct airflow from the lungs.</p>\n\n<p>Seroflo 125 Inhaler combines two active ingredients: salmeterol (a bronchodilator) and fluticasone propionate (a corticosteroid). Salmeterol is a long-acting bronchodilator that works by relaxing the muscles in the airways and widening them, thereby facilitating easier breathing. Fluticasone propionate belongs to the class of corticosteroids and acts on the inner cells of the nasal lining, inhibiting the release of certain inflammatory chemicals in the body. This action provides relief from symptoms such as sneezing, a runny or blocked nose, and sinus discomfort.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<p>The majority of side effects typically resolve on their own as your body adapts to the medication and do not require medical attention. However, if they persist or cause concern, it&#39;s recommended to consult with your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>The most common side effects are listed below:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Cough</li>\n	<li>Upper respiratory tract infection</li>\n	<li>Nasopharyngitis (inflammation of the throat and nasal passages)</li>\n	<li>Sinus inflammation</li>\n	<li>Stomach discomfort</li>\n</ul>','[\"seroflo-inhaler-25-mcg-125-mcg-120-mdi-171187701969.jpg\"]','SE5',1,'0','2024-03-31 09:25:02','2025-07-24 04:36:39'),(614,0,'Seroflo Rotacaps  50mcg 250mcg','seroflo-rotacaps-50mcg-250mcg','Rotacaps','seroflo-rotacaps-50mcg-250mcg-171188983166.jpg','SE250','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>It is important to follow your doctor&rsquo;s instructions and the directions provided with the medication. Below are general guidelines for using Seroflo Rotacaps:</p>\n\n<p>Prepare the inhaler: Remove a Seroflo Rotacap from its blister pack and insert it into the inhaler device.</p>\n\n<p>Breathe out: Exhale fully to empty your lungs before using the inhaler.</p>\n\n<p>Inhale the medication: Put the mouthpiece of the inhaler in your mouth and close your lips around it. Take a deep, slow breath through your mouth and simultaneously press down firmly on the inhaler to release the medication. Continue inhaling until your lungs are full.</p>\n\n<p>Hold your breath: After inhaling the medication, remove the inhaler from your mouth and hold your breath for about 10 seconds, or as long as comfortable.</p>\n\n<p>Exhale slowly: Breathe out slowly and gently.</p>\n\n<p>Rinse your mouth: To minimize the risk of throat irritation and fungal infections, rinse your mouth with water and spit it out after each use.</p>\n\n<p>Clean the inhaler: Wipe the mouthpiece with a clean, dry cloth to keep it free from debris.</p>\n\n<p>It is crucial to use Seroflo Rotacaps regularly and consistently, as prescribed by your doctor, even if you are feeling well. Do not exceed the recommended dose or abruptly stop using the medication without consulting your healthcare provider.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Seroflo Rotacaps 50 mcg 250 mcg offer several benefits in managing asthma and COPD:</p>\n\n<p>Asthma control: The combination of fluticasone propionate and salmeterol helps to control asthma symptoms by reducing airway inflammation and relaxing the muscles in the airways, making breathing easier.</p>\n\n<p>COPD management: Seroflo Rotacaps can also be used to manage symptoms of COPD, including chronic bronchitis and emphysema. The medication helps to reduce airway inflammation and improve lung function.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before using Seroflo Rotacaps, inform your doctor or pharmacist about any allergies you may have, including allergies to fluticasone propionate, salmeterol, or other corticosteroids. Also, disclose any other medical conditions you have, such as heart disease, high blood pressure, diabetes, or thyroid problems.</p>\n\n<p>Seroflo Rotacaps should not be used as a rescue inhaler for sudden asthma attacks or acute COPD exacerbations. Your doctor will prescribe a separate reliever inhaler for those situations.</p>\n\n<p>It Is important to regularly monitor your asthma or COPD symptoms and report any worsening to your healthcare provider. Adjustments to your treatment plan may be necessary.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>Seroflo Rotacaps 50 mcg 250 mcg is a medication used to manage asthma and chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD). It is a combination inhaler that contains two active ingredients: fluticasone propionate (50 mcg) and salmeterol (250 mcg). Fluticasone propionate belongs to a class of drugs called corticosteroids, while salmeterol is a long-acting beta-agonist.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>Like any medication, Seroflo Rotacaps can cause side effects, although not everyone experiences them. Common side effects may include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Hoarseness or throat irritation</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Cough</li>\n</ul>','[\"seroflo-rotacaps-50mcg-250mcg-171188983166.jpg\"]','SE50',1,'0','2024-03-31 12:58:37','2025-07-24 08:21:19'),(615,0,'Seroflo Rotacaps 50mcg 100mcg','seroflo-rotacaps-50mcg-100mcg','Rotacaps','seroflo-rotacaps-50mcg-100mcg-171189018985.jpg','SE100','<p>How to Use:</p>\n\n<p>Prepare: Peel off the aluminum foil cover from the blister strip containing the rotacaps.</p>\n\n<p>Load: Insert the entire blister strip into the provided rotahaler or inhaler device.</p>\n\n<p>Select Rotacap: Rotate the device to align the desired strength (either 50 mcg or 100 mcg).</p>\n\n<p>Breathe Out: Fully exhale to empty your lungs.</p>\n\n<p>Inhale: Place the device&#39;s mouthpiece between your teeth, take a slow breath in through your mouth, and press the buttons to release the medication.</p>\n\n<p>Hold Breath: Remove the device and hold your breath for about 10 seconds.</p>\n\n<p>Exhale: Breathe out slowly.</p>\n\n<p>Repeat: If needed, repeat steps 3 to 7 for additional rotacaps.</p>\n\n<p>Clean and Store: Wipe the mouthpiece, replace the cover, and store the rotacaps in a dry place.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Seroflo 100 Rotacaps 30&#39;s is prescribed for the treatment and prevention of respiratory disord