y machinery, until you understand how the medication affects you.</p>','<p>Sirdalud 2mg, also known as tizanidine 2mg, is a medication that is commonly prescribed for the treatment of muscle spasms and spasticity. It belongs to a class of drugs known as muscle relaxants. Tizanidine works by blocking nerve impulses that are sent to the brain, which helps to relax the muscles and alleviate muscle spasms.</p>\n\n<p>Here Is some important information about Sirdalud 2mg:</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>Most side effects associated with Sirdalud 2mg are generally mild and temporary. If you have concerns about any side effects, it is recommended to consult your doctor. Some common side effects may include:</p>\n\n<p>Drowsiness: Sirdalud 2mg can cause drowsiness, making you feel sleepy or fatigued. It is important to avoid alcohol and other sedatives while taking this medication.</p>\n\n<p>Dry mouth: Some individuals may experience a dry mouth while taking Sirdalud 2mg. Staying hydrated and chewing sugarless gum can help alleviate this symptom.</p>\n\n<p>Low blood pressure: Sirdalud 2mg may cause a temporary drop in blood pressure, leading to feelings of lightheadedness or fainting. It is advisable to get up slowly from a lying or sitting position to minimize this effect.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','[\"sirdalud-2mg-17119516874.jpg\"]','SI02',1,'0','2024-04-01 06:19:51','2025-10-08 07:07:50'),(646,0,'Siromus 1mg','siromus-1mg','tablet','siromus-1mg-171195253188.jpg','SI01','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>Sirolimus 1mg should be taken exactly as prescribed by your doctor. It is important to carefully read and follow all instructions provided with the medication. It is usually taken orally, with or without food, once daily. Do not crush or chew the tablets. If you have any questions regarding the usage, consult your healthcare provider.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Prevention of organ rejection: Sirolimus is highly effective in preventing organ rejection in transplant patients. By suppressi