sting conditions to your healthcare provider. This includes any allergies, liver problems, blood clotting disorders, or a history of certain cancers. Your doctor will evaluate your individual health profile to determine the suitability of Susten Gel for you.</p>','<p>Susten Gel 1.35 gm is a medication that is widely used for hormonal support in women. It contains progesterone, a natural hormone that plays a crucial role in the female reproductive system. Susten Gel is administered vaginally and provides various benefits for women&rsquo;s health. Here is some important information about Susten Gel:</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>While Susten Gel is generally well-tolerated, some women may experience mild side effects. These are usually temporary and subside as the body adjusts to the medication. Common side effects may include:</p>\n\n<p>Vaginal discharge or irritation: Some women may experience mild vaginal discharge or local irritation. These effects are generally mild and resolve on their own.</p>\n\n<p>Breast tenderness: Occasionally, women may notice increased sensitivity or tenderness in the breasts. This effect is usually temporary and not a cause for concern.</p>\n\n<p>Nausea or dizziness: In some cases, women may experience mild nausea or dizziness. These effects are generally transient and typically resolve without intervention.</p>','[\"susten-gel-1-171204699932.jpg\"]','SU1.35',1,'0','2024-04-02 08:37:40','2025-10-08 07:14:38'),(671,0,'Syncapone (37.5+200+150)mg','syncapone-(37.5+200+150)mg','tablet','syncapone-37-171204720724.jpg','SY150','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>You can take your Syncapone 150 Tablet with or without food, although it is recommended that you stay away from meals high in protein and dairy ingredients. On the other hand, it is recommended that it be taken at the same time each day because doing so assists in maintaining a stable amount of the medicine in the body. You should take this medication according to the dosage and length of time that was recommended by your doctor. If you forget to take a dose, you should take it as soon as you remember it. You should never skip a dosage of your medication, and you should make every effort to finish the entire prescribed course of therapy even if you feel better. Because of the potential for adverse effects, it is essential that you do not stop taking this drug all of a sudden without first consulting with your doctor.Take this medication at the prescribed dose and for the prescribed amount of time as directed by your doctor. Take it in one complete bite. Do not chew on it, crush it, or break it in any way. The Syncapone 150 Tablet can be taken either with or without food; however, it is recommended that it be taken at a consistent time each day.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Treatment of Parkinson&#39;s Disease: Syncapone is primarily prescribed for the treatment of Parkinson&#39;s disease, a neurodegenerative disorder that affects movement. The combination of Levodopa, Carbidopa, and Entacapone helps to manage the symptoms of Parkinson&#39;s disease and improve motor function.</p>\n\n<p>Increased Dopamine Levels: Levodopa is converted into dopamine in the brain, which is a neurotransmitter that plays a crucial role in coordinating movement. By increasing dopamine levels, Syncapone helps to compensate for the decreased dopamine production in individuals with Parkinson&#39;s disease, alleviating symptoms such as tremors, stiffness, and bradykinesia (slowness of movement).</p>\n\n<p>Enhanced Effectiveness and Duration: Carbidopa is combined with Levodopa in Syncapone to enhance its effectiveness. Carbidopa prevents the breakdown of Levodopa before it reaches the brain, allowing more of the medication to be available for conversion into dopamine. This combination also helps to extend the duration of the therapeutic effect of Levodopa, providing more consistent symptom relief throughout the day.</p>\n\n<p>Inhibition of Dopamine Breakdown: Entacapone, the third component of Syncapone, acts as a COMT (catechol-O-methyltransferase) inhibitor. COMT is an enzyme that breaks down dopamine in the body. By inhibiting COMT, Entacapone helps to prolong the effect of Levodopa and maintain higher dopamine levels in the brain, further improving motor function and reducing Parkinson&#39;s disease symptoms.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Allergic Reactions: If you have known allergies to any of the components of Syncapone (Levodopa, Carbidopa, or Entacapone), inform your healthcare professional.</p>\n\n<p>Medical History: Inform your healthcare professional about any pre-existing medical conditions, such as heart, liver, or kidney problems, as well as any history of mental health disorders.</p>\n\n<p>Medication Interactions: Syncapone may interact with other medications, including certain antidepressants, antipsychotics, and MAO inhibitors. Inform your healthcare professional about all medications you are taking to avoid potential interactions.</p>\n\n<p>Side Effects: Be aware of potential side effects of Syncapone, such as nausea, dizziness, drowsiness, and hallucinations. Contact your healthcare professional if you experience any concerning or persistent side effects.</p>','<p>Syncapone 150 Tablet is a drug that is available with a doctor&#39;s prescription that is used to treat Parkinson&#39;s disease. This medication helps to lessen shaking that is excessive by reducing the speed at which the body moves. A greater quantity of the chemical messenger that is required to control aberrant movements is produced as a result of its use.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Dryness in mouth</li>\n	<li>Insomnia (difficulty in sleeping)</li>\n	<li>Anxiety</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n</ul>','[\"syncapone-37-171204720724.jpg\"]','SY150',1,'0','2024-04-02 08:40:51','2025-10-08 07:14:48'),(672,0,'Syndopa 25 250 mg','syndopa-25-250-mg','tablet','syndopa-25-250-mg-171310653431.jpg','SY25','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>As directed by your doctor, take Syndopa CR Tablet 10&#39;s. As long as your doctor has recommended it after evaluating your medical state, it is advised that you take the medication. The most frequent adverse effects of Syndopa CR Tablet 10s are dyskinesia (uncontrolled/involuntary muscular movement), nausea, vomiting, loss of appetite, lightheadedness, reduced blood pressure, disorientation, and dysgeusia. The majority of these adverse effects of Syndopa CR Tablet 10&#39;s progressively go away over time without the need for medical care. However, please see a doctor if the adverse effects worsen or persist.As directed by the doctor, take Syndopa CR Tablets 10 with or without food. With a glass of water, swallow it whole. Don&#39;t eat, shatter, or crush it.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Antiparkinson medication like Syndopa CR Tablet 10s can be helpful in the management of symptoms associated with Parkinson&#39;s disease. The medicine known as &#39;Levodopa&#39; and &#39;Carbidopa&#39; are both components of the Syndopa CR Tablet 10&#39;s combo product. Carbidopa falls under the category of decarboxylase inhibitors, whereas levodopa is classified as a member of the category of drugs known as central nervous system agents. Levodopa is a component of medicine that, once it reaches the brain, is converted into dopamine and assists in the regulation of movement. Carbidopa, on the other hand, works by reducing the breakdown of levodopa in the bloodstream. This allows for an increased amount of levodopa to reach the brain, where it can effectively block acetylcholine, which is a chemical messenger in the brain.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>If you have a history of diabetes, heart attacks, mental illness, stomach ulcers, heart disease, or have just undergone surgery, let your doctor know. One may have lightheadedness after using Syndopa CR Tablet 10s, hence it is advised to stay away from any work that requires mental alertness. Patients taking Syndopa CR Tablet 10s may also experience low vitamin B12 levels and elevated levels of methylmalonic acid. In addition, extended use of Syndopa CR Tablet 10s may increase the risk of neuropathy (nerve damage). Patients with gastrointestinal bleeding, psychosis, narrow-angle glaucoma, arrhythmia, and ocular difficulties should use caution when administering Syndopa CR Tablet 10s. If someone is taking monoamine oxidase inhibitors (MAOs) or antidepressants such isocarboxazid, phenelzine, selegiline, or tranylcypromine, the usage of Syndopa CR Tablet 10&#39;s is restricted since it can result in a hypertension crisis.</p>','<p>The medication Syndopa CR Tablet 10&#39;s is classified as an antiparkinson agent, which is a precursor of dopamine, which is a chemical messenger in the brain. Its primary usage is in the treatment of Parkinson&#39;s disease, the symptoms of which include tremors, spasms, muscle stiffness, and a lack of control over the muscles in the body. Parkinson&#39;s disease is a disorder of the central nervous system that affects movement and locomotion. This affects movement and locomotion, which causes stiffness, tremor, difficulties walking, difficulty coordinating, and balance. Parkinson&#39;s disease is characterized by low levels of the neurotransmitter dopamine because the neurons in the brain that are responsible for its production start to die off.</p>\n\n<p>Syndopa CR Tablet 10&#39;s comprises &#39;Levodopa&#39; and &#39;Carbidopa&#39;. Carbidopa is an inhibitor of the decarboxylase enzyme, whereas levodopa is classified as an agent of the central nervous system. Levodopa is a component of medicine that, once it reaches the brain, is converted into dopamine and assists in the regulation of movement. Carbidopa&#39;s mechanism of action involves blocking the breakdown of levodopa in the bloodstream. This allows for increased levels of levodopa to be delivered to the brain.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Confusion</li>\n	<li>Loss of appetite</li>\n	<li>Light-headedness</li>\n	<li>Lowered blood pressure</li>\n</ul>','[\"syndopa-25-250-mg-171310653431.jpg\"]','SY25',1,'0','2024-04-14 14:56:25','2025-10-08 07:14:57'),(673,0,'Syndopa CR 50 200 mg','syndopa-cr-50-200-mg','tablet','syndopa-cr-50-200-mg-171310676034.jpg','SY50','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>It is crucial to follow your doctor&rsquo;s instructions when taking Syndopa CR 50/200mg. Read and adhere to all the guidelines provided on the medication label. It is generally recommended to take this medication exactly as prescribed, usually at specific intervals throughout the day. Do not crush or chew the tablets unless otherwise directed by your healthcare professional.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Syndopa CR 50/200mg offers several positive benefits for individuals with Parkinson&rsquo;s disease, including:</p>\n\n<p>Symptom relief: The combination of carbidopa and levodopa in Syndopa CR 50/200mg helps to restore dopamine levels in the brain, reducing the motor symptoms of Parkinson&rsquo;s disease. This can lead to improved mobility, tremor control, and overall motor function.</p>\n\n<p>Increased quality of life: By effectively managing the symptoms of Parkinson&rsquo;s disease, Syndopa CR 50/200mg can significantly enhance the quality of life for patients. It allows individuals to perform daily activities with greater ease and maintain a more active and independent lifestyle.</p>\n\n<p>Long-acting formulation: The controlled-release formulation of Syndopa CR 50/200mg ensures a gradual and sustained release of the medication, providing a more stable and consistent therapeutic effect throughout the day. This can help minimize fluctuations in symptom control and provide a smoother experience for patients.</p>\n\n<p>Customizable dosing: Syndopa CR 50/200mg is available in different strengths, allowing healthcare professionals to tailor the dosage according to each patient&rsquo;s specific needs. This customization enables optimal symptom management while minimizing the risk of side effects.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before starting Syndopa CR 50/200mg, it is important to inform your healthcare provider about any allergies you may have, including allergies to carbidopa, levodopa, or any other substances. Additionally, disclose your complete medical history, including any previous or current medications, to ensure the safe use of this medication.</p>','<p>Syndopa CR 50/200mg is a medication commonly prescribed for the management of symptoms associated with Parkinson&rsquo;s disease. It combines two active ingredients, carbidopa and levodopa, which work together to alleviate the motor impairments caused by this condition. Syndopa CR 50/200mg comes in a controlled-release formulation, allowing for a sustained and steady release of the medication throughout the day.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Here is some important information about Syndopa CR 50/200mg:</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>While Syndopa CR 50/200mg can be well-tolerated by most individuals, some common side effects may occur. It&rsquo;s important to note that these side effects are typically temporary and tend to resolve as your body adjusts to the medication. If you have any concerns, consult your doctor. Common side effects may include:</p>\n\n<p>Nausea and vomiting: Some individuals may experience mild gastrointestinal symptoms, such as nausea or vomiting, especially during the initial stages of treatment. These effects can often be managed by taking the medication with food or as directed by your healthcare provider.</p>\n\n<p>Dizziness or drowsiness: Syndopa CR 50/200mg may cause dizziness or drowsiness, particularly at the beginning of treatment or when adjusting the dosage. It is important to exercise caution while driving or operating machinery until you know how this medication affects you.</p>','[\"syndopa-cr-50-200-mg-171310676034.jpg\"]','SY50',1,'0','2024-04-14 15:00:59','2025-10-08 07:15:05'),(674,0,'Syndopa Plus 25 100 mg','sy