 levels of methylmalonic acid. In addition, extended use of Syndopa Plus Tablet 15s may increase the risk of neuropathy (nerve damage). Patients with gastrointestinal bleeding, psychosis, narrow-angle glaucoma, arrhythmia, and ocular issues should use Syndopa Plus Tablet 15s with caution. If a person is taking monoamine oxidase inhibitors (MAOs) or antidepressants such isocarboxazid, phenelzine, selegiline, or tranylcypromine, the usage of Syndopa Plus Tablet 15&#39;s is restricted since it can create a hypertension crisis.</p>','<p>A precursor to dopamine (the brain&#39;s chemical messenger), Syndopa Plus Tablet 15s are part of a class of medications known as &quot;antiparkinson agents.&quot; They are generally used to treat Parkinson&#39;s disease, which has symptoms include tremors, spasms, muscle rigidity, and poor motor coordination. Parkinson&#39;s disease is a central nervous system ailment that impairs movement and mobility. It results in stiffness, tremors, trouble walking, coordination issues, and balance issues. Dopamine levels are low in Parkinson&#39;s patients because the brain&#39;s dopamine-producing neurons are starting to die.</p>\n\n<p>Levodopa and carbidopa are both ingredients in Syndopa Plus Tablet 15s. While Carbidopa is a decarboxylase inhibitor, Levodopa is a central nervous system drug. Levodopa, a drug ingredient, transforms into dopamine in the brain and aids in motor coordination. In order to increase the amount of levodopa that reaches the brain, carbidopa works by blocking its breakdown in the bloodstream.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Confusion</li>\n	<li>Loss of appetite</li>\n	<li>Light-headedness</li>\n	<li>Lowered blood pressure</li>\n</ul>','[\"syndopa-plus-25-100-mg-171310752242.jpg\"]','SY250',1,'0','2024-04-14 15:12:48','2025-10-08 07:15:17'),(675,0,'T Bact 7.5 gm Cream','t-bact-7.5-gm-cream','Cream','t-bact-7-171310771026.jpg','TB7.5','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Only use T-Bact Cream 7.5 gm as directed by your doctor.&nbsp; It is not advised for infants younger than two months. T-Bact Cream 7.5 gm should only be applied topically; if it goes in your mouth, nose, or eyes unintentionally, flush those areas with water. Apply T-Bact Cream 7.5 gm to the affected region using a clean cotton ball or gauze swab. To prevent unpleasant side effects, just use the prescribed amount of T-Bact Cream 7.5 gm. As directed by your doctor, apply a tiny amount of T-Bact Cream 7.5 gm to the afflicted region of skin using a cotton swab or gauze pad.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Treatment of Skin Infections: T-Bact Cream is primarily used for the treatment of bacterial skin infections, including impetigo, folliculitis, and secondary infected dermatoses. It helps to eliminate the bacteria causing the infection and promotes healing of the affected skin.</p>\n\n<p>Prevention of Infection: T-Bact Cream can also be used as a preventive measure to reduce the risk of infection in minor cuts, wounds, or abrasions. By applying the cream to the affected area, it creates a barrier that helps prevent the entry and growth of bacteria, reducing the likelihood of infection.</p>\n\n<p>Rapid Healing: T-Bact Cream helps to speed up the healing process by eliminating the bacterial infection. By effectively treating the underlying cause of the skin infection, it allows the body&#39;s natural healing mechanisms to work more efficiently, resulting in faster recovery and improved skin condition.</p>\n\n<p>Localized Treatment: T-Bact Cream provides localized treatment to the affected area, allowing for targeted application and concentration of the active ingredient. This ensures effective treatment directly at the site of the infection, minimizing the risk of systemic side effects.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>There have been cases of Clostridium difficile-associated diarrhea (CDAD) after utilizing popular topical antibiotic treatments. T-Bact Cream 7.5 gm should no longer be used 