sing a clean piece of cotton wool or gauze swab. To prevent undesirable side effects, T Bact Ointment 15 gm should not be used in excess of the authorized dosage.As directed by your doctor, apply a tiny amount of T Bact Ointment 15 gm to the afflicted region of skin using a cotton swab or gauze pad.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Treatment of Skin diseases: Impetigo, folliculitis, and infected wounds are among the bacterial skin diseases that are frequently treated with T-Bact Ointment. It aids in the removal of the infection-causing bacteria, the reduction of swelling, and the promotion of skin healing.</p>\n\n<p>T-Bact Ointment can also be applied before an infection develops to lessen the chance of infection in minor wounds, scrapes, or surgical incisions. The likelihood of getting an infection is decreased by applying the ointment to the affected area, which helps build a barrier that hinders the entry and growth of bacteria.</p>\n\n<p>Localized Therapy: T-Bact Ointment delivers localized therapy to the region in question. This enables concentrated and focused application of the active component, enabling efficient treatment just where the infection is.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Clostridium difficile-associated diarrhea, often known as CDAD, has been linked to the use of some of the most popular topical antibacterial treatments. If CDAD is suspected or proven, continuing therapy with T Bact Ointment 15 gm should be stopped immediately. It is important to discontinue use of T Bact Ointment 15 gm if irritation, severe itching, or a skin rash develops. If you don&#39;t notice any improvement after three to five days, you should talk to your doctor. When applied to infants younger than 2 months of age, T Bact Ointment 15 gm should be used with extreme caution. When used for an extended period of time, T Bact Ointment 15 gm may cause an excessive growth of fungus. In the event that T Bact Ointment 15 gm finds its way into your nose, eyes, or mouth, you should i