, thereby lowering blood pressure and reducing the risk of cardiovascular complications.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>Most individuals tolerate Telma 20mg well, but like any medication, it may have some potential side effects. However, it is important to note that not everyone experiences these side effects, and they are usually temporary. Some of the commonly reported side effects of Telma 20mg include dizziness, headache, fatigue, and gastrointestinal symptoms such as nausea or diarrhea. If you experience any concerning or persistent side effects, it is recommended to consult your healthcare provider for further guidance.</p>\n\n<p>Remember, this information is provided as a general overview and should not replace professional medical advice. It is important to consult your healthcare provider or pharmacist for personalized guidance and to discuss any specific concerns you may have regarding Telma 20mg.</p>','[\"telma-20mg-171387926899.webp\"]','TE20',1,'0','2024-04-23 13:35:43','2025-10-08 07:22:28'),(708,0,'Telma 80mg','telma-80mg','tablet','telma-80mg-171387951651.jpg','TE80','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>It is important to follow your doctor&rsquo;s instructions and take Telma 80mg exactly as prescribed. Read and adhere to all the instructions on the medication label. Do not exceed or reduce the dosage without consulting your healthcare provider. Telma 80mg is usually taken orally once a day, with or without food. Swallow the tablet whole with a glass of water.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Telma 80mg offers several benefits in the management of high blood pressure:</p>\n\n<p>Blood pressure control: Telma 80mg effectively lowers high blood pressure, helping to reduce the risk of heart disease, stroke, and other complications associated with hypertension.</p>\n\n<p>Protection of organs: By controlling blood pressure, Telma 80mg helps protect vital organs such as the heart, kidneys, and blood vessels from damage caused by prolonged high blood pressure.</p>\n\n<p>Prevention of heart attacks: Lowering blood pressure with Telma 80mg can significantly reduce the risk of heart attacks and improve overall cardiovascular health.</p>\n\n<p>Kidney protection: Telma 80mg has been found to slow down the progression of kidney disease in people with high blood pressure, helping to preserve kidney function.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before starting Telma 80mg, it is important to inform your healthcare provider or pharmacist about any allergies you may have, including to this medication or other ARBs. Also, disclose your medical history, including any kidney or liver problems, as dosage adjustments may be necessary.</p>\n\n<p>It Is advisable to avoid alcohol consumption while taking Telma 80mg, as it can increase the blood pressure-lowering effects and may cause dizziness or fainting.</p>\n\n<p>If you are pregnant or planning to become pregnant, inform your healthcare provider, as Telma 80mg may not be suitable during pregnancy. It is also not recommended for breastfeeding mothers.</p>','<p>Telma 80mg is a medication that is commonly prescribed to manage high blood pressure, also known as hypertension. It belongs to a class of drugs called angiotensin II receptor blockers (ARBs). Telma 80mg helps to relax and widen the blood vessels, allowing blood to flow more easily and reducing the strain on the heart.</p>\n\n<p>Here Is some important information about Telma 80mg:</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>Most people tolerate Telma 80mg well, and any side effects are usually mild and temporary. However, it&rsquo;s important to be aware of potential side effects and discuss any concerns with your doctor. Common side effects may include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Dizziness or lightheadedness</li>\n	<li>Fatigue or weakness</li>\n	<li>Nausea or vomiting</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Dry cough (less common than with some other blood pressure medications)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Remember that this list does not include all possible side effects. If you experience any unusual or severe side effects while taking Telma 80mg, contact your healthcare provider immediately.</p>\n\n<p>Overall, Telma 80mg is a valuable medication for the management of high blood pressure, offering significant benefits in protecting your cardiovascular health and reducing the risk of related complications.</p>','[\"telma-80mg-171387951651.jpg\"]','TE80',1,'0','2024-04-23 13:39:39','2025-10-08 07:24:34'),(709,0,'Temoside 100mg','temoside-100mg','tablet','temoside-100mg-171387966367.webp','TE100','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Temoside 100 Capsule 5 should be taken as directed by your doctor. Temoside 100 Capsule 5s may, in some people, result in a loss of appetite, anxiety, disorientation, headache, vomiting, nausea, diarrhoea, constipation, muscle weakness, muscle aches, and fever. These side effects may occur in conjunction with one another or independently. The majority of these adverse reactions to Temoside 100 Capsule 5&#39;s can be managed without medical intervention and will go away on their own as time passes. However, you should consult your physician if the adverse effects continue even after treatment has been discontinued.You should not crush, break, or chew it in any way before swallowing it whole with some water.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Temoside 100 Capsule 5&#39;s are a type of medication known as anti-cancer/antitumor agents that are used to treat certain types of brain tumors, including glioblastoma multiforme (a type of tumor that grows and spreads quickly) in adults and malignant glioma, including glioblastoma multiforme or anaplastic astrocytoma (a rare malignant brain tumor) in patients older than 3 years. It contains temozolomide, which inhibits cell growth and division by attaching to DNA (deoxyribonucleic acid, the cell&#39;s genetic material). Temoside 100 Capsule 5&#39;s stop the growth of tumors in this way.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Temoside 100 Capsule 5s must be taken closely supervised by a doctor. While you are taking Temoside 100 Capsule 5, your condition will be routinely checked by the doctor. Continue taking Temoside 100 Capsule 5&#39;s for the entire time that your doctor has advised in order to effectively treat your disease. Under no circumstances, without first consulting a medical professional, stop taking Temoside 100 Capsule 5 in the middle of a dose. Tell your doctor if you are allergic to any Temoside 100 Capsule 5 ingredients. If you experience allergic reactions, infections, lung, renal, or hepatic diseases, or low blood count (including neutropenia, lymphopenia, or thrombocytopenia), let your doctor know before taking Temoside 100 Capsule 5s. Patients who have considerable bleeding or severe bone marrow depression shouldn&#39;t use temozide 100 capsule 5s. Temoside 100 Capsule 5s should not be taken by women who are pregnant or nursing. When taking Temoside 100 Capsule 5, both men and women should take birth control to prevent getting pregnant or fathering a child. While using Temoside 100 Capsule 5, you must obtain your doctor&#39;s permission before getting any shots or immunizations.</p>','<p>Temoside 100 Capsule 5s is a member of the &quot;anti-cancer/antitumor agent&quot; class of drugs and is used to treat certain types of brain tumors, including glioblastoma multiforme (a tumor that spreads and grows quickly) in adults and malignant glioma, including glioblastoma multiforme or anaplastic astrocytoma (a rare malignant brain tumor) in patients older than 3 years. An unchecked and unregulated cell proliferation in the brain is what is known as a brain tumor.</p>\n\n<p>Temozolomide, an ingredient in Temoside 100 Capsule 5, acts by preventing the synthesis of DNA (deoxyribonucleic acid, the cell&#39;s genetic material), which has an impact on cell development and division. Temoside 100 Capsule 5&#39;s stop the growth of tumors in this way.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Loss of appetite</li>\n	<li>Difficulty speaking</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Diarrhoea</li>\n	<li>Constipation</li>\n	<li>Rash</li>\n</ul>','[\"temoside-100mg-171387966367.webp\"]','TE100',1,'0','2024-04-23 13:42:12','2025-10-08 07:21:41'),(710,0,'Tenoric 100 25 mg','tenoric-100-25-mg','tablet','screenshot-2024-04-23-191852-171388019783.png','TE100','<p>Tenoric Tablet Advantages</p>\n\n<p>High blood pressure, or hypertension</p>\n\n<p>The effects of several substances on your heart and blood vessels are blocked by Tenoric 100 Tablet. This lowers your heart rate and makes your heart beat more gently. It also boosts urine production and helps the body flush out extra fluids. This decreases your blood pressure and minimises your chance of future renal issues, a stroke, or a heart attack. Usually, taking this medication does not result in any immediate benefits for you, but over time, it keeps you healthy. Even if you feel better, you should still take the medication as directed to get the most benefit.</p>','<p>Use of Tenoric Tablets</p>\n\n<p>Follow your doctor&#39;s instructions for this medication&#39;s dosage and duration. Take it all in at once. Don&#39;t eat it, break it, or crush it. It is preferable to take Tenoric 100 Tablet at a certain time each day, whether with food or not.</p>\n\n<p>Functions of Tenoric Tablet</p>\n\n<p>Atenolol and chlorthalidone are two medications that reduce blood pressure together in the Tenoric 100 Tablet. A beta blocker known as atenolol works particularly on the heart to lower heart rate and improve the heart&#39;s ability to pump blood throughout the body. By eliminating surplus water and some electrolytes from the body, the diuretic chlorthalidone reduces blood pressure. Additionally, it enhances blood flow and blood vessel relaxation over time.</p>\n\n<p>Two medications are combined in the Tenoric 100 Tablet to treat hypertension (high blood pressure). It aids in blood pressure management when one medicine is ineffective. Additionally, it lowers the risk of future heart attacks and strokes.</p>\n\n<p>To prevent frequent urination at night, Tenoric 100 Tablet is best taken in the morning, with or without meals. Continue taking it as long as your doctor instructs you to. Do not stop taking this medication on your own, even if you feel OK. High blood pressure frequently has no symptoms. Your condition could worsen if you stop taking it. Blood pressure can be managed by staying active with regular exercise, losing weight, and eating a good diet. As you use this medication, abide by your doctor&#39;s recommendations.</p>\n\n<p>This medication frequently causes adverse effects include lethargy, headaches, and nausea. If any of these concern you, get worse, or don&#39;t go away, talk to your doctor.&nbsp; While taking medication, drink plenty of water to combat dry mouth, muscle weakness, and intense thirst. Low blood pressure might cause headaches or dizziness, but these symptoms improve over time.</p>\n\n<p>Tell your doctor if you have any liver or kidney issues before taking it. Before using this medication, women who are pregnant or nursing should also get counsel from their doctor. Additionally, you must let your doctor know about any additional medications you are taking, especially those for heart disease or high blood pressure. To ensure that this medication is functioning effectively, you should routinely have your blood pressure, kidney function, blood sugar level, and salt levels, such as potassium or magnesium, examined.</p>','<p>Tenoric Tablet side effects</p>\n\n<p>The majority of adverse effects are temporary and go away as your body becomes used to the medication. If they persist or you&#39;re concerned about them, speak with your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>Tenoric side effects frequently</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; nausea and vertigo</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; sluggish heartbeat</li>\n</ul>','[\"screenshot-2024-04-23-191852-171388019783.png\"]','TE100',1,'0','2024-04-23 13:51:39','2025-10-08 07:21:50'),(711,0,'Tenvir 300mg','tenvir-300mg-','tablet','tenvir-300mg-tablets-171388041297.webp','TE300','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>It is important that you take this medication exactly as directed by your doctor. Diarrhea, being ill (vomiting), feeling sick (nausea), bloating, flatulence, weakness, dizziness, headache, abdominal pain, and exhaustion are some of the frequent adverse reactions that might occur after taking Tenvir 300 Tablet 30s. However, you should get medical help if the negative effects don&#39;t go away or get worse.Take the medication in its entirety while drinking water. It should not be crushed or chewed.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>&#39;Tenofovir disoproxil&#39; is an antiretroviral drug that can be found in Tenvir 300 Tablet 30&#39;s. Both HIV and chronic hepatitis B can benefit from its ability to effectively reduce viral replication. It does so by affecting the enzymes that are required for the virus to replicate successfully. Reverse transcriptase is the enzyme that is necessary for the replication of HIV, and DNA polymerase is the enzyme that is necessary for the replication of hepatitis B. These enzymes are obstructed by Tenvir 300 Tablet 30&#39;s, which also reduces the amount of virus in the blood.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>If you have an allergy to &#39;tenofovir disoproxil&#39; or any of the other ingredients found in Tenvir 300 Tablet 30&#39;s, you should not use this medication. In adolescents who already have kidney failure, its use is strictly prohibited. There is an increased risk of osteonecrosis (the death of bone tissue) when this medication is used in combination with other HIV treatments. Patients who have serious liver illnesses, such as chronic hepatitis B or C, have a very high risk of developing fatal consequences if they undergo this procedure. While taking this medication, if you develop any new signs of infection, you should visit a doctor right away because there is a possibility that you could get an opportunistic infection, which is an illness that occurs in individuals who have a compromised immune system. Notify your physician if you are breastfeeding, are pregnant, or are planning to become pregnant in the near future.</p>','<p>Envir 300 Tablet 30&#39;s is a member of the class of pharmaceuticals known as &quot;antiretroviral drugs,&quot; which are used to treat chronic hepatitis B and HIV infection. A sexually transmitted disease called the human immunodeficiency virus (HIV) eventually results in the acquired immunodeficiency syndrome (AIDS). The hepatitis B virus, which causes chronic hepatitis B, is a persistent viral infection.</p>\n\n<p>Tenvir 300 Tablet 30s include &quot;Tenofovir disoproxil,&quot; a &quot;nucleotide reverse transcriptase inhibitor&quot; that blocks the enzymes required for the formation of viruses (reverse transcriptase in HIV and DNA polymerase in HBV). It successfully lessens the signs and symptoms of chronic hepatitis B infection and HIV.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Diarrhoea</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Bloating</li>\n	<li>Flatulence</li>\n	<li>Weakness</li>\n</ul>','[\"tenvir-300mg-tablets-171388041297.webp\"]','TE300',1,'0','2024-04-23 13:54:16','2025-10-08 07:21:59'),(712,0,'Tenvir EM 300/200mg','tenvir-em-300/200mg','tablet','tenvir-em-300-200mg-171388062726.jpg','TE300','<p>How to Use:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Take this medicine at the dose and duration advised by your doctor. Swallow it as a whole. Do not chew, crush, or break it.</li>\n	<li>Your doctor will recommend the best medicines for you and determine the doses that you need. Follow the instructions carefully for all the medicines that you are given.</li>\n	<li>This medicine is best taken with food.</li>\n	<li>Taking these medicines regularly at the right time greatly increases their effectiveness and reduces the chances of HIV becoming resistant to them.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Tenvir-EM Tablet is used to treat HIV infection and is an antiretroviral medicine.</li>\n	<li>Tenvir-EM Tablet 30 reduces the likelihood of developing AIDS and other HIV-related illnesses.</li>\n	<li>The tablet is a combination of two drugs: Emtricitabine and Tenofovir disoproxil fumarate.</li>\n	<li>Emtricitabine and Tenofovir disoproxil fumarate are nucleoside and nucleotide reverse transcriptase inhibitors, respectively.</li>\n	<li>Tenvir-EM Tablet works by disrupting the activity of enzymes that the virus needs to replicate.</li>\n	<li>Taking Tenvir-EM Tablet along with safe sex practices and lifestyle changes can reduce the risk of transmitting or contracting the HIV virus.</li>\n	<li>Tenvir-EM Tablet helps control the HIV infection, improve immune system function, and decrease the chances of complications and new infections.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Inform your doctor about any existing medical conditions or allergies you have before starting the medication.</li>\n	<li>Let your doctor know if you are pregnant, planning to become pregnant, or breastfeeding. The safety of Tenvir-EM Tablet during pregnancy and breastfeeding is not well established.</li>\n	<li>Do not share this medication with others, as it is prescribed based on individual needs.</li>\n	<li>Tenvir-EM Tablet may interact with other medications you are taking. Inform your doctor about any other medications, vitamins, or supplements you are currently taking.</li>\n	<li>Tenvir-EM Tablet may cause dizziness or drowsiness. Avoid driving or operating machinery until you know how the medicine affects you.</li>\n	<li>Inform your doctor if you experience any side effects such as nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, or fever.</li>\n	<li>Follow your doctor&#39;s instructions regarding the dosage and duration of Tenvir-EM Tablet. Do not stop taking the medicine without consulting your doctor.</li>\n	<li>Practice safe sex and take necessary precautions to prevent the transmission of HIV to others.</li>\n</ul>','<p>Tenvir-EM Tablet is an antiretroviral medicine used to manage HIV infection. This medication helps lower the risk of developing AIDS (acquired immunodeficiency syndrome) and other HIV-related ailments. In addition to this, Tenvir-EM Tablet is also used to minimize the risk of acquiring HIV-1 infection if taken daily and used with safe sexual practices.</p>\n\n<p>The combination of two drugs, Emtricitabine and Tenofovir disoproxil fumarate, is what makes up Tenvir-EM Tablet. Emtricitabine is a nucleoside reverse transcriptase inhibitor, while Tenofovir disoproxil fumarate is a nucleotide reverse transcriptase inhibitor. By interfering with the activity of nucleotide and nucleoside reverse transcriptase enzymes, Tenvir-EM Tablet impedes virus replication, which helps combat HIV infection.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>In many cases, side effects of this medication will go away on their own as your body becomes accustomed to it and do not require medical intervention. However, if you experience persistent side effects or are concerned about them, it is advisable to consult with your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>The common side effects are listed below:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Weakness</li>\n</ul>','[\"tenvir-em-300-200mg-171388062726.jpg\"]','TE300',1,'0','2024-04-23 13:57:52','2025-10-08 07:22:16'),(713,0,'Terol LA 2mg','terol-la-2mg','Capsules','terol-la-2mg-171388080893.jpg','TE02','<p>Terol Capsule ER advantages</p>\n\n<p>Symptoms of an overactive bladder (OAB) treatment</p>\n\n<p>Terol LA 2 Capsule ER aids in the treatment of irregular, out-of-control bladder muscular contractions (spasms), which can lead to frequent urination, an urgent need to urinate, and the inability to regulate passing of urine. Additionally, it lessens the urgency to urinate that may be brought on by some urinary tract infections as well as painful or frequent urination. In this method, the symptoms of an overactive bladder are effectively managed.</p>\n\n<p>Terol Ca