ave a history of seizures.</li>\n	<li>Inform your doctor about other medical conditions.</li>\n	<li>Check for potential drug interactions.</li>\n	<li>Consult a doctor if pregnant or breastfeeding.</li>\n	<li>Use with caution with children and the elderly.</li>\n	<li>Follow the prescribed dosage to avoid overdosing.</li>\n	<li>Do not stop abruptly; consult your doctor for discontinuation.</li>\n</ul>','<p>Theo-Asthalin Tablet&nbsp; is a combination medication that contains salbutamol, a bronchodilator, and theophylline, a xanthine and phosphodiesterase inhibitor. It is used to manage chronic respiratory conditions such as asthma and chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD). Asthma is a condition where the airways narrow, swell, and produce excess mucus, causing breathing difficulties. COPD refers to a group of progressive lung diseases, including emphysema and chronic bronchitis, which can lead to shortness of breath and inflammation of the bronchial tubes.</p>\n\n<p>By relaxing and widening the narrowed or blocked airways in the lungs, the Theo-Asthalin Tablet&nbsp; helps manage asthma and COPD. It is prescribed for the treatment of acute asthma attacks and wheezing induced by factors like colds or exercise.</p>\n\n<p>When taking theo-asthalin tablets, they should be taken without food, following the dosage and duration recommended by your doctor. It is important to continue taking the medication as prescribed to maintain symptom control and prevent the condition from worsening. Inform your healthcare team about all other medications you are taking, as there may be potential interactions with the Theo-Asthalin Tablet.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>The majority of side effects do not need medical attention and typically subside as your body adapts to the medication. However, if you are concerned or if the side effects persist, it is recommended that you consult your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>The most common side effects are listed below:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\