ill depend on the purpose for which it is being taken, and your doctor will determine the appropriate amount to alleviate your symptoms. Continue using this medication for the entire prescribed duration. Keep in mind that the Tiova Inhaler does not provide immediate relief for ongoing breathing difficulties or asthma attacks, so it is essential to carry your emergency inhaler with you at all times.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Tiova Inhaler 200 Mdi is classified as a bronchodilator, which is an anti-asthmatic medication used to treat asthma and chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD). It exerts its effects by blocking the receptors for acetylcholine that are released in the cholinergic nerve endings within the airways. By doing so, Tiova Inhaler 200 Mdi helps relax and widen the openings of the airways, facilitating easier airflow in and out of the lungs. This mechanism of action contributes to the treatment of asthma and COPD.</p>\n\n<p>Regular usage of the Tiova Inhaler 200 Mdi can be beneficial for individuals experiencing ongoing shortness of breath associated with conditions like asthma. Additionally, daily use of Tiova Inhaler 200 Mdi can help prevent sudden exacerbations of COPD symptoms, providing relief over a longer period of time. Furthermore, Tiova Inhaler 200 Mdi may be prescribed as an adjunct to other medications for the management of asthma.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Tiova Inhaler 200 Mdi should be used with caution in patients with a history of narrow-angle glaucoma, urinary retention, or prostate enlargement.</li>\n	<li>It is important to inform your doctor about any existing medical conditions, especially if you have a heart condition or high blood pressure.</li>\n	<li>Tiova Inhaler 200 Mdi may cause dizziness or blurred vision, so it is advisable to avoid activities that require alertness until you know how it affects you.</li>\n	<li>Let your doctor know about all the medications you are currently taking, including prescription drugs, over-the-counter medicines, and herbal supplements, as they may interact with Tiova Inhaler 200 Mdi.</li>\n	<li>If you experience any allergic reactions or severe side effects such as difficulty breathing, chest pain, or a rapid heartbeat, seek immediate medical attention.</li>\n	<li>Pregnant or breastfeeding women should consult their doctor before using Tiova Inhaler 200 Mdi.</li>\n	<li>It is important to follow the prescribed dose and frequency and not exceed the recommended use of the inhaler.</li>\n</ul>','<p>Tiova Inhaler 200 Mdi is a bronchodilator medication categorized as an anti-asthmatic agent. It is used to treat asthma and chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD). Asthma is a chronic respiratory condition characterized by narrowed airways, swelling, and excessive mucus production, resulting in breathing difficulties. COPD refers to a group of lung diseases, including emphysema and chronic bronchitis, that cause shortness of breath and inflammation of the bronchial tubes.</p>\n\n<p>Tiova Inhaler 200 Mdi contains the active ingredient &#39;Tiotropium,&#39; which functions by blocking the receptors for acetylcholine released in the cholinergic nerve endings within the airways. By doing so, Tiova Inhaler 200 Mdi relaxes and widens the openings of the airways, facilitating easier airflow in and out of the lungs. This provides relief from the symptoms of asthma and COPD.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>The majority of side effects do not need medical attention and typically subside as your body adapts to the medication. However, if you are concerned or if the side effects persist, it is recommended that you consult your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>The most common side effects are listed below:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Dry mouth</li>\n	<li>Stomach upset</li>\n	<li>Constipation</li>\n	<li>Blurred vision</li>\n	<li>Chest pain</li>\n</ul>','[\"tiova-inhaler-9-mcg-200-mdi-171393588022.webp\"]','TI009',1,'0','2024-04-24 05:18:47','2025-10-08 07:23:51'),(724,0,'Tiova 