scribes them. If you have Parkinson&#39;s disease or myasthenia gravis, let your doctor know because antibiotics like tobramycin might make muscle weakness worse. Toba DM Eye Drops 10 ml include a preservative that may irritate the eyes and discolor soft contact lenses, so it is advisable that you take them out before using them. After using Toba DM Eye Drops 10 ml for 15 minutes, contact lenses can be reinserted. Use of Toba DM Eye Drops 10 ml and topical non-steroidal anti-inflammatory medicine are contraindicated. Dexamethasone is an ingredient in Toba DM Eye Drops 10 ml; using dexamethasone plus a topical NSAID at the same time may cause your eye wound to take longer to heal. Before taking Toba DM Eye Drops 10 ml, please speak to your doctor if you have diabetes. Patients with diabetes have a higher chance of developing cataracts and glaucoma, which affects intraocular pressure. Toba DM Eye Drops 10 ml may temporarily impair vision (blurred vision), thus exercise caution when operating machinery and driving.</p>','<p>Antibiotic and corticosteroid eye drops called Toba DM Eye Drops 10 ml are used to treat bacterial eye and ear infections. It is used to treat eye infections such conjunctivitis (an infection of the eyeball&#39;s outer white membrane) and corneal ulcers (which develop in the cornea, the eye&#39;s inner membrane). This virus is very contagious and can spread from person to person. Pink or red-tinted eyes, a gritty feeling in the eyes, irritation around the eyes, watery eyes, and thick discharge are all signs and symptoms of this condition.</p>\n\n<p>Tobramycin and dexamethasone are also ingredients in Toba DM Eye Drops 10 ml. Tobramycin is an aminoglycoside that causes cell death and prevents bacterial growth by obstructing protein synthesis. Dexamethasone is a corticosteroid drug that lowers inflammation and redness by inhibiting the white blood cells (WBCs) that fight infections.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Eye redness</li>\n	<li>Burning sensation</li>\n	<li>Eye pain</li>\n	<li>Dry eyes</li>\n</ul>','[\"toba-dm-3-mg-and-1-mg-10-ml-171393709378.jpg\"]','TO031',1,'0','2024-04-24 05:39:06','2025-10-08 07:54:32'),(728,0,'Toba Eye Drop  0.3% (5 ml)','toba-eye-drop-0.3-(5-ml)','Drops','toba-eye-drop-0-171393753385.webp','TO03','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>To use Toba Eye Drop 0.3%, follow the instructions provided by your healthcare professional or read and follow the directions on the medication label. Wash your hands before using the eye drops. Tilt your head back and pull down your lower eyelid to create a small pocket. Squeeze the prescribed number of drops into the pocket without touching the tip of the dropper to your eye or any other surface. Gently close your eyes for a few minutes to allow the medication to spread evenly. If you are using other eye medications, wait at least 5 minutes between applications.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Toba Eye Drop 0.3% offers several benefits in the treatment of eye infections and inflammation:</p>\n\n<p>Effective against bacterial eye infections: Toba Eye Drop 0.3% contains tobramycin, which has potent antibacterial properties. It is highly effective in treating bacterial eye infections, including conjunctivitis (pink eye), blepharitis, and other types of ocular infections caused by susceptible bacteria.</p>\n\n<p>Effective relief of symptoms: By targeting and killing bacteria responsible for the infection, Toba Eye Drop 0.3% can provide effective relief from symptoms such as redness, itching, swelling, and discharge. This can help alleviate discomfort and promote healing.</p>\n\n<p>Wide spectrum of activity: Toba Eye Drop 0.3% is effective against a broad range of bacteria, including both Gram-positive and Gram-negative strains. This broad-spectrum activity allows for the treatment of various types of bacterial eye infections.</p>\n\n<p>Convenient and easy to use: Toba Eye Drop 0.3% comes in a convenient dropper bottle, allowing for precise and easy application. The user-friendly design ensures accurate dosing, making it simple to administer the medication without any hassle.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before using Toba Eye Drop 0.3%, it&rsquo;s important to inform your healthcare provider or pharmacist about any known allergies you have, including allergies to tobramycin or other aminoglycoside antibiotics. If you experience any signs of an allergic reaction, such as itching, rash, or swelling, seek medical attention immediately.</p>','<p>Toba Eye Drop 0.3% (5 ml) is a medication commonly used to treat eye infections and inflammation. It contains the active ingredient tobramycin, which belongs to a class of drugs known as aminoglycoside antibiotics. This medication is primarily used to treat bacterial eye infections and is not effective against viral or fungal infections.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>Toba Eye Drop 0.3% is generally well-tolerated, and serious side effects are rare. Most people using this medication do not experience any significant adverse reactions. However, like any medication, Toba Eye Drop 0.3% may have some potential side effects, though they are usually mild and temporary. These can include:</p>\n\n<p>Temporary eye irritation: Some individuals may experience mild burning or stinging sensation in the eyes upon application of the drops. This typically subsides quickly.</p>\n\n<p>Transient blurred vision: Blurred vision may occur temporarily after applying the eye drops. It usually resolves on its own within a short period.</p>\n\n<p>Dryness or discomfort: Some individuals may experience temporary dryness or discomfort in the eyes after using the medication. This can be alleviated by using artificial tears or lubricating eye drops as recommended by your healthcare professional.</p>','[\"toba-eye-drop-0-171393753385.webp\"]','TO03',1,'0','2024-04-24 05:42:27','2025-10-08 07:25:14'),(729,0,'Tonact EZ 20+10mg','tonact-ez-20+10mg','tablet','tonact-ez-20-10mg-171393881255.webp','TO20','<p>Usage:</p>