hole prescribed amount of time, even if you start to feel better. If you suddenly stop taking the medicine without first discussing it with your doctor, you may see an increase in the number of seizures you have. While you are taking this medication, your physician may recommend that you have your serum bicarbonate levels checked on a frequent basis.Take this medication at the prescribed dose and for the prescribed amount of time as directed by your doctor. Take it in one complete bite. Do not chew on it, crush it, or break it in any way. The Topamac 100mg Tablet can be taken either with or without meals; however, it is recommended that it be taken at a consistent time each day.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>A drug called Topamac 100mg Tablet acts as an anticonvulsant (or anti-epileptic) by reducing the nerve impulses that lead to seizures. It will give you more confidence to carry out your everyday activities by reducing the incidence of seizures. Confusion, uncontrollable jerking, loss of awareness, and fear or worry are some of the symptoms that it helps with.</p>\n\n<p>Although there is no physical or psychological reliance (addiction) connected with this medication, it shouldn&#39;t be stopped abruptly. To be effective, it must be taken as directed on a regular basis. A seizure could start if a dose is missed.</p>\n\n<p>In order to prevent migraines</p>\n\n<p>How Topamac 100mg Tablet helps to avoid migraines is not entirely known. It might alter the excessive and aberrant brain nerve cell activity or boost activity in a part of the brain linked to migraines. It can help you go about your regular activities and improve your quality of life by preventing and decreasing the frequency of headaches.</p>\n\n<p>In the Lennox-Gastaut condition</p>\n\n<p>Usually beginning in early childhood, Lennox-Gastaut syndrome (LGS) is an uncommon but severe form of epilepsy. Children that are affected may have various distinct types of seizures. By reducing the nerve impulses that trigger the seizures, Topamac 100mg Tablet aids in both seizure prevention and seizure control.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Follow the prescribed dosage: Take Topamac 100mg exactly as prescribed by your healthcare professional. Do not change the dosage or stop taking the medication without consulting your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>Inform your doctor about your medical history: Before starting Topamac, inform your healthcare professional about any pre-existing medical conditions you have, such as kidney problems, liver disease, glaucoma, or a history of metabolic acidosis. This information helps your doctor determine if Topamac is suitable for you and adjust the dosage if necessary.</p>\n\n<p>Avoid driving or operating machinery: Topamac may cause dizziness, drowsiness, or blurred vision. If you experience any of these side effects, avoid activities that require alertness, such as driving or operating heavy machinery.</p>\n\n<p>Stay hydrated: Topamac can increase the risk of kidney stones and dehydration. Drink plenty of fluids throughout the day to maintain adequate hydration unless otherwise advised by your doctor.</p>','<p>A medication called Topamac 100mg Tablet is taken to treat epilepsy (seizures), as well as to avoid migraine headaches. Additionally, it is utilized in the treatment of Lennox-Gastaut syndrome, which is a kind of epilepsy that manifests itself in early childhood but is quite severe.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Abdominal pain</li>\n	<li>Diarrhea</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n	<li>Fatigue</li>\n	<li>Fever</li>\n	<li>Loss of appetite</li>\n</ul>','[\"topamac-100mg-171393909294.jpg\"]','TO100',1,'0','2024-04-24 06:12:16','2025-10-08 07:25:45'),(731,0,'Topamac 25mg','topamac-25mg','tablet','topamac-25mg-171393941341.webp','TO25','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Although the Topamac 25mg Tablet should ideally be taken every day at the same time, it can be taken with or without food. If you miss a dosage, take it as soon as you remember to do so and k