ing the nerve impulses that cause the seizures.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Adhere to the recommended dosage: Take Topamac 25mg exactly as directed by your doctor. Without first consulting your doctor, never alter the medication&#39;s dosage or stop taking it.</p>\n\n<p>Share your medical history with your doctor: Inform your doctor about any existing medical concerns you have before beginning Topamac, such as renal issues, liver illness, glaucoma, or a history of metabolic acidosis. This information enables your doctor to assess your suitability for Topamac and, if required, modify your dosage.</p>\n\n<p>Topamac may make you drowsy, dizzy, or cause impaired vision, so avoid operating machinery or driving. Avoid engaging in tasks that call for attention, such as operating heavy machinery or operating a vehicle, if you suffer any of these side effects.</p>\n\n<p>Remain hydrated because Topamax raises the risk of dehydration and kidney stones. Unless your doctor instructs you otherwise, drink plenty of liquids throughout the day to maintain appropriate hydration.</p>','<p>Topamac 25mg Tablet is a drug used to treat epilepsy (seizures) and prevent migraine headaches. Additionally, it is used to treat Lennox-Gastaut syndrome, a severe form of epilepsy that first appears in early childhood.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Abdominal pain</li>\n	<li>Diarrhea</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n	<li>Fatigue</li>\n	<li>Fever</li>\n	<li>Loss of appetite</li>\n</ul>','[\"topamac-25mg-171393941341.webp\"]','TO25',1,'0','2024-04-24 06:17:29','2025-10-08 07:25:59'),(732,0,'Topamac 50mg','topamac-50mg','tablet','topamac-50mg-171393964252.png','TO50','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>It is possible to take a Topamac 50mg Tablet with or without food, preferably each day at the same time. If you forget to take a dose, do so as soon as you remember, and even if you feel better, complete the entire course of treatment. Without consulting your doctor, stopping the medicine abruptly could result in more seizures. While using this medication, your doctor may prescribe routine serum bicarbonate level monitoring.Follow your doctor&#39;s instructions for this medication&#39;s dosage and duration. Take it all in at once. Don&#39;t eat it, break it, or crush it. It is preferable to take Topamac 50mg Tablet at a set time rather than with or without food.</p>\n\n<p>Benfits:</p>\n\n<p>An anticonvulsant (or anti-epileptic) drug called Topamac 50mg Tablet works by reducing the nerve impulses that lead to seizures. It will give you more confidence to carry out your everyday activities by reducing the incidence of seizures. Confusion, uncontrollable jerking, loss of awareness, and fear or worry are some of the symptoms that it helps with.</p>\n\n<p>Although there is no physical or psychological reliance (addiction) connected with this medication, it shouldn&#39;t be stopped abruptly. To be effective, it must be taken as directed on a regular basis. A seizure could start if a dose is missed.</p>\n\n<p>In order to prevent migraines</p>\n\n<p>How Topamac 50mg Tablet helps to avoid migraines is not entirely known. It might alter the excessive and aberrant brain nerve cell activity or boost activity in a part of the brain linked to migraines. It can help you go about your regular activities and improve your quality of life by preventing and decreasing the frequency of headaches.</p>\n\n<p>In the Lennox-Gastaut condition</p>\n\n<p>Usually beginning in early childhood, Lennox-Gastaut syndrome (LGS) is an uncommon but severe form of epilepsy. Children that are affected may have various distinct types of seizures. By reducing the nerve impulses that trigger the seizures, Topamac 50mg Tablet aids in seizure prevention and control.</p>\n\n<p>Precutions:</p>\n\n<p>Follow the prescribed dosage: Take Topamac 50mg exactly as prescribed by your healthcare professional. Do not change the dosage or stop taking the medication without consulting your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>Inform your doctor about your medical history: Before starting Topamac, inform your healthcare professional about any pre-existing medical conditions you have, such as kidney problems, liver disease, glaucoma, or a history of metabolic acidosis. This information helps your doctor determine if Topamac is suitable for you and adjust the dosage if necessary.</p>\n\n<p>Avoid driving or operating machinery: Topamac may cause dizziness, drowsiness, or blurred vision. If you experience any of these side effects, avoid activities that require alertness, such as driving or operating heavy machinery.</p>\n\n<p>Stay hydrated: Topamac can increase the risk of kidney stones and dehydration. Drink plenty of fluids throughout the day to maintain adequate hydration unless otherwise advised by your doctor.</p>','<p>A medication called Topamac 50mg Tablet is used to treat epilepsy (seizures) and ward off migraines. Lennox-Gastaut syndrome, a rare but severe form of infantile epilepsy, is another condition for which it is used as a therapy.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Abdominal pain</li>\n	<li>Diarrhea</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n	<li>Fatigue</li>\n	<li>Fever</li>\n	<li>Loss of appetite</li>\n</ul>','[\"topamac-50mg-171393964252.png\"]','TO50',1,'0','2024-04-24 06:21:28','2025-10-08 07:26:11'),(733,0,'Topinate 0.05% 30 gm','topinate-0.05-30-gm','Tube','topinate-0-171393987317.jpg','TO05','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>Use Topinate Cream 30 gm exactly as directed by your doctor or pharmacist. To reap the greatest benefits, it would be better to use Topinate Cream 30 gm frequently. Some people report a brief burning or stinging feeling after applying Topinate Cream 30 gm to their skin. After a few days of use, this stops happening.Only exterior use is permitted. As directed by your doctor, place a tiny quantity of it on the tip of your finger and apply a thin coating to the clean, dry affected region. Avoid getting this product in your eyes or on your nose. Rinse with water liberally if you come into contact with these areas by accident. If your hands are unaffected, wash them before and after usage to stop the virus from spreading.Shampoo: You can use it in place of conventional shampoo when showering or as prescribed by a doctor.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Chemical mediators are responsible for the release of inflammatory chemicals into the skin, which leads to inflammation of the skin. It causes rashes, swelling, and itching, all of which can be alleviated with the use of Topinate Cream 30 gm. It takes aim at the immune system and dampens the immune reaction, buying some time for the irritated skin to recover from the damage it has sustained.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>If you have ever experienced an allergic reaction (hypersensitivity) to another steroid, it is important that you let your doctor know before beginning treatment with Topinate Cream 30 gm. In the event that there has been an overdose, the affected region should be carefully cleaned, and the medication should then be reapplied. Be very careful while applying the medication to the eyelids or anywhere else near the eyes, as there is a possibility of developing cataracts or glaucoma if the medication is allowed to enter the eye on a regular basis. Topinate Cream 30 gm is able to penetrate the skin with relative ease and, with continued usage, may lead to a reduction in the thickness of the skin. When using it on large areas of skin or skin that is broken or damaged, as well as when applying it, be very careful. In the event that you are experiencing visual issues or any other concerning symptoms, consult your physician as soon as possible. It is not recommended to use Topinate Cream 30 gm in conjunction with any other types of creams or ointments, including a moisturizer. It is recommended to wait at least half an hour between applications of clobetasol and any other substance.</p>','<p>A group of drugs known as topical corticosteroids includes Topinate Cream 30 gm. It is used for the treatment of autoimmune skin disorders such as psoriasis (scaly, itchy, and red patches on the skin), lichen planus (purplish, itchy, and flat bumps on the wrists, forearms, or legs), discoid lupus erythematosus (red, coin-shaped scales or crusts on the scalp, cheeks, and ears), and eczema (red and itchy skin). In autoimmune skin disorders, the body&#39;s healthy cells are attacked by the immune system, resulting in inflammation. Topinate Cream 30 gm helps lower inflammation and inhibit the immunological system.</p>\n\n<p>Clobetasol, an active corticosteroid with anti-inflammatory effects on the skin, is a component in Topinate Cream 30 gm. It lessens inflammation-causing chemical messengers that are produced by the body&#39;s generation of specific chemical messengers, such as swelling, redness, and itching. In order to treat skin problems like psoriasis, eczema, lichen planus, and discoid lupus erythematosus, Topinate Cream 30 gm is used.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Burning or stinging sensation</li>\n	<li>Pain (application site)</li>\n	<li>Irritation or itching</li>\n	<li>Skin thinning may cause stretch marks</li>\n	<li>Blood vessels under the surface of your skin may become more noticeable.</li>\n</ul>','[\"topinate-0-171393987317.jpg\"]','TO05',1,'0','2024-04-24 06:25:26','2025-10-08 07:53:38'),(734,0,'Trajenta 5mg','trajenta-5mg','tablet','trajenta-5mg-171394097953.jpg','TR05','<p>Advantages of Trajenta Tablet for Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus Treatment</p>\n\n<p>The drug Trajenta 5mg Tablet is a member of the DPP-4 inhibitors (also known as gliptins) class of medications. It helps your body create more insulin after meals and prevents your body from releasing too much glucose (sugar) into the blood. In doing so, it decreases your body&#39;s blood glucose levels. It often only causes a single common side effect and is taken once day.</p>\n\n<p>In order to effectively manage diabetes, blood glucose levels must be reduced. You will have a lower chance of developing any of the significant complications of diabetes, such as kidney damage, blindness, and amputation of limbs, if you can manage the level. The risk of heart disease and stroke can be decreased with proper diabetes management. You can have a regular, healthy life by taking this medication consistently and adhering to a good diet and exercise routine. As long as it has been prescribed, you should continue using it.</p>\n\n<p>Tablet Trajenta side effects</p>\n\n<p>The majority of adverse effects are temporary and go away as your body becomes used to the medication. If they persist or you&#39;re concerned about them, speak with your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>Utilising a Trajenta Tablet</p>\n\n<p>Follow your doctor&#39;s instructions for this medication&#39;s dosage and duration. Take it all in at once. Don&#39;t eat it, break it, or crush it. It is preferable to take Trajenta 5mg Tablet at a set time rather than with food.</p>\n\n<p>Functions of Trajenta Tablet</p>\n\n<p>An anti-diabetic drug is Trajenta 5mg Tablet. It functions by raising the pancreas&#39;s production of insulin and reducing the hormones that cause blood sugar levels to rise. This lowers the sugar levels during fasting and after meals.</p>','<p>A medication called Trajenta 5mg Tablet is used to treat type 2 diabetes mellitus. To manage blood sugar levels, it is taken in conjunction with a nutritious diet and frequent exercise. This assists in avoiding significant diabetes consequences like kidney damage and blindness.</p>\n\n<p>When diet and exercise alone, or other medications, are unable to control your blood sugar level, Trajenta 5mg Tablet is typically suggested. It may be prescribed by your doctor either by itself or in conjunction with other diabetes medications. Taking it with or without food is acceptable.</p>\n\n<p>Your condition and blood sugar levels will determine the dosage. Use it exactly as your doctor has prescribed. If your doctor has not advised you to stop taking the medication, do not. While taking this medication, it&#39;s crucial to stick to the diet and exercise regimen advised by your doctor. Controlling diabetes involves changing your lifestyle significantly.</p>\n\n<p>Hypoglycemia is one of this medication&#39;s most frequent side effects. Knowing how to handle hypoglycemia is crucial, as are the signs of the condition, which include lightheadedness, sweating, dizziness, fainting, and dry mouth. If you suffer any symptoms, you can carry sugar or glucose candies with you and eat them to control them. In some cases, it can also lead to nasopharyngitis. If any of these side effects persist or bother you, speak with your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>Inform your doctor if you have ever experienced renal illness, heart disease, or pancreas issues before using this medication. The effectiveness of this medication could be hampered by other medications you are taking. Therefore, be careful to tell your doctor about all the other medications you are taking.</p>\n\n<p>Before using it, women who are pregnant or nursing should also visit their doctor. While taking this medication, try to avoid drinking too much alcohol as it may raise your risk of low blood sugar. To make sure the medication is working as it should, you might require regular tests for things like blood glucose levels and kidney function.</p>','<p>Trajenta common side effects</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Low blood glucose, or hypoglycemia</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Nasopharyngitis, or throat and nasal passageway inflammation</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cough</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Vomiting</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Diarrhea</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Constipation</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Chronic pancreatitis</li>\n</ul>','[\"trajenta-5mg-171394097953.jpg\"]','TR05',1,'0','2024-04-24 06:44:35','2025-10-08 07:53:55'),(735,0,'Travatan  2.5 ml (0.004%)','travatan-2.5-ml-(0.004-)','Drops','travatan-2-171394268055.jpg','TR2.5','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>It is important to follow the instructions provided by your doctor or pharmacist when using Travatan. Read the medication label carefully and adhere to the recommended dosage and application guidelines. Apply one drop of Travatan into the affected eye(s) once daily, preferably in the evening, unless directed otherwise by your healthcare professional.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Effective treatment for glaucoma: Travatan is commonly prescribed for the management of glaucoma, a condition characterized by increased pressure in the eye that can lead to optic nerve damage. By reducing intraocular pressure, Travatan helps to prevent further damage and preserve vision.</p>\n\n<p>Reduction of ocular hypertension: Ocular hypertension refers to elevated pressure within the eye, which can increase the risk of developing glaucoma. Travatan is an effective medication for lowering intraocular pressure, aiding in the prevention of potential vision problems associated with ocular hypertension.</p>\n\n<p>Convenient once-daily application: Travatan offers the advantage of once-daily dosing, making it a convenient option for individuals with busy lifestyles. By following the prescribed dosage and applying the medication at the recommended time, you can effectively manage your eye condition without frequent dosing.</p>\n\n<p>Well-tolerated and temporary side effects: Travatan is generally well-tolerated, and any side effects experienced are usually temporary and mild. It is important to note that not everyone will experience side effects, but if they do occur, they are typically limited to mild eye irritation, temporary stinging or burning sensation, and rarely, darkening of the iris or eyelid skin.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Inform your healthcare provider about any allergies or sensitivities you may have before using Travatan, as it contains certain inactive ingredients that could potentially cause an allergic reaction. Your pharmacist can provide additional information and guidance.</p>\n\n<p>If you wear contact lenses, it&rsquo;s advisable to remove them before applying Travatan and wait at least 15 minutes before reinserting them. This helps to ensure optimal absorption and effectiveness of the medication.</p>\n\n<p>Prioritize regular eye check-ups: While using Travatan, it&rsquo;s important to maintain regular visits to your eye care professional for check-ups and monitoring of your eye condition. They can evaluate the progress of your treatment and make any necessary adjustments to optimize your eye health.</p>\n\n<p>Travatan is a valuable medication that effectively treats eye conditions such as glaucoma and ocular hypertension. By following the prescribed dosage and adhering to the instructions provided by your healthcare professional, you can experience the benefits of Travatan while managing your eye health with ease. Remember to consult your doctor or pharmacist for personalized advice and guidance tailored to your specific needs.</p>','<p>Travatan 2.5 ml (0.004%) is a medication that offers numerous benefits and is primarily used to treat certain eye conditions. It contains the active ingredient travoprost, which belongs to a class of medications called prostaglandin analogs. Here&rsquo;s some important information about Travatan:</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Eye redness</li>\n	<li>Itching in eyes</li>\n	<li>Darkening of Eye lids</li>\n</ul>','[\"travatan-2-171394268055.jpg\"]','TR2.5',1,'0','2024-04-24 07:16:02','2025-10-08 07:54:04'),(736,0,'Aerocort Rotacaps 100/100mcg','aerocort-rotacaps-100100mcg','Rotacaps','aerocort-rotacaps-100-100mcg-171817680760.jpg','AER100','<p>How to Use:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Do not swallow Rotacaps. It is important to avoid ingestion of the capsules.</li>\n	<li>Before use, carefully read and follow the directions provided on the label.</li>\n	<li>Place the capsule at the base of the rotahaler, avoiding insertion into the mouthpiece.</li>\n	<li>Twist the mouthpiece completely until you hear a click, ensuring that the capsule is securely in place.</li>\n	<li>Take a deep breath through the mouthpiece, inhaling the medication. Breathe in deeply to ensure effective delivery.</li>\n	<li>Hold your breath for up to 10 seconds to allow the medication to reach deep into the lungs.</li>\n	<li>If any powder remains in the rotahaler after inhalation, repeat the process to ensure complete medication administration.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Aerocort Rotacap is a medication specifically designed to address the challenges faced by individuals with asthma, a condition characterized by narrowed airways and difficulties breathing. This medication works by widening the airways, providing relief from common asthma symptoms such as chest tightness, shortness of breath, wheezing, and coughing. In addition to medication, incorporating regular exercise and yoga into your routine can have long-term benefits, improving asthma symptoms while also promoting overall health.</p>\n\n<p>Aerocort Rotacap is a combination respiratory medicine that contains two active ingredients: beclomethasone dipropionate and levosalbutamol sulfate. Beclomethasone dipropionate is a steroid that effectively inhibits and suppresses inflammatory mediators and cells associated with inflammation. Levosalbutamol sulfate, a short-acting beta-agonist, stimulates the relaxation of smooth muscle cells in the airways, facilitating improved airflow. As a result, Aerocort Rotacap 30 serves as a powerful solution for addressing breathing difficulties related to asthma, including the inflammation and swelling associated with the condition.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Medical supervision is important.</li>\n	<li>Inform your doctor about any allergies or sensitivities.</li>\n	<li>Discuss existing medical conditions.</li>\n	<li>Inform your doctor about all medications you are taking.</li>\n	<li>Be aware of potential side effects and seek medical attention for severe or persistent symptoms.</li>\n	<li>Fol