promoting the natural exfoliation of the outer layers of the skin.</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>The common side effects are listed below:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Burning</li>\n	<li>Irritation</li>\n	<li>Itching&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>Redness</li>\n</ul>','[\"triluma-15-gm-cream-171820429013.jpg\"]','TR15',1,'0','2024-06-12 14:58:20','2025-10-08 07:58:38'),(744,0,'Triohale Inhaler 200 mdi','triohale-inhaler-200-mdi','inhaler','triohale-inhaler-200-mdi-172252323725.png','TR200','<p>How to Use:</p>\n\n<p>For the Inhaler/Transhaler: Prior to usage, ensure that you shake the inhaler thoroughly and refer to the instructions on the label. While inhaling the medication through your mouth, press down on the inhaler once to release the medicine, and hold your breath for approximately 10 seconds. Repeat this process until you have taken the recommended number of puffs as instructed by your doctor. After using the inhaler, rinse your mouth with water and then spit it out.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Symptom Relief: The Triohale Inhaler helps alleviate the symptoms associated with asthma and COPD. It effectively opens up the airways, making it easier to breathe and reducing shortness of breath, wheezing, and chest tightness.</li>\n	<li>Combination Therapy: As a combination inhaler, Triohale contains three active ingredients: tiotropium, formoterol, and ciclesonide. This combination provides a comprehensive approach to managing respiratory conditions by targeting different aspects of the disease. Tiotropium and formoterol act as bronchodilators, relaxing the muscles in the airways and improving airflow. Ciclesonide, a corticosteroid, reduces airway inflammation.</li>\n	<li>Long-Lasting Effect: The Triohale Inhaler is a long-acting inhaler, which means its effects can last for a longer duration compared to short-acting inhalers. This allows for fewer doses throughout the day, improving convenience and compliance with the treatment regimen.</li>\n	<li>Personalized Treatment: The number of puffs advised by your doctor is based on your individual condition and needs. The Triohale Inhaler allows for personalized dosing to ensure optimal symptom control and management.</li>\n	<li>Convenient and Portable: The Triohale Inhaler is a compact and portable device, making it easy to carry and use wherever you go. It provides on-the-go relief and can be easily incorporated into daily routines.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Follow the Instructions: Read and follow the instructions provided with the inhaler carefully. Adhere to the prescribed dosage and frequency recommended by your healthcare professional.</li>\n	<li>Medical Guidance: Consult your doctor before starting the Triohale Inhaler to ensure it is suitable for your specific condition. Inform them about any other medications, allergies, or medical conditions you have.</li>\n	<li>Inhaler Technique: Learn the proper inhaler technique from your healthcare provider to ensure you are using the inhaler correctly and maximizing its effectiveness.</li>\n	<li>Regular Check-ups: Schedule regular check-ups with your doctor to monitor your condition, evaluate the effectiveness of the inhaler, and make any necessary adjustments to your treatment plan.\n	<ul>\n		<li>Rinse Mouth: After using the inhaler, rinse your mouth with water and spit it out. This helps minimize the risk of side effects such as oral thrush or throat irritation.</li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n</ul>','<p>The Triohale Inhaler falls under the category of medications known as respiratory stimulants. Its primary purpose is to address symptoms associated with asthma and chronic obstructive pulmonary diseases (COPD). Asthma, a chronic respiratory condition, involves the narrowing, swelling, and excessive mucus production in the airways, leading to breathing difficulties. COPD encompasses a group of lung diseases characterized by shortness of breath (emphysema) and inflammation of the bronchial tubes (chronic bronchitis).</p>\n\n<p>Triohale Inhaler combines three drugs: tiotropium (an anti-cholinergic), formoterol (a long-acting beta-agonist or bronchodilator), and ciclesonide (a corticosteroid). Tiotropium acts as an anti-cholinergic, while formoterol functions as a bronchodilator. Both medications work by relaxing the muscles in the airways and widening them, making breathing easier for individuals with asthma and COPD. On the other hand, ciclesonide, a corticosteroid, inhibits the release of specific natural substances in the body responsible for airway inflammation.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<p>The most common side effects are listed below:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Fungal infection in the mouth</li>\n	<li>Vomiting</li>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Sore throat, hoarse voice</li>\n</ul>','[\"triohale-inhaler-200-mdi-172252324887.png\"]','TR200',1,'0','2024-08-01 14:41:05','2025-10-08 07:58:53'),(745,0,'Triomune 30+150+200mg Tablets','triomune-30150200mg-tablets','tablet','triomune-30-150-200mg-tablets-172252399629.jpg','TR30','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>To ensure optimal results, it is recommended to follow the instructions provided by your healthcare provider or pharmacist when taking this medication. It is important to read and adhere to all the instructions on the medication label. By using the medication as directed, you can maximize its effectiveness and safety.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Effective HIV treatment: Triomune 30+150+200mg Tablets have been proven to be effective in suppressing the replication of the HIV virus and reducing its levels in the body. By doing so, it helps to control the progression of the disease, prevent further damage to the immune system, and improve overall health.</p>\n\n<p>Simplicity and convenience: Combining three active ingredients into a single tablet simplifies the treatment regimen for individuals with HIV/AIDS. Taking Triomune 30+150+200mg Tablets eliminates the need to take multiple medications separately, making it easier to adhere to the prescribed treatment plan. This convenience can improve medication compliance and reduce the risk of treatment failure.</p>\n\n<p>Long-term viral suppression: Triomune 30+150+200mg Tablets, when taken consistently as prescribed, can achieve long-term viral suppression, meaning that the levels of the HIV virus in the body are reduced to undetectable levels. Maintaining viral suppression is crucial In managing HIV/AIDS and preventing the progression of the disease to advanced stages.</p>\n\n<p>Enhanced immune function: By controlling the replication of the HIV virus, Triomune 30+150+200mg Tablets help preserve and strengthen the immune system. This allows the body to better defend against opportunistic infections and other complications associated with HIV/AIDS. Improved immune function can lead to fewer illnesses and an overall improved sense of well-being.</p>\n\n<p>Combination theIy benefits: The combination of Lamivudine, Stavudine, and Nevirapine in Triomune 30+150+200mg Tablets offers a synergistic effect in suppressing the HIV virus. Each component targets different stages of the virus&rsquo;s lifecycle, maximizing the efficacy of the treatment. This combination approach has been widely studied and is considered a standard of care in HIV/AIDS treatment.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before starting Triomune 30+150+200mg Tablets, it is important to consult with a healthcare professional and disclose your medical history, including any allergies or pre-existing conditions. They can provide guidance on the appropriate usage and monitor for any potential drug interactions.</p>','<p>Triomune 30+150+200mg Tablets are a medication that combines three active ingredients: Lamivudine 150mg, Stavudine 30mg, and Nevirapine 200mg. It is primarily used in the treatment of HIV/AIDS, specifically in the management of the virus and its associated symptoms. This combination medication offers several benefits and can significantly improve the quality of life for individuals living with HIV/AIDS.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>Like any medication, Triomune 30+150+200mg Tablets may cause some side effects, but it is important to note that not everyone experiences them. Additionally, most side effects are temporary and typically subside as the body adjusts to the medication. Common side effects may include:</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Nausea or vomiting</p>\n\n<p>Diarrhea</p>\n\n<p>Headache</p>\n\n<p>Fatigue</p>\n\n<p>Skin rash</p>','[\"triomune-30-150-200mg-tablets-172252399629.jpg\"]','TR30',1,'0','2024-08-01 14:53:53','2025-10-08 07:59:08'),(746,0,'Tropicacyl Eye drop of 5 ml','tropicacyl-eye-drop-of-5-ml','Drops','tropicacyl-eye-drop-of-5-ml-172252425225.jpg','TRO05','<p>How to Use:</p>\n\n<p>Tilt your head back.</p>\n\n<p>Gently pull your lower eyelid downward and outward to create a pocket.</p>\n\n<p>Squeeze the dropper gently and place the prescribed number of eye drops into the pocket formed by the lower eyelid.</p>\n\n<p>Blink a few times to help the liquid spread evenly across the eye.</p>\n\n<p>To prevent the solution from draining into the nose and throat, especially in children, it is recommended to gently press on the inner corner of the eyelid for approximately 3 minutes.</p>\n\n<p>If you need to use more than one drop, wait for about 5 minutes before applying the next drop.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Tropicacyl 1% W/V Eye Drops (5 ml) are utilized to expand (dilate) the pupils, facilitating a thorough examination of the eye&#39;s structure. Its active component, &#39;Tropicamide,&#39; belongs to the classes of &quot;muscarinic antagonists&quot; and &quot;mydriatics.&quot; Acting as an anticholinergic agent, Tropicacyl 1% W/V Eye Drops (5 ml) induces relaxation in the eye muscles. By blocking the activity of muscarinic acetylcholine receptors, it brings about temporary paralysis of the eye (cycloplegia) and short-term dilation of the pupil (mydriasis). This dilation enables a comprehensive evaluation of various eye components, including the lens, vitreous humor, and retina. In addition to its application for pupil dilation, Tropicacyl 1% W/V Eye Drops 5 ml can also be employed in the management of inflammatory eye conditions like iritis (inflammation of the iris) and cyclitis (a type of uveitis affecting the ciliary body of the eye).</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Use Tropicacyl 1% W/V Eye Drops (5 ml) as directed by your doctor or healthcare professional.</p>\n\n<p>Avoid touching the dropper tip to prevent contamination.</p>\n\n<p>Do not use Tropicacyl 1% W/V Eye Drops (5 ml) if you are allergic to any of its ingredients.</p>\n\n<p>Inform your doctor about any existing medical conditions or medications you are taking.</p>\n\n<p>Tropicacyl 1% W/V Eye Drops (5 ml) may cause temporary blurred vision and sensitivity to light. Avoid activities that require clear vision until your vision returns to normal.</p>\n\n<p>If using contact lenses, remove them before applying the eye drops. Wait for at least 15 minutes before reinserting them.</p>\n\n<p>Tropicacyl 1% W/V Eye Drops (5 ml) may interact with certain medications. Consult your doctor or pharmacist for advice if you are taking other eye medications or any systemic medications.</p>\n\n<p>Store the eye drops in a cool, dry place, away from direct sunlight, and out of reach of children.</p>','<p>Tropicacyl 1% W/V Eye Drops 5 ml is classified as an &quot;anticholinergic and anti-muscarinic agent.&quot; Its primary use is to dilate the pupil during eye examinations or diagnostic procedures. Additionally, Tropicacyl 1% W/V Eye Drops (5 ml) is prescribed for the treatment of uveitis, which is inflammation of the uvea, the middle layer of the eye. Dilating the pupil is crucial in intraocular procedures like cataract surgery, as it reduces complications and provides better visibility during the operation.</p>\n\n<p>The active ingredient in Tropicacyl 1% W/V Eye Drops 5 ml is &quot;Tropicamide,&quot; which belongs to the &quot;muscarinic antagonists&quot; and &quot;mydriatics&quot; classes of medications. Tropicamide, an anticholinergic agent, works by blocking the activity of muscarinic acetylcholine receptors. Acetylcholine is a neurotransmitter that sends signals to nerve cells. By blocking these receptors, tropicamide induces short-term dilation of the pupil (mydriasis) and temporary paralysis of the eye (cycloplegia). These effects facilitate a thorough examination of various parts of the eye, including the lens, vitreous humor, and retina.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<p>The majority of side effects do not need medical attention and typically subside as your body adapts to the medication. However, if you are concerned or if the side effects persist, it is recommended that you consult your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>The most common side effects are listed below:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Blurry vision</li>\n	<li>Dry mouth</li>\n	<li>Dry eyes</li>\n	<li>Eye sensitivity</li>\n	<li>Stinging sensation in the eyes</li>\n	<li>Increased pressure in the eye (which may cause headache)</li>\n	<li>Psychotic reactions and behavioral disturbances (especially in children)</li>\n</ul>','[\"tropicacyl-eye-drop-of-5-ml-172252425225.jpg\"]','TRO05',1,'0','2024-08-01 14:58:06','2025-10-08 07:58:19'),(747,0,'Tugain 5% 60ml','tugain-5-60ml','Solution','tugain-5-60ml-172256940741.jpg','TU05','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>Follow the instructions provided by your doctor or those on the medication label when using Tugain 5% 60ml. Typically, the recommended dosage is applying 1ml of the solution twice daily directly to the affected areas of the scalp. It is important to massage the solution gently into the scalp and avoid washing or wetting the scalp for at least four hours after application.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Tugain 5% 60ml offers several benefits for individuals experiencing hair loss:</p>\n\n<p>Hair regrowth: Tugain 5% 60ml has been clinically proven to promote hair regrowth in both men and women with androgenetic alopecia, also known as male or female pattern baldness. It can help stimulate dormant hair follicles, leading to the regrowth of thicker, fuller hair.</p>\n\n<p>Effective for different types of hair loss: Tugain 5% 60ml is beneficial for various types of hair loss, including hereditary hair loss, which is the most common form. It can be used by individuals with thinning hair, receding hairlines, or overall hair loss.</p>\n\n<p>Convenient application: Tugain 5% 60ml is applied topically, which makes it easy to use. The solution can be directly applied to the affected areas of the scalp, and it dries quickly, without leaving a greasy residue.</p>\n\n<p>Well-tolerated: Tugain 5% 60ml is generally well-tolerated by most individuals. Side effects are typically minimal and temporary, such as mild scalp irritation or itching, which usually resolves on its own. Serious side effects are rare.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before starting Tugain 5% 60ml, it is important to consider the following precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Consultation with a healthcare professional: It is recommended to consult a doctor or a dermatologist before starting Tugain 5% 60ml. They can evaluate your condition, provide a proper diagnosis, and recommend the appropriate treatment plan.</p>\n\n<p>Consistency in use: To achieve the best results, it is important to use Tugain 5% 60ml consistently as prescribed. Regular and continuous application is necessary for optimal hair regrowth.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>Tugain 5% 60ml, also known as Minoxidil 5%, is a medication commonly used to treat hair loss and promote hair regrowth. It is available in a topical solution form and is applied directly to the scalp. Minoxidil is a vasodilator, meaning it widens blood vessels, and its exact mechanism of action in hair growth is not fully understood. However, it is believed to improve blood flow to the hair follicles, stimulate hair growth, and prolong the growth phase of the hair cycle.</p>\n\n<p>Here Is some information about Tugain 5% 60ml:</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>Potential shedding: Some individuals may experience a temporary increase in hair shedding when starting Tugain 5% 60ml. This is a normal part of the hair growth cycle and is usually followed by the regrowth of new, healthier hair.</p>\n\n<p>Allergic reactions: If you have known allergies or sensitivities, it is important to inform your healthcare provider before using Tugain 5% 60ml. They can assess if you are at risk of any adverse reactions to the medication or its components.</p>\n\n<p>Overall, Tugain 5% 60ml can be an effective solution for individuals experiencing hair loss. With consistent use and proper application, it can help promote hair regrowth, improve hair density, and enhance overall hair appearance</p>','[\"tugain-5-60ml-172256940741.jpg\"]','TU05',1,'1','2024-08-02 03:30:18','2024-08-02 03:30:18'),(748,0,'Tugain Solution 10 (60 ml)','tugain-solution-10-60-ml','Solution','minoxidil-tugain-10-solution-172534461153.jpg','TU10','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>The dosage and duration will be recommended by your doctor based on your situation. Changes in the color or texture of the hair, excessive hair growth, headaches, itching, skin irritation, dryness, shortness of breath, scaling of the skin, and redness are a few of the side effects of Tugain 10% Solution 60 ml that are frequently reported. Most of the time, these adverse effects subside during the course of treatment without the need for medical attention. Consult a doctor if the negative effects continue or get worse.</p>\n\n<p>The solution/spray form often includes an extended spray-tip applicator and a spray pump applicator. One pump the spray pump while aiming it at the scalp&#39;s bald spots. Use your fingertips to spread the solution after that. Avoid inhaling the spray mist, and after use, wash your hands thoroughly. To apply the solution to broad areas of skin, use the spray pump applicator; for smaller areas, use the spray-tip applicator.Foam: A spray bottle with foam is provided. To get the foam on your fingers, press the nozzle. Spread the foam with your fingertips over the bald spots, then massage the scalp lightly. After application, properly wash your hands.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>10% Tugain Solution A vasodilator called 60 ml is used to treat alopecia (hair loss). It promotes hair growth and stops balding. 10% Tugain Solution In order to enhance blood flow, 60 ml expands blood arteries and opens potassium channels. This vasodilation process encourages blood flow to the hair follicles, giving the hair cells enough nutrients and oxygen. The process of giving the hair cell oxygen and nutrients stops it from dying and promotes hair growth.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p><strong>ALCOHOLIC BEWARE</strong></p>\n\n<p>If you have any questions about using Tugain 10% Solution 60 ml, please talk to your doctor first.</p>\n\n<p><strong>PREGNANCY IS RISKY</strong></p>\n\n<p>It is not advised to use Tugain 10% Solution 60 ml while pregnant.</p>\n\n<p><strong>LIVER CAUTION</strong></p>\n\n<p>Before taking Tugain 10% Solution 60 ml, inform your doctor if you have a history of liver illness or hepatic impairment.</p>\n\n<p><strong>KIDNEY WARNING</strong></p>\n\n<p>If you have ever had kidney illness, tell your doctor before using Tugain 10% Solution 60 ml.</p>\n\n<p><strong>KIDS ARE UNSAFE</strong></p>\n\n<p>Use of Tugain 10% Solution 60 ml should be avoided by children and teenagers under the age of 18.</p>','<p>10% Tugain Solutions In the category of &quot;vasodilators&quot; used to treat alopecia (hair loss), 60 ml is included. Tugain 10% Solution 60 ml promotes hair growth and slows down balding. Alopecia is the term used to describe the thinning or loss of hair on the scalp or any other region of the body.</p>\n\n<p>A vasodilator that opens up the blood vessels is called &quot;Minoxidil,&quot; and it is present in Tugain 10% Solution 60 ml. This vasodilation process aids in supplying oxygen, blood, and nutrients to the hair follicles, avoiding hair cell death, and encouraging the creation of new hair.</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Changes in the colour/texture of the hair</li>\n	<li>Excessive hair growth</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Itching</li>\n	<li>Skin irritation</li>\n	<li>Dryness</li>\n	<li>Shortness of breath</li>\n	<li>Scaling of the skin</li>\n</ul>','[\"minoxidil-tugain-10-solution-172534461153.jpg\"]','TU10',1,'0','2024-09-03 06:23:41','2025-10-08 07:59:34'),(749,0,'Unicontin  Controlled Release Tablets 400mg','unicontin-controlled-release-tablets-400mg','tablets','unicontin-controlled-release-tablets-400mg-172534481447.webp','UN400','<p>Usage:</p>\n\n<p>It is important to follow your doctor&rsquo;s instructions and read the medication label carefully before using Unicontin Controlled Release Tablets 400mg. Take the tablets as prescribed, usually once or twice a day, with or without food. Swallow the tablets whole and avoid crushing or chewing them to ensure the controlled release mechanism works effectively.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Unicontin Controlled Release Tablets 400mg offers several benefits for individuals with respiratory conditions:</p>\n\n<p>Bronchodilation: Theophylline, the active ingredient in Unicontin, helps to relax and open up the airways in the lungs, making breathing easier. This bronchodilatory effect provides relief from symptoms such as wheezing, coughing, and shortness of breath.</p>\n\n<p>Maintenance Therapy: Unicontin is commonly used as a maintenance therapy for long-term management of asthma and COPD. By keeping the airways open and reducing inflammation, it helps prevent asthma attacks and COPD exacerbations, allowing individuals to maintain an active and healthy lifestyle.</p>\n\n<p>Extended Release Formula: Unicontin Controlled Release Tablets 400mg utilize a controlled release mechanism, ensuring a steady and consistent release of the medication over time. This helps maintain therapeutic drug levels in the body, reducing the need for frequent dosing and providing prolonged symptom relief.</p>\n\n<p>Convenience: The once or twice daily dosing schedule of Unicontin Controlled Release Tablets 400mg offers convenience and improves medication adherence. This allows individuals to effectively manage their respiratory condition without frequent interruptions or disruptions to their daily routines.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before starting Unicontin Controlled Release Tablets 400mg, it is important to inform your healthcare provider or pharmacist about any allergies you may have, including to Theophylline or any other substances. Additionally, disclose your medical history, especially if you have any pre-existing heart conditions, liver problems, or seizures, as this may affect the suitability of the medication for you.</p>','<p>Unicontin Controlled Release Tablets 400mg is a medication that provides effective treatment for respiratory conditions such as asthma and chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD). This medication is specifically designed to deliver the active ingredient, Theophylline, in a controlled and sustained manner, ensuring optimal therapeutic benefits.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Here is some important information about Unicontin Controlled Release Tablets 400mg:</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>While side effects are possible with any medication, it is important to note that not everyone experiences them. Common side effects associated with Unicontin Controlled Release Tablets 400mg may include:</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Nausea or stomach upset</p>\n\n<p>Headache</p>\n\n<p>Mild tremors</p>\n\n<p>Insomnia</p>','[\"unicontin-controlled-release-tablets-400mg-172534481447.webp\"]','UN400',1,'0','2024-09-03 06:27:05','2025-10-08 07:57:26'),(750,0,'Unicontin  Controlled Release Tablets 400mg','unicontin-controlled-release-tablets-400mg','tablets','unicontin-controlled-release-tablets-400mg-172534481447.webp','UN