eals; however, it is recommended that it be taken at a consistent time each day.</p>\n\n<p>Uniwarfin 2mg Tablet should not be taken at the same time as foods high in vitamin K, such as spinach, collard greens, broccoli, spring onions, cucumber, or dried basil.</p>\n\n<p>Benfits:</p>\n\n<p>The Uniwarfin 2mg Tablet works by inhibiting a chemical in the body that is responsible for the coagulation of blood. Despite the fact that it does not &quot;dissolve&quot; blood clots, it can prevent them from growing larger, which allows your body to eventually dissolve them on its own. Additionally, it will inhibit the formation of any new ones. Because of this, your blood is able to circulate freely throughout your body, and it is also less probable that a clot would form on the interior of a blood artery as a result. This may help to prevent or lessen the damage caused by a stroke, clots in your lungs (also known as pulmonary embolism), or thrombosis in other blood vessels. Additionally, it can lessen the likelihood that pieces of a clot will separate and move to different locations throughout the body. In order for this medication to work properly, you will need to take the Uniwarfin 2mg Tablet on a consistent basis and make any necessary adjustments to your lifestyle.</p>\n\n<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Follow the prescribed dosage: Take Warfarin exactly as prescribed by your healthcare professional. It is typically taken once a day, usually at the same time each day. Do not change the dosage or stop taking the medication without consulting your doctor.</p>\n\n<p>Regular monitoring: Warfarin requires regular monitoring of your blood&#39;s clotting ability. Your doctor will perform blood tests, such as the international normalized ratio (INR) test, to determine the appropriate dosage for you. Attend all scheduled appointments and inform your doctor of any changes in your health or medication regimen.</p>\n\n<p>Inform your doctor about other medications: Warfarin can interact with many medications, including prescription drugs, over-the-counter medications, and herbal supplements. Inform your healthcare professional about all the medications you are taking to avoid potential interactions that can affect the effectiveness or increase the risk of side effects.</p>','<p>Uniwarfin 2mg Tablet is an oral anticoagulant that helps prevent the formation of potentially dangerous blood clots in the legs, lungs, brain, and heart. This medication comes in tablet form. It is utilized for the treatment of pulmonary embolism, deep vein thrombosis, and stroke prevention</p>','<p>Side effects:</p>\n\n<p>The majority of adverse effects may be managed without medical intervention and will go away as your body becomes used to the medication. If they continue or if you are concerned about them, you should make an appointment with your primary care physician.</p>','[\"uniwarfin-2-mg-172534536595.webp\"]','UN02',1,'0','2024-09-03 06:37:11','2025-10-08 07:57:10'),(752,0,'Urimax 0.4 mg','urimax-04-mg','tablets','urimax-0-172534565740.jpg','UR04','<p>How to use:</p>\n\n<p>As directed, consume 30 Urimax 0.4 Capsules. Low blood pressure (hypotension), dizziness, tiredness, decreased sex desire (libido), inability to get an erection (impotence), tenderness or enlargement of your breasts (in men), sleeplessness, runny nose, or ejaculatory issues are the most frequent adverse effects of Urimax 0.4 Capsule 30&#39;s. As long as you continue to take Urimax 0.4 Capsule 30s, these adverse effects might go away. However, consult a doctor if these adverse effects continue. As prescribed by your doctor, take one Urimax 0.4 Capsule 30s with or without meals. With a glass of water, swallow it whole. Do not chew, break, or chew it.</p>\n\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<p>Tamsulosin is an alpha-blocker that can be found in Urimax 0.4 Capsule 30&#39;s. This medication is typically used to men in order to treat an enlarged prostate gland. Because it is a prodrug, it must first undergo digestion 