al assistance immediately.</p>','[\"volini-gel-30-gm-172718485524.webp\"]','Vo30',1,'0','2024-09-24 13:34:23','2025-10-08 08:04:59'),(771,0,'Azithromycin 500mg','azithromycin-500mg','Tablets','screenshot-2025-07-20-121307-175299380540.png','AZ500','<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Effective against a broad range of bacterial infections</li>\n	<li>Convenient once-daily dosage</li>\n	<li>Often used as a short-course treatment</li>\n	<li>Reduces symptoms quickly and promotes faster recovery</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Dosage:</p>\n\n<p>Azithromycin 500mg is typically taken once daily, either as a single dose or over a 3 to 5-day course, depending on the severity and type of infection. It is usually taken with or without food, but taking it with food can help reduce stomach upset. Always follow the dosage prescribed by your healthcare provider.</p>','<p>Azithromycin 500mg is a widely prescribed antibiotic belonging to the macrolide class, primarily used to treat various bacterial infections. This medication works by inhibiting bacterial protein synthesis, preventing further growth and spread of infection-causing bacteria. It is commonly prescribed for respiratory tract infections, skin infections, ear infections, throat infections, and certain sensually transmitted diseases.</p>','<p>Precautions:</p>\n\n<p>Before taking Azithromycin 500mg, inform your doctor if you have liver, kidney, or heart conditions. Avoid combining with antacids containing aluminum or magnesium, as they may reduce its effectiveness. It is essential to complete the full course to prevent antibiotic resistance.</p>\n\n<p>Possible Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>While generally well-tolerated, some users may experience mild side effects, including:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Nausea</li>\n	<li>Diarrhea</li>\n	<li>Abdominal pain</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Serious allergic reactions are rare but require immediate medical attention.</p>','[\"screenshot-2025-07-20-121307-175299380540.png\"]','AZ500',1,'1','2025-07-20 06:43:38','2025-07-20 06:43:38'),(772,0,'Azithromycin 250mg','azithromycin-250mg','Tablets','screenshot-2025-07-20-123407-175299507527.png','AZ250','<p>Key Benefits of Azithromycin 250mg:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Effectively treats a wide range of bacterial infections</li>\n	<li>Convenient once-daily dosage</li>\n	<li>Often used as a short 3 to 5-day treatment</li>\n	<li>Generally well-tolerated with a low risk of resistance when used properly</li>\n	<li>Offers rapid symptom relief in respiratory and skin-related infections</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Dosage and Usage Guidelines</p>\n\n<p>Azithromycin 250mg is typically prescribed once daily, either alone or in combination depending on the type and severity of the infection. Dosage may vary based on medical condition and body weight. It can be taken with or without food, although taking it with food may reduce the risk of stomach upset.</p>\n\n<p>Usual dosage examples include:</p>\n\n<p>Adults: 500mg on Day 1, followed by 250mg once daily on Days 2 through 5</p>\n\n<p>Children: Dose is weight-based and must be prescribed by a pediatrician</p>\n\n<p>Patients should complete the entire course, even if symptoms improve earlier, to ensure full elimination of the infection and avoid antibiotic resistance.</p>','<p>Azithromycin 250mg is a broad-spectrum antibiotic belonging to the macrolide class, used for treating a variety of bacterial infections. It works by stopping the growth of bacteria by interfering with their protein synthesis. This medication is highly effective against respiratory tract infections, skin infections, ear infections, throat infections, and sexually transmitted infections such as chlamydia. It is not effective against viral infections like the flu or common cold.</p>\n\n<p>Available in tablet form, Azithromycin 250mg is commonly prescribed due to its convenient dosing schedule and fast-acting properties. It offers a reliable solution for patients seeking short-course antibiotic therapy with long-lasting results.</p>','<p>Possible Side Effects:</p>\n\n<p>Azithromycin 250mg is usually well-tolerated, but some individuals may experience mild to moderate side effects, including:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Nausea or vomiting</li>\n	<li>Diarrhea</li>\n	<li>Abdominal pain or cramping</li>\n	<li>Headache</li>\n	<li>Dizziness</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Precautions and Safety Information:</p>\n\n<p>Inform your doctor if you have liver, kidney, or heart disease.</p>\n\n<p>Avoid using antacids containing aluminum or magnesium within 2 hours of taking the medication.</p>\n\n<p>Pregnant or breastfeeding women should use Azithromycin 250mg only under medical advice.</p>\n\n<p>Do not share this antibiotic with others, even if they have similar symptoms.</p>\n\n<p>Rare but serious side effects may include liver problems, irregular heartbeat, or allergic reactions. Contact your doctor immediately if you notice symptoms like skin rash, yellowing of the skin/eyes, or difficulty breathing.</p>','[\"screenshot-2025-07-20-123407-175299507527.png\"]','AZ250',1,'1','2025-07-20 07:04:44','2025-07-20 07:04:44'),(773,0,'Careprost Plus Eye Drop 3ml','careprost-plus-eye-drop-3ml','Drops','screenshot-2025-07-20-170925-175301158575.png','CA003','<p><strong>Key Benefits of Careprost Plus Eye Drop 3ml</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Effectively reduces elevated intraocular pressure</li>\n	<li>Helps prevent further optic nerve damage and vision deterioration</li>\n	<li>Suitable for patients unresponsive to single-agent therapy</li>\n	<li>May enhance eyelash length and fullness as a side effect of Bimatoprost</li>\n	<li>Comes in a convenient 3ml bottle for ease of use</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Dosage:</strong></p>\n\n<p>The usual recommended dose is <strong>one drop in the affected eye(s) once daily</strong>, preferably in the evening. To apply:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Wash hands thoroughly</li>\n	<li>Tilt the head back and pull down the lower eyelid</li>\n	<li>Instill one drop without touching the dropper to any surface</li>\n	<li>Close the eye gently for a few minutes to allow absorption</li>\n</ul>','<p><strong>Careprost Plus Eye Drop 3ml</strong> is a prescription ophthalmic solution formulated to lower intraocular pressure (IOP) in patients with open-angle glaucoma or ocular hypertension. It combines two active ingredients&mdash;<strong>Bimatoprost 0.03%</strong> and <strong>Timolol 0.5%</strong>&mdash;to provide enhanced and sustained pressure control within the eye. Bimatoprost belongs to a class of prostaglandin analogs that increase the outflow of aqueous humor (fluid in the eye), while Timolol is a beta-blocker that reduces fluid production. The dual mechanism helps reduce the risk of optic nerve damage and vision loss.</p>\n\n<p>In addition to its therapeutic benefits for glaucoma, <strong>Careprost Plus</strong> is also known for its cosmetic effect of enhancing eyelash growth&mdash;making lashes appear longer, darker, and thicker over time when applied to the lash line under medical supervision.</p>','<p><strong>Side Effects:</strong></p>\n\n<p>Like all medications, <strong>Careprost Plus Eye Drops</strong> may cause some side effects:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Mild eye irritation or redness</li>\n	<li>Dry or itchy eyes</li>\n	<li>Changes in eye color (increased brown pigmentation)</li>\n	<li>Blurred vision temporarily after application</li>\n	<li>Increased eyelash growth or darkening of the eyelid skin</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Precautions and Safety Tips</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Not recommended for use in children unless directed by a doctor</li>\n	<li>Inform your doctor if you have asthma, heart disease, or other eye conditions</li>\n	<li>Remove contact lenses before use and wait at least 15 minutes before reinserting</li>\n	<li>Do not use if the solution changes color or becomes cloudy</li>\n	<li>Pregnant or breastfeeding women should consult their doctor before using the product</li>\n	<li>Store in a cool, dry place and keep the bottle tightly closed</li>\n</ul>','[\"screenshot-2025-07-20-170925-175301158575.png\"]','CA003',1,'1','2025-07-20 11:39:53','2025-07-20 11:39:53'),(774,0,'Lovegra 100mg','lovegra-100mg','Tablets','screenshot-2025-07-21-102400-175307368592.png','LO100','<p>Benefits:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>\n	<p>Promotes increased blood flow to female genital tissues</p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<p>Enhances natural lubrication and sensitivity</p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<p>Supports arousal and sensual response during intimacy</p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<p>May help improve confidence and mood related to intimate relationships</p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<p>Fast-acting results typically within 30&ndash;60 minutes</p>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The usual dosage of <strong>Lovegra 100mg</strong> is <strong>one tablet taken orally about 30 to 60 minutes before planned intimacy</strong>. It should not be taken more than once in a 24-hour period.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Instructions for use:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>\n	<p>Take with water on an empty stomach for best results</p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<p>Avoid high-fat meals before consumption, as they may delay absorption</p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<p>Use only under the supervision or advice of a healthcare provider</p>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3><strong>Possible Side Effects</strong></h3>\n\n<p>While <strong>Lovegra 100mg</strong> is generally well-tolerated, some users may experience mild to moderate side effects, such as:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>\n	<p>Headache</p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<p>Flushing or facial redness</p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<p>Upset stomach</p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<p>Nasal congestion</p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<p>Mild dizziness</p>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Serious side effects are rare but may include vision disturbances, allergic reactions, or prolonged discomfort. Seek medical attention if you experience chest pain, shortness of breath, or sudden changes in vision or hearing.</p>','<p><strong>Lovegra 100mg</strong> is an oral medication specifically designed to support <strong>female sensual wellness</strong> by improving blood flow to intimate area